Name: Abilisk (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Abilisk is a interdimensional tentacled monster who was devouring the power sources of the Sovereign planet. The Guardians of the Galaxy were hired by the Sovereign people to exterminate the terrifying beast.

Name: Abomination (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Emil Blonsky was a special-ops commando with the British Royal Marines on loan to General Thaddeus Ross in his efforts to capture Bruce Banner better known as Hulk. Blonsky was injected with two dosages of a variant original Super Soldier Serum and later was injected with Bruce Banner's blood causing him to transform into the Hulk-sized Abomination. The Abomination proceeded to go on a rampage in Harlem until he was defeated by Hulk and captured by the United States Armed Forces.

Name: Adam Warlock (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Adam Warlock is the ultimate weapon of the Sovereign, created by Ayesha and High Evolutionary to kill the Guardians of the Galaxy. He was prematurely awakened by High Evolutionary, who tasked him with capturing Rocket Raccoon, only for Adam's efforts to be thwarted by the Guardians. Warlock joined his mother Ayesha on a trip to Counter-Earth to retrieve Rocket, although High Evolutionary destroyed the planet, killing Ayesha. Warlock eventually tried to attack High Evolutionary's ship but failed yet again and was rescued by the Guardians. Warlock later saved Star-Lord from dying in space and joined the new Guardians roster under Rocket's leadership.

Name: Agatha (Pokémon)
Summary: Agatha (キクコ Kikuko) is a member of the Kanto Elite 4. She is the third member as well as the oldest. She specializes in Ghost-types and other menacing looking pokemon.

Name: Ahri
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-A | 4-B | 4-B

Name: Akali
Summary: Abandoning the Kinkou Order and her title of the Fist of Shadow, Akali now strikes alone, ready to be the deadly weapon her people need. Though she holds onto all she learned from her master Shen, she has pledged to defend Ionia from its enemies, one kill at a time. Akali may strike in silence, but her message will be heard loud and clear: fear the assassin with no master.

Name: Alistar
Summary: Always a mighty warrior with a fearsome reputation, Alistar seeks revenge for the death of his clan at the hands of the Noxian empire. Though he was enslaved and forced into the life of a gladiator, his unbreakable will was what kept him from truly becoming a beast. Now, free of the chains of his former masters, he fights in the name of the downtrodden and the disadvantaged, his rage as much a weapon as his horns, hooves and fists.

Name: Archer (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Let's Go P/E)''' | '''Pokémon Team (FR/LG and HG/SS)'''
Summary: Archer (Japanese: アポロ Apollo) is one of the four Team Rocket Executives introduced in Pokémon Gold and Silver. However, he went unnamed until Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver.

Name: Archie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Archie is the boss of Team Aqua. The player only battles him in Seafloor Cavern in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Sapphire. In Ruby, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Magma from expanding the land mass and in Sapphire, he is the main antagonist of the game.

Name: Ardos
Summary: Ardos (Japanese: アルドス Ardos) is one of the five Cipher Admins from Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness. Ardos is one of Grand Master Greevil's two bodyguards, and is revealed at the end of the game to also be one of Greevil's sons (the other bodyguard/son being his twin brother Eldes).

Name: Avengers (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Iron Man: How were you guys planning on beating that? Captain America: Together. Iron Man: We'll lose. Captain America: Then we'll do that together, too.

Name: Bianca (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End and Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (BW2)'''
Summary: Bianca (ベル, Bel) is a Pokémon Trainer from the Unova region.

Name: Bruno (Pokémon)
Summary: Bruno (シバ Siba) is a Fighting-type Trainer and member of the Elite Four of Kanto and Johto.

Name: Caitlin (Pokémon)
Summary: Caitlin is a Pokémon Trainer that first appeared in Johto as the princess of the Battle Castle. She later reappeared as one of the Elite Four of the Unova Region.

Name: Candice (Pokémon)
Summary: Candice is a Gym Leader from Sinnoh and the leader of the Snowpoint Gym.

Name: Chandelure
Summary: Chandelure is a Fire and Ghost-type Pokémon that evolves from Lampent after giving the Lampent a Dusk Stone. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance. It then absorbs their spirit, which it then burns, leaving the body behind.

Name: Charizard
Summary: Charizard is a draconic, bipedal Pokémon and the final stage of the Charmander evolutionary line. It is primarily orange with a cream underside from the chest to the tip of its tail, which burns with a sizable flame.

Name: Cheren (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gym Battle)'''
Summary: Cheren, "The one who seeks the right path" is a main character in Pokémon Black/White and its sequel, Pokémon Black/White 2. Cheren, Bianca and Hilbert all went off on their Pokémon journey on the same day and thus their individual journeys intersected quite often, with Cheren occasionally finding himself duking it out with Hilbert and fighting by his side against Team Plasma. Though Cheren sometimes comes off as cold and distant, he's actually a good hearted and very honest person who seeks to do the right thing. He is also very smart and knowledgeable about Pokémon.

Name: Chitauri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Chitauri are a race of cybernetically enhanced aliens who serve under the leadership of Thanos, who gave them over to Loki for use in his invasion of Earth in an attempt to acquire the Tesseract. Though they successfully invaded the planet through a wormhole created by the Tesseract, they were ultimately defeated by the Avengers.

Name: Clemont
Summary: Clemont is the Lumiose City Gym Leader; the fifth Gym Leader that a Pokémon Trainer must face if they want to challenge the Kalos Elite Four. For the Lumiose Gym’s challenge before the actual Gym battle, much like Blaine, his little sister Bonnie likes to quiz would-be challengers on general information on Pokémon, with the punishment of facing a trainer if they answer wrong.

Name: Colress
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 4)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon World Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Plasma Frigate)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Tree)'''
Summary: However, I disagree!

Name: Cyrus
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Celestic Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Team Galactic HQ)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Distortion World)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Cyrus is the nihilistic main antagonist of the Sinnoh Pokémon games. He is the leader of Team Galactic and wishes to use the power of Palkia and Dialga to erase the universe, and remake it as a realm devoid of spirit.

Name: Dar-Benn (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Supremor Dar-Benn was a revolutionary Kree warrior and an Accuser of the Kree Empire who fought to restore her homeland after a long civil war. Formerly a member of Starforce, she blamed Captain Marvel for inciting a long civil war on Hala, which led to the planet's desolation. After discovering a Quantum Band on MB-418, Dar-Benn tore apart Jump Points in space to extract natural resources from various planets to restore her homeworld. She was eventually killed as a result of using two Quantum Bands at the same time.

Name: Decidueye
Summary: Decidueye (Japanese: ジュナイパー Junaipā) is a dual-type Grass/Ghost Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It evolves from Dartrix and is the final form of Rowlet.

Name: Delphox
Summary: Delphox (Japanese: マフォクシー Mahoxy)is a dual-type Fire/Psychic Pokémon introduced in Pokémon X and Y. It evolves from Braixen and is the final form of Fennekin.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Doctor Strange Supreme (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Stephen Vincent Strange is a sorcerer and a Master of the Mystic Arts. Originally a brilliant, although arrogant, neurosurgeon, Strange got into a car accident which resulted in the death of the love of his life, Doctor Christine Palmer. Fueled by grief, Stephen set off to learn about the mystic arts, and eventually stopped Dormammu from devouring his reality, saving Earth and his universe. Despite this, Strange remained haunted about Christine's death and began a dark journey to gain the power needed to resurrect her, bringing about dangerous consequences for his universe as Doctor Strange Supreme. He is an alternate reality version of Doctor Strange.

Name: Drax the Destroyer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Drax, also known as Drax the Destroyer, is a former intergalactic criminal and a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy. He sought revenge on Ronan the Accuser for killing his wife and daughter, and went on a rampage across the galaxy, ending with him being imprisoned by the Nova Corps in the Kyln. There Drax became uneasy allies with Star-Lord, Gamora, Rocket Raccoon, and Groot. Together they broke out of the Kyln and became embroiled in the Quest for the Orb. After the Battle of Xandar, in which he finally gained the vengeance on Ronan he had so long sought, Drax left Xandar with the other Guardians.

Name: Dystnine
Summary: Dystnine is of a model of Android mass-produced by Gargantua. However, strangely enough, Dystnine inexplicably developed a soul. This caused him to develop a Septima. Sumeragi was going to disassemble him for research purposes, but were stopped by Stella. As such, he began serving the Adept. When iX killed her, this awakened emotions of anger and sadness within Dystnine, greatly improving his Septima to the point that he could fight against iX.

Name: Ebony Maw (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ebony Maw is an adopted child of Thanos and a member of the Black Order. After taking the Tesseract with Thanos and his fellow henchmen, Ebony Maw and Cull Obsidian were sent to take the Time Stone from Doctor Strange. Cull Obsidian is teleported away, but Ebony Maw managed to capture Doctor Strange and attempted transport him to Titan on his ship. However, Iron Man and Spider-Man attacked the ship, and Ebony Maw was killed in the skirmish by being thrown into space.

Name: Ego (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ego was a Celestial, a primordial and extremely powerful entity, and the father of Star-Lord. He originally appeared to be a caring and wise father with a cocky personality, similar to his own son. However, it is later revealed that he is a ruthless entity with a god complex who wishes to conquer the universe. He is a mysterious adventurer from far parts of the galaxy who has heard the legend of the Guardians of the Galaxy following the Battle of Xandar and has come to meet them for the first time. Reunited with his son in 2014, Ego desired to forward his plan to rule the universe by using his son's Celestial genes to terraform the planets he had planted alien seedlings on. Ego's plans were foiled by the Guardians of the Galaxy and he was ultimately destroyed by their hand.

Name: Ein (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shadow PKMN Lab)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)'''
Summary: Ein (Japanese: ボルグ Borg) is one of the original four Cipher Admins. A cruel and callous young scientist, he is long on ambition and short on emotion. He is obsessed with the idea of creating an insanely powerful Pokémon at any cost which he managed to do with amazing results.

Name: Eitri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eitri is the King of the Dwarves, an ancient race of skilled forgers and blacksmiths who hail from Nidavellir. He was forced by Thanos to forge the Infinity Gauntlet. He later worked with Thor, Rocket and Groot to forge Stormbreaker in order to kill Thanos.

Name: Eldes
Summary: Eldes (Japanese: エルデス Eldes) is the younger brother of Ardos and one of the five Cipher Admins of Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness.

Name: Elesa
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Teams (Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokémon Team (World Leaders Tournament)'''
Summary: Elesa, "The Shining Beauty" is a model and Gym Leader in Nimbasa City, region of Unova. She specializes in Electric-type Pokémon.

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Erika (Pokémon)
Summary: Erika is the sleepy fourth Gym leader of Kanto, known as the Nature Loving Princess. She specializes in the Grass-type, and gives out the Rainbow badge when defeated.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Evice
Summary: Evice (Japanese: ワルダック Wardack) is the criminal mastermind behind Cipher. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher Head (Japanese: シャドーのボス Shadow Boss). He disguises himself as the mayor of Phenac City under the name of Es Cade (Japanese: バックレー Backley). In his disguise, he is a fat and jolly gentleman who appears to be worried about the increase in crime caused by Cipher and Team Snagem, yet as the head of Cipher, he appears to have done nothing to stop either of them, ensuring that Snagem and Cipher work without interference.

Name: Faba
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''First Fights Teams''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post Game/Title Defense)'''
Summary: Faba is the Branch Chief of the Aether Foundation and the foundation's "last line of defense".

Name: Falcon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Samuel Thomas "Sam" Wilson, better known as the Falcon, was a former United States Air Force pararescue airman who left active duty when his wing-man Riley died in combat, choosing instead to begin helping any of his fellow veterans who were suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder at Veterans Affairs. During this time, Wilson met and soon became an ally of Captain America during the beginning of the HYDRA Uprising, assisting him in bringing down Alexander Pierce's schemes for Project Insight before then choosing to remain with Captain America. Falcon later joined the Avengers, and has been an active member ever since.

Name: Galio
Summary: Tier: 7-C, Low 6-B against Magic | 7-A, Low 6-B against Magic

Name: Gamora (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gamora is a former assassin and a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy. She became the adopted daughter of Thanos after he killed half of her entire race. She served him for years before betraying him in an attempt to free herself from his ways. She was hired to steal the Orb, and became caught up in the quest for the Orb, becoming friends with the other members of the Guardians of the Galaxy. After the Battle of Xandar, she left to work with them.

Name: Gandalf
Key: '''Gandalf the Grey''' | '''Gandalf the White''' | '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Gandalf, originally known as Olórin, is a member of the order of wizards known as the Istari. Despite his appearance, Gandalf is not a human sorcerer, but rather a Maia of the ancient race of beings known as the Ainur, who existed before the creation of Arda. He is one of the main heroes in both J.R.R Tolkien's Middle-Earth saga and Peter Jackson's live-action adaptation of the books respectively.

Name: Garen Crownguard
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least Low 7-C, possibly 7-A | At least 3-C, likely 3-B

Name: Ghost Rider (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Roberto "Robbie" Reyes grew up in East Los Angeles with his younger brother Gabe, who suffered from paraplegia. He dropped out of high school in eleventh grade, and decided to find work as a mechanic at Canelo's Auto and Body in order to support himself and his brother. He is also possessed by the mystical being known as Ghost Rider.

Name: Ghost Rider (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ghost Rider is the name of several fictional supernatural antiheroes appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. This profile deals with the Johnny Blaze iteration of the character

Name: Giovanni (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Rocket Hideout)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Silph Co.)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Viridian Gym)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Giovanni is the leader of Team Rocket and the Viridian Gym, the father of Silver and a recurring antagonist in the series.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Greevil
Summary: Greevil (Japanese: デスゴルド Deathgold) is the leader of the criminal group Cipher. He is the only character in the game to have the Trainer class Grand Master (Japanese: シャドー総帥 Shadow Leader).

Name: Greninja
Summary: It utilizes its extraordinary jumping abilities to flummox its foes, throwing springy bubbles at them from above their heads.

Name: Grimsley
Summary: Grimsley is a member of the Unova Elite Four and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon.

Name: Groot (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Groot is a hyper-intelligent, tree-like organism from the species Flora colossus native to the planet X. While he possesses human level intellect, Groot's robust and heavyweight physiology causes the organs of his acoustic generation to become stiff and inflexible, rendering the limits of his speech to the simple phrase, "I am Groot."

Name: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nebula: All any of you do is yell at each other. You're not friends. Drax: You're right... We're family.
ID: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-7-A

Name: Hatterene
Summary: Hatenna is a small Pokémon with peculiar behavior. They are known for being very shy and quiet, often preferring locations without people or strong sources of emotion. This aversion is strong enough that they will flee in most circumstances just to attempt to avoid interaction. Such behavior is caused by a feeling of exhaustion when sensing these strong emotions and as such, they will only warm up to those with a calm disposition.

Name: Hulk (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Dr. Robert Bruce Banner is a renowned scientist in the fields of Biochemistry, Nuclear Physics, and Gamma Radiation. He is one of the scientists who tried to recreate the Super Soldier Serum which originated Captain America in World War II, but when an exposure to high levels of Gamma Radiation instead of Vita Radiation went awry, the mild-mannered scientist found himself plagued with a peculiar condition; when angered or provoked, he would transform into the rage-fueled and nearly mindless green-skinned monster known as the Hulk.

Name: Iris (Pokémon)
Summary: Iris is a trainer from Unova. Originally one of the two gym leaders for Opelucid City, she became the champion of the Unova league after extensive training from Drayden.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Jarvan IV
Summary: Tier: 7-C | At least 7-C, possibly 7-A | 7-C | Low 1-C

Name: Jasmine (Pokémon)
Summary: Jasmine is the leader of the Olivine Gym who specializes in Steel-type Pokemon.

Name: Jigglypuff
Summary: Tier: 8-C | At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: K'Sante
Summary: Defiant and courageous, K'Sante battles colossal beasts and ruthless Ascended to protect his home of Nazumah, a coveted oasis amid the sands of Shurima. But after a falling-out with his former partner, K'Sante realizes that in order to become a warrior worthy of leading his city, he must temper his single-minded drive for success. Only then can he avoid falling prey to his own pride and find the wisdom he needs to defeat the vicious monsters threatening his people.

Name: Katarina Du Couteau
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | Low 7-C | 7-C | At least Low 7-C, possibly 7-A

Name: Korath the Pursuer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Vers: Has a Skrull ever simmed you? Korath: Once. It was deeply disturbing. Vers: Why? Korath: Because I stared into the face of my mortal enemy and the face staring back was my own. Att-Lass: Maybe if you were more attractive, then it would be less disturbing. Korath: You think you’re funny. I’m not laughing. Att-Lass: You never laugh. Korath: I laugh, on the inside. I’m not doing it now.

Name: Korrina
Summary: Korrina is the Fighting-type gym leader of Shalour City and granddaughter of the Mega Evolution Guru.

Name: Krakatoa Eruption
Summary: The Krakatoa Eruption was a VEI 6 eruption that destroyed most of the island of Krakatoa and created the loudest sound in recoded history, loud enough that it could be heard 3,000 miles away, and was picked up by barometers all around the globe.

Name: Kree (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gleen Talbot: You're telling me that we got our asses handed to us by little green men. Phil Coulson: They were big and blue.

Name: Lawnmower (Pokémon)
Summary: One of the most peculiar Pokémon characters, this Lawnmower appears in the Pikachu Short “Pikachu’s PikaBoo”.

Name: Lorelei
Summary: Lorelei is the ice user of the Elite Four, and is the first Elite Four member ever met. She is known for her cool and calculated tactics. She is from Four Island on the Sevii Islands, and has a deep affinity to the Icefall Cave there, as that is where she first got her Lapras when she was a child.

Name: Lt. Surge
Summary: Lt. Surge "The Lightning American" is the leader of the Vermillion Gym and mainly uses Electric-type Pokémon. He is the third Gym Leader Red and Blue encounter in their adventures through Kanto. Characterized by his bold and brash composure, Lt. Surge is a war vet who served in the mysterious "Kanto War" of some years ago.

Name: Lusamine
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team''' | '''Merged Lusamine''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Merge Lusamine)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Lusamine is the current president of the Aether Foundation, an organization created to shelter Pokémon from villainous organizations like Team Skull and nurse these Pokémon back to health to be returned to the wild. She is the insane and corrupt president of the Aether Foundation, who not only abuses her own children and has performed various gruesome experiments on the very Pokemon she's supposed to take care of and protect but also plans to go to Ultra Space to reach the Ultra Beasts, even if it means unleashing their fury on the Alola region.

Name: Malphite
Summary: A massive creature of living stone, Malphite was born from the heart of the great Ixtali construct known as the Monolith. He has studied the elemental balance of Runeterra for thousands of years, using his tremendous strength to maintain order in a frequently chaotic world. Now, roused all too often from his slumbers, Malphite endures the fluid temperaments of mortals, while struggling to find a cause worthy of the last of his kind.

Name: Maokai
Summary: Tier: 8-B | 7-A | High 6-A

Name: Maxie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Maxie is the boss of Team Magma. The player battles him in the Mossdeep Space Center in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Ruby. In Sapphire, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Aqua from expanding the sea and in Ruby, he is the main villain of the game.

Name: Maylene
Summary: Maylene is the Veilstone City Gym Leader in Pokémon Diamond, Pearl, and Platinum, and is the fourth Gym Leader that a Trainer in the Sinnoh region must battle in order to challenge the Elite Four. Maylene constantly chases perfection alongside her Fighting-type Pokémon, and her training has made her one of the greatest martial artists and Pokémon trainers in the Sinnoh region. She doesn't remember how, but somewhere along the line she became the Gym Leader for her hometown, earning countless other martial artists as her Gym trainers that she was suddenly in charge of. Undeterred, she continues training, using her challengers as opportunities to locate her own weak points and meet new people.

Name: Miror B.
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pyrite Cave)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cave Poké Spot)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Outskirt Stand)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gateon Port)'''
Summary: Miror B. (Japanese: ミラーボ Mirorbo) is a recurring character and major antagonist from Pokémon Colosseum and Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness. His name is probably derived from mirror ball. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Wanderer (Japanese: さすらい Wanderer).

Name: Monica Rambeau (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Monica Rambeau is the daughter of Maria Rambeau, who was a close friend of Carol Danvers. After the Blip, she became a captain at S.W.OR.D to investigate the Westview Anomaly, which was later revealed to originate from Wanda Maximoff. She was tasked to inspect the anomaly alongside with Jimmy Woo. However, as she approached the anomaly, she was pulled inside the pocket reality and was forcibly given the role of "Geraldine." As a result of coming into contact of the Hex, her genes were rewritten, and she had gained the power to manipulate energy.

Name: Mordekaiser
Summary: Tier: At least Low 6-B, possibly 4-B | 7-A | High 6-A | 4-B | Low 1-C

Name: Ms. Marvel (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Kamran: Look at everything I've done, Kamala. What am I supposed to do now? How can I be normal? Ms. Marvel: There is no normal. There's just us and what we do with what we've been given.

Name: Nascour
Summary: Nascour (Japanese: ジャキラ Jakira) was thought to be the head of Cipher. A man with a terrifying visage, he is gaunt, dressed in dark clothes and possesses wiry, white, serpentine hair. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher (Japanese: シャドー Shadow). Nascour's strategy in battle is to use X Special and other stat-enhancing items on his Pokémon.

Name: Nasus
Summary: Nasus is an imposing, jackal-headed Ascended being from ancient Shurima, a heroic figure regarded as a demigod by the people of the desert. Fiercely intelligent, he was a guardian of knowledge and peerless strategist whose wisdom guided the ancient empire of Shurima to greatness for many centuries. After the fall of the empire, he went into self-imposed exile, becoming little more than a legend. Now that the ancient city of Shurima has risen once more, he has returned, determined to ensure it never falls again.

Name: Nebula (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nebula: I wasn't always like this. War Machine: Me neither. But we work with what we got, right?

Name: Neon J.
Summary: Neon J. is a war veteran turned "commander" of 1010. He created the boyband in order to spread joy to others but somewhere down the line, lost sight of his goals. He teams up with 1010 in Bed Bunk Junction's fourth battle with NSR.

Name: Nidalee
Summary: Raised in the deepest jungle, Nidalee is a master tracker who can shapeshift into a ferocious cougar at will. Neither wholly woman nor beast, she viciously defends her territory from any and all trespassers, with carefully placed traps and deft spear throws. She cripples her quarry before pouncing on them in feline form—the lucky few who survive tell tales of a wild woman with razor-sharp instincts, and even sharper claws...

Name: Nidoking
Summary: Nidoran♂ is a small, quadruped rodent-like Pokémon. It is pinkish purple with darker patches. It has large, spiny ears with teal insides, oversized front teeth, and red eyes. Its back is covered with three lines of large spines that can release potent poisons if threatened. The center line of spines is taller than the other two. The size of the long, pointed horn on its forehead is indicative of the strength of its venom. Nidoran♂ is an exclusively male Pokémon, Nidoran♀ being its female counterpart.

Name: Nidoqueen
Summary: Nidorina is a quadruped, light blue Pokémon with darker blue patches. It has red eyes, large, spiny ears, and has two pointed teeth protruding from its upper jaw. It possesses large poison spikes, which it retracts whenever it is with a group or while resting in its burrow. Its paws have three claws each, and it is able to stand on its hind legs. The hind legs are longer and thicker than its forelegs. It has a stubby tail. This is a female only species; the male counterpart is Nidorino.

Name: Paul (Pokémon)
Summary: Paul is a rather arrogant trainer. From Veilstone City, he headed to Sandgem to get his starter, he has since travelled through Kanto, Johto & Hoenn. However, he is not a caring trainer, what he wants from his Pokémon is pure power and the trainers he faces to be strong. When he first meets Ash, he demands a 3 on 3 Battle, however since Ash was still looking for Pikachu, Ash couldn't battle, this warranted some aggrivation on Paul's part. Paul is also known to release his Pokémon if he deems them weak or useless.

Name: Pikachu
Summary: nan

Name: Quantum Bands (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Quantum Bands are ancient artifacts of the Kree, that are made out of Noor, an energy source used by the Noor Dimension. The bands created the Universal Neural Teleportation Network, which is a system of every jump point existing in the universe. The bands can control the Noor and were pursued by the Clandestines so that they can return to the Noor Dimension. One of the bands was discovered by Aisha and the Clandestines who were searching for artifacts inside the Ten Rings Temple. Years later, one of the bands were bestowed to Kamala Khan and had unlocked her latent powers due to her connection to the Noor. Years after Ms. Marvel mastered her abilities, the second band was discovered in another planet by Dar-Benn who used its powers to create jump points to steal resources from other planets to restore Hala.

Name: Ralts
Summary: Ralts is a Psychic type Pokémon that is capable of sensing emotions. It's evolutions follow suit, with Kirlia being capable of both sensing emotions and casting illusions while its final evolution, Gardevoir, protects its trainer with all its might to the point that it will sacrifice itself for their sake. When using a dawn stone on a male Ralts, the Pokémon will evolve into Gallade, a Pokémon who will protect his trainer with his masterful swordsmanship.

Name: Red Hulk (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Ribbon Demon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Ribbon Demon is a mystical creature that was conjured by the Scarlet Witch to chase after America Chavez. It was summoned in the Gap Junction where America and Defender Strange went to get the Book of Vishanti in order to protect America. The demon managed to catch Defender Strange off guard, impaling him through his chest. Chavez attempted to run to the Book of Vishanti, but was captured in the process. Defender Strange with his last breath of life, used his powers to free Chavez. She was able to escape and later landed into Earth-616 through her portals.

Name: Riven
Summary: Once a swordmaster in the warhosts of Noxus, Riven is an expatriate in a land she previously tried to conquer. She rose through the ranks on the strength of her conviction and her brutal efficiency, and was rewarded with a legendary runic blade—however, on the Ionian front, Riven’s faith in her homeland was tested and ultimately broken. Having severed all ties to the empire, she now wanders with her shattered sword, seeking to atone for a past she cannot fully recall.

Name: Rocket Raccoon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Subject 89P13 is a raccoon who was genetically enhanced by the High Evolutionary - although he shows no knowledge of what a Raccoon is when Peter Quill refers to him as one - giving him intelligence and the ability to speak. Naming himself Rocket, he befriended fellow experiments Lylla, Teefs and Floor, with the four believing they would soon be allowed to live in peace on a new planet. Upon aiding High Evolutionary with a scientific problem, Rocket discovered that he, along with the previous experiments, were slated to be killed. Attempting to free his friends, he cried in horror as High Evolutionary killed Lylla, prompting him to attack his creator in a rage, which in turn caused Teefs and Floor’s deaths. Rocket then boarded a spaceship and fled into the cosmos.

Name: Romeo Conbolt
Summary: Romeo Conbolt is the only son of Fairy Tail's Mage, Macao Conbolt, and a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild.

Name: Ronan the Accuser (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ronan was a radical member of the Kree Empire, and former member of the Accusers. In 1995, during the Kree-Skrull War, Ronan worked with Yon-Rogg and the Starforce after the Ambush on Torfa to wipe out the last of the Skrull refugees. Ronan and the Accusers were then called to drop warheads on Earth to wipe out the remaining Skrull opposition there, but were forced to retreat when Captain Marvel launched a counter-offensive against the Kree, promising retribution.

Name: Sanctuary II
Summary: The Sanctuary II was a massive warship commanded by Thanos. It was likely named after Thanos' previous base of operations, Sanctuary.

Name: Scarlet Witch (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Wanda: You took everything from me! Thanos: I don't even know who you are. Wanda: You will.

Name: Sif (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Lady Sif is the Goddess of War, a feared Asgardian warrior and a good friend of the Thor and the Warriors Three. When Thor almost provoked a war with the Frost Giants and ended up powerless on Earth, Sif and her friends disobeyed the orders of their new king Loki and went to Earth to save their friend. Thanks to them, Thor returned to Asgard and Loki's reign of terror ended.

Name: Silver (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Cherrygrove City)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Azalea Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Burned Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Goldenrod Tunnel)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Victory Road)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)'''
Summary: Silver (Japanese: シルバー Silver) is one of the main characters and the rival of Pokémon Gold, Silver, Crystal and Pokémon HeartGold and SoulSilver. He is the son of Team Rocket Boss Giovanni that fought many times with Ethan, Kris or Lyra.

Name: Sinister Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Stephen Vincent Strange, also known as Sinister Strange, is a minor antagonist in the 2022 Marvel Cinematic Universe film Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness. He is a variant of Earth-199999's Doctor Strange, who was unable to live a life without his love, Christine Palmer.

Name: Snorlax
Summary: nan

Name: Soundwave (Transformers: Prime)
Summary: Soundwave is a former gladiator who turned into one of Megatron's most loyal followers and became the Decepticon's Communications Officer.

Name: Star-Lord (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ego: Stop! Listen- Listen to me! You are a god. If you kill me, you'll be just like everybody else! Star-Lord: What's so wrong with that?

Name: Star-Lord (T'Challa)
Summary: T’Challa, known as Star-Lord was the Prince of Wakanda and son of T’Chaka before he was abducted by the Ravagers, an interstellar crime syndicate led by Yondu, who were hired by Ego to kidnap one of his many sons, Peter Quill. However, by mistake they took T’Challa, who agreed to explore the universe with them.

Name: Stonjourner
Summary: Stonjourner is a tall Pokémon resembling Stonehenge. It has a gray, rectangular body with white eyes and mouth, and is adorned with dark gray spots. On top of its body are two, smaller rectangular stones giving it the appearance of a hat. Its arms are made up of three chained, square rocks alternating between gray and dark gray. It has two large, gray legs which are brown on the lower half. On its lower legs are gray crosses. These resemble the standing stones in Turffield, a place in the Galar region.

Name: Taillow
Summary: Tier: 8-A | At least 7-A

Name: Tatiana Qwartz
Summary: Tatiana Quartz is the CEO of No Straight Roads, a massive record label with a powerful hold on Vinyl City. She leads an EDM empire that governs the music industry, making her genre the dominant one via monopoly, and beating down any attempts to bring rock back.

Name: The Collector (Marvel Cinematic Universe: What If...?)
Summary: Taneleer Tivan, also known as The Collector, is the head of the Tivan Group. Having filled the power vacuum created when Thanos had abandoned his plan of wiping half of the universe, Tivan became the most ruthless kingpin in the intergalactic underworld.
ID: The Collector (Marvel Cinematic Universe: What If...?)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-7-A

Name: The Destroyer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Destroyer was an enchanted automaton controlled by Odin to guard his vault on Asgard. When the throne of Asgard was usurped by Loki, the Destroyer was sent to Earth to kill the exiled and depowered Thor. It found Thor in New Mexico and seemingly killed him, despite the efforts of Sif and the Warriors Three. However, Thor's selfless efforts evacuating the area of innocents made him worthy of his powers again, which allowed him to overpower the Destroyer and render it inoperable. The disabled Destroyer was confiscated by S.H.I.E.L.D. and was reverse-engineered to create a powerful laser weapon.

Name: Theodore Altman (Hulkling)
Summary: Theodore Altman was raised on earth by a nursemaid he called mother until he was 16, unknown of his real origin. He found love with Billy Maximoff, and both were invited by Iron lad to form the Young Avengers where he become Hulkling. Later he found out he was actually son of the Kree Mar-Vell and a princess of the Skrull race called Anelle, making him a hybrid. After eons of war the Kree and Skrull formed an alliance and after proving himself to be able to held Excelsior he become the emperor Dorrek-Vell.

Name: Thor (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor Odinson is the God of Thunder, prince of Asgard and a former member of the Avengers. When his irresponsible behavior threatened his homeland, he was stripped of his power and banished by his father Odin to Earth. While exiled on Earth, Thor learned humility, found love in Jane Foster, and helped to save his new friends from a destructive threat sent by his jealous adoptive brother Loki. In the process, Thor redeemed himself in the eyes of his father and was granted access to his power once more.

Name: Tryndamere
Summary: Fueled by unbridled fury and rage, Tryndamere once carved his way through the Freljord, openly challenging the greatest warriors of the north to prepare himself for even darker days ahead.

Name: Vel'Koz
Summary: Tier: 8-B | 7-A | High 6-C

Name: Vi (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: 7-B | At least 7-B, possibly 7-A

Name: Vileplume
Summary: Vileplume is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with rudimentary hands and feet. It has beady red eyes and a small mouth. On its head is massive red flower with an orange-brown center. Vileplume's flower is said to have the largest petals in the world and is almost too heavy for the Pokémon itself to support. The rounded petals of the flower are red and covered with white spots. A female Vileplume has fewer, but larger, spots on its petals. It can shake, flap, or burst its petals into bloom with a bang in order to release clouds of pollen. This pollen is highly allergenic to humans and toxic to other Pokémon; Vileplume uses it to paralyze its prey. It can also utilize these petals in its former signature move, Petal Dance. Vileplume lives in grassy plains, where it is often mistaken for local flowers.

Name: Wailord
Summary: Wailord is a Water-type Pokémon based off of the blue whale. It was introduced in Pokémon Ruby and Sapphire and is currently the largest Pokémon in existence. It evolves from Wailmer at level 40.

Name: Warwick
Summary: Tier: 7-B | 7-A

Name: Wingull
Summary: Wingull is a seagull Pokémon with wings that are made for soaring on updrafts. It carries food in its beak and makes its nest on the cliffsides. Fishermen take note of when Wingull are nearby, as it is a sign that the surrounding waters are filled with fish.

Name: Xin Zhao
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least Low 7-C, possibly 7-A | 7-C | Low 1-C

Name: Yondu Udonta (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: nan

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Zyra
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-C | 7-A

Name: Ace (Street Fighter)
Summary: Ace (エース Ēsu) is a secret government agent capable of analyzing and copying skills of other fighters.

Name: Aegislash
Summary: Aegislash is a dual-type Steel/Ghost Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It evolves from Doublade when exposed to a Dusk Stone. It is the final form of Honedge. Aegislash can change forms during battle, depending on the moves it is using.

Name: Aero (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lei Ling is Chinese woman who got powers as a child. She went to school and graduated in architecture as the top of her class in Tongji University. She later founded her own firm, Tree Studios, and works there while still acting as the hero known as Aero mostly in the area of Shanghai. She also was part of Agents of Atlas during the War of the Realms, protecting the Pacific Rim.

Name: Aggron
Summary: Aggron (Japanese: ボスゴドラ, Bossgodora) is a dual-type Steel/Rock Pokémon. It evolves from Lairon starting at level 42. It is the final form of Aron. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Aggron using the Aggronite. Aggron is a huge, bipedal Pokémon.

Name: Akatsuki (Under Night In-Birth)
Summary: Akatsuki is a playable character in Under Night In-Birth. He used to be a high-class technical officer of the Imperial Army. He was believed to have died at the critical in the Arctic Ocean during the transportation of a new military unit from an allied country. Fifty years later, he miraculously returns alive and unchanged in appearance. He now resumes his mission, finishing what he started five decades prior.

Name: Alakazam
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Alcyoneus (Riordanverse)
Summary: Alcyoneus is the eldest of the giants spawned by Gaea to overthrow the Olympians after they deposed the Titans. Created to battle Hades, he was the first giant his mother tried to revive by manipulating Hazel Levesque, but the demigod sacrificed herself to stop the giant's complete revival. Alcyoneus was only revived decades later, and was the one responsible for keeping Thanatos, the god of death, imprisioned.

Name: Allen Snider
Summary: Allen Snider (アレン・スナイダー Aren Sunaidā) is an American freestyle karate fighter dedicated to his high intensive training. After losing to Ken Masters in a tournament, he gained a newfound dedication to becoming the best fighter in the world.

Name: Ampharos
Summary: Ampharos, the Light Pokémon is the final stage evolution of the Mareep family. Famed for its ability to give off intense rays of light, Ampharos has been used as a beacon for ships since ancient times.

Name: Amumu
Summary: Amumu is a Yordle, a small and cute creature in the League of Legends universe, who is burdened by an ancient curse. This curse makes him an embodiment of loneliness, and he roams the world in search of companionship. Amumu's touch is said to bring overwhelming sadness to those around him, making forming connections difficult for him.

Name: Ariados
Summary: Ariados is a Pokémon that resembles a spider. It has a red body with black stripes and markings on its rear that form a face. In the center of its head is a small, white horn. Additionally, it also has small purple eyes and a pair of white mandibles. Ariados has four yellow legs with purple stripes; long, pointed growths on its back appear to be remnants of its fifth and sixth legs. Ariados's feet are tipped with tiny hooked claws that enable it to scuttle on ceilings and vertical walls. It spins a single strand of a special string endlessly out of its rear. The string can also be spun from its mouth; however, it is hard to tell which end is which.

Name: B-52 Stratofortress
Summary: The B-52 Stratofortress is a strategic bomber developed by Boeing. It is a long range jet powered aircraft and has been operated by the USAF since the 1950s and still continues to serve the USAF to this day with continuing upgrades and maintenance. The B-52 made its first flight on April 1952. It was also made to replace the earlier Convair B-36 peacemaker, especially in the role of carrying nuclear weapons for Cold War-era deterrence missions.

Name: Basilio
Summary: Basilio is a playable character in Fire Emblem, born on August 13.

Name: Beedrill
Summary: Beedrill is a Poison/Bug, wasp based Pokémon introduced in the first generation. It is noted to be incredibly territorial and poisonous. It evolves from Weedle into Kakuna at level 7, and then from Kakuna into Beedrill at level 10.

Name: Bidoof
Summary: Bidoof (Japanese: ビッパ, Bippa), the Plump Mouse Pokémon is an early game, pure Normal- type rodent Pokémon introduced in Gen IV. It is known to have sharp teeth that grow indefinitely, so it needs to gnaw on things like rocks and trees to keep them down. Its teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata's. It is also said to have nerves of steel, and that it's more agile and active than it appears. It evolves at level 15 into the Normal-/Water- type Bibarel (Japanese: ビーダル Beadaru), the Beaver Pokémon. The Pokédex knows it as a Pokémon that is really good at building dams and is a swimmer as fast as a Feebas, though slow on land. Trainers know it as the Pokémon that can learn the most HMs. Back in Gen IV, it used to have a signature ability in Unaware.

Name: Blair Dame
Summary: Blair Dame (ブレア・デイム Burea Deimu) is the daughter of a wealthy European family, taking has taken up martial arts as a way to defend herself and those she cares about. She is a free spirit, wishing to travel the world. Eventually, she was allowed to, under the condition that a bodyguard stay by her side. During her travels, she became a close companion of Pullum Purna.

Name: Blastoise
Summary: Blastoise is a large, bipedal tortoise-like Pokémon. Its body is dark blue and is mostly hidden by its tough, brown shell. This shell has a pale yellow underside and a white ridge encircling its arms and separating the upper and lower halves.

Name: Blaziken
Summary: Blaziken (Japanese: バシャーモ Bursyamo) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Blitzcrank
Summary: Tier: 7-B | 7-B | 4-B

Name: Bouffalant
Summary: Bouffalant is a Normal-type Pokémon from the Unova region. It is the Bash Buffalo Pokémon and was introduced in Generation V.

Name: Braum
Summary: Blessed with massive muscles, and an even bigger heart, Braum is a beloved hero of the Freljord. Every child born to the ice knows of his legendary strength, capable of felling entire forests of frost-oaks in a single night or rending the very mountains asunder. With a colossal vault door borne across his back as a shield, Braum roams the land as a friend to those in need and a terrible foe of evildoers.

Name: Brock (Pokémon)
Summary: Brock "The Rock-Solid Pokémon Trainer!" is the first Gym Leader Red encountered in his adventures in Kanto. He is an expert and specialist of the Rock typing. Arguably one of the most iconic Gym Leaders in the entire series [Only really rivaled by Misty and Giovanni], Brock has become a recurring character in the Pokémon franchise, appearing in Pokémon Red/Blue/Yellow, Pokémon Adventures and arguably most famously, the Pokémon anime series.

Name: Caitlyn (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: At least 10-B, 7-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, High 6-C with Weapons | At least 10-B, 4-B with Weapons | At least 10-B, At least 7-B with Weapons, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Camille Ferros
Summary: Tier: 7-B | 7-B

Name: Cassiopeia Du Couteau
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least 7-C, possibly 7-B

Name: Castle Bravo Bomb
Summary: Castle Bravo was the code name given to the first United States test of a dry fuel hydrogen bomb, detonated on March 1, 1954, at Bikini Atoll, Marshall Islands, as the first test of Operation Castle. It is the most powerful bomb ever detonated by the United States, producing 30% of the energy produced by Tsar Bomba.

Name: Caterpie
Summary: Butterfree is a dual-type Bug/Flying fully evolved Pokémon based on a butterfly. It evolves from Metapod at level 10, who evolves from Caterpie at level 7. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Chansey
Summary: Happiny, the Playhouse Pokémon, is another baby Pokémon often found carrying around a round white stone, often seen just playing around.

Name: Chesnaught
Summary: Chesnaught is a Grass/Fighting-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI. It evolves from Quilladin who is an evolution of Chespin.

Name: Cinderace
Summary: Cinderace is a Fire type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. By juggling a pebble with its feet, Cinderace can transform it into a burning soccer ball. By putting a spin on the ball, it can launch attacks that its opponents struggle to evade.

Name: Conkeldurr
Summary: Conkeldurr is a fighting type Pokémon from the Unova region introduced in Generation V.

Name: Crobat
Summary: Crobat is a Flying-/Poison-type Pokemon introduced in Generation II. It a purple bat with four wings, with the hind set replacing its legs. It flies silently in the air to sneak up on enemies, but is clumsy while walking. It is also the first Pokemon to be a new evolution from a previous one, followed closely by Steelix and Scizor. It evolves by high friendship from Golbat, who evolves from Zubat at level 25.

Name: Cryogonal
Summary: Cryogonal is an Ice-type Pokémon mainly found in Unova.

Name: Daisy Johnson (Quake)
Summary: Daisy Johnson is the daughter of Calvin Zabo with a woman with the inhuman gene. Her mother gave her to adoption little after she was born, she ended up being adopted and her name become Cory Sutter. As a teen she tried to steal but ended up being caught and causing an earthquake, she was interrogated by Nick Fury who told her the truth about her biological parents and recruited her to S.H.I.E.L.D. She was personally trained by Nick Fury to become the best spy and at the age of 18 she become the director of S.H.I.E.L.D. She named herself Quake after an encounter with the avengers.

Name: Delibird
Summary: Delibird is a dual ice and flying type Pokémon. It is mainly known for transporting food and others goods in its tail, resembling a bag.

Name: Doctrine Dark
Summary: Doctrine Dark was once a brave soldier with an exceptional sense for battle. Dark once served under the orders of Guile with his own special tactical reconnaissance unit. During his tour of duty, his own unit got into a bit of a scuffle with another rival unit, lead by Rolento. The minor scuffle escalated into a full-on battle, with both sides receiving heavy casualties. Doctrine Dark was the only member of his unit to escape.

Name: Dragapult
Summary: Dragapult is an spectral dragon Pokemon and the resident Pseudo Legendary in the 8th generation of Pokemon. Alongside being a ghost dragon, it is based on fighter jets, and fires its first form, Dreepy, from itself like missiles. Apparently, the Dreepy like being launched. It evolves from Drakloak at level 60, which evolves from Dreepy at level 50.

Name: Dragonite
Summary: Dragonite is a "pseudo-legendary" Dragon and Flying-type Pokémon from the first generation, and one of the strongest Pokémon of its time. It evolves from Dratini at level 30, and evolves from Dragonair at 55.

Name: Drampa
Summary: Drampa is a Normal/Dragon-type Pokémon from the Alola region introduced in Generation VII.

Name: Dunsparce
Summary: Dunsparce is an unevolving normal type Pokemon introduced in the second generation.

Name: Durant (Pokémon)
Summary: Durant is an ant with a metal outer shell. Colonies of Durant work together to create complex and interconnected burrows in mountains, while some individuals play different roles in fending off their natural predators.

Name: Dusknoir
Summary: Dusknoir is a final form ghost-type Pokémon introduced in Gen IV. It evolves from Duskull into Dusclops, and from Dusclops into Dusknoir by holding a Reaper Cloth and being traded.

Name: Electivire
Summary: Electivire is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Electabuzz, and the final form of the Gen II Elekid. It evolves when traded with an Electrizer.

Name: Elemental HERO Thunder Giant
Summary: Elemental HERO Thunder Giant is a monster in Yu-Gi-Oh!. He belongs to the Elemental HERO archetype. He is the fusion of Elemental HERO Sparkman and Elemental HERO Clayman.

Name: Emboar
Summary: Emboar (Japanese: エンブオー, Enbuoh) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Pignite starting at level 36. It is the final form of Tepig.

Name: Empoleon
Summary: Empoleon is a Water/Steel type Starter Pokémon from Sinnoh, based on an Emperor Penguin. It evolves from Piplup into Prinplup at level 16, and from Prinplup to Empoleon at level 36.

Name: Exploud
Summary: Exploud is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a large mouth. It has red eyes, a stubby nose, and two peg-like teeth in each jaw. It has protruding tubes with holes along its body: seven forming a crest on top of its head, one on each elbow and knee, two along its back, and one at the end of each of its two tails. The tubes along its head-crest and tails are tipped with yellow, while the ones along its back have yellow semicircular patterns on either side. There are two yellow semicircle markings on its belly, but they are rarely seen due to its giant mouth. Its arms have three thin stripes below its elbow and three fingers. Each foot has four claws, three in the front and one in the back, and a yellow paw pad.

Name: Ezreal
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Magic, potentially Low 6-B with Ne'Zuk's Gauntlet | Unknown, 4-B with Magic | Unknown, 7-B with Magic, 2-A via hax, up to Low 1-C | 4-B

Name: Falinks
Summary: Falinks may appear to only be one caterpillar-like Pokémon, but in reality, it’s six small troopers lined up to create the image of one Pokémon. Five troopers follow their leader, the brass.

Name: Feraligatr
Summary: Feraligatr is the reptilian final water starter from the Johto region. It evolves from Croconaw at level 30, which itself evolves from Totodile at level 18, later than any starter save only for Turtwig, with whom it is tied.

Name: Garchomp
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Garuda (Street Fighter)
Summary: Garuda (ガルダ Garuda) is a demonic being clad in samurai armor capable of absorbing negative energies to strengthen his own power. He is said to have been a culmination of all souls consumed by the Satsui no Hado.

Name: Gengar
Summary: Gengar (Japanese: ゲンガー Gangar) is a dual-type Ghost/Poison Pokémon. It evolves from Haunter when traded. It is the final form of Gastly. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Gengar using the Gengarite. Gengar is a dark purple, bipedal Pokémon with a roundish body. It has red eyes and a wide mouth that is usually curled into a sinister grin. Multiple spikes cover its back, and it has large pointed ears. Its arms and legs are short with three digits on both its hands and feet. It also has a stubby tail. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Gigalith
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Goodra
Summary: Goodra is the Pseudo-Legendary of Gen VI. It appears to be a bipedal draconian Pokémon made of slime. With its purple coloring and goofy smile, it seems to be competing with Dragonite as the lovable dragon powerhouse. It evolves from Goomy into Sliggoo at level 40, and from Sliggoo into Goodra at 50, but only in the overworld rain.

Name: Gothitelle
Summary: Gothitelle, the "Astral Body Pokémon" is a Psychic type Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation. It is the final evolution of Gothita, the "Fixation Pokémon". Gothitelle is infamous for its gloomy and Gothic appearance, as well as macabre Pokédex entries that revolve around the starry sky and the death of their trainers. Gothitelle apparently has the ability to see objects that only it can see, as well as control the minds of children and can even see the death of their trainers looming within the future.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Summary: Grimmsnarl is a dual-type Dark/Fairy Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII. It evolves from Morgrem starting at level 42, who is evolved from Impidimp. It is one of the Pokemon with the ability to Gigantamax

Name: Guhnash
Summary: A planet eating abomination that consumed the Dinaurians home world. A living weapon that can fight with every part of its body, including internal organs, it was called to Earth by the 4 idolcomps but was killed by Hunter.

Name: Guzma
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie Garden)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shady House)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hau'oli City, Team Rocket's Castle and Title Defense)'''
Summary: Guzma (Japanese: グズマ Guzma) is the leader of Team Skull.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clinton "Clint" Barton was a former circus worker and criminal-turned-hero, who received his archery skills as a young boy through training with Swordsman and Trickshot. Barton would eventually join both the East Coast and West Coast branches of The Avengers, even leading at one time.

Name: Haxorus
Summary: Haxorus is a Dragon-type Pokémon native to the Unova region. Also known as the Axe Jaw Pokemon, its sturdy tusks are destructive enough to cut through solid steel without chipping or dulling. Its also known to be relentless when defending its territory, but its sturdy armor and fierce fighting capabilities belie its kind spirit. It evolves from Fraxure who in turn evolves from Axew.

Name: Hayate (Street Fighter)
Summary: Hayate (ハヤテ) is a noble samurai attempting to follow the footsteps of his legendary missing father who sealed the beast of Orochi. When Orochi escapes from his imprisonment and kidnaps the local shrine maiden, Hayate slays the demon like his father did before him. Afterwards, Hayate and the maiden then become the new guardian deities of the village.

Name: Hayate Kamite
Summary: Hayate Kamite (紙手 疾風, かみて はやて) or Hayate II is the descendant of the first Hayate who sealed Garuda away. Seeking to pursue a normal life after becoming his village's guardian deity, he finds himself troubled with the task of continuing his predecessor's work when he becomes possessed by the demon.

Name: Heimerdinger
Summary: A brilliant yet eccentric yordle scientist, Professor Cecil B. Heimerdinger is lauded as one of the most innovative minds and esteemed inventors Piltover has ever seen. Relentless in his work to the point of neurotic obsession, he is fascinated by mysteries that have confounded his contemporaries for decades, and thrives on answering the universe’s most impenetrable questions. Though his theories often appear opaque and esoteric, Heimerdinger believes knowledge should be shared, and is devoted to teaching all who desire it.

Name: Hokuto (Street Fighter)
Summary: Hokuto (ほくと), real name Shirase (訃, しらせ), is a noble practitioner of the ancient martial art kobudō, and sibling to Kairi and Nanase.

Name: Hunter (Fossil Fighters)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 7-B, likely far higher | At least 7-B, likely far higher

Name: Hydreigon
Summary: Hydreigon is a dual-type Dark/Dragon pseudo-legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation V, based on the mythological hydra. It evolves from Zweilous at level 64, who evolves from Deino at level 50. Its most notable trait is its three heads, hence the "drei" in its name, which is German for 3.

Name: Incineroar
Summary: Incineroar (Japanese: ガオガエン, Gaogaen) is a dual-type Fire/Dark Pokémon.

Name: Infernape
Summary: Infernape (Japanese: ゴウカザル, Goukazaru) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Inteleon
Summary: Inteleon is a Water type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. Inteleon is a highly skilled sniper and hunter, prone to using traps to keep enemies from its territory.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 20
Summary: After the S.K.I.N Armor was compromised by Ultron, Tony Stark set out to create a new armor. Designed for any environment, Model 20 was born. After a few uses of the suit, the armor had to unfortunately be self-destructed after it was overtaken by an alien nanoplasm that was causing the suit to become sentient.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 70
Summary: In order to embark on a journey of soul-searching, Tony Stark stepped down from Stark Unlimited, swore off advanced technology and moved to a brownstone in the Lower East Side. He also did away with all of his Iron Man suits, resorting instead on a single vintage-style armor.

Name: Ivy Mike Bomb
Summary: Ivy Mike was the codename given to the first test of a full-scale thermonuclear device, in which part of the explosive yield comes from nuclear fusion. It was detonated on November 1, 1952 by the United States on Enewetak, an atoll in the Pacific Ocean, as part of Operation Ivy, and was the first successful test of a hydrogen bomb.

Name: Janna
Summary: Tier: Varies from 7-B to 4-B | 4-B

Name: Jayce
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 6-C

Name: Jinx (League of Legends)
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Weapons | 5-C, 5-B with the Morning Star | 4-B

Name: Kai'Sa
Summary: Claimed by the Void when she was only a child, Kai'Sa managed to survive through sheer tenacity and strength of will. Her experiences have made her a deadly hunter and, to some, the harbinger of a future they would rather not live to see. Having entered into an uneasy symbiosis with a living Void carapace, the time will soon come when she must decide whether to forgive those mortals who would call her a monster, and defeat the coming darkness together... or simply to forget, as the Void consumes the world that left her behind.

Name: Kairi (Street Fighter)
Summary: Kairi (カイリ) is Hokuto and Nanase's long lost elder brother from the Mizugami clan. A warrior in search of power, willing to surpass his limits, even if it means losing himself in the process.

Name: Karate Kid (Pre-Zero Hour)
Summary: The flat of the champion's foot connects- rending the doors from walls and floor, revealing bedrock-solid quartz molded in the image of glass... And seven human guard-dogs, chosen to challenge the invader's most prized skills... The taunt brings no reply... a silent tension waiting for the first attack. Begin the ballet of murder and watch masters of the art at work, the challenge lying not in the numbers of the attackers, but in their skill and silent determination... and devotion to the death of their foe. Yet this is no ordinary foe... nor even an ordinary master of the martial arts, for he has not the skills learned of a single art, but those of all... and from birth he has given his life over to their total mastery... until his every move shows that he is more than the master of the art from which he takes his name. His moves show the blood of the great black dragon in his veins... and the stern teachings of the sensei who made him a force for good. He is the complete fighting machine in human form... a true champion of combat... Val Armorr, the Karate Kid!

Name: Kassadin
Summary: Cutting a burning swath through the darkest places of the world, Kassadin knows his days are numbered. A widely traveled Shuriman guide and adventurer, he had chosen to raise a family among the peaceful southern tribes—until the day his village was consumed by the Void. He vowed vengeance, combining a number of arcane artifacts and forbidden technologies for the struggle ahead. Finally, Kassadin set out for the wastelands of Icathia, ready to face any monstrous Void-construct in his search for their self-proclaimed prophet, Malzahar.

Name: Kecleon
Summary: Kecleon is a Normal-type Pokémon introduced in Generation III. It is not known to evolve into or from any other Pokémon. Kecleon is a bipedal, reptilian Pokémon that is usually green. On either sides of its head are yellow frills, which are connected by lines to its yellow lips and rings around its eyes. There are small ridges on its shoulders and a red zigzag stripe around its midsection. The hands and feet have three short digits each, and it has yellow soles. It also has a long skinny tail that is usually curled tightly in a spiral.

Name: KGBeast (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Trained by a top-secret cell of the KGB known as The Hammer, Anatoli Knyazev was an assassin known to the C.I.A. as the KGBeast. Having over 200 kills in his debut he was sent to America by The Hammer to assassinate 10 U.S officials, one of which was to visit Gotham City. This caught the Batman's eye and after battling twice the Beast cut his left arm off after it was restrained by the Batrope. He had his left arm replaced with a cybernetic gun, but in their 3rd battle Batman destroyed the gun arm and trapped him in a sewer where, he was later captured by police. Despite this, Anatoli escaped and became a recurring enemy of Batman, until he was killed by Tally Man under orders by Great White Shark.

Name: Kingdra
Summary: Kingdra (Japanese: キングドラ, Kingdra) is a dual-type Water/Dragon Pokémon. It evolves from Seadra when traded holding a Dragon Scale. It is the final form of Horsea.

Name: Kommo-o
Summary: Kommo-o (Japanese: ジャラランガ, Jararanga) is a dual Dragon/Fighting-type Pokémon. It evolves from Hakamo-o and is the final form of Jangmo-o. Having completed its harsh training, Kommo-o returns to its birthplace to protect Jangmo-o. However, it only watches over them from a distance. Because it does not wish to fight weak foes, it clangs its scales together when it senses someone approaching. This ringing sound alerts others of its presence. The power of this Pokémon’s uppercut is enough to send foes flying. Simply raising its arms can generate enough force to change its surroundings. According to legend, Kommo-o's glittering scales are meant to drive away a great darkness. The reason it seeks strong opponents is also said to be a quest for power to defeat the darkness.

Name: Krookodile
Summary: Krookodile is a dual Ground/Dark type Pokémon based on a crocodile from the fifth generation of Pokémon. It evolves from Krokorok at level 40. It is the final form of Sandile.

Name: Latveria
Summary: The Kingdom of Latveria was once a small, isolated nation that was annexed from Hungary, but after it was conquered by Doctor Doom, who assumed the position of its absolute dictator, it became one of the world's greatest superpowers, solely because of his brilliance.

Name: Lickitung
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Lillipup
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Lunatone
Summary: Lunatone is a Rock and Psychic-type Pokémon from the Hoenn Region. It is the Meteorite Pokémon and it debuted in Generation III.

Name: Luxray
Summary: Luxray is the Gleam Eyes Pokémon, based on a lynx. It is an electric type Pokémon that evolves from Luxio at level 30, and is the final form of Shinx. Aside from being a fan favorite, it is known for being able to see through things.

Name: Machamp
Summary: Machamp is a Fighting-type Pokémon. It is the final evolutionary stage of Machop, evolving from Machoke when traded. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Magmortar
Summary: Magmortar is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Magmar, and the final form of the Gen II Magby. It evolves when traded with a Magmarizer. It releases flames of over 3600 degrees Fahrenheit from its arms, quite literally putting the mortar in Magmortar.

Name: Magnemite
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Malzahar
Summary: A zealous seer dedicated to the unification of all life, Malzahar truly believes the newly emergent Void to be the path to Runeterra’s salvation. In the desert wastes of Shurima, he followed the voices that whispered in his mind, all the way to ancient Icathia. Amidst the ruins of that land, he gazed into the dark heart of the Void itself, and was gifted new power and purpose. Malzahar now sees himself as a shepherd, empowered to bring others into the fold...or to release the voidling creatures that dwell beneath.

Name: Mamoswine
Summary: Mamoswine, the Twin Tusk Pokemon, is a Ground/Ice Type Pokemon introduced in Gen IV. It is based on the woolly mammoth and is an evolution of the Gen II Pokemon Piloswine after leveling up while knowing Ancient Power.

Name: Mawile
Summary: Mawile is a Steel/Fairy-type Pokémon originating from Hoenn. They bait their prey with their cute face and then devour them with their back mouth.

Name: Meganium
Summary: Meganium is the grass type starter of Johto and the final evolution of Chikorita. It evolves from Chikorita starting at level 16, and evolves into Meganium at level 32.

Name: Meowscarada
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Metagross
Summary: Metagross is a Dual Steel/Psychic Type and the Iron Leg Pokémon. A rare and powerful species native to the Hoenn region, it is formed when two Metangs, which are created when two Beldums merge, combine into a single Pokémon. Its incredible intelligence and great power make it a formidable opponent, being most famously utilized by the Hoenn League Champion, Steven Stone.

Name: Meteor Crater
Summary: Tier: 7-B

Name: Mimikyu
Summary: Mimikyu is a dual-type Ghost/Fairy Pokémon. It is a lonely Pokémon, who attempts to make friends with humans by disguising itself with a Pikachu-like veil.

Name: Mount St Helens eruption
Summary: Mount St. Helens, a stratovolcano located in Skamania County, in the state of Washington, United States erupted in May 18 of 1980, at 8:32:17 am (PDT). It had a VEI of 5.

Name: Mr. Mime
Summary: nan

Name: Mushrambo
Summary: Mushrambo is the Ultimate warrior of Enterra, and the transformation of Mushra, Sago and Kutal, appearing when Hyper Mushra absorbs Hyper Sago and Hyper Kutal's EnCards.

Name: Nanase (Street Fighter)
Summary: Nanase (七瀬) is the current successor to the Mizugami clan, and younger sister to Kairi and Hokuto. During their conflict, she seeks to chase after them in order to get them to stop fighting. Later, her memories are erased by Hokuto, and she's lead to live a normal life, though some doubts of her origins linger as she unwittingly takes up the name and appearance of her sister.

Name: Nidoking
Summary: Nidoran♂ is a small, quadruped rodent-like Pokémon. It is pinkish purple with darker patches. It has large, spiny ears with teal insides, oversized front teeth, and red eyes. Its back is covered with three lines of large spines that can release potent poisons if threatened. The center line of spines is taller than the other two. The size of the long, pointed horn on its forehead is indicative of the strength of its venom. Nidoran♂ is an exclusively male Pokémon, Nidoran♀ being its female counterpart.

Name: Nidoqueen
Summary: Nidorina is a quadruped, light blue Pokémon with darker blue patches. It has red eyes, large, spiny ears, and has two pointed teeth protruding from its upper jaw. It possesses large poison spikes, which it retracts whenever it is with a group or while resting in its burrow. Its paws have three claws each, and it is able to stand on its hind legs. The hind legs are longer and thicker than its forelegs. It has a stubby tail. This is a female only species; the male counterpart is Nidorino.

Name: Nincada
Summary: Nincada is a Bug/Ground-type Pokémon that resembles an insectoid. It uses its antennae to sense its surroundings, and uses its claws to carve the roots of tree and absorb moisture and nutrients.

Name: Nocturne
Summary: A demonic amalgamation drawn from the nightmares that haunt every sentient mind, the thing known as Nocturne has become a primordial force of pure evil. It is liquidly chaotic in aspect, a faceless shadow with cold eyes and armed with wicked-looking blades. After freeing itself from the spirit realm, Nocturne descended upon the waking world, to feed upon the kind of terror that can only thrive in true darkness.

Name: Norman Osborn
Summary: Norman Osborn is the corrupt founder and head of Oscorp, a multi-billion dollar multinational corporation. After he took the experimental "Goblin Formula" to enhance his intelligence, his already unstable mind fractured further, leading to him becoming the original Green Goblin. In this role, he has been Spider-Man's greatest and most persistent archenemy, responsible for the death of Gwen Stacy. While his primary opponent and obsession is Spider-Man, his goals have branched out further in the past, and, at one time, he was the director of H.A.M.M.E.R., a replacement for S.H.I.E.L.D., and the leader of an Avengers populated by "reformed" supervillains, as the "Iron Patriot".

Name: Oranguru
Summary: Oranguru is a Normal/Psychic type Pokémon that originated from Pokémon Sun and Pokémon Moon. It is an Orangutan inspired Pokémon, which resides in the forests, and often is known for giving instructions to other Pokémon.

Name: Orianna Reveck
Summary: Tier: 7-B | Low 1-C

Name: Oricorio
Summary: Oricorio is a Flying-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VII. While it is not known to evolve into or from any other Pokémon, it can change forms by sipping the nectar of certain flowers.

Name: Passimian
Summary: nan

Name: Pidgey
Summary: Pidgey is the first of the early grass bird final evolutions. It evolves starting at level 18 and evolves from Pidgeotto to Pidgeot at level 36.

Name: Pincurchin
Summary: Pincurchin is an Electric type Pokemon first appearing in the eight generation of Pokemon games. As of now, it is only known to be found in the Galar region. It is not known to evolve into any Pokemon, or have prior evolutions.

Name: Poipole
Summary: Poipole is one of the many Ultra Beasts. It was seen as owned by the Ultra Recon Squad. It is apparently seen as a starter, much like Bulbasaur or Charmander in their world. Despite this, the Pokémon is capable of holding off Pokémon who are easily far stronger than said starters.

Name: Polaris (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Lorna Dane is the illegitimate daughter of the mutant terrorist Magneto, possessing power to manipulate magnetic fields similar to him. Having fought for peaceful coexistence for most of her life, she has been a seasoned member of the X-Men along with her longtime lover Havok, under the codename Polaris, although her impressive abilities lead her to being mind controlled many times to battle her teammates and loved ones.

Name: Poliwrath
Summary: Poliwhirl is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a spherical body. It has bulbous eyes that protrude from the top of its head. A black and white swirl covers its belly, which is actually its organs showing through its thin skin. It appears to have white gloves on its hands and rounded, digit-less feet. When out of water, it sweats to keep its skin moist and healthy. This keeps it covered in an oily fluid that allows it to slip away from enemies. All of its skin feels this way except where its swirl is, which is instead very smooth. The swirl on its belly undulates slowly and staring at it induces drowsiness.

Name: Porygon
Summary: Porygon is a man-made Pokémon created utilizing the latest, most advanced technologies. It consists entirely of programming code and is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy-protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying. Although people anticipate this Pokémon can fly into space, none has managed the feat yet.

Name: Preston Ramirez
Summary: Preston Ramirez is the main antagonist of Preston’s Hourglass, a 2023 mascot horror game by Dreadful Studios. The story follows a team of archaeologists exploring the Prestonian Catacombs, where they uncover an ancient time-manipulating artifact—“Preston’s Hourglass”. Activating it awakens Preston, an eldritch time demon who kills the entire team except one survivor. To escape, the survivor must collect eight spell pieces to seal Preston again. The game’s lore reveals Preston was once a scientist obsessed with time experiments, which caused widespread destruction in the 1970s. His obsession ruined his life and turned him into the monster buried beneath Prestonia, losing his wife in the process.

Name: Primarina
Summary: Primarina (Japanese: アシレーヌ Ashirēnu) is a dual-type Water/Fairy Pokémon.

Name: Psylocke
Summary: A British mutant telepath born into a magical lineage, Elizabeth "Betsy" Braddock's life was bound for weirdness from birth.
