Though Cheren sometimes comes off as cold and distant, he's actually a good hearted and very honest person who seeks to do the right thing. He is also very smart and knowledgeable about Pokémon.

Name: Cherrim
Summary: Cherrim, the Blossom Pokémon, is sensible to sunlight to a notable degree, to the point it may change to it's Sunshine Form if exposed enough.

Name: Chesnaught
Summary: Chesnaught is a Grass/Fighting-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI. It evolves from Quilladin who is an evolution of Chespin.

Name: Chitauri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Chitauri are a race of cybernetically enhanced aliens who serve under the leadership of Thanos, who gave them over to Loki for use in his invasion of Earth in an attempt to acquire the Tesseract. Though they successfully invaded the planet through a wormhole created by the Tesseract, they were ultimately defeated by the Avengers.

Name: Chrysalis (Eternity Girl)
Summary: Caroline Sharp, better known by her alias, Formless Girl, is a fictional character which first debuted in 1956's "The Astounding Tales #32", conceptualized by artist George Sumner and having originally been conceived as a darker take on the superhero genre better defined as an "horror superhero", her character was later remodeled after Sumner's editors pressed him into changing her concept and execution to fit more with the "science-fiction superhero" mold, increasingly popular at the time of her creation. Regardless, the character still steared closely to her creator's original idea, her origin story being given as that of an agent pertaining to a secret governmental organization nominated Alpha-13, who, in a mention with the objective of thwarting the supervillain Madame Atom's plan of detonating a nuclear drill within a Ziggurat holding vast amounts of divine power within itself, thus taking the elemental force of an unspecified Sumerian god unto her body and becoming the most powerful being in the Universe. Attempting to deactivate Atom's drill by hand, Caroline eventually ran low on time and the drill exploded within the Ziggurat, embuing her with the powerful magic contained in the construction and drastically mutating her appearance into that of an inorganic, blue-skinned chimeric humanoid, as a result granting her the power to fully control her own atomic structure, thus turning her into the titular Formless Girl.

Name: Chuul
Summary: Chuuls are the creations of the mighty abeloths created by twisting normal marine life so that they could have servants on the land. All chuuls are the creations of these eldritch aquatic creatures, and have survived since the fall of the Aboleth's empire, constantly growing.

Name: Cinderace
Summary: Cinderace is a Fire type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. By juggling a pebble with its feet, Cinderace can transform it into a burning soccer ball. By putting a spin on the ball, it can launch attacks that its opponents struggle to evade.

Name: Cinderblock
Summary: Cinderblock is a recurring antagonist in the Teen Titans animated series. He serves as a henchman and enforcer for several villains throughout the series, typically Slade.

Name: Clair (Pokémon)
Key: Herself | Gym Battle | Postgame | Pokémon World Tournament
Summary: Clair is the 8th and final Gym Leader in the Johto region. Born to the same clan of Dragon Tamers as Lance (and also being his cousin), Clair has had an affinity for Dragon type Pokémon ever since she was a child. Not to be outdone by her cousin, who became a member of the Elite Four when she was young, Clair too trained vigorously in the ways of Dragon type Pokémon until she finally became the Gym Leader of her hometown. However, as she ascended to the role of Gym Leader, Lance too ascended beyond a member of the Elite Four to become the Indigo League Champion, driving her motivation to catch up to him and prove herself as the ultimate Dragon type Trainer even further to this day.

Name: Classic Loki (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Loki Laufeyson was a variant of Loki who survived Thanos' assault on the Statesman. In the aftermath of the Infinity War, Loki lived on an isolated planet for centuries before attempting to reunite with Thor, although he was pruned by the Time Variance Authority and sent to the Void. After meeting another Loki Variant and Sylvie Laufeydottir, Loki sacrificed his life distracting Alioth in order to save them, and was consumed by the beast.

Name: Claydol
Summary: Claydol is a Pokemon originating from the third generation. It originated as a doll that was brought to life 20,000 years ago and imbued with psychic power. Its limbs are unattached from it, so it uses its psychic powers to levitate them. It evolves from Baltoy at level 36.

Name: Clefairy
Summary: Clefairy is a peculiar and friendly Pokémon often seen at night in mountains dancing to the moon.

Name: Clemont
Summary: Clemont is the Lumiose City Gym Leader; the fifth Gym Leader that a Pokémon Trainer must face if they want to challenge the Kalos Elite Four. For the Lumiose Gym’s challenge before the actual Gym battle, much like Blaine, his little sister Bonnie likes to quiz would-be challengers on general information on Pokémon, with the punishment of facing a trainer if they answer wrong.

Name: Cleveland-class Light Cruiser
Summary: The Cleveland-class light cruisers were built for the U.S. Navy during World War II, and were the most numerous class of light cruisers ever built. The ships were designed with the goal of increased cruising range, anti-aircraft armament, torpedo protection, etc., compared with earlier U.S. cruisers. Fifty-two ships of this class were originally planned, but nine of them were completed as the light aircraft carriers of the Independence class, and two of them were completed to a somewhat different design, called the Fargo class. The Fargo-class cruisers were a modified version of the previous Cleveland-class cruiser design; the main difference was a more compact pyramidal superstructure with single trunked funnel, intended to improve the arcs of fire of the anti-aircraft guns. In all, 13 Fargo-class ships were planned but only Fargo and Huntington were ever completed, the rest being cancelled at varying states of completion with the de-escalation of World War II. Of the 27 Cleveland-class cruisers that were commissioned, one (Galveston) was completed as a guided missile cruiser and five were later modified as Galveston and Providence-class guided missile cruisers. Following the naming convention at the time, all the ships completed as cruisers were named for US cities and towns.

Name: Cloyster
Summary: Shellder is a water-type Pokémon from Kanto. They spend their time hidden away in their shell, their tongue sticking out.

Name: Cobra (Fairy Tail)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Cobra, real name Erik, is a former member of the now-disbanded Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of six powerful Mages. He, along with the other Oración Seis members, sought to find Nirvana, a destructive Magic that was sealed long ago. At some point before seeking Nirvana, Erik implanted a Dragon Slayer Lacrima into his own body, which thereby resulted in him becoming the Poison Dragon Slayer. Cobra was among the few remaining members who formed the Reborn Oración Seis, and later joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. In the year X793, he became the boyfriend of Kinana.

Name: Colress
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 4)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon World Tournament)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Plasma Frigate)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game Battles)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Tree)'''
Summary: However, I disagree!

Name: Conkeldurr
Summary: Conkeldurr is a fighting type Pokémon from the Unova region introduced in Generation V.

Name: Copperajah
Summary: Copperajah, the Copperderm Pokémon, is a Steel-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII and is the evolution of Cufant. It is also one of the few Pokémon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Corsola
Summary: Corsola is a small, pink Pokémon with branch-like growths on its back, which are similar to coral. It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty, and its branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night. The points on its head absorb nutrients from clear water. They cannot survive in polluted water, and their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water, which is why they prefer the unpolluted southern seas. In one south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

Name: Crabrawler
Summary: Crabrawler, and further on Crabominable, is a Fighting-type Pokémon from the Alola region.

Name: Cramorant
Summary: Cramorant is a blue, bird Pokémon resembling a cormorant. It has bright green, large, circular eyes with small pupils and a large, thin yellow beak. It has a ruff of light gray feathers that goes around its torso and sticks out at the back, making them resemble a bib. Its tail feathers have a small dot-shaped marking of this same shade of gray. It has a ruff of feathers on its head, with the largest clump pointing backward and being surrounded by small singular feathers. Its feet are black, webbed, and have three toes. Its wings seem to be perpetually extended.

Name: Crawdaunt
Summary: Corphish is a red crustacean Pokémon, resembling a lobster somewhat, that is capable of living and thriving in harsh environments, which includes incredibly polluted rivers, due to its hardy nature and its ability to adapt, rivalling even Feebas in this regard. It has two large, sharp pincers which it uses to hold on tightly to and catch prey.

Name: Crobat
Summary: Crobat is a Flying-/Poison-type Pokemon introduced in Generation II. It a purple bat with four wings, with the hind set replacing its legs. It flies silently in the air to sneak up on enemies, but is clumsy while walking. It is also the first Pokemon to be a new evolution from a previous one, followed closely by Steelix and Scizor. It evolves by high friendship from Golbat, who evolves from Zubat at level 25.

Name: Cruise Missile
Summary: The cruise missile is generally a sea to land based weapon with high destructive capabilities. A much more known variant is the BGM-109 Tomahawk missile whose original design is still used today.

Name: Cryogonal
Summary: Cryogonal is an Ice-type Pokémon mainly found in Unova.

Name: Cyrus
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Celestic Town)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Team Galactic HQ)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Distortion World)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Cyrus is the nihilistic main antagonist of the Sinnoh Pokémon games. He is the leader of Team Galactic and wishes to use the power of Palkia and Dialga to erase the universe, and remake it as a realm devoid of spirit.

Name: Daisy Johnson (Quake)
Summary: Daisy Johnson is the daughter of Calvin Zabo with a woman with the inhuman gene. Her mother gave her to adoption little after she was born, she ended up being adopted and her name become Cory Sutter. As a teen she tried to steal but ended up being caught and causing an earthquake, she was interrogated by Nick Fury who told her the truth about her biological parents and recruited her to S.H.I.E.L.D. She was personally trained by Nick Fury to become the best spy and at the age of 18 she become the director of S.H.I.E.L.D. She named herself Quake after an encounter with the avengers.

Name: Dar-Benn (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Supremor Dar-Benn was a revolutionary Kree warrior and an Accuser of the Kree Empire who fought to restore her homeland after a long civil war. Formerly a member of Starforce, she blamed Captain Marvel for inciting a long civil war on Hala, which led to the planet's desolation. After discovering a Quantum Band on MB-418, Dar-Benn tore apart Jump Points in space to extract natural resources from various planets to restore her homeworld. She was eventually killed as a result of using two Quantum Bands at the same time.

Name: Darius (League of Legends)
Summary: There is no greater symbol of Noxian might than

Name: Darmanitan
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Death Knight (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Death Knights are immensely powerful undead that commonly rule over massive hordes of less impressive deceased creatures. Damned to eternal suffering, Death Knights are immortal until they repay their grievances- those who in life vowed an oath and defied it before their death. Truly, the Death Knights are the most damned of the Undead, as even their former gods turn their backs on them.

Name: Decidueye
Summary: Decidueye (Japanese: ジュナイパー Junaipā) is a dual-type Grass/Ghost Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It evolves from Dartrix and is the final form of Rowlet.

Name: Deep Sea King
Summary: Deep Sea King was a Demon-level threat who ruled over the Seafolk as their king and claimed the sea as his own. His first appearance came across Stinger, A-Class rank 10 Hero, and easily defeated the tired hero.

Name: Delibird
Summary: Delibird is a dual ice and flying type Pokémon. It is mainly known for transporting food and others goods in its tail, resembling a bag.

Name: Delphox
Summary: Delphox (Japanese: マフォクシー Mahoxy)is a dual-type Fire/Psychic Pokémon introduced in Pokémon X and Y. It evolves from Braixen and is the final form of Fennekin.

Name: Deva
Summary: Devas are messengers of the Good-aligned deities that they serve, generally taking the role of spreading goodness in the lesser planes in the name of their gods- either a subtle humanoid or an animal. When they need to they cast off their guise of mortality and appear in their true godly beauty.

Name: Dewgong
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Dhelmise
Summary: Dhelmise is a Pokémon made up of a ship's anchor and wheel, tied together by green seaweed, which in actuality is the Pokémon's true body. It is said that the souls of seaweed adrift in the waves are reborn as Dhelmise. It maintains itself by infusing its body with new organic material found on the seabed.

Name: Diglett
Summary: Diglett is a Ground-Type Pokémon from Kanto. It is noted for living mainly underground, and usually only having its tiny head exposed.

Name: Doctor Strange (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thor: So, Earth has wizards now? Strange: The preferred term is "Master of the Mystic Arts".

Name: Doctor Strange Supreme (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Doctor Stephen Vincent Strange is a sorcerer and a Master of the Mystic Arts. Originally a brilliant, although arrogant, neurosurgeon, Strange got into a car accident which resulted in the death of the love of his life, Doctor Christine Palmer. Fueled by grief, Stephen set off to learn about the mystic arts, and eventually stopped Dormammu from devouring his reality, saving Earth and his universe. Despite this, Strange remained haunted about Christine's death and began a dark journey to gain the power needed to resurrect her, bringing about dangerous consequences for his universe as Doctor Strange Supreme. He is an alternate reality version of Doctor Strange.

Name: Doctrine Dark
Summary: Doctrine Dark was once a brave soldier with an exceptional sense for battle. Dark once served under the orders of Guile with his own special tactical reconnaissance unit. During his tour of duty, his own unit got into a bit of a scuffle with another rival unit, lead by Rolento. The minor scuffle escalated into a full-on battle, with both sides receiving heavy casualties. Doctrine Dark was the only member of his unit to escape.

Name: Dodrio
Summary: Dodrio is a three headed bird Pokémon based off both, the Ostrich and the Dodo Bird. It evolves from Doduo at level 31.

Name: Donphan
Summary: nan

Name: Doppelganger (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: We want what is ours! I chose your chaplain- his life was to be mine! His wealth, his fine robes, his women- had you not interfered, they would all belong to me!''

Name: Doric
Summary: Doric is an tiefiling who lives in the Neverwinter Wood after being abandoned there as a child and created among an community of wood elves. Even thought she keeps herself emotionally distant she has great affection for her land and her fellow comrades.

Name: Dorina T'sarran
Summary: Dorina T'sarran is a vampire priestess of Kiaransalee, a foul Drow goddess seeking to usurp Lolth. In her state of undeath, Dorina is hailed as a terrifying force and weapon in service of her mother, the great priestess Irae T'sarran. Dorina is regal yet feral, often relying on a combination of elegant planning along with devastating brute force, a tactic which has allowed her to overcome much of the Underdark's Drow population despite being outnumbered. In her mother's genocidal conquest, thousands have fallen at the hands of Dorina. Despite not having a loving relationship with her mother, the two have forged a bond of respect for one another- Dorina's strength serves Irae extremely well, whereas Dorina finds her position to be useful in becoming even more powerful.

Name: Dorzad ain Vereet
Summary: Dorzad ain Vereet is a half-human krinth who grew weary of service to the Shadovar, and began his plans to escape only to wind up leading an organized resistance movement that would help others flee in his stead. During his time in servitude he was known as a master of many trades, including that of brute force. He is known as a practical realist and will take whatever options best present themselves to free his bretheren.

Name: Draco Stormsailer
Summary: Draco Stormsailer was once a nefarious sea captain and brigand, parading across the world gathering treasures tohim. When this life began to weigh heavy on him, he settled down inquiet Rhoona, becoming the High Commander of the city's military forces in short order. During his time in this position, he became close friends with Xanathon, the High Priest of Cretia, who spoke dark whisperings into Draco's ear.

Name: Dragapult
Summary: Dragapult is an spectral dragon Pokemon and the resident Pseudo Legendary in the 8th generation of Pokemon. Alongside being a ghost dragon, it is based on fighter jets, and fires its first form, Dreepy, from itself like missiles. Apparently, the Dreepy like being launched. It evolves from Drakloak at level 60, which evolves from Dreepy at level 50.

Name: Dragonite
Summary: Dragonite is a "pseudo-legendary" Dragon and Flying-type Pokémon from the first generation, and one of the strongest Pokémon of its time. It evolves from Dratini at level 30, and evolves from Dragonair at 55.

Name: Drampa
Summary: Drampa is a Normal/Dragon-type Pokémon from the Alola region introduced in Generation VII.

Name: Drawmij
Summary: Drawmij is a mage from Oerth of considerable power, known for a number of iconic spells he has invented over the years. Among them are included Drawmij's instant summons and Drawmij's marvelous shield, though in truth dozens of widely used spells were penned by the mage. He is a member of the Circle of Eight, a group of extremely powerful archmagi based in Greyhawk, where they promote the virtues of balance and order. In terms of personality, Drawmij is a quiet sort, preferring secrecy, even in regards to his allies.

Name: Drax the Destroyer (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Drax, also known as Drax the Destroyer, is a former intergalactic criminal and a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy. He sought revenge on Ronan the Accuser for killing his wife and daughter, and went on a rampage across the galaxy, ending with him being imprisoned by the Nova Corps in the Kyln. There Drax became uneasy allies with Star-Lord, Gamora, Rocket Raccoon, and Groot. Together they broke out of the Kyln and became embroiled in the Quest for the Orb. After the Battle of Xandar, in which he finally gained the vengeance on Ronan he had so long sought, Drax left Xandar with the other Guardians.

Name: Dream Vestige
Summary: Dream Vestiges are born from the cumulative nightmares of enormous population centers- the first was born from an entire city's population's pent up nightmares after dying during a cursed sleep enchantment. Dream vestiges are nightmares made manifest in our world, and seek to absorb other nightmares into themselves. It consumes all- mind, body, and soul, dead or undead- thus, not even the dead are safe from the all-consuming hunger of the Dream Vestige.

Name: Drednaw
Summary: Drednaw is a powerful snapping turtle Pokemon. They are known for being incredibly difficult to train due to their vicious nature. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Drizzt Do'Urden
Summary: Tier: At least Low 7-B

Name: Duneth Whareill
Summary: Duneth Whareill was the archmage of the Shattered Tower, a great mage institution located in the Drow city of Maerimydra. However, believing himself to be strong enough to take the city for himself, during the Silence of Lolth he betrayed the city and contacted Kurgoth Hellspawn and invited him to invade with Duneth's assistance. Before his plan could come to fruition, however, Duneth was slain by the second betrayal to rock the once-great Drow city- Irae T'sarran and her cult of Kiaransalee murdered Duneth and took the throne of the city for themselves.

Name: Dunsparce
Summary: Dunsparce is an unevolving normal type Pokemon introduced in the second generation.

Name: Duraludon
Summary: Duraludon is a Steel-/Dragon- type Pokemon introduced in the Galar region. It's a cave dwelling dinosaur-like Pokemon. It has an intense rivalry with Tyranitar, due to sharing the same territory, and constantly fights over it. It has the exceptionally durable cells, even compared to other Steel- type Pokemon, which makes it resistant to earthquakes. Despite its heavy look, it's surprisingly light, and is therefore very agile for its size.

Name: Durant (Pokémon)
Summary: Durant is an ant with a metal outer shell. Colonies of Durant work together to create complex and interconnected burrows in mountains, while some individuals play different roles in fending off their natural predators.

Name: Dusknoir
Summary: Dusknoir is a final form ghost-type Pokémon introduced in Gen IV. It evolves from Duskull into Dusclops, and from Dusclops into Dusknoir by holding a Reaper Cloth and being traded.

Name: Dystnine
Summary: Dystnine is of a model of Android mass-produced by Gargantua. However, strangely enough, Dystnine inexplicably developed a soul. This caused him to develop a Septima. Sumeragi was going to disassemble him for research purposes, but were stopped by Stella. As such, he began serving the Adept. When iX killed her, this awakened emotions of anger and sadness within Dystnine, greatly improving his Septima to the point that he could fight against iX.

Name: Earthshaker (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created thousands of years ago by the advanced civilization of Blackmoor, the Earthshaker survived the destruction of its creators. Found hundreds of years later by a Gnome tribe, it now operates as a traveling tourist attraction, mobile home, and as an occasional public builder

Name: Ebony Maw (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ebony Maw is an adopted child of Thanos and a member of the Black Order. After taking the Tesseract with Thanos and his fellow henchmen, Ebony Maw and Cull Obsidian were sent to take the Time Stone from Doctor Strange. Cull Obsidian is teleported away, but Ebony Maw managed to capture Doctor Strange and attempted transport him to Titan on his ship. However, Iron Man and Spider-Man attacked the ship, and Ebony Maw was killed in the skirmish by being thrown into space.

Name: Edgin Darvis
Summary: Edgin Darvis is an human bard from Icewind Dale and was in the past a member of the Harpers, a spy organization dedicated to protecting Faerûn’s common folk, this changed after the death of his wife, when Edgin has forsworn his oath and turned to thievery to support his family. His strong moral compass whoever compels him to steal only from people he believes deserve will not suffer from it.

Name: Edwin Tolstoff
Summary: Edwin Tolstoff was a mighty spellcaster before attempting to gain yet further power by means of dark ascension. Turning to the mighty god of Death, Nerull, he would murder his colleagues to take their power, he attracted the attention of the Worm that Walks. Now, given the power he wanted, he aims to free his master in the hopes of escape.

Name: Eelektross
Summary: Eelektross is an Electric-type Pokémon, introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Eelektrik when given a Thunder Stone, and is the final evolution of Tynamo.

Name: Eevee
Summary: nan

Name: Ego (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ego was a Celestial, a primordial and extremely powerful entity, and the father of Star-Lord. He originally appeared to be a caring and wise father with a cocky personality, similar to his own son. However, it is later revealed that he is a ruthless entity with a god complex who wishes to conquer the universe. He is a mysterious adventurer from far parts of the galaxy who has heard the legend of the Guardians of the Galaxy following the Battle of Xandar and has come to meet them for the first time. Reunited with his son in 2014, Ego desired to forward his plan to rule the universe by using his son's Celestial genes to terraform the planets he had planted alien seedlings on. Ego's plans were foiled by the Guardians of the Galaxy and he was ultimately destroyed by their hand.

Name: Ein (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shadow PKMN Lab)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Realgam Tower)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Deep Colosseum)'''
Summary: Ein (Japanese: ボルグ Borg) is one of the original four Cipher Admins. A cruel and callous young scientist, he is long on ambition and short on emotion. He is obsessed with the idea of creating an insanely powerful Pokémon at any cost which he managed to do with amazing results.

Name: Eitri (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Eitri is the King of the Dwarves, an ancient race of skilled forgers and blacksmiths who hail from Nidavellir. He was forced by Thanos to forge the Infinity Gauntlet. He later worked with Thor, Rocket and Groot to forge Stormbreaker in order to kill Thanos.

Name: Eldes
Summary: Eldes (Japanese: エルデス Eldes) is the younger brother of Ardos and one of the five Cipher Admins of Pokémon XD: Gale of Darkness.

Name: Electivire
Summary: Electivire is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Electabuzz, and the final form of the Gen II Elekid. It evolves when traded with an Electrizer.

Name: Electrode
Summary: Electrode, the evolved form of Voltorb. Known as "The Bomb Ball", it constantly explodes. It is often mistaken for a Pokeball due to its shape and feeds on electricity to the point of being problematic for humans.

Name: Elemental HERO Thunder Giant
Summary: Elemental HERO Thunder Giant is a monster in Yu-Gi-Oh!. He belongs to the Elemental HERO archetype. He is the fusion of Elemental HERO Sparkman and Elemental HERO Clayman.

Name: Elesa
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Teams (Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokémon Team (World Leaders Tournament)'''
Summary: Elesa, "The Shining Beauty" is a model and Gym Leader in Nimbasa City, region of Unova. She specializes in Electric-type Pokémon.

Name: Elfman Strauss
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc to Grand Magic Games Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Elfman Strauss is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and the brother of Mirajane and Lisanna. In the year X782, Elfman was deeply scarred by an incident where his younger sister, Lisanna, was supposedly killed by him when she tried to stop his rampage after he attempted to use Beast Soul: Full-Body Take Over. During his rampage, Elfman hit Lisanna with great force, throwing her a great distance. It is said that due to this, Elfman's heart was locked shut, despite his use of the spell to protect his sisters.

Name: Eli Morrow (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Elias "Eli" Morrow was the maternal uncle of Robbie and Gabe Reyes and a former employee at Momentum Labs. Witnessing the experiments being done by his coworkers, Morrow began to crave the power for himself, and betrayed his colleagues, turning them into ghost-like entities before attacking Joseph Bauer in order to find the Darkhold, but Bauer fell into a coma before revealing its location, and Morrow was imprisoned at South Ridge Penitentiary. He was later kidnapped by Bauer's wife, Lucy in order to force Morrow to use the Darkhold and reverse the process. However, Morrow tricked her and managed to fulfill his original plan, entering the machine and obtaining the power of creating matter at his own will. In the final battle against the S.H.I.E.L.D., Morrow was killed by Ghost Rider, who revealed himself to be Robbie Reyes.

Name: Elise (League of Legends)
Summary: Elise is a deadly predator who dwells in a shuttered, lightless palace, deep in the Immortal Bastion of Noxus. Once she was mortal, the mistress of a once-powerful house, but the bite of a vile spider god transformed her into something beautiful, undying, and utterly inhuman. To maintain her eternal youth, Elise preys upon the innocent, and there are few who can resist her seductions.

Name: Ember Guard
Summary: Ember Guards are dim-witted but ultimately extremely powerful servants of Imix, whom he often gifts to particularly useful followers as bodyguards and brutes. No servant of Imix would ever refuse such a gift, despite the fact that ember guards serve little purpose outside of brutally efficient killing. Their sole source of joy was pain being inflicted on others, making them extremely willing to destroy any enemies of their masters.

Name: Emboar
Summary: Emboar (Japanese: エンブオー, Enbuoh) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Pignite starting at level 36. It is the final form of Tepig.

Name: Empoleon
Summary: Empoleon is a Water/Steel type Starter Pokémon from Sinnoh, based on an Emperor Penguin. It evolves from Piplup into Prinplup at level 16, and from Prinplup to Empoleon at level 36.

Name: Erigor
Summary: Erigor is the strongest member of the former Dark Guild Eisenwald. He became infamously known as the Death God due to being a Mage that only accepted assassination jobs. This epithet of him is supported by his weapon of choice, a scythe. Seven years later, Erigor escaped from imprisonment and became a member of the Reborn Oración Seis under the name of Grim Reaper.

Name: Erika (Pokémon)
Summary: Erika is the sleepy fourth Gym leader of Kanto, known as the Nature Loving Princess. She specializes in the Grass-type, and gives out the Rainbow badge when defeated.

Name: Erza Knightwalker
Summary: Erza Knightwalker is part of the Edolas Kingdom and is the Royal Army Captain of the 2nd Magic War Division. She is the Edolas counterpart of Erza Scarlet. Unlike her Earth Land counterpart, Erza Knightwalker is sadistic and cruel, showing no sympathy towards her enemies; killing them without mercy. She was involved in the killing of over half of the members of Edolas Fairy Tail, thus, earning her epithet. After being beaten by Erza Scarlet for the final time, Knightwalker acts gentler, having been touched by her counterpart's words.

Name: Erza Scarlet (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Erza Scarlet is an infamous S-Class Mage titled "Fairy Queen Titania." She is renowned for her combat prowess as well as her status as one of her guild's most stern disciplinarians. Despite her intimidating exterior, she deeply cares for her comrades and treats them as if they were family, as she lost her own after her hometown was ransacked by fanatical worshippers of the Dark Mage Zeref and was forced to build the Tower of Heaven. She was imprisoned together with several other slaves, most of which were children. Among these children were Jellal Fernandes, Shô, Simon, Wally Buchanan, and Millianna. While they asked each other for their names, she said that her name was just "Erza." Hence, Jellal decided to give her the surname "Scarlet" after her scarlet hair so they would never forget it. Eventually, she rebelled against the cult and escaped, but not without losing Jellal, who had been corrupted by Zeref's Dark Arts. She also served as the guild's 7th Guild Master during Makarov's absence in X792.

Name: Escavalier
Summary: Escavalier is a Bug/Steel type Pokémon, introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Karrablast when traded specifically with a Shelmet, due to a strange, unknown reaction to electrical stimulation.

Name: Eternal Flower Floette
Summary: 3000 years ago, AZ befriended a Floette who was unfortunately forced to enter a war Kalos was facing. She was killed untimely and, in his grief, AZ created the Ultimate Weapon in order to revive her. Floette was resurrected from the dead by the machine draining the life force of the Pokemon soldiers. Disgusted to learn of the source of her resurrection, Floette left AZ.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Evelynn
Summary: Within the dark seams of Runeterra, the demon Evelynn searches for her next victim. She lures in prey with the voluptuous façade of a human female, but once a person succumbs to her charms, Evelynn’s true form is unleashed. She then subjects her victim to unspeakable torment, gratifying herself with their pain. To the demon, these liaisons are innocent flings. To the rest of Runeterra, they are ghoulish tales of lust gone awry and horrific reminders of the cost of wanton desire.

Name: Evergreen
Summary: Evergreen is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and the only female member of the Thunder God Tribe. After Fairy Tail's disbandment she joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the other members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, a little while after the guild's reformation, she left to rejoin Fairy Tail alongside Laxus and the rest of her team.

Name: Evice
Summary: Evice (Japanese: ワルダック Wardack) is the criminal mastermind behind Cipher. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher Head (Japanese: シャドーのボス Shadow Boss). He disguises himself as the mayor of Phenac City under the name of Es Cade (Japanese: バックレー Backley). In his disguise, he is a fat and jolly gentleman who appears to be worried about the increase in crime caused by Cipher and Team Snagem, yet as the head of Cipher, he appears to have done nothing to stop either of them, ensuring that Snagem and Cipher work without interference.

Name: Executioner (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Skurge was an Asgardian warrior and the guardian of the Bifrost Bridge in Heimdall's absence, who became Hela's Executioner. However, his disillusion and inner conflict of his position ultimately made him turn against the Goddess of Death, which allowed his people to survive the destruction of Asgard at the cost of his own life. It also finally made Skurge a hero of Asgard rather than a villain.

Name: Exeggutor
Summary: Exeggcute is a Pokémon resembling six light pink eggs, usually seen arranged with five heads huddled around a sixth. Each "head" has a slightly different facial expression, but each face has triangular eyes with tiny black pupils and a small mouth. Each shell has some cracks, and one member of the bundle usually has its yellow insides or brain exposed. More numerous cracks are a sign that it is close to evolution. Despite looking like eggs, Exeggcute is actually more closely related to plant seeds. It is believed to carry genes of plants and other species. Exeggcute gathers in swarms of six. The heads communicate with each other by using a form of telepathy that only they can understand. Should the number of Exeggcute be reduced to less than six, the remaining Exeggcute will attempt to replace it with a similarly sized Pokémon as seen in the anime. Pidgeotto and Crabrawler are its natural predators, which it chases off with psychokinesis. Exeggcute inhabits jungles and forests.

Name: Exploud
Summary: Exploud is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a large mouth. It has red eyes, a stubby nose, and two peg-like teeth in each jaw. It has protruding tubes with holes along its body: seven forming a crest on top of its head, one on each elbow and knee, two along its back, and one at the end of each of its two tails. The tubes along its head-crest and tails are tipped with yellow, while the ones along its back have yellow semicircular patterns on either side. There are two yellow semicircle markings on its belly, but they are rarely seen due to its giant mouth. Its arms have three thin stripes below its elbow and three fingers. Each foot has four claws, three in the front and one in the back, and a yellow paw pad.

Name: Ezreal
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Magic, potentially Low 6-B with Ne'Zuk's Gauntlet | Unknown, 4-B with Magic | Unknown, 7-B with Magic, 2-A via hax, up to Low 1-C | 4-B

Name: F-117 Nighthawk
Summary: The F-117 Nighthawk is a single seat, twin engine attack aircraft developed by the secretive Skunk Works division of Lockheed and operated chiefly by the USAF. The aircraft is based on the earlier Have Blue technology demonstrator and was the first operational aircraft to be designed around stealth technology.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F-35 Lightning II
Summary: The F-35 Lightning II is family of single-seat, single-engine, all-weather stealth multi-role fighters developed and manufactured by Lockheed Martin for the Joint Strike Fighter program. The fifth-generation combat aircraft is designed to perform ground-attack and air-superiority missions.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Faba
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''First Fights Teams''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post Game/Title Defense)'''
Summary: Faba is the Branch Chief of the Aether Foundation and the foundation's "last line of defense".

Name: Falcon (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Samuel Thomas "Sam" Wilson, better known as the Falcon, was a former United States Air Force pararescue airman who left active duty when his wing-man Riley died in combat, choosing instead to begin helping any of his fellow veterans who were suffering from post-traumatic stress disorder at Veterans Affairs. During this time, Wilson met and soon became an ally of Captain America during the beginning of the HYDRA Uprising, assisting him in bringing down Alexander Pierce's schemes for Project Insight before then choosing to remain with Captain America. Falcon later joined the Avengers, and has been an active member ever since.

Name: Falinks
Summary: Falinks may appear to only be one caterpillar-like Pokémon, but in reality, it’s six small troopers lined up to create the image of one Pokémon. Five troopers follow their leader, the brass.

Name: Fandral (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Fandral was a highly respected Asgardian warrior, friend of Thor and member of the Warriors Three, known for his charm. Alongside all his fellow warriors, Fandral took part in a poorly considered strike against all the Frost Giants of Jotunheim, which soon resulted in Odin banishing Thor to Earth without his powers. When Loki then took the throne of Asgard during Thor's banishment, Fandral and his allies played a key role in saving Thor from the Destroyer before bringing him back to Asgard where he successfully stopped Loki from stealing throne of Asgard and restoring the peace.

Name: Farfetch'd
Summary: Farfetch’d is an avian Pokémon that resembles a light brown duck with a white underbelly. It has a flat, yellow beak, brown eyes, a V-shaped black marking on its forehead, and a three-feather crest on top of its head. Its wings are as big as its body and appear to be prehensile enough to substitute for hands. It has yellow legs with webbed feet and a stubby tail.

Name: Fat Man
Summary: Fat Man was the codename for the type of plutonium atomic bomb that was detonated over the Japanese city of Nagasaki by the United States on 9 August 1945.

Name: Faust (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Faust is the former King of Edolas, banished and succeeded by his disowned son, Mystogan. He is the Edolas counterpart of Makarov Dreyar.

Name: Fearow
Summary: Fearow is the beak Normal/Flying Pokémon and first appears in Generation I. It evolves from Spearow at level 20.

Name: Feraligatr
Summary: Feraligatr is the reptilian final water starter from the Johto region. It evolves from Croconaw at level 30, which itself evolves from Totodile at level 18, later than any starter save only for Turtwig, with whom it is tied.

Name: Ferrothorn
Summary: Ferrothorn. The Thorn Pod Pokemon. It's a metallic Pokemon that resembles a durian with three vine tendrils coming out of it. This Pokemon likes to attach itself onto ceilings and launch spikes at opponents coming beneath it. it evolves from Ferroseed at level 40.

Name: Fiddlesticks
Summary: Something has awoken in Runeterra. Something ancient. Something terrible. The ageless horror known as Fiddlesticks stalks the edges of mortal society, drawn to areas thick with paranoia where it feeds upon terrorized victims. Wielding a jagged scythe, the haggard, makeshift creature reaps fear itself, shattering the minds of those unlucky enough to survive in its wake. Beware the sounding of the crow, or the whispering of the shape that appears almost human...Fiddlesticks has returned.

Name: Fiora Laurent
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-C | Low 7-C, Low 2-C via Hax

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Fizz
Summary: Fizz is an amphibious yordle, who dwells among the reefs surrounding Bilgewater. He often retrieves and returns the tithes cast into the sea by superstitious captains, but even the saltiest of sailors know better than to cross him—for many are the tales of those who have underestimated this slippery character. Often mistaken for some manner of capricious ocean spirit, he seems able to command the beasts of the deep, and delights in confounding his allies and enemies alike.

Name: Flame Snake
Summary: Often used as guards the Flame Snake comes in 3 variants; Small, Lesser and Greater Flame Snake with each one being stronger then the former, the strongest of their kin being theorised to be banished demons cursed into being snakes.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Forretress
Summary: Forretress is a Pokemon debuting in the second generation. It's a bug covered by a steel hard shell. Its inner core has apparently never been seen, even when it feeds.

Name: Fried Justine
Summary: Fried Justine is a Mage of Fairy Tail who didn't often appear in the guild; he is the leader of the Thunder God Tribe. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the other members of the Thunder God Tribe and Laxus. However, after the guild's reformation, he later left Blue Pegasus to join Fairy Tail again along with his team.

Name: Frigga (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Frigga was the Queen of Asgard, wife of Odin, mother of Thor, and adoptive mother of Loki. She attempted to keep the peace between the family even when Loki discovered he was the true son of Laufey and became vengeful towards her and her husband.

Name: Froslass
Summary: Froslass is a Ghost/Ice Pokémon, said in legends to be the spirit of a woman lost on a mountain who possessed an icicle (though this is clearly just a myth). It is vaguely humanoid and its torso seems to look like a kimono, with an obi wrapping around it, and its body is hollow. It Ian based on the Japanese mythical yokai, the Yuki-Onna. It freezes its prey at -58 degrees F, and secretly uses them as decorations. It is the female counterpart to Glalie, and while any Snorunt evolves into Glalie at level 42, female Snorunt evolve into Froslass with the use of a Dawn Stone.

Name: Frost Giants (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Jotunn, or otherwise colloquially referred to as the Frost Giants, coined by the Asgardians, are a race of humanoid giants that live on Jotunheim, one of the Nine Realms.

Name: Fukuro (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Fukuro is a member of Trinity Raven, a group in the assassin guild Death's Head Caucus, that worked under Jellal Fernandes.

Name: Gajeel Redfox (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gajeel Redfox is an Iron Dragon Slayer, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and a former S-Class Mage of Phantom Lord. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, Gajeel joins the Magic Council and becomes the captain of the Custody Enforcement Unit, but after Avatar is defeated, he returns to Fairy Tail. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Gajeel was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Galio
Summary: Tier: 7-C, Low 6-B against Magic | 7-A, Low 6-B against Magic

Name: Gambit
Summary: Remy Lebeau, better known as Gambit, is a semi-reformed thief and member of the X-Men whose troubled past has sometimes come back to haunt him, on the whole however Gambit has left his past behind and is a hero - sharing an on-and-off romantic interest with Rogue, despite the fact he can't touch her without fear of death.

Name: Gamora (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Gamora is a former assassin and a member of the Guardians of the Galaxy. She became the adopted daughter of Thanos after he killed half of her entire race. She served him for years before betraying him in an attempt to free herself from his ways. She was hired to steal the Orb, and became caught up in the quest for the Orb, becoming friends with the other members of the Guardians of the Galaxy. After the Battle of Xandar, she left to work with them.

Name: Gandalf
Key: '''Gandalf the Grey''' | '''Gandalf the White''' | '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Gandalf, originally known as Olórin, is a member of the order of wizards known as the Istari. Despite his appearance, Gandalf is not a human sorcerer, but rather a Maia of the ancient race of beings known as the Ainur, who existed before the creation of Arda. He is one of the main heroes in both J.R.R Tolkien's Middle-Earth saga and Peter Jackson's live-action adaptation of the books respectively.

Name: Gangplank
Summary: As unpredictable as he is brutal, the self-appointed reaver king known as Gangplank rules Bilgewater through a mix of fear, violence, and cunning. Where he goes, death and ruin follow, and such is his infamy and reputation that the merest sight of his black sails on the horizon causes panic among even the hardiest crew.

Name: Gar Shatterkeel
Summary: Gar Shatterkeel was a former servant aboard merchant ships after his family was slaughtered by pirates. Made bitter and cynical by this life, he gathered to him armies of those that feel as he does- that the world would be better made covered in water, to bring about the end of all things.

Name: Garbodor
Summary: Garbodor, the Trash Heap Pokemon. Garbodor is a giant sentient trashbag that is spilled open. It is said that it became sentient due to the combination of garbage bags and industrial waste. It is preyed upon by Alolan Muk. It evolves from Trubbish at level 36. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Garchomp
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Garen Crownguard
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least Low 7-C, possibly 7-A | At least 3-C, likely 3-B

Name: Gargoyle (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gargoyles are monstrosities of stone hailing from the planes of Earth. These prideful predators wait in dormancy, patiently watching for enemies to inflict pain upon. A gathering of Gargoyles oftentimes will resort to banter and bragging to pass the time.

Name: Garuda (Street Fighter)
Summary: Garuda (ガルダ Garuda) is a demonic being clad in samurai armor capable of absorbing negative energies to strengthen his own power. He is said to have been a culmination of all souls consumed by the Satsui no Hado.

Name: General Zod (DC Extended Universe)
Summary: Dru-Zod, commonly known by the alias General Zod, is the leader of Krypton's military and a former longtime friend of Jor-El. Zod believes Jor-El's warnings about the state of Krypton and launches a coup after concluding the Council is incapable of saving their race. When the coup fails, the Council has him and his followers imprisoned within the Phantom Zone, a decision which ironically spares them the fate of their home planet. After arriving on Earth in search of Kal-El, he initiates a war of annihilation against its population for the sake of building a new Krypton.

Name: Gengar
Summary: Gengar (Japanese: ゲンガー Gangar) is a dual-type Ghost/Poison Pokémon. It evolves from Haunter when traded. It is the final form of Gastly. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Gengar using the Gengarite. Gengar is a dark purple, bipedal Pokémon with a roundish body. It has red eyes and a wide mouth that is usually curled into a sinister grin. Multiple spikes cover its back, and it has large pointed ears. Its arms and legs are short with three digits on both its hands and feet. It also has a stubby tail. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Genista
Summary: Genista is the Franxx piloted by Code:556 (Kokoro) and originally Code:214 (Futoshi), but due to the partner swapping, Futoshi was replaced with Code:326 (Mitsuru). The Franxx is owned by Squad 13, and it is named after a genus of bushes.

Name: Ghaele
Summary: Ghaele are the knights-errant of the fey celestials, often serving faerie lords or even certain deities. Of the Eladrin of Arborea, the Ghaele were the most compassionate of the mortals and their plights. Thus, in contrast with their fun-loving species, the Ghaele's hearts were heavy, and many considered them distant and cold. The Ghaele would often wander the Prime Material, loving the place and growing depressed if they were unable to speak to the mortals of the realm.

Name: Ghost Rider (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Roberto "Robbie" Reyes grew up in East Los Angeles with his younger brother Gabe, who suffered from paraplegia. He dropped out of high school in eleventh grade, and decided to find work as a mechanic at Canelo's Auto and Body in order to support himself and his brother. He is also possessed by the mystical being known as Ghost Rider.

Name: Ghost Rider (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Ghost Rider is the name of several fictional supernatural antiheroes appearing in comic books published by Marvel Comics. This profile deals with the Johnny Blaze iteration of the character

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Gigalith
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Giovanni (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Rocket Hideout)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Silph Co.)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Viridian Gym)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 7)'''
Summary: Giovanni is the leader of Team Rocket and the Viridian Gym, the father of Silver and a recurring antagonist in the series.

Name: Girallon
Summary: Girallon are a species of gorilla-like monsters found in D&D. They are known for their carniverous eating habits and their quasi-society found in the jungles of the world. Despite their animalistic intelligence, these creatures did indeed acknowledge the eldest among them as their leaders.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Githzerai
Summary: In times long lost to the rampages of war, the Githzerai were once normal Githyanki who dissented from their brethren and formed a non-evil neutral faction. The Githzerai are ascetic monk-like folk who have settled in Limbo, a plane of chaos- a direct counter to their Lawful nature. They seek to battle the Slaadi, specifically to expand their knowledge in the face of direct adversity, building on the traits they learned from their slavery under the Mind Flayer empire.

Name: Glabrezu
Summary: Glabrezu are demons of pride, preferring to operate by subterfuge rather than raw might. They are often compared to succubi- however, instead of offering affection, they offer wealth, and power. They often act as lone operators in the Abyss, rather than mundane units of any Lords army.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Glalie
Summary: Glalie is an Ice-type Pokémon introduced in generation III. Glalie is a living rock with an armor of ice around it, small horns, and a terrifying face. It is known to flash freeze prey solid, and leisurely eat them while they're stiff. It has a female counterpart in Froslass, and Glalie evolves from Snorunt at level 42.

Name: Gliscor
Summary: Gliscor (Japanese: グライオン Glion) is a dual-type Ground/Flying-type Pokémon introduced in Generation IV. Gliscor resembles a half scorpion/half vampire bat creature. Like Drapion and Skorupi, Gliscor has a barbed stinger on its tail. Due to the stiffness of its wings, it needs to have the wind at its back in order to stay airborne.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Golisopod
Summary: Golisopod is a large, menacing arthropod Pokémon in a hunched-over, humanoid posture. It has a light purplish inner body generously armored with a silvery exoskeleton.

Name: Golurk
Summary: Golurk is a dual-type Ghost/Ground Pokémon. It is a giant golem-like Pokémon that has existed since ancient times. Created as laborers, these Pokémon exist to help other humans and Pokémon, often following their master's orders faithfully unless the seal in their chest is removed.

Name: Goodra
Summary: Goodra is the Pseudo-Legendary of Gen VI. It appears to be a bipedal draconian Pokémon made of slime. With its purple coloring and goofy smile, it seems to be competing with Dragonite as the lovable dragon powerhouse. It evolves from Goomy into Sliggoo at level 40, and from Sliggoo into Goodra at 50, but only in the overworld rain.

Name: Gorguth
Summary: Gorguth is a Death Knight that previously served the Demon Lord Orcus but grew tired of the grotesque demon and his pointless plots, and thus set out to find a master who would take action. And thus the knight found Atropus, and currently leads its hordes of demons and undead to slaughter until Atropus attacks the world. Gorguth hopes for death in this endeavor.

Name: Gothitelle
Summary: Gothitelle, the "Astral Body Pokémon" is a Psychic type Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation. It is the final evolution of Gothita, the "Fixation Pokémon". Gothitelle is infamous for its gloomy and Gothic appearance, as well as macabre Pokédex entries that revolve around the starry sky and the death of their trainers. Gothitelle apparently has the ability to see objects that only it can see, as well as control the minds of children and can even see the death of their trainers looming within the future.

Name: Gray Fullbuster (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gray Fullbuster is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is infamous for his ability to subconsciously strip off his clothing due to the instincts ingrained in him by his teacher's training. Nevertheless, he's a powerful Ice Mage and one of Natsu's main rivals. Gray was from a village up in the North, but the entire village was destroyed by the Demon Deliora. Gray's parents were killed in the incident as well. Along with Ur, a powerful ice Mage, Lyon came investigating Deliora's destruction and found Gray alive among the ruins. Ur took Gray in as her second student and taught him and Lyon Ice-Make Magic. In another encounter with Deliora, his teacher used Iced Shell to seal him away in order to save and protect Gray. After this, Gray took Ur's advice to find strong wizards. This led him to Fairy Tail, where he became a member.

Name: Greevil
Summary: Greevil (Japanese: デスゴルド Deathgold) is the leader of the criminal group Cipher. He is the only character in the game to have the Trainer class Grand Master (Japanese: シャドー総帥 Shadow Leader).

Name: Greninja
Summary: It utilizes its extraordinary jumping abilities to flummox its foes, throwing springy bubbles at them from above their heads.

Name: Griffon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Griffons are intelligent hybrids of lions and eagles. Their majesty is often hailed by cultures throughout the planes as a sign of goodness, and as such they are regularly used as mounts for good-aligned societies. The city of Waterdeep, the largest city of Faerun, maintained a large arsenal of Griffon cavalry. Netheril and Thay are two other superpowers that wielded the might of Griffons as their cavalry units. They are known to feed almost exclusively on horse flesh.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Summary: Grimmsnarl is a dual-type Dark/Fairy Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII. It evolves from Morgrem starting at level 42, who is evolved from Impidimp. It is one of the Pokemon with the ability to Gigantamax

Name: Grimsley
Summary: Grimsley is a member of the Unova Elite Four and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon.

Name: Grizzly Mastodon
Summary: A cousins to the elephant, the Grizzly Mastodon roams the subarctic and arctic lands in large herds. Their great strength and endurance makes so Giants often try to capture and tame them in order to use them as mounts.

Name: Groot (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Groot is a hyper-intelligent, tree-like organism from the species Flora colossus native to the planet X. While he possesses human level intellect, Groot's robust and heavyweight physiology causes the organs of his acoustic generation to become stiff and inflexible, rendering the limits of his speech to the simple phrase, "I am Groot."

Name: Grym
Summary: Grym is a massive golem forged from adamantine that serves as the primary defender of Grymforge, a dwarven citadel constructed from the ruins of a Sharite temple in the Underdark. Smaller than most adamantine golems, Grym is of unique make to combine his might with the terrain effects of the forge itself, making it still a notable opponent. Grym is referred to with awe and some amount of horror in texts describing him, making it clear that if the great Grymforge is sought out to create its famous adamantine constructions, one must first deal with its great guardian.

Name: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Nebula: All any of you do is yell at each other. You're not friends. Drax: You're right... We're family.
ID: Guardians of the Galaxy (Marvel Cinematic Universe)-MarvelCinematicUniverse-7

Name: Guhnash
Summary: A planet eating abomination that consumed the Dinaurians home world. A living weapon that can fight with every part of its body, including internal organs, it was called to Earth by the 4 idolcomps but was killed by Hunter.

Name: Guzma
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie Garden)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shady House)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hau'oli City, Team Rocket's Castle and Title Defense)'''
Summary: Guzma (Japanese: グズマ Guzma) is the leader of Team Skull.

Name: Gyarados
Summary: Gyarados is a Water/Flying Pokémon introduced in Generation I. It is the evolved form of Magikarp. Extremely vicious, enormously destructive, ferociously violent, and horribly brutal, it has a very aggressive nature. Although rarely seen in the wild, once it appears it goes on a rampage. When this happens, it doesn't calm until it has burned everything down and razed the fields and mountains around it. Not even harsh storms are able to stop its rage, and there are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month. A single Gyarados has enough destructive power to totally annihilate even a major city. Gyarados is attracted to violence and tends to appear when there is a world conflict or war. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames. During past wars Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake, and in ancient literature there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared. When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

Name: Halifax Explosion
Summary: The Halifax Explosion was a maritime disaster in Halifax, Nova Scotia, Canada, which happened on the morning of 6 December 1917, caused by a collision between a Norweigan vessel and a French cargo ship laden with high explosives. Approximately 2,000 people were killed and an estimated 9,000 others were injured. The blast was one of the largest man-made non-nuclear explosions releasing and energy equivalent to 2.9 Kilotons of TNT.

Name: Hamadh the Unseen
Summary: Hamadh the Unseen is the leader of The Hidden, a group of "invisibles" that survived the destruction of the Drow city of Maerimydra at the hands of Kurgoth Hellspawn. The group, under Hamadh's leadership, organized the downfall of Irae T'sarran and her temporary regime of power over the city and surrounding areas. However, what became of them afterwards is a mystery.

Name: Hammer (Fable)
Summary: Hammer, formally Sister Hannah, is the Hero of Strength and a companion of The Hero of Bowerstone in Fable II. There are four heroes left, and she is the one that falls under strength. She goes on a mission with The Hero of Bowerstone, and when she came back her dad had been killed. She joined the Hero and helped defeat Lucien at the Spire.

Name: Happy (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Happy is an Exceed from Extalia, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and Team Natsu. He acts as Team Natsu's mascot. Years ago, when Happy was just an egg, he was taken away from his parents, Lucky and Marl, by the queen of Extalia, Shagotte, to carry out the Dragon Slayer assassination plan. In actuality, sending him to Earth Land, along with all the other Exceed eggs, was done to allow him to escape a future disaster in Edolas. In X778, Natsu found Happy's egg in the East Forest of Magnolia Town. Natsu then took it back to the guild where he and Lisanna raised it together every day. One night, Elfman took it to keep it warm and the next day when he brought it back, it began to hatch and out popped a kitten with a pair of wings. Happy's first word was "Aye." Natsu gave him the name "Happy" after Lisanna pointed out the change of the atmosphere from anger to happiness after Happy hatched from the egg. Despite everyone else seeing him as a cat, Natsu thought he was a Dragon.

Name: Hatterene
Summary: Hatenna is a small Pokémon with peculiar behavior. They are known for being very shy and quiet, often preferring locations without people or strong sources of emotion. This aversion is strong enough that they will flee in most circumstances just to attempt to avoid interaction. Such behavior is caused by a feeling of exhaustion when sensing these strong emotions and as such, they will only warm up to those with a calm disposition.

Name: Hawkeye (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Clinton "Clint" Barton was a former circus worker and criminal-turned-hero, who received his archery skills as a young boy through training with Swordsman and Trickshot. Barton would eventually join both the East Coast and West Coast branches of The Avengers, even leading at one time.

Name: Hawkgirl (Kendra Saunders) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Kendra Saunders, Hawkgirl, is the reincarnation of Shrra, an angel cursed by her God to reincarnate across space and time alongside Kthar Deathbringer, who now combats evil as Hawkman. Born despite another Hawkwoman's existence because of Perpetua not wanting her to be whole, Kendra has proved herself a valiant hero among the ranks of the Justice League.

Name: Hawkman (Carter Hall) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: I am Carter Hall. I am Hawkman. I am an archaeologist. A scholar and preservationist of history. More than that, I am history. I've reincarnated across time, stretching back to the dawn of man. I ruled as an ancient Egyptian prince. Battled as a medieval knight. Dueled as an Old West gunhand. Yet lately, I'm plagued by the thought that the subject I know the least about is myself. That pieces of my history are missing. There remains only one truth that I know to be certain -- I am made to soar. I can't remember a life when I wasn't enthralled by flight. Open skies. Then why do I spend so much time underground? Darkness. Suffocating spaces. It's because the past is buried. And I'm swept up in the pursuit of it like a sparrow in a gale. Driven by the twin compulsions of my existence. Exploration and discovery.

Name: Hawkman (Katar Hol) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Katar Hol, known to the public as Hawkman, is a Thanagarian refugee who escaped his planet after accidentally killing his adopted brother, the prince of Thanagar. Bonded with the Nth Metal that his armor and metal are made of, Katar has been a powerful asset to the Justice League of America.

Name: Hawkwoman (Shayera Thal) (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Shayera Thal, Hawkwoman, is the empress of Thanagar and wife of Carter Hall.

Name: Hawlucha
Summary: Hawlucha is a Fighting/Flying-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI.

Name: Haxorus
Summary: Haxorus is a Dragon-type Pokémon native to the Unova region. Also known as the Axe Jaw Pokemon, its sturdy tusks are destructive enough to cut through solid steel without chipping or dulling. Its also known to be relentless when defending its territory, but its sturdy armor and fierce fighting capabilities belie its kind spirit. It evolves from Fraxure who in turn evolves from Axew.

Name: Hayate (Street Fighter)
Summary: Hayate (ハヤテ) is a noble samurai attempting to follow the footsteps of his legendary missing father who sealed the beast of Orochi. When Orochi escapes from his imprisonment and kidnaps the local shrine maiden, Hayate slays the demon like his father did before him. Afterwards, Hayate and the maiden then become the new guardian deities of the village.

Name: Hayate Kamite
Summary: Hayate Kamite (紙手 疾風, かみて はやて) or Hayate II is the descendant of the first Hayate who sealed Garuda away. Seeking to pursue a normal life after becoming his village's guardian deity, he finds himself troubled with the task of continuing his predecessor's work when he becomes possessed by the demon.

Name: Hecarim
Summary: Hecarim is an armored colossus who charges from the Shadow Isles at the head of a deathly host of spectral horsemen to hunt the living. A monstrous fusion of man and beast, cursed to ride for eternity, Hecarim revels in slaughter and crushing souls beneath his armored hooves.

Name: Heimdall (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Heimdall is the Asgardian gatekeeper of the Bifrost Bridge. He has the ability to see and hear nearly everything that occurs in the Nine Realms. Due to his undying loyalty to the people of Asgard, he is a frequent ally of Thor.

Name: Heimerdinger
Summary: A brilliant yet eccentric yordle scientist, Professor Cecil B. Heimerdinger is lauded as one of the most innovative minds and esteemed inventors Piltover has ever seen. Relentless in his work to the point of neurotic obsession, he is fascinated by mysteries that have confounded his contemporaries for decades, and thrives on answering the universe’s most impenetrable questions. Though his theories often appear opaque and esoteric, Heimerdinger believes knowledge should be shared, and is devoted to teaching all who desire it.

Name: Hellfire Engine
Summary: The Hellfire Engine is a warmachine created by devils to be used against mortals and demons, it's only used whenever utter destruction is needed as the Hellfire Engine in incappble of the subtly devils are known for. The Hellfire this creation uses was inveted by the Archdevil Mephisto, this flame is able to harm anyone in the multiverse; even those who are immune to fire.

Name: Heracross
Summary: Heracross is the Pokémon number #214, a dual-type Bug/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Hercules (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hercules (herk-you-lees), god of strength, appears as a large, muscular man with a tangled beard. He wears a lion’s skin and carries a massive club.

Name: Hive (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Alveus, also known as Hive, was a parasitic Inhuman capable of infesting and possessing the bodies of dead humans and controlling other Inhumans through a hive mind. Because of his great powers, Alveus was banished to a barren planet. Alveus' worshipers founded a secret society with the sole purpose of bringing Hive back to Earth to conquer it. Over the centuries, that society evolved into HYDRA. Eventually, Alveus possessed Grant Ward's dead body when he was killed by Phil Coulson with his prosthetic hand on Maveth, and was able to return to Earth once more. Working with Gideon Malick, Alveus soon took the reins of HYDRA from him. Seeking to transform the Earth's population into Inhumans so they could live in peace, Hive and his small army attempted to use Kree blood to recreate the original experiments he had endured thousands of years earlier, kidnapping Holden Radcliffe in order to use his genius to complete his plans while battling the continued efforts of S.H.I.E.L.D. and the Secret Warriors to stop him. As Hive attempted to complete his plan by detonating a warhead filled with Terrigen Mist into the Earth's atmosphere, he was defeated when Lincoln Campbell trapped himself and Hive with the bomb and allowed it to explode safely in space, destroying Alveus.

Name: Hogun (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Hogun was a highly respected Vanir warrior, an ally as well as friend of Thor, and a member of the Warriors Three, known for his stern demeanour. Alongside all his fellow warriors, Hogun took part in a poorly considered strike against all the Frost Giants, which soon resulted in Odin punishing Thor by banishing him to the Earth without his powers. When Loki then took the throne of Asgard during Thor's banishment, Hogun and his allies played a key role saving Thor from the Destroyer before bringing him back to Asgard where he successfully stopped Loki from destroying Jotunheim.

Name: Hokuto (Street Fighter)
Summary: Hokuto (ほくと), real name Shirase (訃, しらせ), is a noble practitioner of the ancient martial art kobudō, and sibling to Kairi and Nanase.

Name: Hop (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mid Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Late Game/Beginning of Post Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End of Post Game/Galarian Star Tournament)'''
Summary: Hop (Japanese: ホップ Hop) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield and Leon's younger brother. He is your main rival throughout the games, eventually undergoing a period of self-doubt after a humiliating defeat at the hands of Bede, as he didn't want to be so weak as to drag down his older brother's name. After his defeat at the hands of the player in the Champion Cup, he eventually decides to work toward becoming a Pokémon Professor.

Name: Horned Devil
Summary: Cornugon, or Horned Devils, alongside many other names, are the elite defense troops of Baator, the Nine Hells. Their laziness causes them to be fearful of any being deemed stronger than them- though this is of little import due to their immense strength and astounding intelligence.

Name: Hoteye (Richard Buchanan)
Summary: Hoteye, real name Richard Buchanan, is a former member of the Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of highly powerful Mages whose goal is to find Nirvana, a destructive power that was sealed away long ago. After his release from prison, he joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. He is the elder brother of Wally Buchanan.

Name: Houndoom
Summary: Houndoom is a Pokémon introduced in Gen II. It evolves from Houndour at level 24.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Hughes (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Hughes is the Captain of the 3rd Magic War Division of the Edolas Royal Army.

Name: Hulk (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Dr. Robert Bruce Banner is a renowned scientist in the fields of Biochemistry, Nuclear Physics, and Gamma Radiation. He is one of the scientists who tried to recreate the Super Soldier Serum which originated Captain America in World War II, but when an exposure to high levels of Gamma Radiation instead of Vita Radiation went awry, the mild-mannered scientist found himself plagued with a peculiar condition; when angered or provoked, he would transform into the rage-fueled and nearly mindless green-skinned monster known as the Hulk.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Hunter (Fossil Fighters)
Summary: Tier: 9-B | At least 7-B, likely far higher | At least 7-B, likely far higher

Name: Hurricane (Real World)
Summary: Hurricanes are massive storm systems that form over the water and move toward land. Threats from hurricanes include high winds, heavy rainfall, storm surge, coastal and inland flooding, rip currents, and tornadoes. These large storms are called typhoons in the North Pacific Ocean and cyclones in other parts of the world.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve.
