However, to avoid being conquered and pillaged of its resources by foreign invaders, the kingdom keeps itself very reclusive and isolated from the rest of the world.

Name: War Machine (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Colonel James Rupert Rhodes, commonly known as Rhodey, is a U.S. military officer and jet pilot in the U.S. Air Force. He is the best friend of Tony Stark and the liaison between Stark Industries and the military in the Department of Acquisitions, when Stark was kidnapped by the Ten Rings, Rhodes led the mission to rescue his friend. He is known as War Machine when wearing his heavily-armed battle suit but his alias was temporarily re-branded to Iron Patriot during the Extremis incident.

Name: War Machine Armor Model 2
Summary: After Parnell Jacobs found the War Machine Model 1, he brought it to Stuart Clarke, who in turn brought it to Sunset Bain, who rebuilt the armor with her own technology.

Name: War Machine Armor Model 4
Summary: nan

Name: Warren Rocko
Summary: Warren Rocko is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild. He is a telepath and invented a magical communication device.

Name: Warwick
Summary: Tier: 7-B | 7-A

Name: Weezing
Summary: Weezing is a pure Poison- type Pokemon introduced in the first generation. It is a purple, cloud-like Pokemon consisting of two heads attached to each other. It consists of toxic gases and exists due to a pool of poisonous gases and a fusion of two Koffing. The two Koffing switch inflation to mix gases. When one inflates, the other deflates. The more it mixes gases, the more putrid it becomes. If one looks closely, they can see the gases swirling around inside the Koffings that make it up. It evolves from Koffing at level 35.

Name: Wendy Marvell (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Wendy Marvell is a young female Sky Dragon Slayer. She was one of the orphans chosen to be a Dragon Slayer four hundred years prior to X777, serving as her foster mother's vessel to travel to X777 through the Eclipse Gate as a part of the plan to exterminate Acnologia. Formerly belonging to the Cait Shelter Guild, she officially joins the Fairy Tail Guild after the events surrounding Nirvana unfold. Following the disbandment of Fairy Tail, Wendy, along with Carla, joined Lamia Scale. After the war between Orochi's Fin and Lamia Scale ends, Wendy left Lamia Scale and helped Natsu restore Fairy Tail.

Name: Werewolf (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Werewolves are canine lycanthropes and are generally regarded as beings of incredible evil (though this is not always the case). In their human forms, werewolves merely seem agitated, easily angered by the slightest inconvenience. Both good and evil werewolves alike flee from civilized society- those that fear the curse fear too for their fellow man, and wish to refrain from killing them. Those that embrace the curse seek to save their own hides, and do not wish to be held responsible for their murderous acts.

Name: Whiplash (Marco Scarlotti)
Summary: Marco Scarlotti was a Maggia enforcer who cared deeply about supporting his family financially, and has been a persistent foe for Iron Man as the first Whiplash.

Name: Whiplash (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ivan Antonovich Vanko was a Russian physicist and the son of the disgraced scientist Anton Vanko. When Vanko's father died penniless due to the actions of Howard Stark, Vanko swore to seek revenge by targeting Howard's son, Tony Stark. Recreating an Arc Reactor based on his father's design and designing an armor similar to Iron Man's, Vanko attacked Stark in Monaco, following the events after he was incarcerated. After he was broken out by Justin Hammer, who had recruited him, Vanko hijacked the Hammer Drones, as well as the Mark I War Machine Armor, in an attempt to assassinate Stark and destroy his legacy.

Name: Whiscash
Summary: Whiscash is a dual Water/Ground type Pokémon introduced in Generation III, being #340 in the Pokédex and the evolution of Barboach. The species is known to be extremely territorial, claiming entire large ponds or swamps as its territory, and if it sees an enemy approaching, it can cause massive earthquakes that can be felt in a three mile radius, which also gave it the ability to sense when real earthquakes will occur. Whiscash are also known to possess extremely voracious appetites, eating anything it sees as long as it's alive.

Name: Wigglytuff (Mystery Dungeon)
Summary: Wigglytuff is the lovable guildmaster of Wigglytuff's Guild, a guild of young explorers out to do jobs and find treasures, and a former member of Team Charm, a Master Rank rescue team. Despite his silly appearance and his naivete, he is revered by many for his ridiculous strength.

Name: Wingull
Summary: Wingull is a seagull Pokémon with wings that are made for soaring on updrafts. It carries food in its beak and makes its nest on the cliffsides. Fishermen take note of when Wingull are nearby, as it is a sign that the surrounding waters are filled with fish.

Name: Wishiwashi
Summary: Wishiwashi is a Water Type Pokémon from Alola. Usually, it is a weak and delicious Pokémon. But if it is threatened, it will call upon its kin to form into its gigantic School form.

Name: Wobbuffet
Summary: Wobbuffet is a Psychic-type Pokémon from the second generation. It is quite special compared to others like it due to lacking any direct attacks. Instead, it endures attacks and then counters. This means that it is never the first one to attack.

Name: Wukong (League of Legends)
Summary: Wukong is a vastayan trickster who uses his strength, agility and intelligence to confuse his opponents and gain the upper hand. After finding a lifelong friend in the warrior known as Master Yi, Wukong became the last student of the ancient martial art known as Wuju. Armed with an enchanted staff, Wukong seeks to prevent Ionia from falling to ruin. Within Ionia’s treetops dwells a vastayan tribe known as the Shimon. These apelike creatures are a wise, cautious people, and as pacifists, chose to build their society away from landwalkers, cultivating their society atop the tallest trees in Ionia. The Shimon see life as an evolutionary climb to wisdom, thus upon death, the Shimon believe they become stones, returning to the soil to begin the climb of life again.

Name: Wyrdeer
Summary: Stantler is a Pokemon introduced in Generation II. It is a normal type Pokemon. Stantler can control the senses of its enemies with the light coming from its antlers, or through a smell it can make. In Pokemon Legends: Arceus, it can evolve into Wyrdeer after using Psyshield Bash enough times in Agile Style. Wyrdeer is currently an extinct Pokemon.

Name: Wyvern (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: 15 feet long and standing on two legs, the Wyvern shares the general apperance of a dragon but lacks the intelligence of one. It's an aggressive predator which dive bombs from the sky on its prey and tries to whisk it away, using its poisonous stinger on them if necessary, some Wyverns also have magic in them due to influnce from the Shadowfell, and they use said magic to cause necrotic damage to their targets.

Name: Xanathon
Summary: Xanathon is the head priest of the immigrants from Ethangar Khanate, a land in the world of Mystara. A powerful cleric of Cretia, he enjoys a special form of immortality granted by his god, which prevents all bodily harm so long as he is not near his soul, which is stored in a gem. Because of this, Xanathon has grown arrogant, and now seeks to take the throne of Rhoona by cursing the duke and performing a coup alongside the head of the guards, Draco Stormsail.

Name: Xayah
Summary: Deadly and precise, Xayah is a vastayan revolutionary waging a personal war to save her people. She uses her speed, guile, and razor-sharp feather blades to cut down anyone who stands in her way. Xayah fights alongside her partner and lover, Rakan, to protect their dwindling tribe, and restore their race to her vision of its former glory.

Name: Xin Zhao
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least Low 7-C, possibly 7-A | 7-C | Low 1-C

Name: Yamask
Summary: Yamask is a shadow-like Pokémon holding a golden mask that has a face from its time as a human. Due to this past, they retains memories from before they became a Pokémon which they can recall when looking at their mask, often crying longingly. The significance of their mask makes them furious when its taken and those who wear their mask can become possessed.

Name: Yanmega
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Yashar
Summary: Yashar is a medusa sorcerer serving under Irae T'sarran during the Silence of Lolth. He is an unusual member of her entourage who guards a large portal to the Ethereal Plane within the Undying Temple. Yashar spends most of his time alone, keeping watch for threats ghostly or otherwise[1].

Name: Yasuo
Summary: An Ionian of deep resolve, Yasuo is an agile swordsman, trained to wield the air itself against his enemies. As a young man, pride led him down a path of loss, costing him his position, his mentor, and ultimately his own brother. Disgraced by false accusations and now hunted as little more than a criminal, Yasuo wanders his homeland seeking redemption for his past, with only the wind to guide his blade.

Name: Yomazu
Summary: Yomazu was one of the most powerful lesser members of the now-disbanded Dark Guild, Grimoire Heart, where he served under Caprico of the Seven Kin of Purgatory. He worked alongside his partner Kawazu.

Name: Yondu Udonta (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: nan

Name: Yone
Summary: In life, he was Yone—half-brother of Yasuo, and renowned student of his village's sword school. But upon his death at the hands of his brother, he found himself hunted by a malevolent entity of the spirit realm, and was forced to slay it with its own sword. Now, cursed to wear its demonic mask upon his face, Yone tirelessly hunts all such creatures in order to understand what he has become.

Name: Youngster Joey
Summary: Youngster Joey is considered the first Pokémon trainer that Ethan ever faces in the Johto Pokémon games. He is first seen battling a trainer named Mikey on Route 30, later seemingly having been defeated after Ethan delivers the Mystery Egg.

Name: Yuka Suzuki
Summary: Yuka Suzuki, is a Mage of Lamia Scale Guild and one of Lyon Vastia's allies. He serves as the guild's anti-Mage, as his Wave Magic can cancel out others' Magic.

Name: Zancrow
Summary: Zancrow was a Fire God Slayer, a member of one of the most powerful Dark Guilds, Grimoire Heart, and was one of the Seven Kin of Purgatory. He was killed by Zeref during the Fairy Tail-Grimoire Heart war on Tenrou Island.

Name: Zed (League of Legends)
Summary: Utterly ruthless and without mercy, Zed is the leader of the Order of Shadow, an organization he created with the intent of militarizing Ionia’s magical and martial traditions to drive out Noxian invaders. During the war, desperation led him to unlock the secret shadow form—a malevolent spirit magic as dangerous and corrupting as it is powerful. Zed has mastered all of these forbidden techniques to destroy anything he sees as a threat to his nation, or his new order.

Name: Zedarr T'sarran
Summary: Zedarr T'sarran is the son of Irae T'sarran and brother of Dorina T'sarran, and also serves as the chief lieutenant of the latter. He is a skilled blackguard of the Drow goddess of murder Kiaransalee and acts as an unholy champion to the goddess' will. His ambitions are simple, serving his family with distinguished pride. Of note among his accomplishments are his position on the hunter-killer team of Irae, an elite task force organized to desroy special targets that might interfere with her plans, as well as the bringing down of Szith Morcane, a small Drow outpost-town outside Maerimydra where Zedarr now resides. Zedarr bears a bond with an infernal Displacer Beast named Ripper, a creature nearly as strong as Zedarr himself- together the two make a terrifying duo in combat.[1]

Name: Ziggs
Summary: Tier: Unknown, 7-B with Hexplosives, higher with Mega Inferno Bomb | 4-B | 5-C

Name: Zilean
Summary: Once a member of Icathia’s governing council, Zilean is a prodigious elemental mage who seeks mastery over time itself. After using his powers in an attempt to save his people from the Void, he now drifts through the past, present, and future, bending and warping the flow of time around him. Zilean has traveled from Runeterra’s mysterious creation, all the way to its seemingly inevitable ending, searching tirelessly for any strand of fate that might undo his homeland’s destruction.

Name: Zindar
Summary: Zindar is a half-dragon sorcerer paid by the merchant princes of Chult to operate and oversee their docks, keeping track of ship manifests, treaties, and other paperwork. It is also his purpose to protect the waters of the area around his home city (Nyanzaru) and regularly offers bounties on particularly troublesome pirates. He maintains a soft spot for adventurers but largely attempts to remain cold because few who travel deep into the jungles of Chult ever return.

Name: Zoldeo
Summary: Zoldeo was a member of the Grimoire Heart Guild and one of the Seven Kin of Purgatory through possession of Capricorn's body. He died after being forcefully removed from his possession of Loke's body.

Name: Zoroark
Summary: Zoroark (Japanese: ゾロアーク Zoroark) is a Dark-type Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It is a bipedal, gray-brown, fox-like Pokémon with crimson and black accents.

Name: Zyra
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | 7-C | 7-A

Name: 1960 Valdivia Earthquake
Summary: The 1960 Valdivia earthquake (Spanish: Terremoto de Valdivia) or Great Chilean earthquake (Gran terremoto de Chile) of 22 May is the most powerful earthquake ever recorded. Various studies have placed it at 9.4–9.6 on the moment magnitude scale. It occurred in the afternoon (19:11 GMT, 15:11 local time), and lasted approximately 10 minutes. The resulting tsunami affected southern Chile, Hawaii, Japan, the Philippines, eastern New Zealand, southeast Australia and the Aleutian Islands. The main tsunami crossed the Pacific Ocean at a speed of several hundred kilometers per hour and devastated Hilo, Hawaii, killing 61 people. Waves as high as 10.7 meters (35 ft) were recorded 10,000 kilometers (6,200 mi) from the epicenter, and as far away as Japan and the Philippines.

Name: Absol
Summary: Absol (Japanese: アブソル, Absol) is a Dark-type Pokémon. While it is not known to evolve into or from any other Pokémon, it can Mega Evolve into Mega Absol using the Absolite.

Name: Accelgor
Summary: Accelgor (Japanese: アギルダー Agilder) is a Bug-type Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Black and White. His aspect resembles a ninja.

Name: Aegislash
Summary: Aegislash is a dual-type Steel/Ghost Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It evolves from Doublade when exposed to a Dusk Stone. It is the final form of Honedge. Aegislash can change forms during battle, depending on the moves it is using.

Name: Aerodactyl
Summary: Aerodactyl (Japanese: プテラ, Ptera) is a dual-type Rock/Flying Fossil Pokémon. It is resurrected from an Old Amber, and while is not known to evolve into or from any other Pokémon, it can Mega Evolve into Mega Aerodactyl using the Aerodactylite.

Name: Agatha (Pokémon)
Summary: Agatha (キクコ Kikuko) is a member of the Kanto Elite 4. She is the third member as well as the oldest. She specializes in Ghost-types and other menacing looking pokemon.

Name: Aggron
Summary: Aggron (Japanese: ボスゴドラ, Bossgodora) is a dual-type Steel/Rock Pokémon. It evolves from Lairon starting at level 42. It is the final form of Aron. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Aggron using the Aggronite. Aggron is a huge, bipedal Pokémon.

Name: Alakazam
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Alcremie
Summary: Alcremie is a cream Pokémon and the evolution of the Milcery. Including its shiny form, this Pokemon has 64 known forms by combining different flavors and topics. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Allister
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Champion Tournament)'''
Summary: Allister (Japanese: オニオン Onion) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. He specializes in Ghost-type Pokémon. He gives the Ghost Badge to Trainers who defeat him. He is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Shield. In Pokémon Sword, Bea takes his place as Stow-on-Side's Gym Leader instead.

Name: Altaria
Summary: Altaria is a Dragon/Flying Pokémon introduced in Hoenn. It is based off of the Peng, and is almost completely shrouded in clouds, boosted even further with its Mega Evolution, in which it becomes Dragon/Fairy Type. It evolves from Swablu at level 35.

Name: Alzack Connell
Summary: Alzack Connell is a Mage from the west, who came to Magnolia as an immigrant and joined the Fairy Tail Guild. Currently, in year X791, he is the husband of Bisca Connell and the father of Asuka Connell. Alzack is a kind and determined individual who loves his comrades and is willing to risk his life to fight for them. However, this determination of his seems to disappear when it comes to Bisca Mulan, the girl he loves and whom he was originally very shy around. Alzack displays extreme dedication towards her, as seen when Bisca was turned to stone by Evergreen under Laxus Dreyar's orders: Alzack was willing to do everything to save her, going as far as to fight and defeat his own guild mates to do so, all the while claiming that he would never forgive Laxus for doing such a thing to her.

Name: Ampharos
Summary: Ampharos, the Light Pokémon is the final stage evolution of the Mareep family. Famed for its ability to give off intense rays of light, Ampharos has been used as a beacon for ships since ancient times.

Name: Anabel (Pokémon)
Summary: Anabel is a Frontier Brain from the Battle Frontier in Pokémon Emerald. While that is the end of her role in Emerald, she plays a bigger part in Pokémon Sun and Moon in the post-game, where it is revealed that she was sucked through an Ultra Wormhole into the Sun/Moon universe, where she becomes part of the International Police and their UB Task Force.

Name: Angel (Sorano Agria)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Angel, real name Sorano Agria, is a powerful Independent Mage and a practitioner of Angel Magic, as well as a former Celestial Spirit Mage. A member of the original Oración Seis, one of the most powerful Dark Guilds that once sought the destructive Magic Nirvana, she was among the few remaining members who formed the Reborn Oración Seis, and later joined Crime Sorcière along with her guildmates that formed the original Oración Seis. She is also the elder sister of Yukino Agria. She later became a member of Sabertooth, joining her younger sister.

Name: Applin
Summary: Applin is a small Pokemon who spends his time inside his apple, hiding from predators until it finds a way to evolve. Appletun is one of two possible evolutions for Applin, which is achieved by feeding Applin a Sweet Apple. Like Flapple, Applin is one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing. Curiously however, unlike other Gigantamax Pokémon, Flapple and Applin have an identical G-Max appearance, though they still differ slightly in abilities. Flapple is one of two possible evolutions for Applin, which is achieved by feeding Applin a Tart Apple. Like Appletun, Flapple is one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing. Curiously however, unlike other Gigantamax Pokémon, Flapple and Applin have an identical G-Max appearance, though they still differ slightly in abilities.

Name: Arbok
Summary: Arbok is a serpentine Pokémon that resembles a cobra. It has narrow eyes and several sharp teeth. Just below its head is a large hood with a face-like pattern. This pattern has over 20 possible variations. The pattern typically has two red and yellow eyespots outlined in black, a wide black streak resembling an upturned mouth, and a black V-shaped stripe above the eyespots.

Name: Arcanine
Summary: Growlithe is a quadruped, canine Pokémon. It has orange fur with black stripes along its back and legs. The fur on its muzzle, chest, belly, and tail is beige, as well as an additional tuft of fur on top of its head. Growlithe's coat is noticeably longer on its chest and tail. It has gray eyes, a black nose, and large, round ears with beige interiors. Its forepaws have two visible claws, while its hind paws have three toes each. Each paw has a brown pad.

Name: Archie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Archie is the boss of Team Aqua. The player only battles him in Seafloor Cavern in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Sapphire. In Ruby, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Magma from expanding the land mass and in Sapphire, he is the main antagonist of the game.

Name: Aria (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Aria is a former S-Class Mage of the now-disbanded Phantom Lord Guild and is the former leader of the Element 4, four of the strongest members in Phantom Lord. He is considered the strongest member in the group, and his element is Air.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: Ash Ketchum (I Choose You)
Key: '''Himself''' | '''Start of Adventure''' | '''Mid-Adventure Pokémon''' | '''End of M20/M21 Pikachu'''
Summary: nan

Name: Audino
Summary: Audino is a Normal-Type Pokémon originating in Pokémon Black and Pokémon White. From Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire, it gained the ability to mega evolve, turning it into a strong Normal/Fairy type Pokémon.

Name: Aurorus
Summary: Aurorus is a Rock/Ice type fossil Pokemon introduced in Generation VI. It has the ability to create a wall out of just freezing air.

Name: Azuma (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Azuma was a member of the Dark Guild Grimoire Heart and was the first of the Seven Kin of Purgatory to arrive on Tenrou Island to battle Fairy Tail.

Name: Azumarill
Summary: Tier: 8-C, higher with Huge Power | At most Low 7-B, higher with Huge Power | At least High 7-A, 6-C with Huge Power

Name: Bastiodon
Summary: Bastiodon is a ceratopsian Fossil Pokémon that debuted in Pokémon Diamond and Pearl. Although it is normally docile and feeds on leaves and berries, it will not hesitate to fight its foes to the death when defending its young, repelling attacks with its shield-shaped head. It evolves from Shieldon.

Name: Bea (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Stow-on-Side Stadium)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion Cup Finals)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Bea (Japanese: サイトウ Saitō) is the Gym Leader of Stow-on-Side's Gym, known officially as Stow-on-Side Stadium. She specializes in Fighting-type Pokémon. She gives the Fighting Badge to Trainers who defeat her. She is also an exclusive Gym Leader on Pokémon Sword.

Name: Beheeyem
Summary: Beheeyem is a psychic type Pokémon from the Unova Region, introduced in Generation V. It is of a potentially alien origin and is masterful at creating illusions and controlling minds. It evolved from the Pokémon Elgyem.

Name: Bewear
Summary: Bewear is a Normal/Fighting-type Pokémon from the Alola region. It has extremely destructive hugs, and it evolved from the adorable and peacful Stufful.

Name: Bickslow
Summary: Bickslow is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and, along with Fried Justine and Evergreen, makes up the Thunder God Tribe. After Fairy Tail's disbandment he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the other members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, after the guilds reformation, he later left to join Fairy Tail again along with his team.

Name: Bisca Connell
Summary: Bisca Connell, formerly Bisca Mulan, was originally an immigrant from the West, who moved to Magnolia and joined the Fairy Tail Guild. During the year X785, she became Alzack Connell's wife and the mother of Asuka Connell.

Name: Bisharp
Summary: It leads a group of Pawniards. Bisharp doesn't even change its expression when it deals the finishing blow to an opponent.

Name: Blastoise
Summary: Blastoise is a large, bipedal tortoise-like Pokémon. Its body is dark blue and is mostly hidden by its tough, brown shell. This shell has a pale yellow underside and a white ridge encircling its arms and separating the upper and lower halves.

Name: Blaziken
Summary: Blaziken (Japanese: バシャーモ Bursyamo) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Blue (Pokémon Let's Go)
Summary: This version of Blue is quite a unique one. Instead of taking the role of an antagonistic rival that is meant to be overcome, he is an older, more mature mentor for the main characters, Chase and Trace. Furthermore, Let’s Go itself is a universe that takes place a bit later than others, where Red, Blue, and Green have all already gone on their Pokémon adventures.

Name: Blue (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Gen 1 Team (First Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Second Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Third Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fourth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Fifth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Sixth Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Seventh Battle)''' | '''Gen 1 Team (Champion Battle)''' | '''Gen 2 Team''' | '''Gen 7 Teams'''
Summary: Blue Oak was the rival in the first Generation of Pokémon. Characterized by his rude and crude personality, Blue embarked on his Pokémon journey at the same time as his rival, Red and was always one step ahead of him no matter where he went. Cocky, arrogant and even a little devious, Blue quickly found himself becoming the Pokémon Master of Kanto, only to be defeated by Red.

Name: Brain (Zero)
Summary: Brain was the leader of the Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of highly powerful Mages whose goal was to find a very destructive Magic known as Nirvana, which was sealed away long ago. Inside him dwelled another, more evil and dangerous personality known as Zero, who acted as guild master of the Oración Seis. He met his death at the hands of Cobra.

Name: Brambleghast
Summary: Brambleghast (Japanese: アノホラグサ Anohoragusa) is a dual-type Grass/Ghost Pokémon introduced in Generation IX. Bearing a striking resemblance to a tumbleweed, it tends to wander more desolate and dry areas as the winds pull it along.

Name: Breloom
Summary: Shroomish is a small Pokémon similar to a mushroom. It has beady black eyes and a half-triangle-shaped mouth. Its upper body is beige with frilled segments along the bottom and a small opening at the top. There are green spots marking its upper body, while its lower body is completely green. It has small, round feet and no visible arms or hands. When it senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters toxic spores from the top of its head. These spores can make trees and weeds wilt and cause whole body pain if inhaled.

Name: Brock (Pokémon)
Summary: Brock "The Rock-Solid Pokémon Trainer!" is the first Gym Leader Red encountered in his adventures in Kanto. He is an expert and specialist of the Rock typing. Arguably one of the most iconic Gym Leaders in the entire series [Only really rivaled by Misty and Giovanni], Brock has become a recurring character in the Pokémon franchise, appearing in Pokémon Red/Blue/Yellow, Pokémon Adventures and arguably most famously, the Pokémon anime series.

Name: Bronzong
Summary: Bronzong. The Bronze Bell Pokemon. This Pokemon existed long ago and was revered as a bringer of rain. It evolves from Bronzor at level 33.

Name: Bruno (Pokémon)
Summary: Bruno (シバ Siba) is a Fighting-type Trainer and member of the Elite Four of Kanto and Johto.

Name: Buizel
Summary: Buizel, the Sea Weasel Pokémon, is known to be an unique swimmer by moving its tails like a screw.

Name: Buneary
Summary: Buneary, the Rabbit Pokémon is a Normal type introduced in the Fourth Generation of Pokémon.

Name: Byro (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Byro is the Chief of Staff of the Royal Army of Edolas.

Name: Caitlin (Pokémon)
Summary: Caitlin is a Pokémon Trainer that first appeared in Johto as the princess of the Battle Castle. She later reappeared as one of the Elite Four of the Unova Region.

Name: Camerupt
Summary: Camerupt (Japanese: バクーダ Bakuuda) is a dual-type Fire/Ground Pokémon from Hoenn based off of a camel. It evolves from Numel starting at level 33.

Name: Cana Alberona
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Cana Alberona is a member of the Fairy Tail Guild, and is a potential S-Class Mage. She is a heavy drinker, but hardly ever gets drunk, no matter how much she drinks. She is also the daughter of Gildarts Clive.

Name: Carla (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Carla is an Exceed, the daughter of Queen Shagotte, and a close companion to Wendy Marvell. She and Wendy belonged to Cait Shelter before joining Fairy Tail. After the disbandment of Fairy Tail, Carla, along with Wendy, joined Lamia Scale. She's a major supporting character. Carla is a small, white Exceed with pink ears and brown eyes, which are smaller than Happy's eyes. She also has two whiskers on each side of her face. Carla wears a pink bow near the end of her tail. Carla's usual top consists of a mustard yellow and pink top with a pink bow tie. She wears a pink skirt with this top. Carla, like other characters, seems to switch outfits on a regular basis. When Carla uses Magic, she sprouts two angel-like wings to fly. Her pink Guild Mark is located on her back.

Name: Centiskorch
Summary: Centiskorch, the Radiator Pokémon, is a Bug-/Fire-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII and is the evolution of Sizzlipede. It is also one of the few Pokémon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Chansey
Summary: Happiny, the Playhouse Pokémon, is another baby Pokémon often found carrying around a round white stone, often seen just playing around.

Name: Cherrim
Summary: Cherrim, the Blossom Pokémon, is sensible to sunlight to a notable degree, to the point it may change to it's Sunshine Form if exposed enough.

Name: Chesnaught
Summary: Chesnaught is a Grass/Fighting-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI. It evolves from Quilladin who is an evolution of Chespin.

Name: Cinderace
Summary: Cinderace is a Fire type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. By juggling a pebble with its feet, Cinderace can transform it into a burning soccer ball. By putting a spin on the ball, it can launch attacks that its opponents struggle to evade.

Name: Clair (Pokémon)
Key: Herself | Gym Battle | Postgame | Pokémon World Tournament
Summary: Clair is the 8th and final Gym Leader in the Johto region. Born to the same clan of Dragon Tamers as Lance (and also being his cousin), Clair has had an affinity for Dragon type Pokémon ever since she was a child. Not to be outdone by her cousin, who became a member of the Elite Four when she was young, Clair too trained vigorously in the ways of Dragon type Pokémon until she finally became the Gym Leader of her hometown. However, as she ascended to the role of Gym Leader, Lance too ascended beyond a member of the Elite Four to become the Indigo League Champion, driving her motivation to catch up to him and prove herself as the ultimate Dragon type Trainer even further to this day.

Name: Claydol
Summary: Claydol is a Pokemon originating from the third generation. It originated as a doll that was brought to life 20,000 years ago and imbued with psychic power. Its limbs are unattached from it, so it uses its psychic powers to levitate them. It evolves from Baltoy at level 36.

Name: Clefairy
Summary: Clefairy is a peculiar and friendly Pokémon often seen at night in mountains dancing to the moon.

Name: Cloyster
Summary: Shellder is a water-type Pokémon from Kanto. They spend their time hidden away in their shell, their tongue sticking out.

Name: Cobra (Fairy Tail)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Cobra, real name Erik, is a former member of the now-disbanded Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of six powerful Mages. He, along with the other Oración Seis members, sought to find Nirvana, a destructive Magic that was sealed long ago. At some point before seeking Nirvana, Erik implanted a Dragon Slayer Lacrima into his own body, which thereby resulted in him becoming the Poison Dragon Slayer. Cobra was among the few remaining members who formed the Reborn Oración Seis, and later joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. In the year X793, he became the boyfriend of Kinana.

Name: Conkeldurr
Summary: Conkeldurr is a fighting type Pokémon from the Unova region introduced in Generation V.

Name: Copperajah
Summary: Copperajah, the Copperderm Pokémon, is a Steel-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII and is the evolution of Cufant. It is also one of the few Pokémon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Corsola
Summary: Corsola is a small, pink Pokémon with branch-like growths on its back, which are similar to coral. It continuously sheds and grows. The tip of its head is prized as a treasure because of its beauty, and its branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night. The points on its head absorb nutrients from clear water. They cannot survive in polluted water, and their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water, which is why they prefer the unpolluted southern seas. In one south-sea nation, the people live in communities that are built on groups of these Pokémon.

Name: Crabrawler
Summary: Crabrawler, and further on Crabominable, is a Fighting-type Pokémon from the Alola region.

Name: Cramorant
Summary: Cramorant is a blue, bird Pokémon resembling a cormorant. It has bright green, large, circular eyes with small pupils and a large, thin yellow beak. It has a ruff of light gray feathers that goes around its torso and sticks out at the back, making them resemble a bib. Its tail feathers have a small dot-shaped marking of this same shade of gray. It has a ruff of feathers on its head, with the largest clump pointing backward and being surrounded by small singular feathers. Its feet are black, webbed, and have three toes. Its wings seem to be perpetually extended.

Name: Crawdaunt
Summary: Corphish is a red crustacean Pokémon, resembling a lobster somewhat, that is capable of living and thriving in harsh environments, which includes incredibly polluted rivers, due to its hardy nature and its ability to adapt, rivalling even Feebas in this regard. It has two large, sharp pincers which it uses to hold on tightly to and catch prey.

Name: Crobat
Summary: Crobat is a Flying-/Poison-type Pokemon introduced in Generation II. It a purple bat with four wings, with the hind set replacing its legs. It flies silently in the air to sneak up on enemies, but is clumsy while walking. It is also the first Pokemon to be a new evolution from a previous one, followed closely by Steelix and Scizor. It evolves by high friendship from Golbat, who evolves from Zubat at level 25.

Name: Darmanitan
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Dewgong
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Dhelmise
Summary: Dhelmise is a Pokémon made up of a ship's anchor and wheel, tied together by green seaweed, which in actuality is the Pokémon's true body. It is said that the souls of seaweed adrift in the waves are reborn as Dhelmise. It maintains itself by infusing its body with new organic material found on the seabed.

Name: Diglett
Summary: Diglett is a Ground-Type Pokémon from Kanto. It is noted for living mainly underground, and usually only having its tiny head exposed.

Name: Dodrio
Summary: Dodrio is a three headed bird Pokémon based off both, the Ostrich and the Dodo Bird. It evolves from Doduo at level 31.

Name: Donphan
Summary: nan

Name: Dragapult
Summary: Dragapult is an spectral dragon Pokemon and the resident Pseudo Legendary in the 8th generation of Pokemon. Alongside being a ghost dragon, it is based on fighter jets, and fires its first form, Dreepy, from itself like missiles. Apparently, the Dreepy like being launched. It evolves from Drakloak at level 60, which evolves from Dreepy at level 50.

Name: Dragonite
Summary: Dragonite is a "pseudo-legendary" Dragon and Flying-type Pokémon from the first generation, and one of the strongest Pokémon of its time. It evolves from Dratini at level 30, and evolves from Dragonair at 55.

Name: Drednaw
Summary: Drednaw is a powerful snapping turtle Pokemon. They are known for being incredibly difficult to train due to their vicious nature. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Duraludon
Summary: Duraludon is a Steel-/Dragon- type Pokemon introduced in the Galar region. It's a cave dwelling dinosaur-like Pokemon. It has an intense rivalry with Tyranitar, due to sharing the same territory, and constantly fights over it. It has the exceptionally durable cells, even compared to other Steel- type Pokemon, which makes it resistant to earthquakes. Despite its heavy look, it's surprisingly light, and is therefore very agile for its size.

Name: Dusknoir
Summary: Dusknoir is a final form ghost-type Pokémon introduced in Gen IV. It evolves from Duskull into Dusclops, and from Dusclops into Dusknoir by holding a Reaper Cloth and being traded.

Name: Eelektross
Summary: Eelektross is an Electric-type Pokémon, introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Eelektrik when given a Thunder Stone, and is the final evolution of Tynamo.

Name: Electivire
Summary: Electivire is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Electabuzz, and the final form of the Gen II Elekid. It evolves when traded with an Electrizer.

Name: Electrode
Summary: Electrode, the evolved form of Voltorb. Known as "The Bomb Ball", it constantly explodes. It is often mistaken for a Pokeball due to its shape and feeds on electricity to the point of being problematic for humans.

Name: Elfman Strauss
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc to Grand Magic Games Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Elfman Strauss is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and the brother of Mirajane and Lisanna. In the year X782, Elfman was deeply scarred by an incident where his younger sister, Lisanna, was supposedly killed by him when she tried to stop his rampage after he attempted to use Beast Soul: Full-Body Take Over. During his rampage, Elfman hit Lisanna with great force, throwing her a great distance. It is said that due to this, Elfman's heart was locked shut, despite his use of the spell to protect his sisters.

Name: Emboar
Summary: Emboar (Japanese: エンブオー, Enbuoh) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Pignite starting at level 36. It is the final form of Tepig.

Name: Empoleon
Summary: Empoleon is a Water/Steel type Starter Pokémon from Sinnoh, based on an Emperor Penguin. It evolves from Piplup into Prinplup at level 16, and from Prinplup to Empoleon at level 36.

Name: Erigor
Summary: Erigor is the strongest member of the former Dark Guild Eisenwald. He became infamously known as the Death God due to being a Mage that only accepted assassination jobs. This epithet of him is supported by his weapon of choice, a scythe. Seven years later, Erigor escaped from imprisonment and became a member of the Reborn Oración Seis under the name of Grim Reaper.

Name: Erza Knightwalker
Summary: Erza Knightwalker is part of the Edolas Kingdom and is the Royal Army Captain of the 2nd Magic War Division. She is the Edolas counterpart of Erza Scarlet. Unlike her Earth Land counterpart, Erza Knightwalker is sadistic and cruel, showing no sympathy towards her enemies; killing them without mercy. She was involved in the killing of over half of the members of Edolas Fairy Tail, thus, earning her epithet. After being beaten by Erza Scarlet for the final time, Knightwalker acts gentler, having been touched by her counterpart's words.

Name: Erza Scarlet (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Erza Scarlet is an infamous S-Class Mage titled "Fairy Queen Titania." She is renowned for her combat prowess as well as her status as one of her guild's most stern disciplinarians. Despite her intimidating exterior, she deeply cares for her comrades and treats them as if they were family, as she lost her own after her hometown was ransacked by fanatical worshippers of the Dark Mage Zeref and was forced to build the Tower of Heaven. She was imprisoned together with several other slaves, most of which were children. Among these children were Jellal Fernandes, Shô, Simon, Wally Buchanan, and Millianna. While they asked each other for their names, she said that her name was just "Erza." Hence, Jellal decided to give her the surname "Scarlet" after her scarlet hair so they would never forget it. Eventually, she rebelled against the cult and escaped, but not without losing Jellal, who had been corrupted by Zeref's Dark Arts. She also served as the guild's 7th Guild Master during Makarov's absence in X792.

Name: Escavalier
Summary: Escavalier is a Bug/Steel type Pokémon, introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Karrablast when traded specifically with a Shelmet, due to a strange, unknown reaction to electrical stimulation.

Name: Eternal Flower Floette
Summary: 3000 years ago, AZ befriended a Floette who was unfortunately forced to enter a war Kalos was facing. She was killed untimely and, in his grief, AZ created the Ultimate Weapon in order to revive her. Floette was resurrected from the dead by the machine draining the life force of the Pokemon soldiers. Disgusted to learn of the source of her resurrection, Floette left AZ.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Evergreen
Summary: Evergreen is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and the only female member of the Thunder God Tribe. After Fairy Tail's disbandment she joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the other members of the Thunder God Tribe. However, a little while after the guild's reformation, she left to rejoin Fairy Tail alongside Laxus and the rest of her team.

Name: Evice
Summary: Evice (Japanese: ワルダック Wardack) is the criminal mastermind behind Cipher. He is the only character in the games to have the Trainer class Cipher Head (Japanese: シャドーのボス Shadow Boss). He disguises himself as the mayor of Phenac City under the name of Es Cade (Japanese: バックレー Backley). In his disguise, he is a fat and jolly gentleman who appears to be worried about the increase in crime caused by Cipher and Team Snagem, yet as the head of Cipher, he appears to have done nothing to stop either of them, ensuring that Snagem and Cipher work without interference.

Name: Exeggutor
Summary: Exeggcute is a Pokémon resembling six light pink eggs, usually seen arranged with five heads huddled around a sixth. Each "head" has a slightly different facial expression, but each face has triangular eyes with tiny black pupils and a small mouth. Each shell has some cracks, and one member of the bundle usually has its yellow insides or brain exposed. More numerous cracks are a sign that it is close to evolution. Despite looking like eggs, Exeggcute is actually more closely related to plant seeds. It is believed to carry genes of plants and other species. Exeggcute gathers in swarms of six. The heads communicate with each other by using a form of telepathy that only they can understand. Should the number of Exeggcute be reduced to less than six, the remaining Exeggcute will attempt to replace it with a similarly sized Pokémon as seen in the anime. Pidgeotto and Crabrawler are its natural predators, which it chases off with psychokinesis. Exeggcute inhabits jungles and forests.

Name: Exploud
Summary: Exploud is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a large mouth. It has red eyes, a stubby nose, and two peg-like teeth in each jaw. It has protruding tubes with holes along its body: seven forming a crest on top of its head, one on each elbow and knee, two along its back, and one at the end of each of its two tails. The tubes along its head-crest and tails are tipped with yellow, while the ones along its back have yellow semicircular patterns on either side. There are two yellow semicircle markings on its belly, but they are rarely seen due to its giant mouth. Its arms have three thin stripes below its elbow and three fingers. Each foot has four claws, three in the front and one in the back, and a yellow paw pad.

Name: Farfetch'd
Summary: Farfetch’d is an avian Pokémon that resembles a light brown duck with a white underbelly. It has a flat, yellow beak, brown eyes, a V-shaped black marking on its forehead, and a three-feather crest on top of its head. Its wings are as big as its body and appear to be prehensile enough to substitute for hands. It has yellow legs with webbed feet and a stubby tail.

Name: Faust (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Faust is the former King of Edolas, banished and succeeded by his disowned son, Mystogan. He is the Edolas counterpart of Makarov Dreyar.

Name: Fearow
Summary: Fearow is the beak Normal/Flying Pokémon and first appears in Generation I. It evolves from Spearow at level 20.

Name: Feraligatr
Summary: Feraligatr is the reptilian final water starter from the Johto region. It evolves from Croconaw at level 30, which itself evolves from Totodile at level 18, later than any starter save only for Turtwig, with whom it is tied.

Name: Ferrothorn
Summary: Ferrothorn. The Thorn Pod Pokemon. It's a metallic Pokemon that resembles a durian with three vine tendrils coming out of it. This Pokemon likes to attach itself onto ceilings and launch spikes at opponents coming beneath it. it evolves from Ferroseed at level 40.

Name: Forretress
Summary: Forretress is a Pokemon debuting in the second generation. It's a bug covered by a steel hard shell. Its inner core has apparently never been seen, even when it feeds.

Name: Fried Justine
Summary: Fried Justine is a Mage of Fairy Tail who didn't often appear in the guild; he is the leader of the Thunder God Tribe. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, he joined the Blue Pegasus Guild along with the other members of the Thunder God Tribe and Laxus. However, after the guild's reformation, he later left Blue Pegasus to join Fairy Tail again along with his team.

Name: Froslass
Summary: Froslass is a Ghost/Ice Pokémon, said in legends to be the spirit of a woman lost on a mountain who possessed an icicle (though this is clearly just a myth). It is vaguely humanoid and its torso seems to look like a kimono, with an obi wrapping around it, and its body is hollow. It Ian based on the Japanese mythical yokai, the Yuki-Onna. It freezes its prey at -58 degrees F, and secretly uses them as decorations. It is the female counterpart to Glalie, and while any Snorunt evolves into Glalie at level 42, female Snorunt evolve into Froslass with the use of a Dawn Stone.

Name: Fukuro (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Fukuro is a member of Trinity Raven, a group in the assassin guild Death's Head Caucus, that worked under Jellal Fernandes.

Name: Gajeel Redfox (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gajeel Redfox is an Iron Dragon Slayer, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and a former S-Class Mage of Phantom Lord. After Fairy Tail's disbandment, Gajeel joins the Magic Council and becomes the captain of the Custody Enforcement Unit, but after Avatar is defeated, he returns to Fairy Tail. Originally a Dragon Slayer from four hundred years past, Gajeel was sent to the future to assist in the destruction of Acnologia.

Name: Galaxy Team
Summary: Many years ago, the land of Sinnoh was completely uninhabited by humans. Eventually, a large band of explorers landed upon its shore and over time they built a village to call their own; that being Jubilife Village, officially kicking off the colonization of the Sinnoh region. There was one major problem that they faced, however: Humans did not nearly have the standards of Pokémon training that they do in modern days, making even navigating areas with Pokémon present a life-threatening journey. To get around this, they set up the Galaxy Team in their proud village, splitting among 6 Corps everything they would need to do to thrive in the land of Sinnoh:

Name: Garbodor
Summary: Garbodor, the Trash Heap Pokemon. Garbodor is a giant sentient trashbag that is spilled open. It is said that it became sentient due to the combination of garbage bags and industrial waste. It is preyed upon by Alolan Muk. It evolves from Trubbish at level 36. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Garchomp
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Gengar
Summary: Gengar (Japanese: ゲンガー Gangar) is a dual-type Ghost/Poison Pokémon. It evolves from Haunter when traded. It is the final form of Gastly. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Gengar using the Gengarite. Gengar is a dark purple, bipedal Pokémon with a roundish body. It has red eyes and a wide mouth that is usually curled into a sinister grin. Multiple spikes cover its back, and it has large pointed ears. Its arms and legs are short with three digits on both its hands and feet. It also has a stubby tail. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Gigalith
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Glalie
Summary: Glalie is an Ice-type Pokémon introduced in generation III. Glalie is a living rock with an armor of ice around it, small horns, and a terrifying face. It is known to flash freeze prey solid, and leisurely eat them while they're stiff. It has a female counterpart in Froslass, and Glalie evolves from Snorunt at level 42.

Name: Gliscor
Summary: Gliscor (Japanese: グライオン Glion) is a dual-type Ground/Flying-type Pokémon introduced in Generation IV. Gliscor resembles a half scorpion/half vampire bat creature. Like Drapion and Skorupi, Gliscor has a barbed stinger on its tail. Due to the stiffness of its wings, it needs to have the wind at its back in order to stay airborne.

Name: Gloria (Pokémon)
Summary: Gloria is a girl from Postwick and the main protagonist of Pokémon Sword version and Pokémon Shield version. Born and raised as the neighbor of Leon, the greatest Trainer that Galar has ever known, Gloria was destined for greatness at a young age as she became fast childhood friends with his younger brother, Hop.

Name: Golisopod
Summary: Golisopod is a large, menacing arthropod Pokémon in a hunched-over, humanoid posture. It has a light purplish inner body generously armored with a silvery exoskeleton.

Name: Goodra
Summary: Goodra is the Pseudo-Legendary of Gen VI. It appears to be a bipedal draconian Pokémon made of slime. With its purple coloring and goofy smile, it seems to be competing with Dragonite as the lovable dragon powerhouse. It evolves from Goomy into Sliggoo at level 40, and from Sliggoo into Goodra at 50, but only in the overworld rain.

Name: Gothitelle
Summary: Gothitelle, the "Astral Body Pokémon" is a Psychic type Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation. It is the final evolution of Gothita, the "Fixation Pokémon". Gothitelle is infamous for its gloomy and Gothic appearance, as well as macabre Pokédex entries that revolve around the starry sky and the death of their trainers. Gothitelle apparently has the ability to see objects that only it can see, as well as control the minds of children and can even see the death of their trainers looming within the future.

Name: Gray Fullbuster (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Gray Fullbuster is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, wherein he is a member of Team Natsu. He is infamous for his ability to subconsciously strip off his clothing due to the instincts ingrained in him by his teacher's training. Nevertheless, he's a powerful Ice Mage and one of Natsu's main rivals. Gray was from a village up in the North, but the entire village was destroyed by the Demon Deliora. Gray's parents were killed in the incident as well. Along with Ur, a powerful ice Mage, Lyon came investigating Deliora's destruction and found Gray alive among the ruins. Ur took Gray in as her second student and taught him and Lyon Ice-Make Magic. In another encounter with Deliora, his teacher used Iced Shell to seal him away in order to save and protect Gray. After this, Gray took Ur's advice to find strong wizards. This led him to Fairy Tail, where he became a member.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Summary: Grimmsnarl is a dual-type Dark/Fairy Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII. It evolves from Morgrem starting at level 42, who is evolved from Impidimp. It is one of the Pokemon with the ability to Gigantamax

Name: Grimsley
Summary: Grimsley is a member of the Unova Elite Four and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon.

Name: Guzma
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie Garden)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shady House)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hau'oli City, Team Rocket's Castle and Title Defense)'''
Summary: Guzma (Japanese: グズマ Guzma) is the leader of Team Skull.

Name: Gyarados
Summary: Gyarados is a Water/Flying Pokémon introduced in Generation I. It is the evolved form of Magikarp. Extremely vicious, enormously destructive, ferociously violent, and horribly brutal, it has a very aggressive nature. Although rarely seen in the wild, once it appears it goes on a rampage. When this happens, it doesn't calm until it has burned everything down and razed the fields and mountains around it. Not even harsh storms are able to stop its rage, and there are records of this Pokémon's rampages lasting a whole month. A single Gyarados has enough destructive power to totally annihilate even a major city. Gyarados is attracted to violence and tends to appear when there is a world conflict or war. When humans begin to fight, it will appear and burn everything to the ground with intensely hot flames. During past wars Gyarados would appear and leave blazing ruins in its wake, and in ancient literature there is a record of a Gyarados that razed a village when violence flared. When Magikarp evolves into Gyarados, its brain cells undergo a structural transformation. It is said that this transformation is to blame for this Pokémon's wildly violent nature.

Name: Happy (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Happy is an Exceed from Extalia, a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and Team Natsu. He acts as Team Natsu's mascot. Years ago, when Happy was just an egg, he was taken away from his parents, Lucky and Marl, by the queen of Extalia, Shagotte, to carry out the Dragon Slayer assassination plan. In actuality, sending him to Earth Land, along with all the other Exceed eggs, was done to allow him to escape a future disaster in Edolas. In X778, Natsu found Happy's egg in the East Forest of Magnolia Town. Natsu then took it back to the guild where he and Lisanna raised it together every day. One night, Elfman took it to keep it warm and the next day when he brought it back, it began to hatch and out popped a kitten with a pair of wings. Happy's first word was "Aye." Natsu gave him the name "Happy" after Lisanna pointed out the change of the atmosphere from anger to happiness after Happy hatched from the egg. Despite everyone else seeing him as a cat, Natsu thought he was a Dragon.

Name: Hawlucha
Summary: Hawlucha is a Fighting/Flying-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI.

Name: Haxorus
Summary: Haxorus is a Dragon-type Pokémon native to the Unova region. Also known as the Axe Jaw Pokemon, its sturdy tusks are destructive enough to cut through solid steel without chipping or dulling. Its also known to be relentless when defending its territory, but its sturdy armor and fierce fighting capabilities belie its kind spirit. It evolves from Fraxure who in turn evolves from Axew.

Name: Heracross
Summary: Heracross is the Pokémon number #214, a dual-type Bug/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Hoteye (Richard Buchanan)
Summary: Hoteye, real name Richard Buchanan, is a former member of the Oración Seis, a Dark Guild composed of highly powerful Mages whose goal is to find Nirvana, a destructive power that was sealed away long ago. After his release from prison, he joined Crime Sorcière per Jellal's request to help him take down Zeref. He is the elder brother of Wally Buchanan.

Name: Houndoom
Summary: Houndoom is a Pokémon introduced in Gen II. It evolves from Houndour at level 24.

Name: Hououmon
Summary: Its Special Move "Starlight Explosion" has become even more powerful due to the increase in its holy power.

Name: Hughes (Fairy Tail)
Summary: Hughes is the Captain of the 3rd Magic War Division of the Edolas Royal Army.

Name: Hydreigon
Summary: Hydreigon is a dual-type Dark/Dragon pseudo-legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation V, based on the mythological hydra. It evolves from Zweilous at level 64, who evolves from Deino at level 50. Its most notable trait is its three heads, hence the "drei" in its name, which is German for 3.

Name: Ichiya Vandalay Kotobuki
Summary: Ichiya Vandalay Kotobuki is the ace of the Blue Pegasus Guild, as well as the leader of the Trimens (composed of Hibiki Lates, Ren Akatsuki, and Eve Tearm). Ichiya is a womanizer like the rest of his group. Unlike them, he is nowhere near as "handsome", though he thinks of himself as such. Regardless, the Trimens call him "Aniki" (Older Brother) or "Master" and show a great deal of respect for him.

Name: Incineroar
Summary: Incineroar (Japanese: ガオガエン, Gaogaen) is a dual-type Fire/Dark Pokémon.

Name: Indeedee
Summary: Indeedee, the Emotion Pokemon, is a Psychic/Normal type Pokemon introduced in Generation 8. It was first seen in the Galar regions. They are one of the few Pokemon with major differences between their two sexes, and even their statistics in games change slightly depending on their gender.

Name: Infernape
Summary: Infernape (Japanese: ゴウカザル, Goukazaru) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Inteleon
Summary: Inteleon is a Water type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. Inteleon is a highly skilled sniper and hunter, prone to using traps to keep enemies from its territory.

Name: Juvia Lockser
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Juvia Lockser is one of the main supporting protagonists of Fairy Tail. Formerly a member of the Phantom Lord Guild, she joined Fairy Tail after Phantom Lord was disbanded. After the battle of Tartarus, Fairy Tail disbanded. Juvia traveled with her beloved Gray Fullbuster to Amefurashi Village and resided there until Gray's disappearance due to him joining Avatar as a spy. Heartbroken, she stayed in the village to wait for Gray until Natsu's group arrived to find a sick Juvia. Cured by Wendy, she joined the battle against Avatar and reunited with Gray. After the event of Avatar, Juvia, and other Fairy Tail members restored the guild.

Name: Jynx
Summary: Jynx is an Ice-Psychic type Pokémon originated from Kanto. It behaves with noises comparable to human speech, yet it can´t be understood by humans.

Name: Kabutops
Summary: Kabutops is a fossil Pokémon introduced in the Kanto region. Originally, it is acquired by beating the Super Nerd for his Dome Fossil (or Helix Fossil). It is then taken to the Cinnabar Research Lab and turned into a level 5 Kabuto. It evolves at level 40.

Name: Kain Hikaru
Summary: Kain Hikaru was a member of the now-disbanded Dark Guild Grimoire Heart, as well as one of its Seven Kin of Purgatory.

Name: Kangaskhan
Summary: Kangaskhan, the Parent Pokemon, is a Normal-Type Pokemon introduced in the first generation. It is a purely female Pokemon without any evolutions. It carries its offspring in its pouch at all times, and is the only Pokemon who most of its information has a lot to have a lot to do with being a mother, aside from Marowak (and unlike Marowak, the mother lives). If anyone touches its child, it will attack the assaulter in an outrage. This parent-child relationship comes into completion with its Mega Form, where its child comes out of the pouch to fight, though the mother becomes worried about its future, as the child gains violent tendencies.

Name: Kawazu
Summary: Kawazu was a low-ranking, yet deceptively strong, member of the now-disbanded Dark Guild Grimoire Heart, and was under the command of Caprico. He worked alongside his partner Yomazu.

Name: Kecleon (Mystery Dungeon)
Summary: In the Pokémon Mystery Dungeon series, Kecleon serves as shopkeepers throughout the entire franchise. These Kecleon Shops exist to assist players through their game by offering various food items, TMs, and other goods. Items can also be sold to Kecleon Shop for Poké, the in-game currency. Kecleon either set up shop in towns or in the mystery dungeons themselves. Anyone who is foolish enough to steal from a Kecleon in a mystery dungeon will be labelled by the Kecleon as a thief (which will get the attention of nearby enemies) and will be chased and attacked by the Kecleon while other Kecleon appear to help apprehend the thief.

Name: Kinana
Summary: Kinana is a member of the Fairy Tail Guild and the former pet of Oración Seis member, Cobra. Unlike most other members of Fairy Tail, she initially joined the guild as an employee, rather than as a Mage. After Fairy Tail's disbandment she is finally able to use magic, rejoining the guild as a Mage.

Name: Kingdra
Summary: Kingdra (Japanese: キングドラ, Kingdra) is a dual-type Water/Dragon Pokémon. It evolves from Seadra when traded holding a Dragon Scale. It is the final form of Horsea.

Name: Kingler
Summary: Kingler is a crab based Pokémon introduced in Gen I. It evolves from Krabby starting at level 28. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Klodoa
Summary: Klodoa is a Magic Staff able to speak human language and levitate. Formerly used by Brain, it was referred to as the seventh member of the Oración Seis, or just as Brain's staff. Seven years later, Klodoa returns wearing a magical bear costume and calling himself Jackpot, a member of the now-disbanded dark guild, Reborn Oración Seis.

Name: Kommo-o
Summary: Kommo-o (Japanese: ジャラランガ, Jararanga) is a dual Dragon/Fighting-type Pokémon. It evolves from Hakamo-o and is the final form of Jangmo-o. Having completed its harsh training, Kommo-o returns to its birthplace to protect Jangmo-o. However, it only watches over them from a distance. Because it does not wish to fight weak foes, it clangs its scales together when it senses someone approaching. This ringing sound alerts others of its presence. The power of this Pokémon’s uppercut is enough to send foes flying. Simply raising its arms can generate enough force to change its surroundings. According to legend, Kommo-o's glittering scales are meant to drive away a great darkness. The reason it seeks strong opponents is also said to be a quest for power to defeat the darkness.

Name: Korrina
Summary: Korrina is the Fighting-type gym leader of Shalour City and granddaughter of the Mega Evolution Guru.

Name: Krookodile
Summary: Krookodile is a dual Ground/Dark type Pokémon based on a crocodile from the fifth generation of Pokémon. It evolves from Krokorok at level 40. It is the final form of Sandile.

Name: Lance (Pokémon)
Summary: Lance (ワタル Wataru) is a Dragon-type Trainer, a member of the Kanto Elite Four in Pokémon Red, Blue, Fire Red and Leaf Green. 3 years later, after Red and Blue left the Indigo Plateau, he became Pokémon Champion of Kanto in Gold, Silver, Crystal, HeartGold and SoulSilver. Later on, he participated in the Pokémon World Tournament in Black 2 and White 2.

Name: Lapras
Summary: Lapras, the Transport Pokémon, is a Water-/Ice- Type, plesiosaur-based Pokémon. It is known to be quite gentle, able to read the minds of others, and understand human speech. It loves to carry humans and other Pokémon on its back. Because of their gentle nature, this Pokémon rarely fights, and due to this, it has been caught and poached to near extinction, starting a conservation effort. It is known to sing an enchanting cry when in a good mood, but in the evenings, it sings plaintively as it seeks what few others of its kind remain. Thankfully, by the time of Sun and Moon, protective regulations have saved the species, so much that there's an overabundance in Alola.

Name: Levy McGarden
Summary: Levy McGarden is a member of Team Shadow Gear, along with Jet and Droy. She loves to read books and has a very cheerful personality, being able to get along with many other guild members. Levy and Lucy quickly became friends through their mutual interest in books. Levy's magic is called Solid Script. It allows her to make words solid and then throw the words at her opponent. For instance, if the word fire were to be thrown at her opponent the victim would feel as if he were hit by a fireball.

Name: Lickitung
Summary: Tier: 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Lillipup
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Lisanna Strauss
Summary: Lisanna Strauss is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, the younger sister of Elfman and Mirajane, and a childhood friend of Natsu. She almost lost her life in the attempt to control her brother, after his full-body Take Over went out of control, although she actually didn't die. Mirajane was tending her wounds when a portal opened and took her into another world. When she woke up, she found herself in a totally different Guild. Everyone at the guild believed that she was the Lisanna they knew, and welcomed her back. From what she saw, she realized that their "Lisanna" was dead. She then decided to pretend to be their Lisanna, in order to make them happy. After the Edolas arc, she returned to Earthland.

Name: Loke (Leo)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Celestial Spirit)''' | '''In X791 (Eclipse Celestial Spirit)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Loke is a member of Fairy Tail who was revealed to be the Celestial Spirit Leo, who is known as "The Lion". He is the leader of the 12 Golden Zodiac Keys. His Key is currently owned by Lucy Heartfilia.

Name: Lorelei
Summary: Lorelei is the ice user of the Elite Four, and is the first Elite Four member ever met. She is known for her cool and calculated tactics. She is from Four Island on the Sevii Islands, and has a deep affinity to the Icefall Cave there, as that is where she first got her Lapras when she was a child.

Name: Lucy Heartfilia (X784 to X792)
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792'''
Summary: Lucy Heartfilia is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild and a member of Team Natsu. The daughter of Layla and Jude Heartfilia, she has a family history tied to magic; her parents were members of the guild "Love & Lucky" until Layla's pregnancy prompted them to strike out on their own. Lucy's name itself is a quirky coincidence: her parents noticed their former guild's name, missing a "K," read "Love & Lucy." Her father founded the influential Heartfilia Konzern, one of Fiore's wealthiest organizations. Following her mother Layla's death, Lucy's relationship with her father deteriorated, leading to years of loneliness and neglect. Seeking a new life, she ran away from home, hoping to join Fairy Tail. During her journey, she encountered Natsu Dragneel and Happy, who rescued her from the corrupt wizard Bora and ultimately brought her into the Fairy Tail Guild, where she's been a valued member ever since.

Name: Lurantis
Summary: Lurantis is a Grass-type Pokémon originating from the Alola region. It is the evolved form of Fomantis - the sickle grass pokemon.

Name: Lusamine
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team''' | '''Merged Lusamine''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Merge Lusamine)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Lusamine is the current president of the Aether Foundation, an organization created to shelter Pokémon from villainous organizations like Team Skull and nurse these Pokémon back to health to be returned to the wild. She is the insane and corrupt president of the Aether Foundation, who not only abuses her own children and has performed various gruesome experiments on the very Pokemon she's supposed to take care of and protect but also plans to go to Ultra Space to reach the Ultra Beasts, even if it means unleashing their fury on the Alola region.

Name: Luxray
Summary: Luxray is the Gleam Eyes Pokémon, based on a lynx. It is an electric type Pokémon that evolves from Luxio at level 30, and is the final form of Shinx. Aside from being a fan favorite, it is known for being able to see through things.

Name: Lycanroc
Summary: Lycanroc is a Rock-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VII. It evolves from Rockruff starting at level 25. The form it takes upon evolving depends on the moment of the day Rockruff is leveled up. During the day, it would evolve in Midday Form, and during the night, into Midnight Form. Sometimes in a rare natural phenomenon when the sun gives off green light around sunset or sunrise, Rockruff would evolve into Dusk form.

Name: Lyon Vastia
Summary: Lyon Vastia is an Ice wizard who is the arch rival of Gray Fullbuster. Like Gray, Lyon trained under his master Ur. He's also Gray's senior and a user of the dynamic Ice molding magic, with molding speed that far exceeds Gray's. Introduced as an antagonist very early in the series, Lyon who at the time went by the epithet "Reitei Lyon" which roughly translates to "Sub-Zero Emperor Lyon", has since being defeated by Gray, turned good and is now a member, and the ace of the legal guild Lamia Scale as well as one of the most powerful wizards in the city of Fiore.

Name: Macao Conbolt
Summary: Macao Conbolt is a veteran Mage of Fairy Tail, and their Fourth Guild Master, following the disappearance of Makarov Dreyar and those who were with him.

Name: Machamp
Summary: Machamp is a Fighting-type Pokémon. It is the final evolutionary stage of Machop, evolving from Machoke when traded. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Magcargo
Summary: Magcargo is a limbless, snail-like Pokémon consisting almost entirely of bright red magma. Its oval eyes are large and yellow with small pupils, and extend upward from its head. It has a bulbous snout and a wide mouth, with two drops of magma dangling from each side of its upper jaw. Magcargo's back is protected by a gray, spherical shell composed of hardened, but brittle magma, forming irregular lumps and plates. A streak of fire leaks from the side of its shell. Magcargo's lower body is amorphous and covered in bubbles of magma.

Name: Magmortar
Summary: Magmortar is a Gen IV Pokémon and the evolution of the Gen I Magmar, and the final form of the Gen II Magby. It evolves when traded with a Magmarizer. It releases flames of over 3600 degrees Fahrenheit from its arms, quite literally putting the mortar in Magmortar.

Name: Magnemite
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Mamoswine
Summary: Mamoswine, the Twin Tusk Pokemon, is a Ground/Ice Type Pokemon introduced in Gen IV. It is based on the woolly mammoth and is an evolution of the Gen II Pokemon Piloswine after leveling up while knowing Ancient Power.

Name: Manectric
Summary: Manectric (ライボルト Livolt), the Discharge Pokémon is an Electric Type Pokémon introduced in the third generation of Pokémon.

Name: Marnie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (First battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Second battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Third battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Fourth battle/Champion tournament)'''
Summary: Marnie (Japanese: マリィ Mary) is one of the rival characters in Pokémon Sword and Shield, the others being Hop and Bede, and specializes in Dark-type Pokémon. She eventually replaces her older brother Piers as the Gym Leader of her hometown Spikemuth. As the Spikemuth Gym Leader, she gives the Dark Badge to Trainers who defeat her.

Name: Max Alors
Summary: Max Alors is a Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild who is in charge of most of the guild's social activities, given his love for talking to people. His Magic is a type of Sand Magic: Sandstorm.

Name: Maxie (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mt. Chimney)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Seafloor Cavern)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Battle Maison)''' | '''Pokémon (Team Gen 7)'''
Summary: Maxie is the boss of Team Magma. The player battles him in the Mossdeep Space Center in Emerald and Mt. Chimney and Seafloor Cavern in Ruby. In Sapphire, he is an ally to the player on his/her mission to stop Team Aqua from expanding the sea and in Ruby, he is the main villain of the game.

Name: Meganium
Summary: Meganium is the grass type starter of Johto and the final evolution of Chikorita. It evolves from Chikorita starting at level 16, and evolves into Meganium at level 32.

Name: Meowscarada
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Meowstic
Summary: Meowstic is a Psychic-type Pokémon from the Kalos region, introduced in Generation VI.

Name: Meowth
Summary: Meowth is a small, feline Pokémon with cream-colored fur that turns brown at the tips of its hind paws and tail. Its ovoid head features four prominent whiskers, wide eyes with slit pupils, two pointed teeth in the upper jaw, and a gold koban coin embedded in its forehead. Its ears are black with brown interiors and are flanked with an additional pair of long whiskers. Meowth is a quadruped with the ability to walk on its hind legs; while the games always depict Meowth on two legs, the anime states that Meowth normally walks on all fours. It can freely manipulate its claws, retracting them when it wants to move silently. The tip of its tail curls tightly. Meowth is attracted to round and shiny objects and has the unique ability to produce coins using Pay Day. Being nocturnal, it is known to wander about city streets at night and pick up anything that sparkles, including loose change. Upon finding a sparkling object, its eyes will glitter and the coin on its forehead will shine brightly. It shares this intrigue with Murkrow, with whom it often fights with for objects and prey. Meowth is a playful but fickle Pokémon with the capacity for human-like intelligence. At least one member of the species teaching itself how to speak. Meowth tends to live in urban areas. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Meowth (Team Rocket)
Summary: Meowth is a Member of the Team rocket Trio. Upon being abandoned on a box by his mother as a baby, he was forced to take care of himself on the streets, eventually learning how to talk and walk on 2 legs to impress a female meowth. Upon repeated failures and crimes committed, he was approached by team rocket and found his goal in life, being Giovanni's own pet to obtain a father figure, besides achieving wealth and power.

Name: Meredy
Summary: Meredy was a member of Grimoire Heart and one of the Seven Kin of Purgatory. Currently, she is a member and co-founder of Crime Sorcière, an Independent Guild.

Name: Mest Gryder
Summary: Mest Gryder is a member of Fairy Tail, a former member of the Magic Council, and a former Division Head of the Rune Knights. In X784, he used his Memory Control to deceive the members of the Fairy Tail so that he could infiltrate the guild, while in actuality he was always a member of Fairy Tail who erased his own memories to successfully infiltrate the aforementioned Magic Council, using the alias Doranbolt.

Name: Metagross
Summary: Metagross is a Dual Steel/Psychic Type and the Iron Leg Pokémon. A rare and powerful species native to the Hoenn region, it is formed when two Metangs, which are created when two Beldums merge, combine into a single Pokémon. Its incredible intelligence and great power make it a formidable opponent, being most famously utilized by the Hoenn League Champion, Steven Stone.

Name: MetalGarurumon
Summary: Tier: Unknown | 9-B | High 8-C | At least High 8-C | High 7-A | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least High 6-C | At least High 6-C | 5-B | At least 5-B

Name: Millianna
Summary: Millianna is one of Erza Scarlet's childhood friends from their days as slaves at the Tower of Heaven, having additionally worked as one of Jellal's minions for a time. She is currently a Mage of the all-female guild—Mermaid Heel. She is an avid cat lover, having decorated her entire room with a cat theme.

Name: Milotic
Summary: Feebas is a shabby, old-looking fish-like Pokémon. It has large, hollow eyes, large spots covering its body, dull pink lips and a deprived look. Due to its ugly appearance, it is largely ignored by predators, Trainers, and researchers alike. Despite this however, Feebas has the unique trait of being able to survive in any water, no matter how polluted, making it quite hardy.

Name: Mirajane Strauss
Key: '''In X784''' | '''In X791 (Key of the Starry Sky Arc)''' | '''In X791 (Grand Magic Games Arc to Tartaros Arc)''' | '''In X792''' | '''In X793'''
Summary: Mirajane Strauss is a former S-Class Mage of the Fairy Tail Guild, as well as its "drawing card", and is often a model for the Sorcerer Magazine. She is the older sister of Elfman and Lisanna. In her younger years, Mirajane was known as "The Demon", and before Lisanna's pseudo-death, she used to be a very feared person, infamous amongst guilds and criminals alike. Due to a past incident involving the apparent death of her younger sister, Lisanna, Mirajane somehow lost much of her magical ability and her will to fight (both of which have since returned), and her personality changed drastically. Now, Mirajane is a loving and caring person who treats her friends, and even strangers, with kindness. Mirajane plays a motherly role within the guild, and is often seen running the bar at the guild hall.

Name: Misty
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Rematch)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)'''
Summary: Misty (Japanese: カスミ Kasumi) is a Gym Leader of Cerulean City's Gym, known officially as the Cerulean Gym. She gives the Cascade Badge to Trainers who defeat her in battle. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon.

Name: Mount Vesuvius eruption
Summary: The Mount Vesuvius eruption of the year 79, is one of the eruptions with the highest kill counts, claiming over 2,000 lives. It had a VEI of 5.

Name: Mr. Mime
Summary: nan

Name: Mudsdale
