Summary: Edgin Darvis is an human bard from Icewind Dale and was in the past a member of the Harpers, a spy organization dedicated to protecting Faerûn’s common folk, this changed after the death of his wife, when Edgin has forsworn his oath and turned to thievery to support his family. His strong moral compass whoever compels him to steal only from people he believes deserve will not suffer from it.

Name: Edwin Tolstoff
Summary: Edwin Tolstoff was a mighty spellcaster before attempting to gain yet further power by means of dark ascension. Turning to the mighty god of Death, Nerull, he would murder his colleagues to take their power, he attracted the attention of the Worm that Walks. Now, given the power he wanted, he aims to free his master in the hopes of escape.

Name: Eevee
Summary: nan

Name: Electrode
Summary: Electrode, the evolved form of Voltorb. Known as "The Bomb Ball", it constantly explodes. It is often mistaken for a Pokeball due to its shape and feeds on electricity to the point of being problematic for humans.

Name: Ember Guard
Summary: Ember Guards are dim-witted but ultimately extremely powerful servants of Imix, whom he often gifts to particularly useful followers as bodyguards and brutes. No servant of Imix would ever refuse such a gift, despite the fact that ember guards serve little purpose outside of brutally efficient killing. Their sole source of joy was pain being inflicted on others, making them extremely willing to destroy any enemies of their masters.

Name: Emboar
Summary: Emboar (Japanese: エンブオー, Enbuoh) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Pignite starting at level 36. It is the final form of Tepig.

Name: Empoleon
Summary: Empoleon is a Water/Steel type Starter Pokémon from Sinnoh, based on an Emperor Penguin. It evolves from Piplup into Prinplup at level 16, and from Prinplup to Empoleon at level 36.

Name: Ethan (Pokémon)
Summary: Ethan is a young boy who turned 10 and went on his Pokémon journey in HeartGold and SoulSilver, 3 years after the original FireRed and LeafGreen. Having a similar story to his predecessor, on his tenth birthday he got to see his local Professor and pick out a First Partner Pokémon to take on his journey.

Name: Exeggutor
Summary: Exeggcute is a Pokémon resembling six light pink eggs, usually seen arranged with five heads huddled around a sixth. Each "head" has a slightly different facial expression, but each face has triangular eyes with tiny black pupils and a small mouth. Each shell has some cracks, and one member of the bundle usually has its yellow insides or brain exposed. More numerous cracks are a sign that it is close to evolution. Despite looking like eggs, Exeggcute is actually more closely related to plant seeds. It is believed to carry genes of plants and other species. Exeggcute gathers in swarms of six. The heads communicate with each other by using a form of telepathy that only they can understand. Should the number of Exeggcute be reduced to less than six, the remaining Exeggcute will attempt to replace it with a similarly sized Pokémon as seen in the anime. Pidgeotto and Crabrawler are its natural predators, which it chases off with psychokinesis. Exeggcute inhabits jungles and forests.

Name: Exploud
Summary: Exploud is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a large mouth. It has red eyes, a stubby nose, and two peg-like teeth in each jaw. It has protruding tubes with holes along its body: seven forming a crest on top of its head, one on each elbow and knee, two along its back, and one at the end of each of its two tails. The tubes along its head-crest and tails are tipped with yellow, while the ones along its back have yellow semicircular patterns on either side. There are two yellow semicircle markings on its belly, but they are rarely seen due to its giant mouth. Its arms have three thin stripes below its elbow and three fingers. Each foot has four claws, three in the front and one in the back, and a yellow paw pad.

Name: F-15 Eagle
Summary: The F-15 is a fighter aircraft currently serving in the United States Air Force, and several other air forces around the world. Created in response to a satelite photograph of the MiG-25, to this day it remains one of the primary fighters of the USAF, having served over 3 decades with a combat record including 104 enemy aircraft shot down, 1 satellite, no air-to-air losses of its own, and only 3 confirmed losses from groundfire.

Name: F/A-18 Hornet
Summary: The F/A-18 Hornet is a twin engine all-weather carrier capable multirole fighter developed and designed by McDonnell Douglas (Now Boeing) and Northrop. It was derived from the earlier YF-17 design designed by the latter in the 1970s for use by the US Navy and Marine Corps. It has also seen service in use by several other nations, and first flew in 1978, entering service for the first time in 1983.

Name: Farfetch'd
Summary: Farfetch’d is an avian Pokémon that resembles a light brown duck with a white underbelly. It has a flat, yellow beak, brown eyes, a V-shaped black marking on its forehead, and a three-feather crest on top of its head. Its wings are as big as its body and appear to be prehensile enough to substitute for hands. It has yellow legs with webbed feet and a stubby tail.

Name: Fearow
Summary: Fearow is the beak Normal/Flying Pokémon and first appears in Generation I. It evolves from Spearow at level 20.

Name: Feraligatr
Summary: Feraligatr is the reptilian final water starter from the Johto region. It evolves from Croconaw at level 30, which itself evolves from Totodile at level 18, later than any starter save only for Turtwig, with whom it is tied.

Name: Ferrothorn
Summary: Ferrothorn. The Thorn Pod Pokemon. It's a metallic Pokemon that resembles a durian with three vine tendrils coming out of it. This Pokemon likes to attach itself onto ceilings and launch spikes at opponents coming beneath it. it evolves from Ferroseed at level 40.

Name: Fire Giant
Summary: Strong and proud, the Fire Giants are the artisans of the Giant race. They stand at around 18 feet tall, always being clad in armor and carrying a weapon. They build massive forts, using their immunity to fire to have them be located in areas of great heat.

Name: Flame Snake
Summary: Often used as guards the Flame Snake comes in 3 variants; Small, Lesser and Greater Flame Snake with each one being stronger then the former, the strongest of their kin being theorised to be banished demons cursed into being snakes.

Name: Flesh Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Created by various evil spellcasters across D&D, a Flesh Golem is various bodies sown together and animated through magic in order to create a minion for one's bidding. Flesh Golems can be created from various creatures ranging from humans, Scale Ones, and all the way to demons. No matter what a Flesh Golem is a fierce enemy to face in combat.

Name: Formian
Summary: Formians are ant-like outsiders hellbent on meticulous keeping of order, to the point that their views often align with that of the Modron civilization. They resided in Mechanus, always keeping perfect order in their strict hierarchy of society. Formians create a hivemind based around their queen at a vast radius of fifty miles, thus ensuring their civilizations may never falter.

Name: Forretress
Summary: Forretress is a Pokemon debuting in the second generation. It's a bug covered by a steel hard shell. Its inner core has apparently never been seen, even when it feeds.

Name: Gambit
Summary: Remy Lebeau, better known as Gambit, is a semi-reformed thief and member of the X-Men whose troubled past has sometimes come back to haunt him, on the whole however Gambit has left his past behind and is a hero - sharing an on-and-off romantic interest with Rogue, despite the fact he can't touch her without fear of death.

Name: Gandalf
Key: '''Gandalf the Grey''' | '''Gandalf the White''' | '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Gandalf, originally known as Olórin, is a member of the order of wizards known as the Istari. Despite his appearance, Gandalf is not a human sorcerer, but rather a Maia of the ancient race of beings known as the Ainur, who existed before the creation of Arda. He is one of the main heroes in both J.R.R Tolkien's Middle-Earth saga and Peter Jackson's live-action adaptation of the books respectively.

Name: Gar Shatterkeel
Summary: Gar Shatterkeel was a former servant aboard merchant ships after his family was slaughtered by pirates. Made bitter and cynical by this life, he gathered to him armies of those that feel as he does- that the world would be better made covered in water, to bring about the end of all things.

Name: Garbodor
Summary: Garbodor, the Trash Heap Pokemon. Garbodor is a giant sentient trashbag that is spilled open. It is said that it became sentient due to the combination of garbage bags and industrial waste. It is preyed upon by Alolan Muk. It evolves from Trubbish at level 36. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Garchomp
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Gargoyle (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Gargoyles are monstrosities of stone hailing from the planes of Earth. These prideful predators wait in dormancy, patiently watching for enemies to inflict pain upon. A gathering of Gargoyles oftentimes will resort to banter and bragging to pass the time.

Name: Gengar
Summary: Gengar (Japanese: ゲンガー Gangar) is a dual-type Ghost/Poison Pokémon. It evolves from Haunter when traded. It is the final form of Gastly. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Gengar using the Gengarite. Gengar is a dark purple, bipedal Pokémon with a roundish body. It has red eyes and a wide mouth that is usually curled into a sinister grin. Multiple spikes cover its back, and it has large pointed ears. Its arms and legs are short with three digits on both its hands and feet. It also has a stubby tail. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Genista
Summary: Genista is the Franxx piloted by Code:556 (Kokoro) and originally Code:214 (Futoshi), but due to the partner swapping, Futoshi was replaced with Code:326 (Mitsuru). The Franxx is owned by Squad 13, and it is named after a genus of bushes.

Name: Ghaele
Summary: Ghaele are the knights-errant of the fey celestials, often serving faerie lords or even certain deities. Of the Eladrin of Arborea, the Ghaele were the most compassionate of the mortals and their plights. Thus, in contrast with their fun-loving species, the Ghaele's hearts were heavy, and many considered them distant and cold. The Ghaele would often wander the Prime Material, loving the place and growing depressed if they were unable to speak to the mortals of the realm.

Name: Ghoul (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Ghoul''' | '''Lacedon''' | '''Elder Ghoul''' | '''Vapour Ghoul''' | '''Shadow Ghoul''' | '''Noble/Wizard Ghoul''' | '''Cleric Ghoul''' | '''Abyssal Ghoul''' | '''Flesh Seeker''' | '''Whisperer Ghoul''' | '''Gatherer Ghoul''' | '''Ghoul Warrior''' | '''Ghoul Stalker''' | '''Gravetouched Ghoul''' | '''Ghast''' | '''Darkpach Ghoul'''
Summary: Ghouls are malicious undead that haunt battlefields and scenes of slaughter. Not unlike maggots or Carrion Crawlers, they sweep to the scent of freshly killed flesh in droves to devour and consume. The first ghoul was made when Doresain, an elf worshiper of Orcus, consumed human flesh. As a reward, Orcus granted him a domain in his layer of the Abyss- however, this was lost when Yeenoghu overthrew Doresain. When Orcus failed to act on his behalf, Doresain turned back to the elf gods, who saved him from total annihilation once more.

Name: Giant-Killer
Summary: Experts in fighting Giants, the Giant-Killer is a prestige class dedicated to combating that category of monsters. Often born from disasters caused by Giants, when not out hunting Giants they are often a nuisances, with them usually being boastful and arrogant. However once a Giant is involved they are the people one wants the most in the forefront.

Name: Giff
Summary: One of the many space faring races, the Giff is in appearance basically a hippopotamus walking on two legs. Their original world lost to the sands of time, the Giff can be found anywhere in space offering their services to the highest bidder. Giff are natural masters of guns, and are often trained in using a multitude of other weapons as well. They enjoy the thrill of combat, especially the sight of explosions, which is why they take payment in the form of gunpowder.

Name: Gigalith
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Girallon
Summary: Girallon are a species of gorilla-like monsters found in D&D. They are known for their carniverous eating habits and their quasi-society found in the jungles of the world. Despite their animalistic intelligence, these creatures did indeed acknowledge the eldest among them as their leaders.

Name: Githyanki
Summary: Githyanki are the half of the Gith species that ended up following the original Gith, a member of their formerly nameless species hailing from a distant planet. When the time came to rebel against those who had enslaved them- the Mind Flayer empire, at the peak of its power- Gith led the charge and the Githyanki by her side. Now, battalions of the Githyanki scour the universe for more signs of their eternal foes, the Mind Flayers.

Name: Githzerai
Summary: In times long lost to the rampages of war, the Githzerai were once normal Githyanki who dissented from their brethren and formed a non-evil neutral faction. The Githzerai are ascetic monk-like folk who have settled in Limbo, a plane of chaos- a direct counter to their Lawful nature. They seek to battle the Slaadi, specifically to expand their knowledge in the face of direct adversity, building on the traits they learned from their slavery under the Mind Flayer empire.

Name: Glabrezu
Summary: Glabrezu are demons of pride, preferring to operate by subterfuge rather than raw might. They are often compared to succubi- however, instead of offering affection, they offer wealth, and power. They often act as lone operators in the Abyss, rather than mundane units of any Lords army.

Name: Gliscor
Summary: Gliscor (Japanese: グライオン Glion) is a dual-type Ground/Flying-type Pokémon introduced in Generation IV. Gliscor resembles a half scorpion/half vampire bat creature. Like Drapion and Skorupi, Gliscor has a barbed stinger on its tail. Due to the stiffness of its wings, it needs to have the wind at its back in order to stay airborne.

Name: Golurk
Summary: Golurk is a dual-type Ghost/Ground Pokémon. It is a giant golem-like Pokémon that has existed since ancient times. Created as laborers, these Pokémon exist to help other humans and Pokémon, often following their master's orders faithfully unless the seal in their chest is removed.

Name: Goodra
Summary: Goodra is the Pseudo-Legendary of Gen VI. It appears to be a bipedal draconian Pokémon made of slime. With its purple coloring and goofy smile, it seems to be competing with Dragonite as the lovable dragon powerhouse. It evolves from Goomy into Sliggoo at level 40, and from Sliggoo into Goodra at 50, but only in the overworld rain.

Name: Gorguth
Summary: Gorguth is a Death Knight that previously served the Demon Lord Orcus but grew tired of the grotesque demon and his pointless plots, and thus set out to find a master who would take action. And thus the knight found Atropus, and currently leads its hordes of demons and undead to slaughter until Atropus attacks the world. Gorguth hopes for death in this endeavor.

Name: Gothitelle
Summary: Gothitelle, the "Astral Body Pokémon" is a Psychic type Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation. It is the final evolution of Gothita, the "Fixation Pokémon". Gothitelle is infamous for its gloomy and Gothic appearance, as well as macabre Pokédex entries that revolve around the starry sky and the death of their trainers. Gothitelle apparently has the ability to see objects that only it can see, as well as control the minds of children and can even see the death of their trainers looming within the future.

Name: Greninja
Summary: It utilizes its extraordinary jumping abilities to flummox its foes, throwing springy bubbles at them from above their heads.

Name: Griffon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Griffons are intelligent hybrids of lions and eagles. Their majesty is often hailed by cultures throughout the planes as a sign of goodness, and as such they are regularly used as mounts for good-aligned societies. The city of Waterdeep, the largest city of Faerun, maintained a large arsenal of Griffon cavalry. Netheril and Thay are two other superpowers that wielded the might of Griffons as their cavalry units. They are known to feed almost exclusively on horse flesh.

Name: Grimmsnarl
Summary: Grimmsnarl is a dual-type Dark/Fairy Pokémon introduced in Generation VIII. It evolves from Morgrem starting at level 42, who is evolved from Impidimp. It is one of the Pokemon with the ability to Gigantamax

Name: Grizzly Mastodon
Summary: A cousins to the elephant, the Grizzly Mastodon roams the subarctic and arctic lands in large herds. Their great strength and endurance makes so Giants often try to capture and tame them in order to use them as mounts.

Name: Grym
Summary: Grym is a massive golem forged from adamantine that serves as the primary defender of Grymforge, a dwarven citadel constructed from the ruins of a Sharite temple in the Underdark. Smaller than most adamantine golems, Grym is of unique make to combine his might with the terrain effects of the forge itself, making it still a notable opponent. Grym is referred to with awe and some amount of horror in texts describing him, making it clear that if the great Grymforge is sought out to create its famous adamantine constructions, one must first deal with its great guardian.

Name: Hamadh the Unseen
Summary: Hamadh the Unseen is the leader of The Hidden, a group of "invisibles" that survived the destruction of the Drow city of Maerimydra at the hands of Kurgoth Hellspawn. The group, under Hamadh's leadership, organized the downfall of Irae T'sarran and her temporary regime of power over the city and surrounding areas. However, what became of them afterwards is a mystery.

Name: Hatterene
Summary: Hatenna is a small Pokémon with peculiar behavior. They are known for being very shy and quiet, often preferring locations without people or strong sources of emotion. This aversion is strong enough that they will flee in most circumstances just to attempt to avoid interaction. Such behavior is caused by a feeling of exhaustion when sensing these strong emotions and as such, they will only warm up to those with a calm disposition.

Name: Haxorus
Summary: Haxorus is a Dragon-type Pokémon native to the Unova region. Also known as the Axe Jaw Pokemon, its sturdy tusks are destructive enough to cut through solid steel without chipping or dulling. Its also known to be relentless when defending its territory, but its sturdy armor and fierce fighting capabilities belie its kind spirit. It evolves from Fraxure who in turn evolves from Axew.

Name: Hellfire Engine
Summary: The Hellfire Engine is a warmachine created by devils to be used against mortals and demons, it's only used whenever utter destruction is needed as the Hellfire Engine in incappble of the subtly devils are known for. The Hellfire this creation uses was inveted by the Archdevil Mephisto, this flame is able to harm anyone in the multiverse; even those who are immune to fire.

Name: Hercules (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hercules (herk-you-lees), god of strength, appears as a large, muscular man with a tangled beard. He wears a lion’s skin and carries a massive club.

Name: Horned Devil
Summary: Cornugon, or Horned Devils, alongside many other names, are the elite defense troops of Baator, the Nine Hells. Their laziness causes them to be fearful of any being deemed stronger than them- though this is of little import due to their immense strength and astounding intelligence.

Name: Houndoom
Summary: Houndoom is a Pokémon introduced in Gen II. It evolves from Houndour at level 24.

Name: Hulking Hurler
Summary: A class for massive creatures, the Hulking Hurler is someone who specializes in throwing objects incredibly hard. Often found amongst Giants, there are some smaller creatures which employ these tactics and act as a sort of artillery.

Name: Hydra (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Hydras are monstrosities with crocodile-like bodies and serpentine heads, ranging in number from five to twelve. Each hydra is descended from the primordial hydras, created when the dragon goddess Tiamat slew a fellow dragon deity, spreading her blood across the multiverse, each blood drop spawning a fearsome hydra. Hydras are famed for their unending hunger, for their sickening gluttony that often leads each head to turn on each other, devouring itself alive. Many warriors would hunt down and kill a Hydra in order to prove their strength.

Name: Hydreigon
Summary: Hydreigon is a dual-type Dark/Dragon pseudo-legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation V, based on the mythological hydra. It evolves from Zweilous at level 64, who evolves from Deino at level 50. Its most notable trait is its three heads, hence the "drei" in its name, which is German for 3.

Name: Imix
Summary: Imix is the Elemental Prince of Fire, and the evil protector of the element, and is older than the world itself. As with his element, he is passionate and ill-tempered, quickly engaging in battles. Imix's activities in the world are largely confined to Oerth and his work with the Temple of Elemental Evil, where he left his aspect to defend it.

Name: Incineroar
Summary: Incineroar (Japanese: ガオガエン, Gaogaen) is a dual-type Fire/Dark Pokémon.

Name: Inevitable
Summary: Inevitables are the judges of the gods, extensions of cosmic law. Many are forged in the extraplanar city of Sigil, and are tasked with upholding specific contracts written up in the halls of the city. Originally these creatures were made by Primus, and even the most wily and secretive of traders will enter into contracts with them- nothing is more straightforward and true than the ideals that forge the Inevitable's will. Inevitables care not for intent or purpose- only for the words written in their contracts. Lethal force is used to ensure such words are stood by.

Name: Infernape
Summary: Infernape (Japanese: ゴウカザル, Goukazaru) is a dual-type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.

Name: Inteleon
Summary: Inteleon is a Water type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. Inteleon is a highly skilled sniper and hunter, prone to using traps to keep enemies from its territory.

Name: Iron Man (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: J.A.R.V.I.S.: Sir, there are still terabytes of calculations needed before an actual flight is adju- Tony: J.A.R.V.I.S., sometimes you gotta run before you can walk.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 16
Summary: This new armor was built by Tony Stark after returning from a Counter-Earth created by Franklin Richards during the Heroes Return storyline. The armor would later be re-donned and reused in Iron Man Legacy Vol 1.

Name: Iron Man Armor Model 19
Summary: Stark was skeptical about creating more Iron Man armors after the previous model had become sentient. At Askew, he began experimenting with new ideas, eventually completing a new design. Tony would later abandon the armor after Ultron attempted to use S.K.I.N. as a weapon of mass destruction, before constructing Model 20.

Name: Jallarzi Sallavarian
Summary: Jallarzi Sallavarian is an archmage of Greyhawk, and the youngest member of the Circle of Eight, an organization run by Mordenkainen to maintain his philosophy of the Balance, and ensure good and evil endure in equal parts. Though she is the least learned of the Circle's members, she has proven herself capable time and time again.

Name: Jarlaxle Baenre
Summary: Who is this maestro, this puppet master, pulling the strings of so many marionettes? Who is this maestro, turning the wheels of Faerûn, playing the music of fate to the ears of all who would listen?

Name: Jellicent
Summary: Jellicent is a dual-type Ghost/Water Pokémon. They are a large jellyfish-like Pokémon consisting mostly of water whose appearance varies based on gender. Groups of them are known to gather during full moons in order to capture prey. Where these groups go, ships that pass by them are known to disappear and it is often believed that Jellicent are responsible for these disappearances. These sunken ships are often turned into their lairs afterward.

Name: Jhorganni
Summary: Jhorganni is one of the leading clerics in Irae T'sarran's army of Kiaransalee followers. Previously, she was a devout follower of Lolth[1], but after failing one of the trials set before her by Lolth she was transformed into a Drider for her insolence. She ultimately betrayed her goddess for this punishment, and turned to Kiaransalee, seeing it as an opportunity to simultaneously redeem herself and to damage her goddess' plans.

Name: Jigglypuff
Summary: Tier: 8-C | At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Kamen Rider Kabuto (A.R. World)
Summary: Similar to his main universe counterpart, Sohji was chosen to wield the power of Kamen Rider Kabuto and face the Worm threat that has plagued Japan. However, while fighting a Phylloxera Worm, his Zector was left damaged and malfunctioning, thus leaving him in a state of eternal Clock Up. Despite his newfound predicament, he continued protecting his city from Worms. However, the Phylloxera Worm he fought had taken over his identity and deemed him a rogue agent of Zect.

Name: Kamen Rider Kuuga
Key: '''Yusuke Godai''' | '''Growing Form''' | '''Regular Forms''' | '''Rising Forms''' | '''Amazing Mighty Form''' | '''Ultimate Form'''
Summary: I don't want to see people crying anymore. I want everyone to smile! So have a good look... at my... transformation!

Name: Kamen Rider OOO
Key: '''Eiji Hino''' | '''The Revival of Greeed, the Birth of OOO, and the Scramble of Medals (Episodes 1-16)''' | '''The Man of One Hundred Million, the Other Ankh, and the Purple Medals (Episodes 17-38)''' | '''The Bond of Allies, the End of the World, and the Greed Towards Tomorrow (Episodes 39-48)''' | '''Post-Series''' | '''Heisei Generations FINAL''' | '''OOO 10th: Core Medal of Resurrection'''
Summary: Eiji Hino (火野 映司, Hino Eiji?) is the main protagonist of Kamen Rider OOO. He is a 21-year-old homeless traveller who was the son of a politician. When traveling to Africa, he befriended a little girl named Ruu and attempted to use his fortune to help her struggling village. Unfortunately, this would drag Eiji into the civil war that this village was involved in. During the situation, he failed to save Ruu from being tragically killed. Eiji was then held for ransom which his parents ended up paying for, as well as using the situation as a means to gain support for their public platform.

Name: Kas the Bloody Handed
Summary: Kas the Bloody-Handed was a powerful warrior who famously never suffered a wound in battle. Because of this, he was courted by the lich Vecna to join and lead his armies into battle- a task Kas accepted for the glory promised in return. Over the years, Kas led countless successful campaigns for his lord, eventually becoming the second-in-command of Vecna's entire empire in return for his service. As a reward for his services, Vecna forged for Kas a sword of immense power with a shard of the lich himself within it- known simply as the Sword of Kas, it was made from the black metal of the stars, and spoke to Kas of power greater than he currently possessed.

Name: Kingdom of Blackmoor
Summary: An ancient nation that predates the modern world of Mystara. Possessing hyper-advanced technology, Blackmoor was able to construct weapons of enormous destruction and objects of incredible power. Prideful and arrogant, eventually they destroyed themselves when a nuclear reactor went critical and destroyed the majority of their civilization. The survivors of Blackmoor would colonize another planet, but like before their arrogance resulted in their destruction.

Name: Kingdra
Summary: Kingdra (Japanese: キングドラ, Kingdra) is a dual-type Water/Dragon Pokémon. It evolves from Seadra when traded holding a Dragon Scale. It is the final form of Horsea.

Name: Kingler
Summary: Kingler is a crab based Pokémon introduced in Gen I. It evolves from Krabby starting at level 28. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Kommo-o
Summary: Kommo-o (Japanese: ジャラランガ, Jararanga) is a dual Dragon/Fighting-type Pokémon. It evolves from Hakamo-o and is the final form of Jangmo-o. Having completed its harsh training, Kommo-o returns to its birthplace to protect Jangmo-o. However, it only watches over them from a distance. Because it does not wish to fight weak foes, it clangs its scales together when it senses someone approaching. This ringing sound alerts others of its presence. The power of this Pokémon’s uppercut is enough to send foes flying. Simply raising its arms can generate enough force to change its surroundings. According to legend, Kommo-o's glittering scales are meant to drive away a great darkness. The reason it seeks strong opponents is also said to be a quest for power to defeat the darkness.

Name: Kraken (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Krakens are an ancient, feared, and ferocious race of monsters that have existed since the beginning of time, where they served as warriors to the gods. After the war of the gods ended, they went to the depths of the ocean where they wished to never be bound by beings ever again and bring terror and ferocity on their own end. Whenever a Kraken attacks, nothing can stop it, warships and galleons vanish, ocean trade and communication is destroyed, and entire villages, towns, and cities are destroyed as a side effect if they desire to go onto land to nest. Some are even virtually gods that are worshiped and have cults and minions on land and sea, a Kraken pleased with its worshipers will becalm the sea and bring with it a plentiful amount of fish to the faithful. However, the devious mind of a Kraken is ancient and destructive, ultimately always bent to the devastation of all things.

Name: Krookodile
Summary: Krookodile is a dual Ground/Dark type Pokémon based on a crocodile from the fifth generation of Pokémon. It evolves from Krokorok at level 40. It is the final form of Sandile.

Name: Krull
Summary: Krull was a tortle death cleric of Tiamat. The death-priest conducted numerous experiments in Arkhan's Tower in Avernus in an attempt to control the Hand of Vecna wielded by Arkhan. He was interested in obtaining artifacts and creatures that might help with his experiments, such as an orb of dragonkind or a unicorn. Krull had his entire shell carved with runes of prayers to Tiamat in Draconic.

Name: Kuo-Toa
Summary: Kuo-Toa are a species of fish-human hybrids that once dominated the surface world, ruling the islands and seas alike. However, they were driven away from their homes, deep into the Underdark, the evil world beneath the world.

Name: Kurgoth Hellspawn
Summary: Kurgoth Hellspawn is a fiendish half-fire giant who has led a burning crusade across the Underdark, pillaging and toppling cities with ease. His greatest accomplishment was his demolition of the Drow city of Maerimydra with the assistance of the city's archmage. However, Maerimydra's head priestess, an albino drow named Irae T'sarran, quickly consolidated all forces to the castle of the city, leading to an extensively drawn out siege with Kurgoth and his army of demons and freed slaves on one side, and Irae and her army of drow cultists and risen undead on the other.

Name: Lillipup
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Lizardfolk
Summary: Lizardfolk are reptilian humanoids native to the world of Toril that tend to dwell in semi-aquatic environments (such as swamplands and coastlines). An exceedingly practical folk, they do not desire riches or knowledge that don't have use in normal day-to-day survival activities. Their people are hardy, and can adapt to most environments- so despite being dominated culturally by the likes of humans, dwarves, and elves, they rarely hold complaint for the lands leftover for their dominions.

Name: Lord Soth
Summary: ...But I bow in the presence of a master.''

Name: Lurantis
Summary: Lurantis is a Grass-type Pokémon originating from the Alola region. It is the evolved form of Fomantis - the sickle grass pokemon.

Name: Luxray
Summary: Luxray is the Gleam Eyes Pokémon, based on a lynx. It is an electric type Pokémon that evolves from Luxio at level 30, and is the final form of Shinx. Aside from being a fan favorite, it is known for being able to see through things.

Name: Lycanroc
Summary: Lycanroc is a Rock-type Pokémon introduced in Generation VII. It evolves from Rockruff starting at level 25. The form it takes upon evolving depends on the moment of the day Rockruff is leveled up. During the day, it would evolve in Midday Form, and during the night, into Midnight Form. Sometimes in a rare natural phenomenon when the sun gives off green light around sunset or sunrise, Rockruff would evolve into Dusk form.

Name: Machamp
Summary: Machamp is a Fighting-type Pokémon. It is the final evolutionary stage of Machop, evolving from Machoke when traded. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Madam Eva
Summary: Madam Eva is an ancient witch and fortune teller, currently residing with the Vistani of Barovia. In truth, she is the half-sister of Strahd von Zarovich, though would not dare to reveal this to the count. Hundreds of years ago, she appeared in his court, serving as a simple maid- after Sergei's murder, she retreated to where she resides now, with the Vistani. She has been touched by Mother Night herself, gifted with carelessness. With these gifts she is one of the few capable of leaving Barovia, using her gifts to search for a successor to Strahd, so he may finally escape Barovia.

Name: Magcargo
Summary: Magcargo is a limbless, snail-like Pokémon consisting almost entirely of bright red magma. Its oval eyes are large and yellow with small pupils, and extend upward from its head. It has a bulbous snout and a wide mouth, with two drops of magma dangling from each side of its upper jaw. Magcargo's back is protected by a gray, spherical shell composed of hardened, but brittle magma, forming irregular lumps and plates. A streak of fire leaks from the side of its shell. Magcargo's lower body is amorphous and covered in bubbles of magma.

Name: Magnemite
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Maliskra
Summary: Maliskra is a half-medusa, half-fire elemental attendant to the avatar of Imix in the Temple of Elemental Evil. As the attendant to Imix, she is among the most powerful member of his cult at the time, even superior to the current leader, Vanifer.

Name: Mamoswine
Summary: Mamoswine, the Twin Tusk Pokemon, is a Ground/Ice Type Pokemon introduced in Gen IV. It is based on the woolly mammoth and is an evolution of the Gen II Pokemon Piloswine after leveling up while knowing Ancient Power.

Name: Manectric
Summary: Manectric (ライボルト Livolt), the Discharge Pokémon is an Electric Type Pokémon introduced in the third generation of Pokémon.

Name: Marilith (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mariliths are generals and dictators of the Abyss, often leading the armies of other powerful demons or indeed, their own forces. Regardless of where they lie, a Marilith is sure to assume a position of power- if not in the military then the head of a particularly notable established organization. Often times they travel alongside Balors as their right-hand soldiers. They thrive on grand schemes and army-level tactics, though are also well versed in one on one confrontations. Unlike most other demons, a Marilith prefers to analyze the situation first- not out of fear, but out of patience and understanding, a rare and lethal trait among the forces of chaos.

Name: Marlos Urnrayle
Summary: Malos Urnrayle is a medusa of unusual power and current leader of the Cult of the Black Earth. A noble and intelligent creature, he was prideful and mocking of his foes. Before becoming the cult's leader he was a noble of Cormyr who wasted his family's fortune, spending the riches on exotic and depraved celebrations.

Name: Marowak
Summary: Marowak is the Bone Keeper Pokémon. It's a pure Ground-type. As a Cubone, it was a timid Pokemon that constantly cried over the death of its mother, and wore her skull on its head to hide its face. Upon evolving into Marowak, the skull fuses with its own head, and it overcomes past its sadness to become a tough and savage Pokemon adept at using bones as weapons. It takes vengeance on its natural enemy in Mandibuzz, which preys on Cubone, and its implied that Mandibuzz are responsible for the death of the mother.

Name: Meepo
Summary: Meepo the Dragon-Keeper was once the lowliest of kobolds, weak even for their lowly kind. As such, he was assigned by his then-master, Yusdrayl, to tend to the dragon their tribe had captured, who went by the name of Calcryx; this essentially meant Meepo was assigned to clean the dragon's feces. However, when the dragon was captured by the goblins who also lived in the same dungeon space (dubbed the Sunless Citadel), Meepo's reputation amongst his kin plummeted even lower, and he was destitute, until a party of adventurers arrived and assisted Meepo's tribe in re-capturing the dragon. This state of affairs lasted only briefly before the adventurers ultimately slew the dragon, killing all of Meepo's tribe as a consequence: only Meepo escaped.

Name: Meganium
Summary: Meganium is the grass type starter of Johto and the final evolution of Chikorita. It evolves from Chikorita starting at level 16, and evolves into Meganium at level 32.

Name: Meowscarada
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Meowth
Summary: Meowth is a small, feline Pokémon with cream-colored fur that turns brown at the tips of its hind paws and tail. Its ovoid head features four prominent whiskers, wide eyes with slit pupils, two pointed teeth in the upper jaw, and a gold koban coin embedded in its forehead. Its ears are black with brown interiors and are flanked with an additional pair of long whiskers. Meowth is a quadruped with the ability to walk on its hind legs; while the games always depict Meowth on two legs, the anime states that Meowth normally walks on all fours. It can freely manipulate its claws, retracting them when it wants to move silently. The tip of its tail curls tightly. Meowth is attracted to round and shiny objects and has the unique ability to produce coins using Pay Day. Being nocturnal, it is known to wander about city streets at night and pick up anything that sparkles, including loose change. Upon finding a sparkling object, its eyes will glitter and the coin on its forehead will shine brightly. It shares this intrigue with Murkrow, with whom it often fights with for objects and prey. Meowth is a playful but fickle Pokémon with the capacity for human-like intelligence. At least one member of the species teaching itself how to speak. Meowth tends to live in urban areas. It is also one of few pokemon capable of Gigantamaxing.

Name: Metagross
Summary: Metagross is a Dual Steel/Psychic Type and the Iron Leg Pokémon. A rare and powerful species native to the Hoenn region, it is formed when two Metangs, which are created when two Beldums merge, combine into a single Pokémon. Its incredible intelligence and great power make it a formidable opponent, being most famously utilized by the Hoenn League Champion, Steven Stone.

Name: Mind Flayer (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mind Flayers are horrific, eldritch creatures associated with the dark depths of the D&D settings. They are renowned for being horrendously evil and for their mental capacities. Mind Flayers thrive by devouring the minds of other creatures, generally only interacting with other species at all to eat them or to enslave their kind.

Name: Misdreavus
Summary: Misdreavus is a Ghost-type Pokémon from Johto. They are known to be mischievous and love to scare people and Pokémon alike. As they feed off fear, they don't particularly fancy those who are hard to scare. The orbs they wears around their neck are implied to contain their prey's fear, as they emit shrieks.

Name: Misty
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Gym Battle)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 1:Rematch)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 2)''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Gen 5)'''
Summary: Misty (Japanese: カスミ Kasumi) is a Gym Leader of Cerulean City's Gym, known officially as the Cerulean Gym. She gives the Cascade Badge to Trainers who defeat her in battle. She specializes in Water-type Pokémon.

Name: Modron
Summary: Quote? You desire a quote? The One and the Prime does not give 'quotes'.

Name: Muk
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Mummy (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Mummies are a type of powerful undead, known primarily for their appearance of ceremonial wrappings around their entire bodies as well as for their horrifying ability to cause creatures to rot away with a single touch. They are typically found in deserts and are raised by the dark gods residing in the sandy dunes. They were normally found guarding tombs containing great wealth, and deterred all but the most resilient adventurers.

Name: Murkrow
Summary: Murkrow is an avian Pokémon with a peculiar appearance, their head feathers resembling a witch's hat and their tail resembling a witch's broom. This along with their thieving habits and methods of getting away from chases by losing their enemies in mountainous regions caused them to be loathed. They are often seen as bringers of misfortune although this reputation is mostly said rather than shown.

Name: Nalfeshnee
Summary: Nalfeshnee are massive demons of rage and avarice, resembling a grotesque mixture of ape and boar. They stand at the forefront of the Abyss, guarding the entryways and passing judgement on all souls who happen to pass through to their afterlife. The ways of the Nalfeshnee are unknown, though most merely assume the Nalfeshnee picks at random whether a soul will be devoured, turned to a Dretch, or a Lemure. On extremely rare occasions the Nalfeshnee may hand-pick a particularly valuable soul and elevate it to a higher level of life immediately. Given the opportunity to fight, a Nalfeshnee is a brutal and unfair fighter, disabling enemies and then ripping them apart.

Name: Narek, the Thing in the Shaft
Summary: Narek was once a son of Kas the Bloody Handed and a talented sorcerer, one who gained the attention of Vecna himself. Eventually, the lich (who was not a god at the time) bestowed upon Narek some great tome of arcane power. Jealous of his son's achievements, and worried that he may outshine himself, Kas stuck Narek in a prison just outside of his library, forever acting as a guard. There he would attempt a spell that was beyond his abilities, transforming him into a horrendous monstrosity constantly seeking to devour those that tread above.[1]
ID: Narek, the Thing in the Shaft-DungeonsandDragons-Low 7-B

Name: Natu
Summary: Natu, the Tiny Bird Pokémon, is a Psychic/Flying type. It is young, so its wings have not yet fully developed, and has to hop around instead. Although it likes to stare at things, it is very timid and will flinch easily upon detecting movements. They pick food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding the spines and buds.

Name: Neronvain
Summary: Neronvain is the Green Wyrmspeaker in the Reformed Cult of the Dragon, and largely acts as a warlord in the Misty Forest, using his connections to the green dragons there to enact large raids. Once he was the prince of those lands, until his exile at the hand of his father- in retaliation, he allied with the dragon Chuth and decimated the kingdom, all the while gathering treasures for the Dragon Queen, Tiamat. He was slain sometime after his raiding by a band of adventurers.

Name: Nidoking
Summary: Nidoran♂ is a small, quadruped rodent-like Pokémon. It is pinkish purple with darker patches. It has large, spiny ears with teal insides, oversized front teeth, and red eyes. Its back is covered with three lines of large spines that can release potent poisons if threatened. The center line of spines is taller than the other two. The size of the long, pointed horn on its forehead is indicative of the strength of its venom. Nidoran♂ is an exclusively male Pokémon, Nidoran♀ being its female counterpart.

Name: Nidoqueen
Summary: Nidorina is a quadruped, light blue Pokémon with darker blue patches. It has red eyes, large, spiny ears, and has two pointed teeth protruding from its upper jaw. It possesses large poison spikes, which it retracts whenever it is with a group or while resting in its burrow. Its paws have three claws each, and it is able to stand on its hind legs. The hind legs are longer and thicker than its forelegs. It has a stubby tail. This is a female only species; the male counterpart is Nidorino.

Name: Nincada
Summary: Nincada is a Bug/Ground-type Pokémon that resembles an insectoid. It uses its antennae to sense its surroundings, and uses its claws to carve the roots of tree and absorb moisture and nutrients.

Name: Ninetales
Summary: Vulpix is a small, quadruped, fox-like Pokémon. It has red-brown pelt with a cream-colored underbelly. It has brown eyes, large, pointed ears with dark brown insides, and a triangular dark brown nose. Its paws are slightly darker than the rest of its pelt and have light brown paw pads. On top of its head are three curled locks of orange fur with bangs, and it has six orange tails with curled tips. However, Vulpix is born with only a single, white tail. The tails grow hot as it approaches evolution. Vulpix is capable of manipulating fire to such precision as to create floating wisps of flame. These wisps are sometimes mistaken for ghosts by humans, but Vulpix uses them to assist in catching prey. Inside its body is a flame that never goes out. When the temperature outside increases, it will expel flames from its mouths to prevent its body from overheating. Vulpix is known to feign injury to escape from opponents too powerful for it to defeat. Vulpix can be found most commonly in grassy plains.

Name: Noctowl
Summary: Noctowl is a Normal-/Flying-Type Pokémon based off an owl. This nocturnal Pokémon can see in pitch black darkness like it's midday, which enables it to unfailingly catch its prey in darkness, giving it the title "The Emperor of Dark Nights". This Pokémon is highly intelligent, and twists its head 180 degrees while thinking. It evolves from Hoothoot at level 20.

Name: Nycaloth
Summary: Nycaloths are powerful and intelligent greater yugoloths native to all of the Lower Planes, though mainly found in Gehenna. Their role in yugoloth society often takes up that of scouts and observers, traveling the Abyss and the Nine Hells, scouring for information on the tanar'ri and baatezu. In combat, nycaloths are elite airborne shock troops of the yugoloth legions and are feared by even greater devils and demons for their combat wit. Unlike other yugoloths, nycaloths are noted to be extremely loyal to their superiors, provided they are treated well. However, above all else the nycaloth is easily angered- it is said that they are prone to destroy entire companies of lesser yugoloths in fits of rage.

Name: Nystul
Summary: Nystul is a member of the Circle of Eight[1], hailing from the land of Tenh in the Flanaess. As a member of the Circle of Eight, his goal is to preserve the balance of the multiverse alongside his fellow members and their leader, Mordenkainen. Of the members of the Circle, Nystul is the most tactically-minded and subtle, often taking on false appearances magically to deceive his enemies and friends alike- in fact, it is said that he only shows his true form to his fellow Circle members. Some suspect this is because his true form- a tall, gangly human with a staggering height of over two meters- causes him some level of embarrassment.

Name: Obould Many-Arrows
Key: '''Orc Chief''' | '''King of the Citadel of Many-Arrows''' | '''Exarch of Gruumsh'''
Summary: Obould Many-Arrows is widely regarded as the most iconic orc in the Forgotten Realms, and a recurring opponent of Drizzt Do'Urden and Bruenor Battlehammer, among others. A cunning and intelligent creature even by human standards, Obould established himself as an Orcish power when he wiped out and took in several other orcish tribes, establishing a kingdom in the Spine of the World. Eventually, Obould signed a peace treaty (much to the dismay of his followers) with elf, human, and dwarf, cementing the existence of his kingdom as a major power in Faerun.

Name: Octillery
Summary: Remoraid is a Water Type Pokémon from Johto. It has the particular ability to shoot water with incredible accuracy.

Name: Ohio-class Submarine
Summary: The Ohio class of nuclear-powered submarines is the sole class of ballistic missile submarines (SSBN) currently in service with the United States Navy. Fourteen of the eighteen boats are SSBNs, which, along with U.S. Air Force strategic bombers and intercontinental ballistic missiles, constitute the nuclear-deterrent triad of the U.S. The remaining four have been converted from their initial roles as SSBNs to cruise missile submarines (SSGNs). The Ohio-class boats, each displacing 18,750 tons submerged, are the third largest submarines in the world, behind the 48,000-ton Typhoon class and 24,000-ton Borei class of the Russian Navy. The Ohio class replaced the Benjamin Franklin- and Lafayette-class SSBNs.

Name: Omastar
Summary: Omastar is an ancient Pokémon, formerly thriving through the Kanto seas, and the final evolution of Omanyte. While their shell made them extremely tough, it eventually lead to their extinction, as it made them too slow to move and feed.

Name: Otiluke
Summary: Otiluke was a member of the Circle of Eight, a powerful archmage society based in the city of Greyhawk that specialized in the maintenance of the "Balance"- a philosophy created by Mordenkainen, the leader of the group. Short, volatile, and proud, Otiluke was primarily chosen due to his political power in Greyhawk, as he held the seat of head of the mage college as well as oligarch of the city. In the group, he was known for his short temper and mocking tones, which led to a few rivalries with his supposed allies, most notably Rary the Traitor.

Name: Otto
Summary: Otto is a legendary mage hailing from Greyhawk, and originally a servant of Robilar and is most known for his odd appearance compared to his companions. Where the visage of a proud mage is often seen for his fellows, Otto is instead fat and wildly overdressed at all times, bearing a glistening smile along with clothes fit for the richest dining event. A cheerful and outgoing man, Otto is ready always to make merry with his peers. To signify this, he often somewhat alters spells to include music in their effects, ensuring that even in the cacophany of combat, his sound is heard.

Name: Pachirisu
Summary: Pachirisu is an Electric-type Pokémon originally released in Pokémon Diamond and Pearl.

Name: Palafin
Summary: Palafin is a Water-type Pokémon, introduced in Generation IX. It evolves from Finizen at Level 38 while the player is connected to a Union Circle Group.

Name: Palossand
Summary: Palossand is a Ground/Ghost type Pokémon from the Alola region. Originally a mound of sand built by a child, this mound came to life by unknown means and possessed anyone who put their hand through its "mouth". After possessing enough people it was able to transform its body from a mound of sand into a sand castle. Underneath Palossand are the bones of those it has consumed the vitality of.

Name: Parasect
Summary: Paras is an orange, insectoid creature resembling the nymph stage of a cicada. Its ovoid body is segmented, and it has three pairs of legs. The foremost pair of legs is the largest and has sharp claws at the tips. There are five specks on its forehead and three teeth on either side of its mouth. It has circular eyes with large pupils. Red-and-yellow mushrooms known as tochukaso grow on this Pokémon's back. The mushrooms can be removed at any time and grow from spores that are doused on this Pokémon's back at birth by the mushroom on its mother's back. Tochukaso are parasitic in nature, drawing their nutrients from the host Paras's body in order to grow and exerting some command over the Pokémon's actions. For example, Paras drains nutrients from tree roots due to commands from the mushrooms. The mushrooms are also popular among collectors and have medicinal uses, usually involving extended life.

Name: Patrina Velikovna
Summary: In life, Patrina Velkovna was sister to Kasimir Velikov, and love interest of Strahd von Zarovich, a fact for which her brother orchestrated her stoning. After her death, Rahadin was ordered to wipe out her people for their transgressions against Strahd's love- every other female of her kind was eradicated, and Kasimir's ears were sliced off.

Name: Pidgey
Summary: Pidgey is the first of the early grass bird final evolutions. It evolves starting at level 18 and evolves from Pidgeotto to Pidgeot at level 36.

Name: Pit Fiend
Summary: Pit Fiends are the highest tier of devils present in Baator, the Nine Hells, and act as generals of the armies of lesser baatezu around them, as well as the ultimate manipulators and agents of corruption of mortals. Of all sixteen ranks of baatezu, Pit Fiends sit at the top of the hierarchy.

Name: Plague Brush
Summary: Massive balls of vines, the Plague Brush are massive spheres of tumbleweed which roam around the plains and sometimes roll over to other dimensions.

Name: Planetar
Summary: Planetars are powerful warriors, the mighty legionnaires of angelic armies that serve as an extension of their gods. The presence of a planetar on a world is an earth-shattering event, creating rain for the downtrodden and drought for the forsaken, and an insect plague for heretics. The might of these angels is absolute.

Name: Poliwrath
Summary: Poliwhirl is a blue, bipedal Pokémon with a spherical body. It has bulbous eyes that protrude from the top of its head. A black and white swirl covers its belly, which is actually its organs showing through its thin skin. It appears to have white gloves on its hands and rounded, digit-less feet. When out of water, it sweats to keep its skin moist and healthy. This keeps it covered in an oily fluid that allows it to slip away from enemies. All of its skin feels this way except where its swirl is, which is instead very smooth. The swirl on its belly undulates slowly and staring at it induces drowsiness.

Name: Polteageist
Summary: Sinistea is the result of a lonely spirit possessing a cold, leftover cup of tea. The yellow swirl is a sign of its wellbeing, and disrupting the swirl can result in Sinistea growing dizzy. It can absorb a creature’s life-force after they drink it, but the opportunity rarely arises due to its horrendous taste.

Name: Popeye (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: An incredible fighter, Popeye is an amazing sailor who can even fight dragons once he eats spinach.

Name: Porygon
Summary: Porygon is a man-made Pokémon created utilizing the latest, most advanced technologies. It consists entirely of programming code and is capable of reverting itself entirely back to program data and entering cyberspace. This Pokémon is copy-protected so it cannot be duplicated by copying. Although people anticipate this Pokémon can fly into space, none has managed the feat yet.

Name: Primarina
Summary: Primarina (Japanese: アシレーヌ Ashirēnu) is a dual-type Water/Fairy Pokémon.

Name: Primeape
Summary: Mankey is a simian Pokémon, similar to a New World monkey. It is a bipedal and has a round body covered in whitish, shaggy fur. Its nose is similar to a pig’s snout, and it has narrow, red eyes and triangular ears with brown insides. Mankey's three-fingered hands, two-toed feet, and the tip of its curved, prehensile tail are brown. Along with Stufful, it is the smallest Fighting-type. Mankey specializes in physical fighting and is very aggressive and short-tempered. When angry, Mankey begins shaking and its breathing turns rough. Its rage peaks quickly, preventing its victim from being able to flee. It will rampage until it falls asleep, but its anger remains in its dreams. This causes it to wake up and become furious all over again. However, this constant release of stress grants it a long life. Mankey can be found in the mountains, where it lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason. If it loses sight of its colony or if it is left alone to rage, its loneliness causes it to become infuriated.

Name: Psyduck
Summary: Psyduck is constantly stunned by its headache and can´t think very clearly. It usually is quiet, trying to calm its headache. However, when its headache becomes too strong, it releases tension in the form of strong psychic powers. The use of these powers produces brain waves identical to those seen in sleepers, and is unable to recall these episodes.

Name: Purple Worm
Summary: A powerful beast, the Purple Worm is a massive worm which tunnels in the ground in constant search of food, the tunnels it leaves behind are often used by other underground races as living places. In combat a Purple Worm simply tries to sting, bite and swallow its prey until it's dead.

Name: Quagsire
Summary: Quagsire is a Water-/Ground- 2 Stage Pokémon introduced in Generation II. It is a laid back Pokémon with a carefree nature, coming off as a little bit dopey. It evolves from Wooper at level 20.

Name: Quaquaval
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Rage Drake
Summary: The Rage Drake is a a primitive creature that's more akin to a cruel animal than an actual dragon. They also lack any sort of special magical abilities and thus they rely on stealth and brute force.

Name: Rahadin
Summary: Rahadin is the dusk elf servant of Strahd, and his long-time immortal brother-in-arms. He was banished from the Dusk Elf kingdoms for refusing to bow down to the king. He is credited as Strahd's most powerful general and having slaughtered thousands of men in the name of his count.

Name: Rakshasa (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Rakshasa''' | '''Greater Rakshasa''' | '''Ak'chazar''' | '''Naztharune''' | '''Dread Knight''' | '''Lord of Dust''' | '''Zakya''' | '''Half-Dragon Rakshasa''' | '''Naityan Rakshasa''' | '''Overlord'''
Summary: Rakshasa are fiendish creatures born from the Lower Planes with the appearance of humanoid tigers of proud stature, distinguishable from similar creatures such as Weretigers by their hands, which can bend both backwards and forwards. Extravagant and conniving by nature, Rakshasa plague all the Planes with their manipulations, constantly enacting plots to achieve greater power. They serve countless masters- their own Rajahs, demon lords[1], yugoloths, night hags, and even the mightiest of devils. As manipulators and masterminds, the Rakshasa ply their trade from their luxuriously decorated palaces, subtly tipping the scales in planar and political conflicts as it suited their wants.

Name: Ralts
Summary: Ralts is a Psychic type Pokémon that is capable of sensing emotions. It's evolutions follow suit, with Kirlia being capable of both sensing emotions and casting illusions while its final evolution, Gardevoir, protects its trainer with all its might to the point that it will sacrifice itself for their sake. When using a dawn stone on a male Ralts, the Pokémon will evolve into Gallade, a Pokémon who will protect his trainer with his masterful swordsmanship.

Name: Rampardos
Summary: Rampardos is a fossil Pokémon introduced in Generation IV based off of family of dinosaurs known as Pachycephalosauridae. It is revived from a Skull Fossil and evolves from Cranidos at level 30.

Name: Raticate
Summary: Raticate is a Normal-type Pokémon introduced in the first generation. It evolves from Rattata, one of the first Pokémon a trainer can get, at level 20. It can gnaw through almost anything with its ever-growing fangs, and will bite a hand clean off if someone tries to touch its whiskers, which it uses to keep balance. It normally has a violent disposition and is an excellent swimmer due to its webbed feet. It has an Alolan form that is Dark/Normal.

Name: Red Dragon (Dungeons and Dragons)
Key: '''Wyrmling to Young''' | '''Juvenile to Mature Adult''' | '''Old to Ancient''' | '''Wyrms and Great Wyrms'''
Summary: And belching fire, and began to lunge down

Name: Regisaur
Summary: Nicknamed the ruler of dinosaurs, the Regisaur is a gigantic Tyrannous Rex, with elemental energy flowing through its veins. Its size is so great that it can swallow Giants whole with a single bite.

Name: Rescue (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Pepper Potts was the personal assistant of Tony Stark who eventually developed romantic feelings for him. After Tony became the superhero Iron Man, she helped him defeat the Iron Monger, a former business partner of his, and Aldrich Killian, a terrorist who claimed to be the Mandarin, concurrently becoming Tony's girlfriend and the new CEO of Stark Industries, but was forced to break up with him as he had to lead the Avengers on an offensive against HYDRA. Following the Avengers Civil War, the two rekindled their relationship, eventually getting married and having a daughter, Morgan, when Tony returned from his failed battle with the genocidal alien warlord Thanos on Titan, who ultimately used a completed Infinity Gauntlet to wipe out half of all life in the entire universe.

Name: Rhyhorn
Summary: Rhyhorn is a Rock/Ground-type Pokémon typically found in the Kanto region. It is known for its short temper, poor memory, and incredible hardiness.

Name: Rictavio
Summary: Rictavio, also known by his former name of Rudolph van Richten, is a legendary vampire hunter posing as a bard/circus ringleader in Barovia. He is also the former mentor of Ezmerelda d'Avenir. After having slain his son following his turning into a vampire spawn, and having witnessed his wife die to yet another vampire, Rictavio has spent his life hunting the undead ruthlessly. Now, as he nears the end of his life, he aims to slay the greatest vampire of all time- Strahd von Zarovich.

Name: Rillaboom
Summary: Rillaboom is a Grass type starter Pokémon from the Galar region. Rillaboom always carries its signature drum with it on its back, and pulls it out when engaged in battle. This bass drum is crafted from a tree stump, with several thick branch stumps protruding from it, which form both the legs of the bass drum as well as mid and high toms. Rillaboom also carries two drumsticks in its cuffs and takes them out to beat its drum.

Name: Roxanne (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Gym Pokémon''' | '''Rematch Teams''' | '''Strongest Hoenn Team''' | '''Pokémon World Tournament'''
Summary: Roxanne is the Rustboro City Gym Leader, and is the first Gym Leader that a novice Trainer in the Hoenn region must battle in order to challenge the Elite Four. Roxanne became a Gym Leader to apply what she learned in the Pokémon Trainer School in practice, and thus enjoys using what she’s learned in her studies in battle, and loves even more to see how other people have formed their own strategy. When Brendan challenged her for the Stone Badge, she wasted no time urging him to show her how he battles, and with which Pokémon.

Name: Salamence
Summary: Salamence is a pseudo-legendary Pokémon from the Hoenn region. It evolves from Bagon at level 30 and from Shelgon at level 50. It is said to have grown wings from a sudden mutation from it constantly believing it can.

Name: Salazzle
Summary: Salazzle is a dual-type Poison/Fire Pokémon. It evolves from a female Salandit starting at level 33.

Name: Samurott
Summary: Oshawott is a Water-type starter Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It is a small, sea otter-like creature that carries a sea shell around with it, which it uses in battle.

Name: Sanctuary II
Summary: The Sanctuary II was a massive warship commanded by Thanos. It was likely named after Thanos' previous base of operations, Sanctuary.

Name: Sandslash
Summary: Sandslash is a bipedal, ground dwelling pholidote Pokémon. Although Sandslash is usually bipedal, it can run on all fours. Most of its underside is light yellow with a white underbelly. It has a narrow muzzle, almond-shaped blue eyes, and a thick tail. Its back is mostly covered in sharp, brown quills formed from its tough, dry hide. It has two large claws on its paws and feet. These claws are its primary weapons and are used for slashing, but can also be used for burrowing. Its claws and spikes can both break off and are shed regularly, but grow back quickly. It can curl into a large ball, which allows it to roll to attack or escape, protect itself from heatstroke, and guard its belly. Sandslash is also adept at climbing trees and is prone to ambush its enemies from above. Sandslash can mostly be found in deserts.

Name: Seaking
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Serperior
Summary: Serperior (Japanese: ジャローダ, Jalorda) is a Grass-type Pokémon introduced in Generation V. It evolves from Servine starting at level 36. It is the final form of Snivy.

Name: Severin Silrajin
Summary: Severin Silrajin was the leader of the Cult of the Dragon during the Tyranny of Dragons crisis in the Forgotten Realms, and was considered a significant threat to the safety of the Sword Coast during his reign. During his time as head Wyrmspeaker, Severin reformed the cult's core belief systems, turning from the previous fascination with dracoliches to living, breathing dragons. To help with this goal, he sought to summon Tiamat from her prison in Avernus, as well as her temple. In doing so, he forged alliances with several noteworthy organizations- most notably the Red Wizards of Thay, a magical organization he sought to use for the ritual he devised to summon the Dragon Queen.

Name: Shuppet
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Siege Crab
Summary: Siege Crabs are biologically warped mundane crabs, modified by means of magic to be living war machines of devastating might. Over the decades of its creation, the siege crab is equipped with a coral circlet that allows it to be mind-controlled. They were first created by the Kuo-Toa, though their use has likely spread since then.

Name: Sir Godfrey Gwilym
Summary: Sir Godfrey Gwilym was one of the holy knights of the Order of the Silver Dragon who perished in the assault on Argynvost. The lover of Vladmir Horngaard, he simply rots away in anger, unable to die due to the undead curse that afflicts him. Eventually, a band of adventurers appears to give him hope for the honor of his order, and he sets out to assist them in taking down Strahd von Zarovich himself.

Name: Skeledirge
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Skeleton (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Skeletons are one of, if not the most common types of Undead in any D&D setting. Cheap, loyal, and easy to make, they often serve as the vast majority of a necromancer's army or are found wandering, mindless, across the world. Oftentimes skeletons were made of a variety of creatures, even non-humanoids such as dragons, giants, and beasts.

Name: Slaking
Summary: Slaking (Japanese: ケッキング, Kekking) is a Normal-type Pokémon introduced in Generation III.

Name: Slowpoke
Summary: Slowpoke is a water and psychic type Pokémon found mainly in Kanto. It is known to be a very slow and lazy Pokémon, spending most of its time laying near water sources and fishing. Slowbro is one of the evolution of Slowpoke. After having a Shellder bites onto its tail and injects a kind of venom, it evolved into Slowbro. It can Mega Evolve into Mega Slowbro. Slowking is the other evolution of Slowpoke. The Shellder biting onto its head caused it to suddenly become extremely intelligent, even more so than humans.

Name: Sneasel
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | High 7-A

Name: Soelma Nilaenish
Summary: Soelma Nilaenish is an ancient and scholarly elf woman who became a wizard and loremaster. After her guardian, an aunt, died, she was left alone from the young age of 196. Throughout her life she has studied much and seen all, leaving her reclusive but highly intelligent. She is considered extraordinary among scholars in her fields.

Name: Sofina
Summary: Sofina, or Lady Sofina during her time as Forge Fitzwilliam ally, is an human wizard and member of the Red Wizards of Thay. Being the main antagonist in the movie Dungeons & Dragons: Honor Among Thieves.

Name: Solom Ned'razak
Summary: Solom Ned'razak is an archmage of the Drow and the leader of the Inverted Tower, a small academic community located in Szith Mercane where he teaches his small band of students the ways of the arcane. He is a frugal sort, believing there is strength in doing without the comforts of life. His primary concerns in life is simply in the exploration of the arcane arts- to that end he is willing to lend whatever strength he must to the local powers in return for peace and quiet in his studies.

Name: Staraptor
Summary: Staraptor is a grayish-brown, avian Pokémon similar to a large bird of prey. It has small, red eyes and a thin, yellow beak with a black tip. There is a circular white patch on its forehead, which is smaller on the female. Larger white markings cover the front of its throat and chest, separated by a black ruff encircling the shoulders. A red-tipped, black crest extends over its head, nearly reaching the tip of its beak.

Name: Starmie
Summary: Starmie is a Water/Psychic type Pokémon introduced in the first generation, resembling a starfish that's doubled, and with red core in the center. Due to its weird design, strange habits, and mysterious nature, it was thought by some to be some sort of alien invader. It evolves from Staryu with a Water Stone. It is notable for being the only Pokémon to remain a competitive mainstay in all generations without being on the ban-list.

Name: Steelix
Summary: Steelix is the evolved form of Onix. It evolves after being traded while holding a Metal Coat.

Name: Stone Giant
Key: '''Regular''' | '''Elder''' | '''Dreamwalker''' | '''Cairwight''' | '''Stalker of Baphomet''' | '''Evil Earth''' | '''Runecarver''' | '''Earth Titan''' | '''Rockspeaker''' | '''Scion of Skoraeus'''
Summary: One of the main giant races, the Stone Giant is a mighty foe for anyone to face. They are hulking, gray-skinned humanoid-looking creatures that stand 18 feet tall. They can live up to 800 years, and while they're not the smartest of the Giant kin, they are usually far smarter than the likes of Hill Giants.

Name: Stone Golem (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: The Stone Golem is the strongest of the common golems, often also being the prettiest looking due to being often assigned to guard museums.

Name: Strahd von Zarovich
Summary: Count Strahd von Zarovich was once a powerful warrior before he felt the curse of middle age. To avoid this coming death and the onset of feebleness, Strahd made a blood pact with the "Dark Powers" in order to achieve Immortality- and in the process, sacrificed his brother to make good on the pact. This sacrifice had a second purpose- it allowed Strahd to pursue Tatyana, the bride of his brother whom he jealously coveted.

Name: Swampert
Summary: Tier: At most Low 7-B | 7-B | High 7-A | 6-C

Name: Swanna
Summary: nan

Name: Talonflame
Summary: Talonflame is an avian Pokémon that closely resembles a falcon. Its plumage is predominantly red-orange, with gray underparts and black tips on its long, pointed wings. Ovular orange spots dot its underside, and flame patterns mark the boundaries between colors on its body. Large yellow talons extend from the shaggy feathers on its legs. Talonflame has a pointed crest atop its head and a black and yellow mask-like pattern around its eyes. Its black beak is hooked with a yellow cere. It also has long black tail-feathers marked with three yellow "v"-shapes. The tail ends in two points and has another feather sticking out of the base on each side, giving the impression of the fletching on the end of an arrow.

Name: Tangrowth
Summary: nan

Name: Thalquam
Summary: Thalquam was a normal Mind Flayer, once, until her cadre duergar slaves rose up against her. She was enslaved for three years, performing the same wretched labor she had forced upon her slaves, until a group of adventurers came upon the situation. After slaying the duergar, the adventurers refused to kill the squalid remains of Thalquam, who joined them, offering her strength. This act of mercy drove Thalquam to completely alter her worldview, until she took a vow of non-violence to repent for her evil past.

Name: The Leviathan
Key: '''Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''Greater Aspect of the Leviathan''' | '''The Leviathan'''
Summary: Sharp tooth and merciless of fang,

Name: The Sword of Kas
Summary: Legends say Vecna's descrution destruction came at Kas's hand, but Vecna also wrought his rebellious lieutenant, leaving only his Kas's sword behind.

Name: The Undying Temple
Summary: Orb Wraiths are an extremely rare conglomeration of singular wraiths merged together to form one unified entity. In particular, these wraiths inhabit the negative energy orb of the Undying Temple, an extraplanar undead structure bound to the will of Irae T'sarran. The Orb Wraith is the living embodiment of the temple's will, and its death represents the death of the temple itself. It is one of the final threats to adventurers seeking to bring Irae low, and one of the greatest monstrosities currently inhabiting the Drow city of Maerimydra.

Name: Tinkaton
Summary: Tinkatink (Japanese: カヌチャン Kanuchan) is a dual-type Fairy/Steel Pokémon introduced in Generation IX.

Name: Toucannon
Summary: Toucannon is a Normal/Flying type Pokémon introduced in Generation VII.

Name: Toxapex
Summary: Toxapex is a Water and Poison-type Pokémon native to the Alola region. A cruel and relentless hunter, it leaves trails of Corsola bits in its wake as it crawls along the sea floor. It is infamous for its excruciatingly painful toxin whose effects last for three days and three nights. Even after the victim recovers, there will still be after-effects.

Name: Toxicroak
Summary: Toxicroak is a dark blue and teal, bipedal Pokémon resembling a poison dart frog. Its head bears a gently-upward curling spike which seems to be a part of the skull. Its eyes are bright yellow, sinister and intimidating, with a small snake-like pupil. Its mouth gives an appearance of a mouth-guard, with its red upper lip curling upward at the ends in a very intimidating manner. Underneath its chin is a bulbous red vocal sac, which is smaller on a female Toxicroak. It has three fingers and one large red claw on the back of each hand. These claws on the backs of their hands can channel poison. Its forearms have two black rings encircling them. Its legs are muscular and seem to be adapted for speedy attacks. It has three toes on its feet, with a red middle toe on each foot, and a sharp spike which juts out of its heels. Underneath the pelvic area are two white horizontal lines. Thick black lines run down the sides of its body and surrounding its limbs, making them seem as if the limbs are detachable. The black lines go up into its face and surround the eyes before meeting in the middle of its snout, just above the upper lip.

Name: Trapinch
Summary: Trapinch is a Ground type Pokémon introduced in the third generation of Pokémon. Described as being patient, Trapinch is an immensely powerful Pokémon for its size, being able to crush boulders with a single crunch. Eventually, it can evolve into "Vibrava" and later into "Flygon", an extremely famous and powerful Pokémon that's often referred to as "The Elemental Spirit Of The Desert" or "The Desert Spirit"

Name: Treant (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Living tree; the "'Treant"' serves as the forest's guardian. They are generally peaceful but will attack any evil creature or those who carelessly use fire. Treants come in many varieties, with some having creatures like Rot Grub on their bodies to combat pests.

Name: Trident D5
Summary: The UGM-133 Trident II (Trident D5) is a submarine-launched ballistic missile developed by the United States of America. Deployed aboard Ohio-class and and Vanguard-class ballistic missile submarines of the US and Royal Navy, respectively, the Trident Missile carries anywhere from 8 to 12 nuclear-tipped Multiple Independently Targetable re-entry Vehicles (MIRVs).

Name: Trident SLBM
Summary: The Trident submarine-launched ballistic missile (SLBM) is built by Lockheed Martin Space Systems in Sunnyvale, California.

Name: Troll (Dungeons and Dragons)
Summary: Trolls are giants outside of the Ordining, largely due to their predatorial and uncivilized ways of life. In fact, they are not believed to be direct relatives of giants at all, and are only classified as such due to their large stature and ability to mate with true giants. They could be found almost anywhere, with multitudes of sub-species forming as a result of their extremely varied environment choices. Some could be found in the boiling hot jungle, while others function perfectly fine in the bone-chilling arctic wastelands, while yet others could survive in active volcanoes.

Name: Trumpet Archon
Summary: Trumpet Archons are the messengers and mighty servants of the Tome and Throne Archons, and are the main form of archons sent to the Prime Material Planes, as guides to the living. They are revered for their mastery over life, and for their bravery in facing eternal destruction should they die.

Name: Tunguska Event
Summary: The Tunguska event was a large explosion that occurred in Russia, near the Stony Tunguska River. It flattened an estimated 80 million trees over an area of 2, 150 square kilometers, causing a shockwave that has been estimated to be a 5.0 on the Richter scale. As it occurred in the sparsely populated Siberia, no casualties have ever been reported.

Name: Typhlosion
Summary: Typhlosion is the final form of the fire starter Pokémon from Johto. It seems to be based off of the honey badger. It evolves from Cyndaquil starting at level 16, and then again from Quilava at level 36.

Name: Tyranitar
Summary: s Pokédex entry from "Pokemon Diamond and Pearl"

Name: Tyrantrum
Summary: Tyrantrum is a Rock/Dragon-type fossil Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It is notorious as the most powerful of all known fossil Pokémon.

Name: Ulmo Lightbringer
Summary: Ulmo Lightbringer is a Halfling rogue-turned-monk, and a righteous crusader of Heironeous. After converting to worship of the god during a stint of jailtime, Ulmo was pardoned and allowed to take part in a holy crusade at the behest of a paladin. He remained relatively unfaithful, and felt doubt towards his god, until he channeled his god directly after one of his comrades was slain- through focus and faith alike, Ulmo managed to resurrect his fallen comrade, a practically unheard of feat outside of clerics and other divine servants. From that day forward, Ulmo was a stalwart of his god, and became known as an Exalted Hero.

Name: Ultroloth
Summary: Ultroloths are the final evolutionary point of yugoloth society- they are the faceless manipulators, connivers, and masterminds behind every single one of the yugoloths' billions of plots and schemes.
