Summary: Beefcake (マルゴリ, Marugori) was a regular human until he drank the Biceps Brachii King steroid provided by his older brother, Oldface, which turned him into a mutated giant.

Name: Blackarachnia (Transformers Animated)
Summary: She was once an Autobot with the name of Elita-1, but after an incident on a strange planet, she was mutated into a half-Cybertronian and half-spider being. She defected to the Decepticons' side with the hope of finding a cure.

Name: Blackout (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Blitzwing (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Blitzwing is a Decepticon with multiple personalities (A hammy and hotheaded one, a cold and icy strategist and an insane random one), despite having this problem, he is one of the deadliest Decepticons around and one of the most unpredictable.

Name: Bulkhead (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Raised on a backwater energon farm, Bulkhead joined the Autobot academy to achieve the lofty goal of becoming a lowly space bridge technician rather than a warrior. He also has an unfortunate tendency to break stuff by accident due to his sheer strength and natural clumsiness

Name: Bumblebee (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Bumblebee is one of the main characters in Transformers Animated and one of the Autobots. He is very hyperactive, cracks jokes at any time, but when the opportunity arises, he is one cunning fighter.

Name: Cirno
Summary: Cirno (チルノ) is an ice fairy who first appeared on the second stage of Embodiment of Scarlet Devil. As a fairy, she is exceptionally strong for her kind, matching the power of some weak youkai. However, compared to most of Gensokyo's residents, she's quite weak. Her personality is childish and she is sometimes considered stupid.

Name: Danjuro Tobita (Gentle Criminal)
Summary: Danjuro Tobita (飛田 弾柔郎 Tobita Danjūrō), better known as Gentle Criminal (ジェントル・クリミナル Jentoru Kuriminaru), is a small-time villain who has his assistant La Brava film his numerous petty crimes in order to raise awareness of the flaws in hero society. Once an aspiring hero-in-training with failing grades, his life turned upside down when he used his Quirk to try and save someone in the middle of a hero operation, inadvertently causing the person serious injury and his expulsion from school as well as being disowned by his parents.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Doman Shirino
Summary: Doman Shirino (巳厘野 道満 Shirino Douman) is an Onmyoji who is the current head of the Shirino clan. He is also the friend and rival of Seimei Ketsuno.

Name: Eternity Larva
Summary: Eternity Larva is a fairy who represents butterflies and the general metamorphosis of insects. Her power seems greatly enhanced by an unknown source in Hidden Star in Four Seasons.

Name: Findorr Calius
Summary: Findorr Calius (フィンドール・キャリアス, Findōru Kyariasu) is the 24th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Fishbone D
Summary: Fishbone D was the first Hollow introduced in the series, was eventually killed and cleansed by Ichigo Kurosaki after he initially gained his powers from Rukia Kuchiki.

Name: Ganju Shiba
Summary: Ganju Shiba (志波 岩鷲, Shiba Ganju) is a resident of Rukongai in Soul Society. He is a member of the former noble Shiba Clan, and the younger brother of Kaien and Kūkaku Shiba.

Name: Giant Toad
Summary: The Giant Toad is the guardian of the pond named after itself. It is usually calm and gentle, even protecting the pond.

Name: Gintoki Sakata
Key: '''Beginning of the series''' | '''Yoshiwara in Flames Arc and onwards''' | '''Diviner Arc to End of the Series'''
Summary: Sakata Gintoki (坂田 銀時, Sakata Gintoki) is the founder and president of the Yorozuya Gin-Chan, as well as a highly skilled samurai, having fought in the Joui War in the past. During the war, he became known as the White Demon (白悪魔, Shiroyasha) due to his powerful swordplay and demonic white appearance. Now, he is in an era where the samurai are no longer needed. To add to his troubles, oppressive aliens have moved in to invade. Gintoki lives with Kagura and Shinpachi, taking on odd jobs to make the world a better place... and to pay their rent.

Name: Glavenus
Summary: Glavenus are Brute Wyverns first introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Grand Fisher
Summary: Grand Fisher (グランドフィッシャー, Gurando Fisshā) is a Hollow that had evaded Shinigami for 54 years and is responsible for the death of Ichigo Kurosaki's mother, Masaki Kurosaki. He later transformed into an imperfect Arrancar following his defeat at the hands of Ichigo, but was killed by Isshin Kurosaki.

Name: Grimlock (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Grimlock is a Tyrannosaurus rex in charge of a small, three-mech group of dinosaur transformers known as the Dinobots. Born from a fusion of Earth and Cybertronian technology, with some AllSpark intervention thrown in, he's a force to be reckoned with. A little short on brains and a lot short on temper, Grimlock's answer to a problem is usually the simplest: squash it, slash it, bite it, burn it, or eat it.

Name: Hajime Obi
Summary: Hajime Obi (尾美一, Obi Hajime) is the former head coach of the Koudoukan.

Name: Hina Kagiyama
Summary: Hina Kagiyama (鍵山 雛, Kagiyama Hina) is a misfortune goddess that resides in the Great Youkai Forest, at the base of Youkai Mountain. It is her job to amass misfortune and scare off any humans that get too close.

Name: Homer Simpson
Summary: Homer Jay Simpson is the main protagonist of the animated sitcom series, The Simpsons, and one of the most recognizable cartoon characters of all time. He lives in the town of Springfield with his wife and three children and usually works as a nuclear power plant safety inspector, although over the years he has taken on many other jobs, such as being a food critic and a bodyguard. Generally, Homer takes a lazy and sometimes ignorant view on the world around him but has also shown genuine care and love for his family and friends. Homer Simpson was created by Matt Groening all the way back in 1987, with the character still going strong today.

Name: Housen
Summary: Housen (鳳仙) was the ruler of Yoshiwara, considered the most powerful Yato in the universe, obtaining the title of "King of the Night", did not solely come from him being the ruler of Yoshiwara, the land of eternal night, but also from being known as "King of the Yato".

Name: Ice King (Fortnite)
Summary: The Ice King is a character from the game Fortnite. The ruler of Polar Peak and the wielder of the legendary Infinity Blade, he wreaked havoc during Fortnite's seventh season by freezing the entire island over in minutes and summoning a legion of Ice Fiends across the map. The Ice King was formerly unlockable during Season 7 by getting to Tier 100 on the Battle Pass but has since been unavailable.

Name: Ichigo Kurosaki (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Substitute Soul Reaper''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Post-Visored Training''' | '''Final Grimmjow Fight''' | '''Full Hollowfication''' | '''Post-Resurrection''' | '''Post-Dangai Training'''
Summary: Ichigo Kurosaki (黒崎くろさき 一いち護ご, Kurosaki Ichigo?) is the son of Masaki and Isshin Kurosaki, a Quincy with the powers of a Soul Reaper. Years after the death of his mother, Ichigo uses his innate spiritual awareness to help local ghosts, and unlocks his potential as a Soul Reaper when Rukia Kuchiki comes along in pursuit of a Hollow.

Name: Ikkaku Madarame
Summary: Ikkaku Madarame (斑目 一角, Madarame Ikkaku) is the lieutenant and former 3rd Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Iku Nagae
Summary: Iku Nagae (永江 衣玖 Nagae Iku) is a messenger of the Dragon Palace, whose job is to observe the daily mood of the atmosphere.

Name: Ironhide (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Thousands of years ago, with Cybertron's energy reserves dwindling and the Transformer race splintering into warring factions, Ironhide was part of the Thetacons, violent militants who rejected the teachings of Sentinel Prime. He was part of the battle to seize the retrieved AllSpark from Sentinel's band, but when that group used the AllSpark to revitalise Cybertron (proving Sentinel was right all along), the Thetacons lay down their arms. Ironhide did not understand what the Cube was going to be used for if not for subjugation, and Optimus informed him it was to spread "freedom". In gratitude, Ironhide spoke to his commanders about building a temple to house the AllSpark.

Name: Isane Kotetsu
Summary: Isane Kotetsu (虎徹 勇音, Kotetsu Isane) was the lieutenant of the 4th Division under Captain Retsu Unohana, but after Unohana’s death during the Thousand-Year Blood War, she was promoted to the rank of Captain.

Name: Izuru Kira
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Izuru Kira (吉良 イヅル, Kira Izuru) is the lieutenant of the 3rd Division in the Gotei 13, formerly under Captain Gin Ichimaru and currently under Captain Rōjūrō Ōtoribashi.

Name: Jiraia
Summary: Danzo Tobita (鳶田 段蔵, Tobita Danzou), more commonly known as Jiraia the Spider (蜘蛛手の地雷亜), was born into a samurai clan and was a prodigy in the ninja arts. He used to be a member of the Oniwabanshuu, working under the Shogun, the founder and former leader of the Hyakka, former leader of the Red Spiders (Benigumoto) and Tsukuyo's master. He is the main antagonist of the Red Spider Arc.

Name: Jirocho Doromizu
Summary: Jirocho Doromizu (泥水 次郎長, Doromizu Jirochou) was the leader of the yakuza syndicate Dobunezumi Group, and one of the ruling 4 Devas of Kabuki District before he stepped down from his position in favor of his daughter, with whom he wanted to spend more time. He also carries old ties with Otose and Terada Tatsugorou, with the three of them being close friends in the past. He is the main antagonist of the Kabukicho Four Devas Arc.

Name: Kagura (Gintama)
Summary: Kagura (神楽) is a member of the Yorozuya and the main female protagonist of Gintama. She is a member of the Yato Tribe and the daughter of Umibouzu. Kamui, one of the main antagonists of the series, is also her older brother.

Name: Kamui (Gintama)
Summary: Kamui (神威) is the biological son of Umibouzu and the biological elder brother of Kagura. He becomes Housen's pupil. Due to his excellent fighting skills, he became the Captain of 7th Division of Harusame. He is known as the Lightning Spear in the division, the most powerful combat unit within the said group, and Overlord of Yoshiwara after Housen's death.

Name: Kogasa Tatara
Summary: Kogasa Tatara (多々良 小傘 Tatara Kogasa) is a subspecies of the Tsukumogami, a Karakasa obake. Originally coming from the Outside World, she ended up in Gensokyo where she became a Youkai that feeds on fear. Although with time passing, humans became less scared and she was left desperately trying to scare humans.

Name: Kon
Summary: Kon (コン, Kon) is an Underpod (部下強化型 (アンダーポッド), Andāpoddo; Japanese for "Lower Part-Strengthened Form") Mod-Soul created during Project Spearhead. His name is short for Kaizō Konpaku (改造 魂魄, Modified soul). Kon typically inhabits a stuffed lion, but occasionally doubles as a Soul Candy pill for Ichigo Kurosaki, taking charge of Ichigo's Human body.

Name: Kotarou Katsura
Summary: Kotarou Katsura (桂 小太郎, Katsura Kotarou) is the leader of the moderate Joui (攘夷) faction and a fugitive wanted by the authorities. He is also proficient in the art of escape from the Shinsengumi, penitentiaries and explosives. Long ago, he fought alongside Gintoki Sakata, Shinsuke Takasugi and Tatsuna Sakamoto against the Amantos in the Joui War. After the war, Katsura continued his activities fighting against the government.

Name: Kūkaku Shiba
Summary: Kukaku Shiba (志波しば 空鶴くうかく, Shiba Kūkaku?) is the head of the Shiba Clan. She is the older sister of Ganju Shiba, the younger sister of the late Kaien Shiba, as well as the niece of Isshin Kurosaki.[3] She is also a personal friend of Yoruichi Shihoin.

Name: Leanbow
Summary: Leanbow is Udonna's husband, Bowen's father (AKA Nick Russel), and the mentor of Daggeron and Calindor. He was known for his honor and valor which Calindor resented. As a Mystic, he can assume "Ancient Mystic Mode", resembling a red/purple fiery demon wielding a sword and shield. Twenty years prior to the series, Leanbow led the other Mystics in the Great Battle against the Supreme Master of the Underworld, and his Forces of Darkness led by Morticon in order to prevent them entering the human realm. The forces of good magic eventually forced the Forces of Darkness through the Gate of the Underworld, with Leanbow personally taking on Morticon at one point. In order to keep the Forces of Darkness from escaping the Underworld, he held back the Darkness hordes from the Gate while Niella the Gatekeeper sealed both it and Leanbow into the Underworld.

Name: Letty Whiterock
Summary: Letty Whiterock (レティ・ホワイトロック) is a seasonal youkai who's only seen during winter. She seems fittingly cold towards most of the humans she meets and is feared by humans as she is known to freeze them.

Name: Livio the Double Fang
Summary: Tier: 7-B

Name: Lugnut (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Lugnut is a Decepticon that appears in the series Transformers: Animated. His sheer physical strength makes him a force to be reckoned with for the Autobots on Earth, and a valuable asset to the Decepticons. Though he is brutish, he is very articulate when praising his glorious leader (which comprises almost all of what he says), and does what he can to serve his master's plans. This loyalty is so strong that even Megatron himself has been annoyed by it on occasion, but still appreciates it, using Lugnut's mentality to bind with the Omega Supreme clones.

Name: Mai Teireida
Summary: Mai Teireida is one of the two humans acting as Okina's subordinates and dancer, who have for job to draw the latent abilities in all things. They used to be regular human children, but due to Okina's magical power, their humanity is questionable.

Name: Malfestio
Summary: Malfestios are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Generations.

Name: Megatron (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: During the dark age of Cybertron after the fall of the Dynasty of Primes, Megatron became a follower of Sentinel Prime. Sentinel recovered the AllSpark, and planned to transport a sun to repower it and the rest of Cybertron. The Thetacons, who believed Sentinel to be a mad heretic, launched an attack on the AllSpark's facility. Megatron, Optimus, Shockwave, and Elita-One fended off the Thetacons when Sentinel and Wheeljack successfully transported a star to Cybertron. The Thetacons laid down their arms, but Megatron resented that so many of his comrades had died before Cybertron's new dawn, and it was only by Optimus's persuasion that Megatron found it within himself to forgive his enemies and shake the Thetacon Ironhide's hand.

Name: Megatron (Transformers Animated)
Summary: If you were to ask Megatron to describe himself in one word, he'd probably go with "heroic". He sees himself as a freedom fighter leading the Decepticons in a righteous struggle against "Autobot tyranny". The fact he's hoping to replace that with Decepticon tyranny isn't really a concern... to him, at least. A fanatic at spark, he revels in every Autobot who suffers at Decepticon hands and doesn't register beings like humans as anything more than "collateral damage."

Name: Melody (VShojo Mythos)
Summary: nan

Name: Metastacia
Summary: Metastacia is a special Hollow which specifically hunted and consumed Soul Reapers at night, was killed by Rukia Kuchiki after he fused himself with Kaien Shiba's body.

Name: Minamitsu Murasa
Summary: Minamitsu Murasa was a regular human from the distant past. However, after having died in the ocean, she became a ghost, namely, a Ship Phantom. She sank numbers of ships after her death until she met Byakuren, who took her under her wing and made her the captain of the Palanquin Ship. Years after, Murasa worked alongside several others youkai to bring Byakuren back from her sealing.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Mothership (Fortnite)
Summary: The Mothership is a massive flying saucer first seen in Fortnite: Battle Royale, Chapter 2 Season 7. The Motherships first appearance was as an enormous, imposing antagonist, which destroyed The Spire, and seemingly stole the Zero Point.

Name: Nakeem Grindina
Summary: Nakeem Grindina (ナキーム・グリンディーナ, Nakīmu Gurindīna) is Arrancar Catorce (14) in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Grimmjow Jaegerjaquez's five Fracción.

Name: Nanao Ise
Summary: Nanao Ise (伊勢 七緒, Ise Nanao) is the co-lieutenant of the First Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Shunsui Kyōraku, and Vice-President of the Shinigami Women's Association.

Name: Nargacuga
Summary: Nargacuga are Flying Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom Unite.

Name: Nemu Kurotsuchi
Summary: Nemu Kurotsuchi (涅くろつち ネム, Kurotsuchi Nemu?), formerly known as Nemuri Nanagō (眠ねむり七號ななごう?, Sleeping Number 7), was the lieutenant of the 12th Division of the Gotei 13 formally serving under her father Captain Mayuri Kurotsuchi.

Name: Nicholas D Wolfwood
Summary: Tier: 7-C | 7-B

Name: Nine (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Nine (ナイン Nain) was a villain and the primary antagonist of My Hero Academia: Heroes Rising. Having contracted an illness, Nine proved himself to be compatible with All For One's Quirk Factor, allowing him to obtain a weaker version of All For One. With it, he went to Nabu Island and tried to steal a Quirk that would have cured his illness, but he failed in his task.

Name: Nitori Kawashiro
Summary: Nitori Kawashiro (河城 にとり, Kawashiro Nitori) is a very shy Kappa who lives on the Youkai Mountain. She has the trademark ability of all kappa to manipulate water. Like many of her kind, she is intelligent and very capable with technical inventions as she is an engineer.

Name: Nobume Imai
Summary: Nobume Imai (今井信女, Imai Nobume) is a female member and a part of the assassination unit of the Mimawarigumi. She is also the vice captain of the Mimawarigumi, which gives her a relatively huge role in the Baragaki Arc, in which she appeared as the secondary main antagonist. She was a Naraku member during her childhood.

Name: Oboro
Summary: Oboro (朧) is the current leader of the Tensho School and the strongest assassin with in the Naraku Faction. He is one of the major antagonists of the series, starting from Ikkoku Keisei Arc. Also he once fought against Gintoki Sakata during in the Amanto War but wasn't able to kill him.

Name: Omega Supreme (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Omega Supreme was an Autobot that was mortally wounded. His body was heavily modified and turned into a giant transforming spaceship under the command of Optimus Prime.

Name: Optimus Prime (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Optimus Prime was the last surviving descendant of the Dynasty of Primes, orphaned and hidden away to protect him from the evil of The Fallen. Optimus grew up with no knowledge of who he was, and was eventually found by Sentinel Prime, who claimed to be descended from Primus himself. Joining Sentinel's tribe of "Autobots", Optimus worked with his teacher and other pupils Megatron and Elita-One to restore order to an energy-starved Cybertron by helping to locate the lost AllSpark, buried far beneath Cybertron's surface. Re-energized by a star harnessed by the science of Wheeljack, the AllSpark restored life and energy to Cybertron, unifying the planet once more, but the old and weary Sentinel Prime had no desire to lead this new, united populace. At last, he revealed to Optimus the secret of his heritage, and that he, as "Optimus Prime", ought to succeed him as leader.

Name: Optimus Prime (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the leader of a space bridge repair team that gets involved in the war when Megatron's troops target them. After a fight they crash land on Earth and wake up 50 years later, they decide to stay on the planet to protect it from the Decepticons.

Name: Orihime Inoue
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Orihime Inoue (井上いのうえ 織姫おりひめ, Inoue Orihime?) is a Human living in Karakura Town. She is a student at Karakura High School, where she is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki and her best friend, Tatsuki Arisawa. At some point during the Epilogue, she and Ichigo fell in love and eventually started a family.

Name: Ozpin
Summary: Professor Ozpin is the headmaster of Beacon Academy, first seen in Volume 1 inquiring Ruby Rose about where she learned how to fight, her future goals, and her desire to join his school. He is frequently seen with his cane despite having no visible motor impairment.

Name: Parsee Mizuhashi
Summary: Parsee Mizuhashi (水橋 パルスィ) is a hashihime - or bridge princess - that guards the bridge between the surface world and the Underworld. She is immensely jealous of everyone and everything, regardless of situation or logic.

Name: Peace Walker
Summary: Peace Walker, also known as Basilisk, was a walking nuclear-armed AI weapon developed by Huey Emmerich and Strangelove. In 1973, CIA Station Chief Hot Coldman commissioned the creation of Peace Walker in order to fulfill his vision of the "perfect nuclear deterrent".

Name: Project Zen
Summary: Over 30 years before the last remnants of humanity were all but extinguished, Project Zen was found by the Doctor and the Professor. Alone and extensively damaged, she used what strength she had left to call and reach out to them. She was adopted into their family and given the new name, Zentreya. The couple and the android they found that day formed humanity's last hope against the rogue artificial intelligence, Melware, three decades later.

Name: Prowl (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Prowl is the loner of the Autobot team lead by Optimus Prime. He was trained in the art of Cyber-Ninjutsu, making him the most skilled and one of the most valuable members of the team.

Name: Raiden (Metal Gear)
Key: '''Metal Gear Solid 2''' | '''Metal Gear Solid 4''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Updated Patriots Cyborg Body)''' | '''Metal Gear Rising (Custom Cyborg Body)'''
Summary: Vamp: You, too... Immortal? Raiden: No. I just don't fear death.

Name: Rangiku Matsumoto
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Rangiku Matsumoto (松本 乱菊, Matsumoto Rangiku) is the lieutenant of the 10th Division of the Gotei 13, serving under Captain Tōshirō Hitsugaya.

Name: Ratchet (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Ratchet was a civilian mechanic, and one of the best on all of Cybertron during the war. He became a Space Bridge technician because he could not stand the violence any longer, so he ends up with Optimus and his crew.

Name: Rathalos
Key: '''Base/HC/Azure/HC Azure/Destruction Wyvern Rathalos''' | '''Flame Rathalos''' | '''Silver/HC Silver Rathalos''' | '''Dreadking Rathalos''' | '''Zenith Rathalos''' | '''Zerureusu'''
Summary: The flagship monster of the entire Monster Hunter series and one of only two monsters to have appeared in every game in the series. Rathalos is a type of monster known as a Flying Wyvern, and it uses the fire element as its primary weapon.

Name: Renji Abarai
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Royal Guard Training'''
Summary: Renji Abarai (阿散あば井らい 恋れん次じ, Abarai Renji?) is the lieutenant of the 6th Division under Captain Byakuya Kuchiki. He formerly served as the 6th Seat of the 11th Division under Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Rin Kaenbyou
Summary: Rin Kaenbyou (火焔猫 燐), also known as Orin, is one of Satori Komeiji's pets. She carts the dead and dying into the Hell of Blazing Fires, where they are burnt as fuel.

Name: Rukia Kuchiki
Summary: Rukia Kuchiki (朽くち木き ルキア, Kuchiki Rukia?) is the current Captain of the 13th Division. She formerly served as lieutenant of the 13th Division under Captain Jūshirō Ukitake. Rukia is the adoptive younger sister of Byakuya Kuchiki and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Sari Sumdac
Summary: Sari is a technorganic and the daughter of Isaac Sumdac. She spent all her time within her father's laboratories, receiving her education from robots. Despite this, she doesn't seem like a shut-in. She's curious, excitable and adventurous.

Name: Satono Nishida
Summary: Satono Nishida is one of the two humans acting as Okina's subordinates and dancer, who have for job to draw the latent abilities in all things. They used to be regular human children, but due to Okina's magical power, their humanity is questionable.

Name: Satori Komeiji
Summary: Satori Komeiji (古明地 さとり) is the mistress of the Palace of the Earth Spirits, and the elder sister of Koishi Komeiji. Her ability to passively read the minds of others has caused her to be loathed and feared by humans and youkai, but she finds love in the animals that cannot normally be understood by others. She has many pets, including Utsuho Reiuji and Rin Kaenbyou.

Name: Seimei Ketsuno
Summary: Seimei Ketsuno (結野 晴明, Ketsuno Seimei) is the current head of the Ketsuno clan. He is a genius and is considered to be the strongest onmyoji in the clan's entire history. He is also the brother of Ketsuno Crystel.

Name: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna
Summary: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna (少名 針妙丸 Sukuna Shinmyoumaru) is an inchling living in the Shining Needle Castle. Her ancestor Issun-Boushi exterminated an oni, and obtained the oni's treasure, the "Miracle Mallet".

Name: Shinsuke Takasugi
Summary: Shinsuke Takasugi (高杉 晋助, Takasugi Shinsuke) is the leader of the Kiheitai, an extremist group which he resurrected from the Joui Wars. The Kiheitai is a Joui faction bent on causing world destruction. He's one of the main characters who were originally meant to be a main antagonist of the series due to his first appearance.

Name: Shockwave (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Eons after the Dynasty of Primes were vanquished, Cybertron fell into dark times. The AllSpark had been buried somewhere within Cybertron and been dismissed as a legend, and the planet itself lacked a star to orbit. As energy became more and more scarce, Cybertronians segregated into tribes. Shockwave chose to rally behind Sentinel Prime, who claimed to be descended from Primus himself. However, he faced opposition from the non-believer Thetacons, and Shockwave joined Megatron, Optimus, and several others in repelling their attacks. Ultimately, Sentinel Prime won the day, as he and Wheeljack were successful in locating the lost AllSpark and harnessing a new sun to orbit. This, however, did not please Shockwave. Now that the war was over, he was dissatisfied, and he no longer knew his purpose. This shocked his old friend, Megatron, and Shockwave explained that it was the journey he enjoyed, not the destination. Plus, well, that new sun was kind of bright.

Name: Shūhei Hisagi
Summary: Shūhei Hisagi (檜佐木ひさぎ 修しゅう兵へい, Hisagi Shūhei?) is the co-lieutenant of the 9th Division, formerly under Captain Kaname Tosen and currently under Captain Kensei Muguruma. He shares his position with Mashiro Kuna.

Name: Soga no Tojiko
Summary: Soga no Tojiko (蘇我 屠自古) is a vengeful spirit and one of Toyosatomimi no Miko's followers.

Name: Sougo Okita
Summary: Sougo Okita (沖田 総悟, Okita Sougo) is the former 1st Division Captain of the Shinsengumi and was a trainee at Kondou Isao's dojo in his youth. He is the younger brother of Okita Mitsuba who raised him after their parents passed away. He was one of the best swordsmen there even before joining the force where he is also recognized as one of the best swordsmen in the Shinsengumi.

Name: Starscream (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Many years before civil war broke out on Cybertron, Starscream was guarding a hatchling school trip when they were attacked by a subterranean monster. He was saved by Megatron and Shockwave, much to his irritation, but Megatron liked Starscream's "feisty" attitude, and saw a place for him in the future of Cybertron he hoped to shape. He later joined Megatron's Defense Force, and was very much at home, killing a malcontent that challenged the new order in spite of surrendering.

Name: Starscream (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Starscream is the second-in-command of the Decepticon army. He is also a backstabbing and short-tempered soldier. His mission is to eliminate Megatron so he can become the one in charge instead. After being killed by Megatron for his traitorous deeds, he was accidentally imbued with a shard of the Allspark when it was destroyed by Optimus Prime, allowing him to continuously revive after being slain.

Name: Tetsucabra
Summary: Tetsucabra is the first Amphibian fought in Monster Hunter 4. It is a large, frog-like monster.

Name: The Demi-Hollow
Summary: The Demi-Hollow was previously a Jibakurei before he was transformed into a Hollow after Don Kanoji accidentally destroyed his Chain of Fate, was eventually killed and cleansed by Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: The Last Prime (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: The Last Prime was the last surviving member of the Dynasty of Primes, who were the first Transformers created by the Allspark. He used the last remnants of his power and energy to seal away the Fallen and created a tomb to hide the Matrix, the key to the Star Harvester.

Name: The Menos Grande
Summary: The Menos Grande is seemingly a special type of Hollow, being compared similar to that of a Gillian Menos Grande, was eventually killed and erased by Ryūken Ishida

Name: Thermobaric missile (Resident Evil)
Summary: The thermobaric missile is used to blow up Raccoon City in an attempt to stop the infection from spreading.

Name: Toushirou Hijikata
Summary: Toushirou Hijikata (土方 十四郎, Hijikata Tōshirō) is currently the Vice-Commander of the Shinsengumi. He is commonly known as the Demonic Vice-Commander (鬼の副長, Oni no Fukucho), striking fear into his enemies and subordinates (with the exceptions of Isao Kondou and Sougo Okita).

Name: Tsukuyo
Summary: Tsukuyo (月詠), also known as the Death God Courtesan (死神太夫, shinigami tayuu), is a highly skilled ninja, specializing in the usage of kunai, having trained under the infamous assassin and then-Leader of Hyakka, Jiraia. She is the current leader of the Hyakka Yoshiwara's guardians (吉原自警団「百華」の頭), an all-female law enforcement squad formerly deployed by Housen.

Name: Uragaan
Summary: Uragaans are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Utsuro
Summary: Utsuro (虚) was an immortal being born with the ability to absorb a high amount of Altana which granted him his ageless immortality and regenerative capabilities.

Name: Vaccine Man
Summary: Vaccine Man (ワクチンマン, Wakuchin Man) is a Mysterious Being born due to the massive pollution released across the Earth by human beings, on top of the first monster we're introduced to in the series. According to him, he was created as an incarnation of nature's wrath, meant to wipe out humanity and thus effectively vaccinate the earth against future infections.

Name: Wreckage (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Cold, distant, quiet among Decepticons, Wreckage is the indiscriminate, hot-blooded, stone-cold destroyer, a bringer of destruction, and a counterpart to the hot-wired Brawl. Deliberate and methodical in his attacks, he enjoys getting up close and personal to his targets and watching his foes squirm in agony as his twin swords cut deep below their armor. Circuits popping and vital processors sizzling to uselessness are the music he longs to make, and none of the Decepticons can argue with his taste for making Autobots suffer.

Name: Yamame Kurodani
Summary: Yamame Kurodani (黒谷 ヤマメ) is a tsuchigumo - an earth spider, that lives in the entrance to the Underworld.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yian Garuga
Summary: Yian Garugas are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom.

Name: Yoshika Miyako
Summary: Yoshika Miyako is a Jiang Shi that has been brought back to life by her mistress, Seiga Kaku. She mainly wanders around the cemetery and guards it, with no particular reasons.

Name: Youkai Mountain
Summary: The Youkai Mountain is an important landmark in Gensokyo and home to several youkai, as per its name. The mountain covers several smaller locations such as the Giant Toad's Pond, the Moriya Shrine, the Genbu Ravine and the Untrodden Valley.

Name: Yumichika Ayasegawa
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Yumichika Ayasegawa (綾あや瀬せ川がわ 弓ゆみ親ちか, Ayasegawa Yumichika?) is the 3rd Seat officer and former 5th Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Alphonse Elric
Summary: Alphonse Elric (アルフォンス・エルリック, Arufonsu Erurikku) is the younger brother of Edward Elric, the Fullmetal Alchemist, Al is also a victim of the failed Human Transmutation experiment in which Ed lost his right arm and left leg. Having had his entire physical being taken away from him in the aftermath of the tragedy, Alphonse exists solely as a soul alchemically bound to a large suit of steel armor. Now, Al travels with his brother in search of the legendary Philosopher's Stone, an item with the power to restore their bodies to normal.

Name: Anne Boonchuy
Key: '''Season 1-2''' | '''Season 3''' | '''Incomplete Calamity Form''' | '''Complete Calamity Form''' | '''With Secret Spell'''
Summary: Anne Boonchuy was pressured by her friends into stealing a strange music box on her 13th birthday which mystically activated and sent them to Amphibia, a realm populated by talking amphibians, where Anne lands in the town of Wartwood. There she is taken in by the Plantar family, who help Anne on her journey to find a way back home.

Name: Armored Gorilla
Summary: Armored Gorilla (アーマードゴリラ, Āmādo Gorira) is an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution. Unlike his peers, Armored Gorilla's body is mostly robotic. He is the third-strongest specimen in the House of Evolution, and its only battle cyborg.

Name: Artifact Boss
Summary: The Artifact is an energy source created by the High goblin Urick to power the robot control center, which kept the robots active and fighting for the Goblins. Years later, the rogue Monk Xander was handed the Artifact by Lucas, allowing him to take control of the robots, and later power the Armageddon Machine. After being thwarted by Lucas and Knack, Xander unleashed the Artifact upon Knack before succumbing to his wounds. Said Artifact turned into the Artifact Boss and proceeded to face Knack.

Name: Asaemon Ikeda
Summary: Asaemon Ikeda (池田 朝右衛門, Ikeda Asaemon) is the 19th Ikeda Yaemon of the Ikeda Clan. Beforehand, she was adopted into the clan and given the title "17th Ikeda Yaemon" by her adoptive father, the 16th Ikeda Yaemon. After failing to execute him with Kimoarai, she left the Ikeda Clan as a traitor, with her adoptive brother being the successor of the title. Asaemon was then sold to the Hitotsubashi Faction by the 18th Ikeda Yaemon, but she survived and received the title again after his death.

Name: Atsuya Kusakabe
Summary: Listen up you curse users!! I don't know what the hell happened, but those two there fighting are special grade! Think of them as elephants tap dancing on ants. To be clear, we're the ants...

Name: Awakened Cockroach
Summary: Awakened Cockroach (覚醒ゴキブリ, Kakusei Gokiburi), is a Demon-level monster and member of the Monster Association.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: Bakuzan (One Punch Man)
Summary: Bakuzan is a sadistic martial artist who uses the "Dark Hell Assassination" technique and was thought to be a top contender in the Super Fight tournament until he was soundly defeated by Saitama. Frustrated, he devours multiple monster cells when given the opportunity, but the strain initially knocked him out. He later returns as an ape-like monster, attacking both Suiryu and Gouketsu.

Name: Beast King
Summary: Beast King (獣王 Jūō) was an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution. The Beast King is the leader of Dr. Genus' strike force and second-strongest specimen in the House of Evolution, exceeded only by Carnage Kabuto.

Name: Bentham (Mr. 2 Bon Clay)
Summary: Bentham, also known by his epithet "Bentham of the Wild" and his alias Mr. 2 Bon Clay, is a former officer agent of Baroque Works and an okama (a Japanese slang term for a transvestite). Strangely enough, he was the only higher up member that lacks a female partner of the same rank. Possibly due to believing he fits the role of both male and female, probably due to his powers and lifestyle as a self-proclaimed okama. He was thus assigned both a number and a holiday for his code name.

Name: Bling-Bling Boy
Summary: Eugene "Bling-Bling Boy" Hamilton is a recurring anti-hero in the series who has a one-sided crush on Susan Test.

Name: Blitzwing (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Blitzwing was a Decepticon Seeker sent to hunt down Bumblebee on Earth.

Name: Bug God
Summary: Bug God (蟲神, Mushigami) was a Demon-level Mysterious Being from the Monster Association.

Name: Bumblebee (2018 Reboot)
Summary: A scout under the command of Optimus Prime, B-127, later called Bumblebee by Charlie Watson, was part of the final battle for Cybertron — a battle that ended with the Autobot position overrun by the Decepticons and necessitating a full-scale Autobot evacuation of Cybertron. As part of this evacuation, Prime tasked him with a reconnaissance mission to the distant planet of Earth—its location hidden from the Decepticons — in the hopes that the scout could establish a base for the Autobots to regroup and strike back.

Name: Bushidrill
Summary: Bushidrill is the A-Class rank 4 hero and a Disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. Alongside his partners Iaian and Okamaitachi, Bushidrill is a skilled and powerful swordsman. Each is described as being worthy of S-Class, though they are forced to stay in their current positions due to Sweet Mask, who remains at Rank 1 of A-Class.

Name: Carlito Keyes
Summary: Tier: 10-A, 7-C with preparation

Name: Cheetor (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Cheetor is one of main characters in Beast Wars. Cheetor is full of youthful overconfidence. He's also the fastest Maximal on four legs which, combined with his impulsive nature, often gets him into more trouble than he can handle.

Name: Chitose Kizuki (Curious)
Summary: Chitose Kizuki (気月置歳 'Kidzuki Chitose), also known by the code name Curious (キュリオス Kyuriosu), was one of the minor antagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia, the executive director of Shoowaysha Publishing and a former member of the Meta Liberation Army.

Name: Choze
Summary: Choze is a martial arts competitor from One Punch Man. He comes from a clan of eugenicists determined to create a "superior race." Due to years of selective breeding with the best of genes, Choze was born with naturally superhuman abilities, which he uses to brutally torture others for his pleasure.

Name: Combustion Man
Summary: Combustion Man was a mysterious, silent assassin sent by Zuko to eliminate Aang.

Name: Crocodile (One Piece)
Summary: Crocodile is the second of the Seven Warlords of the Sea to be formally introduced and serves as the main antagonist of the Alabasta Saga. He is one of the longest running primary adversaries of the series as well as the first enemy to hand Luffy a complete and utter defeat, not once but twice. He secretly formed a criminal organization called Baroque Works, whose public aim was to take over the prosperous of Alabasta and create a utopia and led it as its president. To accomplish this, he worked to undermine Alabasta King's influence by defeating criminals before the royal army could, and by exploiting a drought in order to pit the kingdom against an army of rebels. His Devil Fruit, the Sand-Sand Fruit (Suna Suna no Mi), lets him turn into and control sand, a very useful ability in the desert kingdom.

Name: Daz Bonez (Mr. 1)
Summary: Daz Bonez is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works and was the highest ranked male Officer Agent and the strongest under Crocodile himself. His codename was Mr. 1 and his partner was Miss Doublefinger.

Name: Death Gatling
Summary: Death Gatling (デスガトリング, Desu Gatoringu) is an A-Class Rank 8 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Demonic Fan
Summary: Demonic Fan (扇風鬼, Senpūki) was a Mysterious Being of unknown origin that appears to be a sentient robotic fan.

Name: Dhruv Lakdawalla
Summary: Dhruv Lakdawalla is a jujutsu sorcerer from the past who was incarnated by Kenjaku for the Culling Game. This is the second incarnation for the veteran sorcerer who once conquered Japan on his own during the Civil War of Wa.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Dinobot (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Dinobot used to be a Predacon. When he and his Predacon peers crashed on what seemed to be the wrong planet alongside a Maximal exploration vessel, he rebelled against Megatron and joined the Maximal team.

Name: Do-S
Summary: "Monster Princess" Do-S (怪人姫弩S, Kaijin Hime Do S) is a Demon-level mysterious being and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Doman Shirino
Summary: Doman Shirino (巳厘野 道満 Shirino Douman) is an Onmyoji who is the current head of the Shirino clan. He is also the friend and rival of Seimei Ketsuno.

Name: Dr. Drakken
Summary: Drew Theodore P. Lipsky was an inventor, even from a young age, being able to develop fantastical yet strange devices by the time he hit the fourth grade, using them to get an edge in sports. After a humiliation in university involving him creating the first Bebe Robot prototypes, he dropped out of school and decided to pursue his true calling in life: crime. At some point, his skin turned blue for unknown reasons, and since then, he has become one of Kim Possible's most prominent enemies under the name Dr. Drakken.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Electric Catfish Man
Summary: Electric Catfish Man (電気ナマズ男, Denkinamazu Otoko) is an enlarged catfish with muscular human arms and legs and a Tiger level threat that first appeared alongside his partner Maiko Plasma during the Monster Raid, assigned by Gyoro-Gyoro to attack D-City.

Name: End City
Summary: The End Cities are the only inhabited places in the End, an alternate dimension to the Overworld. They are occupied by the Endermen, a mysterious alien kind who travels to the other dimensions at night and comes back when day breaks. They appear to worship a being of immense power; the Ender Dragon.

Name: End Crystal
Summary: End Crystals are a group of artifacts found in the End. They are mainly used to support the Ender Dragon.

Name: Ender Dragon (Minecraft)
Summary: The Ender Dragon is the final boss of Minecraft. It lives in The End, a separate dimension from the Overworld and the homeland of the Endermen.

Name: Enderman
Summary: The Enderman is a mob in Minecraft. It stands at 2.9 meters/blocks tall, one taller than The Player.

Name: Evil Eye (One Punch Man)
Summary: Evil Eye (ジャガン, Jagan) is a psychic monster from the Monster Association. Originally a weak esper, Gyoro Gyoro implanted the eyes of monsters slain by heroes on his body their remnant thoughts and hatred for heroes successfully empowering him.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: Eyesight
Summary: Eyesight is a Demon-level member of the Monster Association. She is a Gorgon-like creature, possessing the lower body of a serpent and several living snakes for her hair. Each of the snakes in her hair uses a different type of venom, with varying degrees of potency.

Name: Face Ripper
Summary: Face Ripper (カオハギ, Kaohagi) was a Demon-level monster and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Father (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Once, far before the events of the series, he was simply Homunculus, or Dwarf In The Flask, a small entity created by the chief alchemist of the country of Xerxes, from the blood of a nameless slave. Homunculus taught the slave, whom he'd named Van Hohenheim, about a mysterious science known as Alchemy, which he used to elevate his social standing until he became the servant of the king of Xerxes himself. Dying of old age, the king latched onto Homunculus' promises of immortality, and helped him set up a country-wide transmutation circle, being told that it would bring him eternal life by draining the souls of the entire country within him. However, Homunculus had set up the circle in such a way that the souls would flow into him and Hohenheim instead, killing the king and destroying Xerxes in one night.

Name: Fubuki (Blizzard of Hell)
Summary: Fubuki (フブキ?), also known by her hero alias Blizzard of Hell is the B-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. She is an Esper, the younger sister of Tatsumaki, and the leader of the Blizzard Group, a B-Class hero faction. She and her sister are known as the Psychic Sisters. Fubuki is one of the few people who are aware of Saitama's strength and is currently trying to recruit him into her group. She's also a self-declared member of the Saitama Group.

Name: Fumihiko Takaba
Summary: Fumihiko Takaba (髙たか羽ば 史彦ふみひこ, Takaba Fumihiko?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a comedian before awakening his cursed technique during the culling games and becoming one of the strongest competitors and his role was vital in defeating the Special Grade past sorcerer Kenjaku.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: G4
Summary: G4 is a self-proclaimed "Machine God" built by the same organization that Hammerhead stole his armor from. His goal was to force "The World's Strongest Man" King to fight him in order to test his abilities. Being far too terrified to face him however, King runs away, leaving the S-Class cyborg Genos to fight the Machine God instead.

Name: G5 (One-Punch Man)
Summary: G5, the self-proclaimed "machine god", is the immediate successor of the battle robot G4 and was created by the same mysterious group known simply as "The Organization". For unknown reasons, which he refuses to reveal to Gyoro Gyoro, The Organization sent G5 on their behalf as an ally of the Monster Association, defeating Narinki's Private Squad to prove his loyalty.

Name: Gale Wind
Summary: Gale Wind (疾風のウィンド, Hayate no uindo) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Hellfire Flame. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Gigakigan
Summary: Gigakigan was a gigantic rock monster. After spending over a thousand years collecting energy underneath a mountain of magma whilst bearing witness to his brethren being mined away by humans, he gained consciousness in order to take his revenge against humanity, first seen splitting a cliff-side apart over an unknown city before being reduced to rubble by Tatsumaki.

Name: Gigantomachia
Summary: Gigantomachia (ギガントマキア Gigantomakia) is a villain associated with the League of Villains. He is one of All For One's faithful servants and his former bodyguard, later serving his successor, Tomura Shigaraki. He is an incredibly powerful force, considered a "walking disaster" by heroes.

Name: Gintoki Sakata
Key: '''Beginning of the series''' | '''Yoshiwara in Flames Arc and onwards''' | '''Diviner Arc to End of the Series'''
Summary: Sakata Gintoki (坂田 銀時, Sakata Gintoki) is the founder and president of the Yorozuya Gin-Chan, as well as a highly skilled samurai, having fought in the Joui War in the past. During the war, he became known as the White Demon (白悪魔, Shiroyasha) due to his powerful swordplay and demonic white appearance. Now, he is in an era where the samurai are no longer needed. To add to his troubles, oppressive aliens have moved in to invade. Gintoki lives with Kagura and Shinpachi, taking on odd jobs to make the world a better place... and to pay their rent.

Name: Godzilla (Godzilla: Cataclysm)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was the first in a wave of radiation-born monsters, and made consequent appearances across the world, rampaging through numerous towns and various other places. Called to be the most powerful God out there, he destroyed the world in his battle with other kaiju.

Name: Green Dragon
Summary: Green Dragon is the sole protector of the Sword of Fate, he was the one to banish the Black Samurai and give his sword to Shaggy and Scooby Doo.

Name: Grizzly Nyah
Summary: Grizzly Nyah (グリズニャー, Gurizunyā) was a Mysterious Being that used to belong to a Hero Association staff.

Name: Groribas
Summary: Groribas was a member of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of alien pirates that traveled across the universe. Despite being one of Boros' top fighters, he was killed instantly by Saitama.

Name: Hajime Kashimo
Summary: Turn up the volume!! Because this is a funeral for the living!!

Name: Hellfire Flame
Summary: Hellfire Flame (業火のフレイム, Gōka no fureimu) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Gale Wind. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Himiko Toga
Summary: Himiko Toga (渡我被身子 Toga Himiko) is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was a member of the group's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, L.O.V. and the Meta Liberation Army merged to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and Himiko became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Hiromi Higuruma
Summary: Hiromi Higuruma (日ひ車ぐるま 寛ひろ見み, Higuruma Hiromi?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a defense attorney who often took on impossibly difficult cases in order to protect the wrongfully accused. Having since given up on the justice system completely, Hiromi participated in the Culling Game as one of the top players. He initially serves as an antagonist of the Culling Game Arc before battling Yuji Itadori and choosing to cooperate after he reminded him of his roots. He used his one hundred to add a rule to the Culling Game allowing the transfer of points between players as per Yuji's request and departed, planning to turn himself in for the murder of the judge and prosecutor at his last trial once the Culling Game's barriers were lifted.

Name: Hizashi Yamada (Present Mic)
Summary: Hizashi Yamada (山田ひざし Yamada Hizashi), also known as Present Mic (プレゼント・マイク Purezento Maiku), is a Pro Hero who teaches English at U.A. High School.

Name: Hollow (SHY)
Summary: Mai is a former ninja from a village that was cut off from the rest of society, only protecting it from the shadows. She is the sister of Ai and is a member of Amarariruku.

Name: Housen
Summary: Housen (鳳仙) was the ruler of Yoshiwara, considered the most powerful Yato in the universe, obtaining the title of "King of the Night", did not solely come from him being the ruler of Yoshiwara, the land of eternal night, but also from being known as "King of the Yato".

Name: Hundred-Eyes Octopus
Summary: Hundred-Eyes Octopus is a powerful monster briefly shown in the One Punch Man manga. The monster's nickname comes from it having many eyeballs. It is a Demon level threat who is a member of the Monster Association, a group of Mysterious Beings dedicated to taking down the heroes. The octopus wreaks havoc by devouring large buildings throughout I-City, which makes it grow more powerful. It was killed by the S-Class hero; Tatsumaki.

Name: Iaian
Summary: Iaian is the A-Class rank 2 hero of the Hero Association and a disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. He wears Western armor and specializes in Iaido. His left arm was blown off by an alien, and he has been a one-armed man ever since. He and the other two students of Atomic Samurai, Okamaitachi and Bushidrill, are all immensely powerful swordsmen. The three of them together can even defeat stronger Demon-level threats. Still, they cannot advance to S-Class because Sweet Mask, an eligibility examiner of S-Class, judges them to be unworthy. Nonetheless, Iaian is aware of the fact and still tries his best to become stronger.

Name: Inasa Yoarashi (Gale Force)
Summary: Inasa Yoarashi (夜嵐イナサ Yoarashi Inasa), also known as Gale Force (レップウ Reppū), is a first-year student at Shiketsu High School, U.A.'s rival. He was the top-recommended student for U.A. High before withdrawing his application. Gale Force is an energetic and enthusiastic young man who expresses himself with vigor. His signature trait is his undying love for passion above all else. He believes all heroes should have a fiery passion that motivates them to help others. He has a habit of approaching strangers to try and make friends with them. He also appears to enjoy passionate battles and desires to be a part of them. He disapproves of heroes who do not have hot spirits and believes people filled with hatred are unfit to be heroes and he refuses to recognize them as such. This is why he hates Endeavor and his son Shoto. Both of them had cold angry eyes when he met them and both of them blew him off despite his warm greetings.

Name: Iroh
Summary: Iroh is a supporting character in Avatar: The Last Airbender.

Name: Iron Golem (Minecraft)
Summary: Iron Golems are large, strong utility mobs in "Minecraft" that defend villagers. It has potentially the 3rd strongest Overworld attack in the game.

Name: Isamu (Child Emperor)
Summary: Child Emperor (童帝, Dōtei) is the S-Class Rank 5 hero for the Hero Association. So far, he is the youngest hero in the Hero Association. He has his own laboratory in Y-City.

Name: Ivor (Minecraft)
Summary: Ivor is an antagonist turned one of the deuteragonists in Minecraft: Story Mode. He is a former member of the Order of the Stone, and the only one who disagreed to keep up with their lie. He thus created the Wither Storm as an attempt to prove that the Order weren't true heroes.

Name: Jesse (Minecraft)
Summary: Jesse is the main protagonist of the spin-off game "Minecraft: Story Mode". They start out as a simple town resident, but they soon get themselves in the middle of a quest to save the world from the Wither Storm.

Name: Jin Bubaigawara (Twice)
Summary: Jin Bubaigawara (分倍河原仁 Bubaigawara Jin), also known as Twice (トゥワイス Tuwaisu), was a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of the organization's Vanguard Action Squad. Later on, his organization and the Meta Liberation Army merged to create the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants. Even Hawks, the number 2 Pro Hero, believed Twice to be the most dangerous of Shigaraki's lieutenants.

Name: Jiraia
Summary: Danzo Tobita (鳶田 段蔵, Tobita Danzou), more commonly known as Jiraia the Spider (蜘蛛手の地雷亜), was born into a samurai clan and was a prodigy in the ninja arts. He used to be a member of the Oniwabanshuu, working under the Shogun, the founder and former leader of the Hyakka, former leader of the Red Spiders (Benigumoto) and Tsukuyo's master. He is the main antagonist of the Red Spider Arc.

Name: Jirocho Doromizu
Summary: Jirocho Doromizu (泥水 次郎長, Doromizu Jirochou) was the leader of the yakuza syndicate Dobunezumi Group, and one of the ruling 4 Devas of Kabuki District before he stepped down from his position in favor of his daughter, with whom he wanted to spend more time. He also carries old ties with Otose and Terada Tatsugorou, with the three of them being close friends in the past. He is the main antagonist of the Kabukicho Four Devas Arc.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome. He's the only son of Hugh and Lila and brother of Susan and Mary (who had brown hair in the 2004 pilot). Because he has Susan and Mary by his side, he can live any kid's dream, only to find that some dreams aren't worth living. He is usually seen with his partner-in-crime and best friend Dukey, his genetically altered dog. He also gives Johnny Coupons to his sisters for helping him with his daily problems. When redeemed, he does their tests for free. Johnny and his sisters are often the cause of some problems in Porkbelly.

Name: Katsuya Serizawa
Summary: Katsuya Serizawa is a minor antagonist and later supporting character in Mob Psycho 100. He was a natural-born esper who couldn't properly control his powers, leading him to a life of isolation and depression, with emotional outbursts that would alienate him further. However, upon being recruited into claw by Touichirou Suzuki, Serizawa found a new purpose in his life in serving him, although this was an illusion of friendship he wouldn't realize until his confrontation with Mob.

Name: Kenjaku
Summary: Kenjaku (羂けん索じゃく, Kenjaku?) is one of the primary antagonists of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He is an ancient sorcerer who has goals against the Jujutsu High and Tengen, using curses to complete his plan.

Name: Kim Possible (Character)
Summary: Kimberly Ann "Kim" Possible is a high school student and freelance hero/vigilante. She is unusual in this in that she not only lacks a secret identity, but also remains on good terms with various law enforcement, government, and military agencies. For the most part, her classmates are aware of her work but do not comment on it unless it affects them directly. At school, she is cast as one of the "popular kids", head of her cheerleading squad at school, and a straight-A student, rather than as a misunderstood outsider/underdog as typical of the genre.

Name: King Andrias
Summary: King Andrias is the king of Amphibia and leader of Newtopia. He is initially introduced as a benevolent king who only wants to help Anne and her friends, but as events unfold he is revealed to actually be a major antagonist in the series, serves as a major opposing force against the main cast while also being a pawn in his master's plan.

Name: King Bumi
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C, likely 7-C

Name: Kinji Hakari
Summary: It all has to do with the fever. Both the deceiver and the deceived are in a fever to change their lives. People get high on the fever and make mistakes. And me? I love the fever! However, without it, people can't even fall in love. Do you know a more direct way of dealing with the fever? Life itself is a gamble. Lots of girls have dumped me 'cause they hate gambling, but they don't understand. Society tramples on guys who can't bet big and guys who don't know when to quit. Everyone gambles. What they hate is losing and going to ruin.

Name: Knack (Character)
Summary: Knack is the titular character in the game of the same name. He is a being made up of ancient relics that was brought to life by Doctor Vargas as a way to combat the Goblin threat.

Name: Kotarou Katsura
Summary: Kotarou Katsura (桂 小太郎, Katsura Kotarou) is the leader of the moderate Joui (攘夷) faction and a fugitive wanted by the authorities. He is also proficient in the art of escape from the Shinsengumi, penitentiaries and explosives. Long ago, he fought alongside Gintoki Sakata, Shinsuke Takasugi and Tatsuna Sakamoto against the Amantos in the Joui War. After the war, Katsura continued his activities fighting against the government.

Name: Kurourushi
Summary: Kurourushi (黒沐くろうる死し?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. It was a special grade cockroach cursed spirit released from Kenjaku's Cursed Spirit Manipulation in order to participate in the Culling Game as a player.

Name: Kyoka Jiro (Earphone Jack)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Kyoka Jiro (耳郎響香 Jirō Kyōka) is a student at U.A. High, training to become a Pro Hero. She is known as Earphone Jack (イヤホンジャック Iyahon Jakku).

Name: Kyoshi
Summary: Kyoshi was the Earth Kingdom born Avatar preceding Avatar Roku and immediately succeeding Avatar Kuruk of the Northern Water Tribe. She was both the largest and the longest living Avatar.

Name: Lord Boros
Summary: https://vsbattles.fandom.com/wiki/File:BorosIntroduction.ogg

Name: Lucas (Knack)
Summary: Lucas is the level-headed friend of Knack and long time lab assistant of Doctor Vargas.

Name: Mahoraga
Summary: Eight-Handled Sword Divergent Sila Divine General Mahoraga (八やつ握かの剣つるぎ異い戒かい神しん将しょう魔ま虚こ羅ら, Yatsuka-no-Tsurugi Ikaishinshō Makora?) is the most powerful shikigami of the Ten Shadows Technique. In order to summon this entity, an individual must stretch out both hands and recite the incantation "Furube Yurayura".

Name: Max (Lightning Max)
Summary: Max, also known by his hero alias Lightning Max, is the Rank 19 A-Class Hero for the Hero Association. He fought against Deep Sea King but was easily defeated. After recovering from his injuries, he began to train so that he can one day overcome the Sea King's strength.

Name: Mechamaru
Summary: The fact that a doll like you and not a human like me gets to live so carefree in the sun really pisses me off!

Name: Megatron (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Megatron is the leader of the Predacons and a descendant from the original G1 Megatron. He has a twisted sense of humor and is prone to monologues.

Name: Megumi Fushiguro
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event Arc''' | '''Shibuya Incident Arc'''
Summary: Megumi Fushiguro (伏ふし黒ぐろ 恵めぐみ, Fushiguro Megumi?) is the deuteragonist of the Jujutsu Kaisen series. Born into the Zenin clan, a prestigious family of jujutsu sorcerers, Megumi inherits the unique Ten Shadows Technique, which allows him to summon and control various shikigami using his cursed energy.

Name: Melzargard
Summary: Melzargard was one of the Dark Matter Thieves, a group of extraterrestrial pirates that traveled across space. He was one of Boros' strongest warriors tasked with protecting the ship, eliminating any intruders on sight. After the destruction of A-City, Melzalgald was engaged in battle by Iaian. However, the A-class hero was no match to the mighty alien and quickly lost his arm. Soon, Atomic Samurai, Bang, Metal Bat, and Pri-Pri-Prisoner arrived to fight the hostile alien. Following a lengthy and seemingly fruitless battle, Metal Bat discovered Melzargard's weakness (destroying the marbles on his body), allowing the heroes to eliminate the extraterrestrial being.

Name: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus
Summary: Metal Gear Sahelanthropus is a Metal Gear featured in Metal Gear Solid V: The Phantom Pain. Created by Huey Emmerich and funded by the Soviet Union, Sahelanthropus was in actuality a project overseen by XOF, the covert strike force and at-the-time usurper of the shadow government known as The Patriots. Encountered by Venom Snake several times in Afghanistan, he managed to best the machine multiple times, eventually capturing it after the death of Skull Face, the leader of XOF. Snake kept it at Mother Base for some time, until it was stolen by Eli with the help of the Third Child, who took it to Central Africa, where he, the remnants of XOF and Venom Snake with his Diamond Dogs private military company, fought to reclaim the weapon. Snake eventually won the day, but Sahelanthropus was destroyed in battle.

Name: Mezo Shoji (Tentacole)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Mezo Shoji (障子目蔵 Shōji Mezō), also known as Tentacole (テンタコル Tentakoru), is a student attending U.A. in order to become a Pro Hero. Despite his intimidating appearance, he is quite a friendly and gentle person who will work well with anyone. He is not the type to hold grudges and displays no ill will towards those who unwillingly harm him.

Name: Miguel Oduol
Summary: How many years do you think it took for my country's shamans to weave this one rope...!?

Name: Mirage (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Mirage likes to think that he's the life of the party, always eager for a chance to show off his unique skills; like his ability to generate lifelike holograms which he can use to disorient and outmaneuver foes, or his impressive shapeshifting ability that allows him to take multiple alternate modes at a time. He hates being cooped up and forced to hide out on Earth, because doing so means he has no one to get into trouble with. He's also quite the talker, always ready to rattle off a wisecrack or a reference to some Earth media he's seen since his time on the planet. This unfortunately has lead him to become a bit of an outcast among the other Autobots, who see him as reckless and aloof, compounded by his frequent disregard for Optimus Prime's orders.

Name: Mirio Togata (Lemillion)
Summary: Mirio Togata (通形ミリオ Tōgata Mirio), also known as Lemillion (ルミリオン Rumirion), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School.

Name: Momo Yaoyorozu (Creati)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Momo Yaoyorozu (八百万百 Yaoyorozu Momo) is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training under the name, "The Everything Hero: Creati" (万物ヒーロー クリエイティ Banbutsu Hīrō Kurieiti). She is a very intelligent and dedicated person who acts as a natural leader. She is generally very level-headed and calm even in dangerous situations.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Mosquito Girl
Summary: Mosquito Girl is a prototype artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution. As a hybrid between human and mosquito, she has control over large swarms of the insects, using them to collect blood as sustenance or repair any bodily damage.

Name: Mothership (Fortnite)
Summary: The Mothership is a massive flying saucer first seen in Fortnite: Battle Royale, Chapter 2 Season 7. The Motherships first appearance was as an enormous, imposing antagonist, which destroyed The Spire, and seemingly stole the Zero Point.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Narinki’s Private Squad
Summary: Narinki's Private Squad is a private rescue squad created by Narinki to free his son, Waganma, from the Monster Association.

Name: Nicholas D Wolfwood
Summary: Tier: 7-C | 7-B

Name: Nico Robin
Key: '''Alabasta Arc''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Thriller Bark Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Adventurer, archaeologist, ex-Dragon, and Ms. Exposition, Nico Robin is one of the darker and more enigmatic members of the Straw Hats.

Name: Ochako Uraraka (Uravity)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Ochako Uraraka (麗日お茶子 Uraraka Ochako), also known as Uravity (ウラビティ Urabiti), is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training assisting to the U.A. High School.

Name: Okamaitachi
Summary: Okamaitachi is the A-Class rank 3 hero and a Disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. Alongside her partners Iaian and Bushidrill, she is an immensely powerful and skilled swordswoman. Each is described as being worthy of S-Class, though they are forced to stay in their current positions due to Sweet Mask, who remains at Rank 1 of A-Class.

Name: Optimus Primal (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Optimus Primal had the burden of leadership unexpectedly thrust upon him when Unicron attacked his homeworld. He and a handful of Maximals successfully evacuated their doomed planet and used the Transwarp Key to flee across time and space, a journey that led them to ancient Earth.

Name: Optimus Primal (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Optimus Primal is the leader of the Maximals. He is their best fighter and one of the few of them that can fight evenly with Megatron.

Name: Optimus Prime (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the heroic leader of the Autobots. During the fall of Cybertron, Optimus would lead the remaining troops of the Autobot resistance off Cybertron, so that they may regroup and retake their planet from the Decepticon forces.

Name: Ozai
Summary: Ozai was the Fire Lord and absolute ruler of the Fire Nation during the final years of the Hundred Year War. He was the second son of Azulon and Ilah, the younger brother of Iroh, uncle of Lu Ten, husband to Ursa, the father of Prince Zuko and Princess Azula, and grandfather to Izumi. Ozai was a firebending master and, prior to the ending of the War, was believed to have been one of the most powerful firebenders in the world.

Name: Phoenix Man
Summary: Phoenix Man is a Demon level threat, who first appears accompanied by Elder Centipede as part of the Monster Association. Phoenix Man is more civilized than other monsters, expressing care for his allies. However, that doesn't stop his desire to dethrone Monster King Orochi and become the most powerful monster alive.

Name: Pride
Summary: Pride (プライド, Puraido) was the first Homunculus that Father created, and resembles his original form. He masquerades as Selim Bradley (セリム・ブラッドレイ, Serimu Buraddorei), the adoptive son of King Bradley, and is the final one of the seven Homunculi to be revealed.

Name: Pureblood
Summary: Pureblood is a vampire that comes from a ancient bloodline of vampires. He despises the other monsters around him, and claims to be the strongest natural monster on Earth. He is a very powerful monster, being a Demon-level threat, and works for the Monster Association under the monster king, Orochi, in order to wipe out the Hero Association.

Name: Puri-Puri-Prisoner
Summary: Puri-Puri-Prisoner is an S-Class hero, rank 16th dropped to 17th. He is an athletic and flamboyant homosexual man. He constantly checks out all the men he is attracted to and assaults them with no regard for their sexuality, which is why he is in prison despite being a hero. He repeatedly escapes from jail during his hero activities.

Name: Rafflesidon
Summary: Rafflesidon (ラフレシドン, Rafureshidon; Viz: Lafreshidon) was a Monster that appeared to assist Senior Centipede in fighting Metal Bat.

Name: Rampage (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Rampage used to be a Maximal which was experimented on to recreate Starscream's nearly indestructible spark. The experiment went horrible wrong, so much that it destroyed his mind, turning him into a sociopath.

Name: Ramza Beoulve
Summary: Ramza Beoulve, also known as Ramza Lugria, is the main protagonist in Final Fantasy Tactics. Third son of House Beoulve, son of Barbaneth Beoulve and a commoner woman of the Lugria family, Ramza is the younger half-brother of Dycedarg and Zalbaag, and the full older sibling of Alma.

Name: Rattrap (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Rattrap is a spy that works for the Maximals. He is a guy who prefers attacking from the back than face on.

Name: Ravager (Minecraft)
Summary: Ravagers are large hostile mobs that spawn in raids.

Name: Rhino Wrestler
Summary: Rhino Wrestler (サイレスラー, Sai Resurā) was a Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association who first appeared during the attack in S-City.

Name: Rikiya Yotsubashi (Re-Destro)
Summary: Rikiya Yotsubashi (四ツ橋力也 Yotsubashi Rikiya), also known as Re-Destro (リ・デストロ Ri-Desutoro), is the President and CEO of the Detnerat Company, a lifestyle support company, as well as the Grand Commander of the modern Meta Liberation Army, which he runs in secret. He is also the son of the infamous villain Destro, and is the main antagonist of the Meta Liberation Army Arc. His organization later merged with the League of Villains to create a union known as the Paranormal Liberation Front. He stepped down as Grand Commander to become one of the group's nine lieutenants.

Name: Ritsu Kageyama
Summary: Ritsu Kageyama is the younger brother of Mob and a major supporting character in the anime/manga series Mob Psycho 100. While his brother is socially inept and lacking in motivation and accomplishment, Ritsu is a star student, with perfect grades and a place on the Student Council of Salt Middle School, and is generally amiable to his older brother.
