However, his drive to be a good brother towards Mob was discovered to be a front to his genuine fear and jealousy of his brother's power only striving to be a good sibling to avoid confronting the form that he observed his brother take when knocked out.

Name: Roku
Summary: Roku was the Fire Nation-born Avatar immediately succeeding Avatar Kyoshi and preceding Avatar Aang. Roku's memory served as a guiding force for Aang throughout his quest to end the Hundred Year War.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Royal Ripper
Summary: Royal Ripper (キリサキング, Kirisa Kingu) is a monster affiliated with the Monster Association.

Name: Ryomen Sukuna
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Ryu Ishigori
Summary: In my first life, I was a moderate eater. I fought worthy opponents and met a good woman. So I don't particularly have any regrets. But I can't stand this vague thirst Okkotsu. And no one understands why I can't get no satisfaction. These cigarettes have a sweet aftertaste. My life never had dessert.

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Scourge (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Scourge is the cunning, ruthless, and treacherous leader of the Terrorcons and the most fearsome hunter in the universe.

Name: Seimei Ketsuno
Summary: Seimei Ketsuno (結野 晴明, Ketsuno Seimei) is the current head of the Ketsuno clan. He is a genius and is considered to be the strongest onmyoji in the clan's entire history. He is also the brother of Ketsuno Crystel.

Name: Senior Centipede
Summary: Senior Centipede (ムカデ先輩, Mukade Senpai; Viz: Centisenpai) was a Monster that appeared after Metal Bat defeated Junior Centipede and Venus Mantrap. He was killed by Metal Bat in the manga, and by Garou in the Webcomic.

Name: Shaggy Rogers (Cartoon)
Summary: Norville "Shaggy" Rogers is a member of Mystery Inc., and the owner and best friend of their team's mascot: Scooby Doo, a talking Great Dane.

Name: Shego
Summary: Shego is a villainess who works for Dr. Drakken as his sidekick. Since her main duty to Drakken entails stealing things on his request and protecting him from harm, she frequently engages Team Possible in battle. Though under contract with the scientist, she has occasionally worked with other villains as well, such as Motor Ed and Señor Senior, Junior.

Name: Shinji Nishiya (Kamui Woods)
Summary: Shinji Nishiya (西屋森児 Nishiya Shinji), also known by his hero name, Kamui Woods (シンリンカムイ Shinrin Kamui), is the No. 7 Pro Hero and member of The Lurkers.

Name: Showerhead
Summary: Showerhead was a Demon level threat and a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen attacking Garou alongside his teammates Super Mouse and Unihorn, before the three of them were incinerated by Overgrown Rover's energy blast.

Name: Shuichi Iguchi (Spinner)
Summary: Shuichi Iguchi (伊口秀一 Iguchi Shūichi), also known as Spinner (スピナー Supinā), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He is obsessed with the ideals of the Hero Killer: Stain, and is determined to revive Stain's vision of society through himself. His group later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Snek
Summary: Snek, also known by his hero alias, Snakebite Snek is the Rank 37 A-Class Hero, he is in charge of F-City.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic
Summary: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic (音速のソニック Onsoku no Sonikku) is a villain in the series, first appearing as a bodyguard hired by Mr. Monier. He grew up in a ninja village, honing his skills to near perfection. He views Saitama as his eternal rival, ever since the hero "defeated" him in a rather embarrassing manner.

Name: Spring Mustachio
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''Monster Raid Arc and Onwards'''
Summary: Spring Mustache (バネヒゲ, Banehige) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 28. He was partnered up with Golden Ball to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Stinger
Summary: Stinger (スティンガー, Sutingā) is the A-Class Rank 10 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Suguru Geto
Summary: An endless cycle of exorcism and consumption. Exorcise. Consume. It's a taste that nobody knows. The taste of a curse. Like ingesting a rag used to wipe up vomit. Exorcise. Consume. For whom? Ever since that day... It's been running through my head. What I saw was nothing out of the ordinary. A hideous evil known to everyone. Knowing that full well... I chose to protect them as a Jujutsu Sorcerer. Don't lose your way. Follow through with your duty as a Jujutsu Sorcerer... Monkeys...

Name: Suiryu (One Punch Man)
Summary: Suiryu (スイリュー, Suiryū) is a Martial Artist and user of the Void Fist. He is said to be a top contender in the Super Fight tournament. Initially, he is shown to be easygoing and laidback, only caring about the prize money for the tournament he was joining. His power and level of skill had also turned him into something akin to Saitama, who is always bored by the lack of challenge he receives from his opponents.

Name: Takako Uro
Summary: Silence! "Live for others"! "You don't need to be anybody special"! The only ones who say that are people who have already achieved something!

Name: Tanktop Master
Summary: Tanktop Master (タンクトップマスター, Tankutoppu Masutā) is the S-Class Rank 16 hero. He is the eldest and most powerful of the Tanktop brothers, as well as the most level-headed and wise. He plays a minor role in the Alien Invasion arc and a greater role in the Hero Hunt arc. Tanktop Master battles Garou to avenge Tanktop Vegetarian, and proves to be superior. However, upon seeing Garou's state, along with advice from Mumen Rider, he decides to spare the human monster. Unfortunately, once Garou had seen through Tanktop Master's attacks, he went back on the offense and defeated the hero. In the hospital, Tanktop Master tells Saitama that Garou's fighting style makes him especially deadly to heroes.

Name: Teru Momijiyama (Shy)
Key: '''Beginning of Series to Yuri Orphanage Arc''' | '''Tokyo Recapture arc'''
Summary: Teru Momijiyama (紅葉山テル, Momijiyama Teru), better known as Shy (シャイ Shai), is the main protagonist of the manga series SHY. Living in a world where every country has a hero to protect it. She is a middle school student and the successor to her older sister Mei Momijiyama, the previous Hero of Japan. After her passing, her Heart Shift Bracelets were given to her at her funeral. After which she chose to use the Bracelets to become Japan's new hero, and to live up to her sister's legacy. Even though she struggles with talking to crowds, or even just doing her job as a hero.

Name: Teruki Hanazawa
Summary: Teruki Hanazawa is a former antagonist and current ally of Mob. He used to be an arrogant and proud esper who believed he was the star protagonist of his life. This mainly stems from his belief that only he had the power of an esper to make his life easier. But his encounter with Mob did not just change his beliefs but also his hairstyle.

Name: The Devourer
Summary: The Devourer is a monster from Fortnite: Battle Royale, it has been a prominent part of the story during season 9 of the game, having been first spotted in Polar Peak, and has since broke out of the glacier and battled the Mecha Team Leader.

Name: The End (Minecraft)
Summary: The End is a dark, space-like dimension which the player travels to through the use of an Ender Portal. The dimension is filled with end stone islands surrounded by a pitch-black void, a void similar to that found beneath the Overworld as well as both above and below the Nether.

Name: The Final Guardian
Summary: The Final Guardian is a Guardian Knack faces towards the end of the game. It is a titanic creature made up of stone that protects the Giant Orb. It is capable of becoming one with the Giant Orb, making it one of the biggest characters in the first game.

Name: The Foundation (Fortnite)
Summary: The Foundation is the founder and leader of the Seven. He is an organic entity in a suit that has been keeping him alive in infinite realities and in the Nothing beyond them. He has a lot of knowledge about The Zero Point and The Cube. The Foundation assisted Agent Jones in fixing the Zero Point after it was nearly absorbed by Galactus, and after the initial invasion of the Last Reality, eventually makes his way back to flip the Athena Island to the other side.

Name: The Mecha
Summary: The Mecha is a large robot introduced in Season 9 of Fortnite: Battle Royale. Serving as a protagonist that would eventually contend with, and overcome The Devourer.

Name: The Player (Minecraft)
Summary: The Player is the protagonist of Minecraft. Known as either Steve or Alex depending on the player's choice, they are a lone miner in an endless blocky world, trying their best to survive.

Name: The Three Crows
Summary: The Three Crows were Gouketsu's disciples back before any of them had become monsterfied. After the monsterfication process took place they all transformed into three identical-looking monsterized crows, completely devoid of their individual personalities. The three first appeared alongside their master during the monster raid where they attacked the Super Fight tournament to recruit new members for the Monster Association. After incapacitating several martial artists, the three were soundly dispatched and killed by Suiryu, Lightning Max and Snek.

Name: Tonraq
Summary: Tonraq is a powerful waterbending master and chief of the Southern Water Tribe. Born as heir to the chief of the Water Tribes, he is the older brother of Unalaq. Growing up in the Northern Water Tribe, Tonraq served as the Northern military's general in his youth, though was banished and disinherited following the destruction of a sacred spiritual forest at his hands.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Toph Beifong
Summary: Toph Beifong is an earthbending master, one of the most powerful of her time, and the discoverer of metalbending. Blind since birth, Toph was constantly treated condescendingly because of her disability, particularly by her overprotective parents, Lao and Poppy Beifong. Upon discovering badgermoles, earthbending animals who were also blind, she learned how to use earthbending as an extension of her senses. This gave her the ability to "see" every vibration that passes through the ground. She became Avatar Aang's earthbending teacher.

Name: Tsuyu Asui (Froppy)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tsuyu Asui (蛙吹梅雨 Asui Tsuyu), also known as Froppy (フロッピー Furoppī), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. She's known for her stoic and unflappable attitude, being able to work well under pressure, contrasting heavily against her far more emotional classmates.

Name: Unihorn
Summary: Unihorn was a Demon level threat and a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen attacking Garou alongside his teammates Super Mouse and Showerhead, before being snapped to pieces by Overgrown Rover

Name: Uraume
Summary: nan

Name: Vacuuma
Summary: Vacuuma was a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen absorbing several weaker monsters into his trunk to gain their abilities, before being killed by Pri-Pri-Prisoner.

Name: Van Hohenheim
Summary: Van Hohenheim (ヴァン・ホーエンハイム, Ban Hōenhaimu) is the estranged father of Edward and Alphonse Elric. Previously, he had been known only as Slave No. 23. However, the Homunculus, grateful for the blood that brought him into the world and the unwavering friendship, bestowed upon the slave the gifts of a proper name, education, freedom, and ultimately, a body that never decays. Nevertheless, the freed slave, now known as Hohenheim, strongly condemned the gift of immortality that cost countless lives. Since then, Hohenheim has turned bitterly against Homunculus, sworn to end his agonizing immortality, and set free all the souls trapped within their bodies. Likewise, to prevent a similar tragedy from ever happening again.

Name: Warden (Minecraft)
Summary: The Warden is an extremely powerful hostile mob that is native to the Deep Dark biome and its ancient cities. It is thought that the Wardens patrol these cities to guard whatever treasures lie inside. Their most distinguishable feature is their blindness - they instead determine where their victims are through their heightened senses of sound and smell.

Name: Waspinator (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Waspinator is a Predacon and the "red-shirt" of the army; he works as a recon unit, checking out and spying on their enemies, the Maximals.

Name: Watchdog Man
Summary: Watchdog Man (番犬マン Banken-man) holds the 12th rank among the S-Class Heroes of the Hero Association. Despite his silly appearance, he is widely feared and respected worldwide. As the vigilant protector of Q-city, Watchdog Man actively hunts down monsters within his jurisdiction and appears to effortlessly handle any challenges that come his way. His formidable reputation deters almost everyone from challenging him. However, the self-proclaimed "hero hunter" Garou, though fatigued, dared to confront him but was swiftly overpowered and forced to retreat.

Name: Wither
Summary: The Wither is a floating, three-headed powerful boss mob, and is the second boss mob to be added to Minecraft after the Ender Dragon. It can be summoned by Steve via placing three Wither Skulls on top of Soul Sand in a T pattern.

Name: Yama (One Piece)
Summary: The Commander of Enel's Divine Soldiers who moves lightly despite his great size. Yama is fanatically loyal to Enel to the point he will even reprimand The Priests if he feels like they’re being disrespectful in his god’s presence. He also has no interest in the past. During his fight with Robin, he kept mercilessly destroying the ancient ruins, thus earning her wrath and spurring her to defeat him.

Name: Yawara Chatora (Tiger)
Summary: Yawara Chatora (茶ちゃ虎とら柔やわら Chatora Yawara), also known as Tiger (虎とら Tora), is a Pro Hero and member of the Wild, Wild Pussycats.

Name: Yorozu
Summary: Cut It!! Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut Me Open! Cut My Love Buried In This Flesh!! And See It With Your Own Eyes!

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die. I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Yuki Tsukumo
Summary: What kind of woman is your type?

Name: Yuta Okkotsu
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Zala (Miss Doublefinger)
Summary: Zala, better known by her alias Miss Doublefinger, was the second highest ranking female agent in the secret organization known as Baroque Works. As an officer agent, she was partnered with Mr. 1. Like her partner, she's calm and professional, although feels sorry for Nami's awkwardness with her new weapon. She has eaten the Toge Toge no Mi which gives her the ability to grow spikes able to pierce walls on all her body or turn her body parts in big spikes.

Name: Zombie (Minecraft)
Summary: The Zombie is a hostile mob and the most common and basic enemy of the sandbox video game, Minecraft. They come out only at night, and attack local villages, killing Villagers and often turning them into Zombie Villagers.

Name: Zombieman
Summary: Zombieman is the S-Class Rank 8 superhero for the Hero Association. He was created by the founder of the House of Evolution, Dr. Genus.

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Absalom (One Piece)
Summary: Absalom, also known as “Absalom of the Graveyard”, was the leader of the Zombie Soldiers and Zombie Generals of Thriller Bark and a member of the Mysterious Four before Gekko Moriah's defeat. He was also a well-known pervert, unashamed of the idea of sexual harassment or assault as he desperately seeks a woman to be his bride, specifically, a human one that was too weak to fight off his advances; the zombies under his command nickname him "Erosalom" due to his highly amorous nature, despite him being their leader.

Name: Abuto
Summary: Abuto (阿伏兎) is a member of the 7th Division of Harusame's Thunder Guns, the most powerful combat unit under Captain Kamui's leadership, within the Harusame group. He is the secondary main antagonist of Yoshiwara in Flames Arc.

Name: Acidwire
Summary: Acidwire is the Hollowfied version of Orihime Inoue's brother, Sora Inoue. While introduced as vengeful because of Orihime's lack of prayers and stories he usually received, he eventually has a change of heart and forcefully kills and cleanses himself with Ichigo Kurosaki's Zanpakuto.

Name: Agrias Oaks
Summary: Lady Agrias Oaks is a secondary character appearing in Final Fantasy Tactics, initially as a guest character working together with Ramza Beoulve through the story, finally joining him during the events of Chapter 2.

Name: Airachnid (Transformers One)
Summary: Airachnid is Sentinel Prime's assistant and primary enforcer. To call her "no nonsense" would be an understatement; the only time she smiles is when she's causing others suffering or going in for the kill. She is an unrelenting, and humorless, hunter and spy with a vast array of receptors and scanners at her disposal, which allow for her to keep tabs on anything that might jeopardize Sentinel's claim to power.

Name: Akua Shuzen
Summary: Akua Shuzen is the oldest daughter of the Shuzen vampire sisters and is considered as the strongest among them. She is the last descendant of Alucard and shared the first vampire's desire to eradicate the human race after humans mercilessly killed her best friend, Jasmine. However, after being introduced to her youngest sister, who strongly resembles Jasmine, she gradually neglects her revenge and vows to protect Moka at any cost.

Name: Alisa Bosconovitch
Summary: Alisa Bosconovitch is a character in the Tekken series who was introduced in Tekken 6: Bloodline Rebellion. She is an android created by Doctor Bosconovitch in the image of his deceased daughter, who initially helped Lars to recover his memories.

Name: Alphonse Elric
Summary: Alphonse Elric (アルフォンス・エルリック, Arufonsu Erurikku) is the younger brother of Edward Elric, the Fullmetal Alchemist, Al is also a victim of the failed Human Transmutation experiment in which Ed lost his right arm and left leg. Having had his entire physical being taken away from him in the aftermath of the tragedy, Alphonse exists solely as a soul alchemically bound to a large suit of steel armor. Now, Al travels with his brother in search of the legendary Philosopher's Stone, an item with the power to restore their bodies to normal.

Name: Alucard (Rosario + Vampire)
Summary: nan

Name: Amber (RWBY)
Summary: Amber was the previous Fall Maiden. As a young girl, she received the powers of the Fall Maiden, granting her tremendous power and becoming the next in a line that persisted for thousands of years. However, due to the actions of Cinder Fall, half of her powers were stolen, causing her to fall into a coma. As she was unlikely to ever wake up, and in order to ensure that the rest of the powers would not go to her assailant, Ozpin and his group planned on transferring her portion to someone else. However, she would eventually be killed by Cinder during the Battle of Beacon, causing the rest of the powers to go to her.

Name: Anakaris
Summary: Anakaris is a video game character in Capcom's Darkstalkers fighting game series, first appearing in Darkstalkers: The Night Warriors. Pharaoh Anakaris was the wise ruler of a large kindgom in Egypt, 5000 years ago. Upon his death, his remains have been entombed into a pyramid, in order to preserve them and allow him to ascend to godhood. However, after the pharaoh's death, the kingdom quickly fell to ruin.

Name: Anna Williams
Summary: Anna Williams is a character in the Tekken series. She is trained in martial arts and always appears in her trademark red silk dress and/or a blue version of it.

Name: Anne Boonchuy
Key: '''Season 1-2''' | '''Season 3''' | '''Incomplete Calamity Form''' | '''Complete Calamity Form''' | '''With Secret Spell'''
Summary: Anne Boonchuy was pressured by her friends into stealing a strange music box on her 13th birthday which mystically activated and sent them to Amphibia, a realm populated by talking amphibians, where Anne lands in the town of Wartwood. There she is taken in by the Plantar family, who help Anne on her journey to find a way back home.

Name: Antenmaru
Summary: Antenmaru (闇天丸) was one of the strongest of the wrathful gods once sealed away by the Ketsuno clan's predecessors. Doman Shirino brought him back into this world to use his power to win against Seimei Ketsuno, however, would be completely consumed by the demon god and was ultimately stopped by the combined efforts of the Ketsuno and Shirino clans along with Gintoki's gang.

Name: Apollo (One-Punch Man)
Summary: Apollo is a member and agent of Tsukuyomi, an organization that researches psychic powers and creates artificial espers that, in the past, bought Tatsumaki from her parents and experimented on her when she was a child.

Name: Aqua Minato
Summary: Aqua Minato is a "marine maid-styled virtual maid". She's a kind and sweet girl, who's always there to help her friends or those in need in acts of selflessness. She's fairly childish and airheaded, so while she enjoys pulling pranks, she often gets pranked instead. Likely out of a hobby of hers, she cosplays as a maid and she isn't actually one. She can fly with her twintails, which are also somehow detachable from her head. She's hopelessly infatuated with Okayu Nekomata. She's often seen bickering with Shion Murasaki.

Name: Armored Gorilla
Summary: Armored Gorilla (アーマードゴリラ, Āmādo Gorira) is an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution. Unlike his peers, Armored Gorilla's body is mostly robotic. He is the third-strongest specimen in the House of Evolution, and its only battle cyborg.

Name: Artifact Boss
Summary: The Artifact is an energy source created by the High goblin Urick to power the robot control center, which kept the robots active and fighting for the Goblins. Years later, the rogue Monk Xander was handed the Artifact by Lucas, allowing him to take control of the robots, and later power the Armageddon Machine. After being thwarted by Lucas and Knack, Xander unleashed the Artifact upon Knack before succumbing to his wounds. Said Artifact turned into the Artifact Boss and proceeded to face Knack.

Name: Asaemon Ikeda
Summary: Asaemon Ikeda (池田 朝右衛門, Ikeda Asaemon) is the 19th Ikeda Yaemon of the Ikeda Clan. Beforehand, she was adopted into the clan and given the title "17th Ikeda Yaemon" by her adoptive father, the 16th Ikeda Yaemon. After failing to execute him with Kimoarai, she left the Ikeda Clan as a traitor, with her adoptive brother being the successor of the title. Asaemon was then sold to the Hitotsubashi Faction by the 18th Ikeda Yaemon, but she survived and received the title again after his death.

Name: Astalos
Summary: Astalos is one of four flagships of Monster Hunter Generations/Monster Hunter X.

Name: Asuka Kazama
Summary: Ever since she was a child, Asuka had received training in Kazama Style Traditional Martial Arts from her father. Born with a strong sense of justice, Asuka was well known around Osaka for breaking up fights in the neighborhood.

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Atlesian Colossus
Summary: The Atlesian Colossus is an enormous mech created by Atlas with the purpose of defend the city of Argus if giant Grimm were to attack the city from the ocean. While not in use it is stored inside the Argus Military Base.

Name: Atsuya Kusakabe
Summary: Listen up you curse users!! I don't know what the hell happened, but those two there fighting are special grade! Think of them as elephants tap dancing on ants. To be clear, we're the ants...

Name: Awakened Cockroach
Summary: Awakened Cockroach (覚醒ゴキブリ, Kakusei Gokiburi), is a Demon-level monster and member of the Monster Association.

Name: Ayame Nakiri
Summary: Ayame Nakiri is an oni, a type of demon, has two horns growing out of her forehead and is over 1500 years old. She's from the Underworld Academy, of which she's the respected student council president, and is a trained swordswoman who wields two katanas, Rakshasa and Asura. Despite her status, she's fairly chaotic and uncontrollable, tends to act in nonsensical ways, and enjoys pranking people with will-o’-the-wisps. She's also fairly airheaded and easily excitable, which sometimes causes trouble.

Name: Ayame Sarutobi
Summary: Ayame Sarutobi (猿飛 あやめ, Sarutobi Ayame), mostly referred to as Sa-chan, is a ninja from the Oniwabanshuu by training, but is currently working as an assassin. She also has a part-time job at the Kunoichi Café. Since her initial appearance, she has developed a seriously obsessive infatuation with Sakata Gintoki, to the point of even stalking him.

Name: Azazel (Tekken)
Summary: Azazel is the main antagonist and Final Boss of Tekken 6. He is the entity that telepathically spoke to Jin Kazama and told him to plunge the world into chaos to gather the necessary negative energy to awake and destroy humanity.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: B-127 (Transformers One)
Summary: B-127 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A worker in the lowest level of Waste Management, sub-level 50, Bee's isolation caused him to become extremely talkative, to the point of talking to himself and his imaginary friends, all to keep himself company. Upon meeting Orion Pax and D-16, who had both been banished to waste management, the trio would accidentally stumble upon a map leading to the lost Matrix of Leadership. Bee would then assist the two in finding the artifact, hoping to become good friends with the two.

Name: B.B. Hood
Summary: B.B. Hood, or Baby Bonnie Hood (known as Bulleta in Japan), is a playable character introduced in Darkstalkers 3. She is an exceptional Darkhunter who goes after the Darkstalkers for profit, and one of the few in the world able to fight with the strongest of them.

Name: Bad (Metal Bat)
Summary: Bad (バッド, Baddo?), also known by his hero alias Metal Bat (金きん属ぞくバット, Kinzoku Batto?), is an S-Class hero, ranked 15 in the Hero Association. Despite his low status among the S-Class heroes, he is considered one of the strongest. Metal Bat's "Kiai" (fighting spirit) is the key to his strength; the more damage he takes, the stronger he becomes. His power grows in direct proportion to his injury and mental state, to the point where he can eventually defeat superior opponents on his own. Metal Bat typically treats both his allies and enemies badly. However, he is a kind and gentle soul to his younger sister.[1]

Name: Bad Mr. Frosty
Summary: Bad Mr. Frosty is a sentient snowman brought to life by the impact of a strange meteorite. Since then, he has become a rather aggressive, violent creature who participates in the ClayFighter tournaments.

Name: Bakuzan (One Punch Man)
Summary: Bakuzan is a sadistic martial artist who uses the "Dark Hell Assassination" technique and was thought to be a top contender in the Super Fight tournament until he was soundly defeated by Saitama. Frustrated, he devours multiple monster cells when given the opportunity, but the strain initially knocked him out. He later returns as an ape-like monster, attacking both Suiryu and Gouketsu.

Name: Bandit Princess
Summary: Bandit Princess is a minor antagonist in Adventure Time and the primary antagonist in the episode I am a Sword! She is a villainous princess of an unknown kingdom who found the Finn Sword after he lost it. Much of Bandit Princess' personality and origin is currently unknown, however she appears to be a cartoonishly evil character, slaying various inhabitants of Ooo, sacking their villages and stealing their wealth .

Name: Barricade (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Many years in the past, when Cybertron had just come under the rule of the Defense Force and the Science Division, Barricade was a member of the Defense Force under the command of High Protector Megatron. He participated in missions to rid the planet of "malcontents" who protested against the new order, and like many of his peers, he did so ruthlessly.

Name: Barricade (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Dark of the Moon''' | '''The Last Knight'''
Summary: Barricade is apparently a complicated robot. He's considered "fractious" even by Decepticon standards, yet is willing to give Starscream the benefit of the doubt and follow where he leads, at least for the time being. Though not totally dedicated to the service of the Decepticons' current leader, he is much more cautious and reserved about expressing mutinous dissent than say most. He believes that Starscream is vital in their search for Megatron and the AllSpark. In many ways this makes him Starscream's closest ally in the naturally combative Decepticon ranks. Then again, it's been said that he likes to trick people into trusting him, just so he can see their reactions when they find out just how much of a bad idea it was. As such, he has disguised himself as an Earth police car in an attempt to fool the humans around him.

Name: Beast King
Summary: Beast King (獣王 Jūō) was an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution. The Beast King is the leader of Dr. Genus' strike force and second-strongest specimen in the House of Evolution, exceeded only by Carnage Kabuto.

Name: Bedtime Bear (Original)
Summary: Bedtime Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. As his name would suggest, he can most often be found dozing off at just about any place or time. However, when the situation calls for it, he can be dependable and is always willing to help out those who need it. It is his duty to make sure everyone on Earth and in the Care Bear family gets enough sleep and dreams peacefully.

Name: Beefcake
Summary: Beefcake (マルゴリ, Marugori) was a regular human until he drank the Biceps Brachii King steroid provided by his older brother, Oldface, which turned him into a mutated giant.

Name: Bella Noche
Summary: Bella Noche is a minor antagonist in Adventure Time, appearing in the episode, "Betty". Her true form originally existed in another dimension, before being freed through a ritual performed by a group of wizards in Wizard City. However, she would be defeated by Betty by being kicked in the face.

Name: Bentham (Mr. 2 Bon Clay)
Summary: Bentham, also known by his epithet "Bentham of the Wild" and his alias Mr. 2 Bon Clay, is a former officer agent of Baroque Works and an okama (a Japanese slang term for a transvestite). Strangely enough, he was the only higher up member that lacks a female partner of the same rank. Possibly due to believing he fits the role of both male and female, probably due to his powers and lifestyle as a self-proclaimed okama. He was thus assigned both a number and a holiday for his code name.

Name: Beros (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Beros (ベロス Berosu) was a villain working for Flect Turn in My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. She was the main hunter of Deku and Rody Soul, attempting to stop their interference in the plans of Humarize.

Name: Betty Grof
Summary: Betty Grof was once a kind and collected young woman who was a budding Antiquarian, as well as the fiance to Simon Petrikov. Though little of her personality has been shown, she has been depicted as being very strong willed and tough, as well as determined and dedicated to protecting her boyfriend. After Simon first went mad with the crown, she ran to find safety, only to force herself through a portal to the future to be with Simon once again.

Name: Bishamon
Summary: Bishamon is a playable character in the Darkstalkers series and covers the role of the accursed samurai.

Name: Blackarachnia (Transformers Animated)
Summary: She was once an Autobot with the name of Elita-1, but after an incident on a strange planet, she was mutated into a half-Cybertronian and half-spider being. She defected to the Decepticons' side with the hope of finding a cure.

Name: Blackout (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Blackout (Michael Bay)
Summary: The massive Blackout has been described as the "hound" of Megatron. In better days he was always to be found looming powerful and silent behind his leader's right shoulder. When given a target he hunts it down with fierce determination. Blackout is not happy with the progress Starscream is making towards finding the missing Decepticon leader. He suspects (quite rightly) that Starscream would prefer Megatron to stay lost. Blackout is openly mutinous and will challenge Starscream's leadership at any opportunity, not for his own sake, but to better serve his ultimate goal of finding his lost master. Blackout has a sneaky side and uses his symbiotic companion Scorponok's small size to great advantage.

Name: Bling-Bling Boy
Summary: Eugene "Bling-Bling Boy" Hamilton is a recurring anti-hero in the series who has a one-sided crush on Susan Test.

Name: Blitzwing (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Blitzwing was a Decepticon Seeker sent to hunt down Bumblebee on Earth.

Name: Blitzwing (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Blitzwing is a Decepticon with multiple personalities (A hammy and hotheaded one, a cold and icy strategist and an insane random one), despite having this problem, he is one of the deadliest Decepticons around and one of the most unpredictable.

Name: Blueno
Summary: Blueno is one of the members of CP9.

Name: Bobert
Summary: Bobert is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. It is a robot that is a student at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Bonecrusher (Michael Bay)
Summary: Bonecrusher, known as the Claw of Megatron, is a Transformer that can be described with one word: Hate. While other Decepticons get by on greed, ambition, or just their fondness for dispensing chaos, Bonecrusher is fueled by sheer, unrelenting hate. He hates everyone and everything, be they Autobot, Decepticon, or anything in-between—he even hates himself, revolted by his misshapen, hunchbacked robot mode, which he considers a reflection of all the ugliness and malice inside himself. The full force of this vicious cycle of hatred finds release in explosive frenzied bursts of psychotic brutality, as Bonecrusher takes out the full force of his bitterness and self-loathing on anyone who looks at him sideways. He hates that. He also hates Megatron, but would hate being terminated by the Decepticon leader more, so he sticks around.

Name: Brawl (Michael Bay)
Summary: To say Brawl is a warrior is like calling Cybertron a hunk of metal. Brawl does not just enjoy fighting, he is consumed by it. Tearing Autobots apart is embedded into his very core, and every fiber-optic cable of his being is obsessed with wild, unyielding combat. The only thing he enjoys, or even cares about, is the fury of battle. And he loves a good explosion. Particularly if it's one he created, and if it's an Autobot that is exploding.

Name: Breakdown (Transformers: Prime)
Summary: Breakdown is a Decepticon that appears in Transformers: Prime. He has held a long-lasting rivalry with the Autobot Bulkhead, with the two trading blows frequently when Team Prime has had to fight the Decepticons. Despite his alignment, he has a number of more admirable traits, including respect for the cannon fodder Vehicons and his enemies, along with his friendship with his fellow Decepticon Knock Out, who often accompanied him on missions. Though he is not a particularly brainy fighter, he is still very capable in battle. Despite his brutish figure and personality, Breakdown is also wrought with paranoia and insecurity.

Name: Brook
Summary: Brook is the crew's musician. He ate the Revive-Revive Fruit (Yomi Yomi no Mi), which enabled his spirit to reanimate his corpse after he died. Unfortunately, after his death, his spirit got lost for an entire year before finding his body, and it had decayed into a skeleton. He later developed the ability to control his own soul. Deprived of his shadow by the Warlord of the Sea, Gecko Moria, he was adrift within the gloomy Florian Triangle until he met the Straw Hats by chance.

Name: Bryan Fury
Summary: Bryan Fury was an officer in the International Police Organization who was killed in a shoot-out in Hong Kong. Bryan's corpse was transported to the laboratory of a man named Doctor Abel. This scientist came to the last step of completing his Cyborg Army master project and thought that a perfect cyborg must have the mechanics built by his rival, Dr. Boskonovitch, so he reanimated Fury's body and sent him off to collect this data. In his former life, Bryan was known as a skillful detective, but on the other side, he was always followed by dark rumors. Investigating the Hong Kong drug trade, Lei Wulong discovered that Fury had connections with drug dealers. Bryan sneaks into the 'King of Iron Fist Tournament, targeting Yoshimitsu, who has strong ties with Boskonovitch.

Name: Bug God
Summary: Bug God (蟲神, Mushigami) was a Demon-level Mysterious Being from the Monster Association.

Name: Bulkhead (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Raised on a backwater energon farm, Bulkhead joined the Autobot academy to achieve the lofty goal of becoming a lowly space bridge technician rather than a warrior. He also has an unfortunate tendency to break stuff by accident due to his sheer strength and natural clumsiness

Name: Bulkhead (Transformers: Prime)
Summary: Bulkhead looks huge and menacing but is actually quite careless and gentle souled. Though he's neither a brainiac nor a fast runner, Bulkhead is one of the most sturdy members of Team Prime. He's afraid of hurting things smaller and more fragile than him, but his new human friend, Miko Nakadai, has helped him grow past that. He has a low tolerance for jerks and is quite happy to let people like that stew in the trouble they've made for themselves, but his better impulses—or at least, needling from those around him—always sway him into helping in the end. For all his sweetness, he's still a Wrecker through and through. Yet despite participating in several major battles and campaigns, his past career has left some painful psychological scars. Being a part of the Autobots' black ops team means you have to do the dirty work, and Bulkhead's seen many horrors and friends meet a bad end. Though saddened by his traumatic experiences with the Wreckers, he's joined up with Optimus Prime to end the fight with Megatron, for the sake of all his brothers and comrades.

Name: Bumblebee (2018 Reboot)
Summary: A scout under the command of Optimus Prime, B-127, later called Bumblebee by Charlie Watson, was part of the final battle for Cybertron — a battle that ended with the Autobot position overrun by the Decepticons and necessitating a full-scale Autobot evacuation of Cybertron. As part of this evacuation, Prime tasked him with a reconnaissance mission to the distant planet of Earth—its location hidden from the Decepticons — in the hopes that the scout could establish a base for the Autobots to regroup and strike back.

Name: Bumblebee (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Bumblebee was born over 10,000 years ago, one of the second generation of Cybertronians spawned by the AllSpark since its rediscovery and the revitalization of Cybertron. He and Cliffjumper were guardians of the AllSpark at the Temple of Simfur. During the war, Bumblebee was placed in command of a small Autobot unit at the AllSpark's hiding place in Tyger Pax, on the assumption that the Decepticon would focus their attention on Simfur; unfortunately, Megatron sensed the AllSpark's true location, and Bumblebee and his men found themselves under attack by the Decepticon leader and his troops. Swindle tried and failed to torture the AllSpark's precise hiding spot out of Bumblebee, forcing Megatron to take up the task, but even 'Bee did not know exactly where it was—moments later, both he and Megatron could only watch as the cube was blasted into space from a launch site nearby. A furious Megatron crushed Bumblebee's voice capacitor beyond repair in a petty act of revenge and took off after the AllSpark; although the young bot survived and was dubbed a hero for his actions, he feared that all the Autobots had done was potentially spread their war to other worlds.

Name: Bumblebee (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Revenge of the Fallen''' | '''Dark of the Moon''' | '''Age of Extinction to The Last Knight'''
Summary: Bumblebee is an Autobot Scout and one of Optimus Prime's most trusted lieutenants. Although he is not the strongest or most powerful of the Autobots, Bumblebee more than makes up for this with a bottomless well of luck, determination, and bravery. He would gladly give his life to protect others and stop the Decepticons.

Name: Bumblebee (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Bumblebee is one of the main characters in Transformers Animated and one of the Autobots. He is very hyperactive, cracks jokes at any time, but when the opportunity arises, he is one cunning fighter.

Name: Bushidrill
Summary: Bushidrill is the A-Class rank 4 hero and a Disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. Alongside his partners Iaian and Okamaitachi, Bushidrill is a skilled and powerful swordsman. Each is described as being worthy of S-Class, though they are forced to stay in their current positions due to Sweet Mask, who remains at Rank 1 of A-Class.

Name: Cade Yeager
Summary: All humans make mistakes. Sometimes, what comes from those mistakes comes the best thing that ever happened to them. That's what Cade Yeager believes when he looks at his daughter, to whom he and his girlfriend gave birth at the cost of their high school graduation. While Cade is not the most responsible father in the world, his most redeeming quality is that when it comes to keeping his daughter safe, he does not go back on his word, no matter what; a promise he made to his bride before she passed away. He does have a creative and optimistic mind, lending it to building all kinds of inventions to make a good business out of. Sadly, none of these inventions have brought in much profit for his family. Knowing all of the opportunities he lost, he has sworn not to let history repeat itself, which is probably why he disapproves of Tessa dating boys before she graduates from high school.

Name: Calliope Mori (Holo no Graffiti)
Summary: Calliope Mori is Death-sensei's, the Grim Reaper's, first apprentice. Due to modern medical care causing a decline in the reaping business, Calliope decided to become a VTuber to harvest souls instead, and pursue a music career. Calliope is a reaper herself, who has existed since the dawn of life.

Name: Carlito Keyes
Summary: Tier: 10-A, 7-C with preparation

Name: Carnage Kabuto
Summary: Carnage Kabuto (阿あ修しゅ羅らカブト, Ashura Kabuto?) was an artificial mutant created by Dr. Genus of the House of Evolution and is by far their strongest creation. He is an extremely unstable being while also being very intelligent (which Dr. Genus also confirmed to be true), but has an insatiable bloodlust and thus had to be locked up because he kept killing anything that got near him. He considers himself far superior to humans, calling himself a 'new human' that Dr. Genus was looking for, and believing that all should bow to his will. Carnage Kabuto is also very sarcastic and low-tempered, which is considered by Genus to be one of his main failures.

Name: Chatsberry
Summary: Chatsberry is the Candy Elemental, and one of the beings that have existed before the Mushroom War. He, along with the other Elementals of his time, was frozen by Urgence Evergreen after trying to stop him. It is unknown what happened to Chatsberry after that, but it is likely that he perished when the Catalyst Comet arrived.

Name: Cheer Bear (Original)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first debuted as a character on American Greetings cards in 1982. True to her name, Cheer specializes in lifting people's spirits whenever they're feeling down. Just about the only time one will find her feeling down is when there's someone who seems like they are nigh-impossible to encourage. However, this only ever leads Cheer to try harder. She constantly surprises those who doubt her capabilities with how multi-talented she truly is.

Name: Cheetor (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Cheetor is one of main characters in Beast Wars. Cheetor is full of youthful overconfidence. He's also the fastest Maximal on four legs which, combined with his impulsive nature, often gets him into more trouble than he can handle.

Name: Chitose Kizuki (Curious)
Summary: Chitose Kizuki (気月置歳 'Kidzuki Chitose), also known by the code name Curious (キュリオス Kyuriosu), was one of the minor antagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia, the executive director of Shoowaysha Publishing and a former member of the Meta Liberation Army.

Name: Chojuro Kon (Chimera)
Summary: Chojuro Kon (今こん鳥ちょう獣じゅう郎ろう Kon Chojuro), also known as Chimera (キメラ Kimera), is a villain working with Nine in the film My Hero Academia: Heroes Rising.

Name: Choze
Summary: Choze is a martial arts competitor from One Punch Man. He comes from a clan of eugenicists determined to create a "superior race." Due to years of selective breeding with the best of genes, Choze was born with naturally superhuman abilities, which he uses to brutally torture others for his pleasure.

Name: Cinder Fall
Summary: Cinder Fall is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. She is a member of Salem's Inner Circle as well as the leader of her own faction, which includes Roman Torchwick, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black. Cinder is imperious and cunning, with a touch of cruelty. Usually, she maintains a calm and collected demeanor and is willing to take over a fight if necessary. She is also ambitious and demanding, doesn't seem to tolerate failure, and dislikes when she is disobeyed, reprimanding Emerald and Mercury when they failed to obey her orders to keep their hands clean. She is shown to be an excellent strategist as well, often planning ahead to keep her goals in reach while keeping her accomplices on a strict "need to know" basis. Following the Battle of Beacon, Cinder is the current Fall Maiden.

Name: Cinnamon Bun
Summary: Cinnamon Bun is a major recurring character in Adventure Time. Originally a dim witted but friendly servant and surrogate son of Princess Bubblegum, Cinnamon Bun was infamous for his childish antics and clumsy behavior, often making huge mistakes or even destroying buildings in his misguided attempts to be cool. After defecting to the Flame Kingdom, Cinnamon Bun matured and grew greatly, but also became much more cynical and confused about his life.

Name: Cirno
Summary: Cirno (チルノ) is an ice fairy who first appeared on the second stage of Embodiment of Scarlet Devil. As a fairy, she is exceptionally strong for her kind, matching the power of some weak youkai. However, compared to most of Gensokyo's residents, she's quite weak. Her personality is childish and she is sometimes considered stupid.

Name: Combustion Man
Summary: Combustion Man was a mysterious, silent assassin sent by Zuko to eliminate Aang.

Name: Cozy Heart Penguin
Summary: Cozy Heart Penguin is a Care Bear Cousin who originated in the first feature length Care Bears Movie. She can frequently be found swimming in the arctic waters of the Forest of Feelings, and she considers it her task to spread warmth and joy to all she comes across. Cozy Heart also happens to be the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't a mammal.

Name: Crankcase (Michael Bay)
Summary: Crankcase is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was tasked with capturing Sentinel Prime but was intercepted by Ironhide and Sideswipe and was killed by the former.

Name: Crocodile (One Piece)
Summary: Crocodile is the second of the Seven Warlords of the Sea to be formally introduced and serves as the main antagonist of the Alabasta Saga. He is one of the longest running primary adversaries of the series as well as the first enemy to hand Luffy a complete and utter defeat, not once but twice. He secretly formed a criminal organization called Baroque Works, whose public aim was to take over the prosperous of Alabasta and create a utopia and led it as its president. To accomplish this, he worked to undermine Alabasta King's influence by defeating criminals before the royal army could, and by exploiting a drought in order to pit the kingdom against an army of rebels. His Devil Fruit, the Sand-Sand Fruit (Suna Suna no Mi), lets him turn into and control sand, a very useful ability in the desert kingdom.

Name: Crosshairs
Summary: When the chips are down, Crosshairs is the kind of guy you'd want on your team. Or you would, if it wasn't for the fact that he's self-loving and more than a bit of a jerk. Crosshairs is a paratrooper who's a mouthful of snark with a bad attitude. He's got little respect for Optimus Prime, harboring a desire to just be on his own or otherwise be in charge himself. Despite these vices, Crosshairs is still a crack shot who always hits the ground running and makes mincemeat out of Decepticons with his firearms before they even know what hit them. And if the chips are really down, he'll come through in the end for his fellow Autobots.

Name: Crowbar (Michael Bay)
Summary: Crowbar is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was tasked with capturing Sentinel Prime but was intercepted by Ironhide and Sideswipe and was killed by the former.

Name: Danjuro Tobita (Gentle Criminal)
Summary: Danjuro Tobita (飛田 弾柔郎 Tobita Danjūrō), better known as Gentle Criminal (ジェントル・クリミナル Jentoru Kuriminaru), is a small-time villain who has his assistant La Brava film his numerous petty crimes in order to raise awareness of the flaws in hero society. Once an aspiring hero-in-training with failing grades, his life turned upside down when he used his Quirk to try and save someone in the middle of a hero operation, inadvertently causing the person serious injury and his expulsion from school as well as being disowned by his parents.

Name: Dark Heart
Summary: Dark Heart is the primary antagonist of the second Care Bears feature film. He is a demonic entity who intends to capture each member of the Care Bear Family and spread his influence to everyone on Earth. Unlike most other adversaries of Care-a-Lot, however, Dark Heart's malicious ways come not from his hatred of caring but from his initial inability to understand it. After the near-death of his friend, Christy, helps him realize his capacity to care about others, he abandons his evil ways and his powers in the process.

Name: Dark Star Saber
Summary: A terrifying weapon forged by Megatron following his humiliating defeat at the hands of Optimus Prime, the Dark Star Saber is powered by pure Dark Energon and is even stronger than its inspiration, possessing all of its abilities and none of its drawbacks, such as its requirement of a Prime to wield.

Name: Darkwing Duck
Summary: When he was young, Drake Mallard looked up to comic book heroes and often wished he had the courage to stand up to bullies. On the night of his senior prom, he got his chance. When his classmate Elmo Sputterspark, the rat who would go on to be known as the super-villain Megavolt, attacked the dance with his newfound electrical abilities, Drake donned a mask left over from a theater production and defeated Megavolt, marking his first ever adventure as the costumed crime fighter Darkwing Duck. Darkwing achieved real fame when he took down St. Canard's kingpin of crime, Taurus Bulba, adopting the grandaughter of one of Bulba's victims, Gosalyn Waddlemeyer.

Name: Daz Bonez (Mr. 1)
Summary: Daz Bonez is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works and was the highest ranked male Officer Agent and the strongest under Crocodile himself. His codename was Mr. 1 and his partner was Miss Doublefinger.

Name: Death Gatling
Summary: Death Gatling (デスガトリング, Desu Gatoringu) is an A-Class Rank 8 hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Demon Cat
Summary: The Demon Cat is a dungeon boss encountered in the S01E18 episode Dungeon in Adventure Time. He is a sadistic creature who takes pride in having approximate knowledge of many things.

Name: Demonic Fan
Summary: Demonic Fan (扇風鬼, Senpūki) was a Mysterious Being of unknown origin that appears to be a sentient robotic fan.

Name: Denki Kaminari (Chargebolt)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Denki Kaminari (上鳴電気 Kaminari Denki), also known as Chargebolt (チャージズマ Chājizuma), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. Chargebolt is a friendly, social, and energetic boy who likes to hang out with people. He is rather casual when interacting with others, including the generally unfriendly Dynamight. He may come off as blunt and reckless at times, but is always well-meaning.

Name: Devastator (Michael Bay)
Summary: Devastator is a Decepticon combiner formed from the Constructicons. He was formed in Egypt to aid the Fallen and Megatron in their quest to harvest Earth's Sun.

Name: Devil Long Hair
Summary: Devil Long Hair is a Demon-level member of the Monster Association. He is extremely obsessed with his very long head of hair, and treats his opponents mockingly.

Name: Dhalsim
Summary: Dhalsim is a video game character from the Street Fighter series of fighting games. Dhalsim is famous throughout the Street Fighter series for his stretchy, lanky body and fire attacks.

Name: Dhruv Lakdawalla
Summary: Dhruv Lakdawalla is a jujutsu sorcerer from the past who was incarnated by Kenjaku for the Culling Game. This is the second incarnation for the veteran sorcerer who once conquered Japan on his own during the Civil War of Wa.

Name: Diablos
Key: '''Diablos/HC Diablos/Gilded Diablos''' | '''Black Diablos''' | '''HC Black Diablos''' | '''Bloodbath Diablos''' | '''Varusaburosu'''
Summary: Diablos is a large dangerous Flying Wyvern which inhabits the Monster Hunter world's desert regions. Despite being a herbivore, it's incredibly aggressive which has earned it the title of "Tyrant of the Desert".

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Dino (Michael Bay)
Summary: A vigorous warrior, Dino (Or Mirage) is always among the first on the battlefield thanks to his impatience. His peers would call him either bold or reckless, depending on who you ask.

Name: Dinobot (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Dinobot used to be a Predacon. When he and his Predacon peers crashed on what seemed to be the wrong planet alongside a Maximal exploration vessel, he rebelled against Megatron and joined the Maximal team.

Name: Do-S
Summary: "Monster Princess" Do-S (怪人姫弩S, Kaijin Hime Do S) is a Demon-level mysterious being and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Doman Shirino
Summary: Doman Shirino (巳厘野 道満 Shirino Douman) is an Onmyoji who is the current head of the Shirino clan. He is also the friend and rival of Seimei Ketsuno.

Name: Donovan Baine
Summary: Donovan was a half-vampire, half-human child. He and his mother were outcasts of their village due to Donovan's cursed blood. During his childhood, something caused his cursed blood to awaken and he killed everyone in the village including his mother.

Name: Dr. Drakken
Summary: Drew Theodore P. Lipsky was an inventor, even from a young age, being able to develop fantastical yet strange devices by the time he hit the fourth grade, using them to get an edge in sports. After a humiliation in university involving him creating the first Bebe Robot prototypes, he dropped out of school and decided to pursue his true calling in life: crime. At some point, his skin turned blue for unknown reasons, and since then, he has become one of Kim Possible's most prominent enemies under the name Dr. Drakken.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Earl of Lemongrab (Original)
Summary: Earl of Lemongrab is a recurring character in Adventure Time. He first appears in the episode Too Young. He is the high-strung, overly-zealous, obnoxious, stubborn ruler of the Earldom of Lemongrab, and the heir to the Candy Kingdom. It is possible that he is no longer heir to the throne because as of Hot Diggity Doom, the Candy Kingdom is now a democracy. He is the creation of Princess Bubblegum and the first of her experiments to go wrong. He was able to usurp the throne of the Candy Kingdom on the technicality of Bubblegum's de-aging. Once Princess Bubblegum was 18 again, she fires him, and he returns to Lemongrab.

Name: Earl of Lemongrab 3
Summary: Earl of Lemongrab 3 is the third Earl of Lemongrab, created by Princess Bubblegum from the parts of the original Lemongrab, Lemongrab 2 and various Lemon People. The current Lemongrab now resides in Castle Lemongrab, where he continues ruling the Earldom and its people. He retains at least some of his earlier incarnations memories, if not all of them.

Name: Eijiro Kirishima (Red Riot)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Shie Hassaikai Arc''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Eijiro Kirishima (切島鋭児郎 Kirishima Eijirō), also known as Red Riot (烈怒頼雄斗 Reddo Raiotto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero. Like Deku, he's kind, friendly, and has real dreams of being an altruistic hero, having been inspired by his idol, Crimson Riot. He has a bit of a fixation with doing "manly" things, rating actions as "manly" or "unmanly" depending on how much he approves of them.

Name: Electric Catfish Man
Summary: Electric Catfish Man (電気ナマズ男, Denkinamazu Otoko) is an enlarged catfish with muscular human arms and legs and a Tiger level threat that first appeared alongside his partner Maiko Plasma during the Monster Raid, assigned by Gyoro-Gyoro to attack D-City.

Name: Elita-1 (Transformers One)
Summary: Elita-1 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A no-nonsense bot, Elita-1 was the head of an Energon mining crew, maintaining a spotless record while harvesting large amounts of energon for the good of Cybertron. Up until a mining incident involving Orion Pax and D-16, which involved her demotion, leading to a disdain particularly towards the former.

Name: Eliza (Tekken)
Summary: Eliza is a young female Vampire that has been imprisoned in a wing of the Rochefort Estate.

Name: End City
Summary: The End Cities are the only inhabited places in the End, an alternate dimension to the Overworld. They are occupied by the Endermen, a mysterious alien kind who travels to the other dimensions at night and comes back when day breaks. They appear to worship a being of immense power; the Ender Dragon.

Name: End Crystal
Summary: End Crystals are a group of artifacts found in the End. They are mainly used to support the Ender Dragon.

Name: Ender Dragon (Minecraft)
Summary: The Ender Dragon is the final boss of Minecraft. It lives in The End, a separate dimension from the Overworld and the homeland of the Endermen.

Name: Enderman
Summary: The Enderman is a mob in Minecraft. It stands at 2.9 meters/blocks tall, one taller than The Player.

Name: Enel
Summary: Enel is the former "God" of Skypiea and the main antagonist of the Skypiea Arc. Two years ago, after his defeat by the Straw Hat Pirates, he arrived at the moon and became its new ruler.

Name: Enforcer (Michael Bay)
Summary: The Enforcer is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was sent to kill Dino and Bumblebee after they activated a Decepticon space port, though he was killed soon after.

Name: Eternity Larva
Summary: Eternity Larva is a fairy who represents butterflies and the general metamorphosis of insects. Her power seems greatly enhanced by an unknown source in Hidden Star in Four Seasons.

Name: Evil Eye (One Punch Man)
Summary: Evil Eye (ジャガン, Jagan) is a psychic monster from the Monster Association. Originally a weak esper, Gyoro Gyoro implanted the eyes of monsters slain by heroes on his body their remnant thoughts and hatred for heroes successfully empowering him.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: Eyesight
Summary: Eyesight is a Demon-level member of the Monster Association. She is a Gorgon-like creature, possessing the lower body of a serpent and several living snakes for her hair. Each of the snakes in her hair uses a different type of venom, with varying degrees of potency.

Name: Face Ripper
Summary: Face Ripper (カオハギ, Kaohagi) was a Demon-level monster and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Father (Fullmetal Alchemist)
Summary: Once, far before the events of the series, he was simply Homunculus, or Dwarf In The Flask, a small entity created by the chief alchemist of the country of Xerxes, from the blood of a nameless slave. Homunculus taught the slave, whom he'd named Van Hohenheim, about a mysterious science known as Alchemy, which he used to elevate his social standing until he became the servant of the king of Xerxes himself. Dying of old age, the king latched onto Homunculus' promises of immortality, and helped him set up a country-wide transmutation circle, being told that it would bring him eternal life by draining the souls of the entire country within him. However, Homunculus had set up the circle in such a way that the souls would flow into him and Hohenheim instead, killing the king and destroying Xerxes in one night.

Name: Felicia (Darkstalkers)
Summary: Felicia is one of the protagonists in the Darkstalkers video game franchise created by Capcom. She is a catwoman (bakaneko in Japanese folklore) who was taken in and raised by a sister named Rose, who gave her the name Felicia from the word Felicity.

Name: Feng Wei
Summary: Feng was the best student of his school and the star pupil of the "God Fist" style, however he broke the dojo's rules and was scolded by his master, whom he killed. He then seeked on getting the God Fist scroll, and destroyed many dojos before entering the King of Iron Fist tournament where he eventually found the scroll, where it stated that he needs to defeat all the other martial arts masters, conquer and transcend their styles in order to become the perfect warrior and become the Dragon God.

Name: Findorr Calius
Summary: Findorr Calius (フィンドール・キャリアス, Findōru Kyariasu) is the 24th Arrancar in Sōsuke Aizen's army and one of Baraggan Louisenbairn's six Fracción.

Name: Finn the Human
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Finn the Human, real name Finn Mertens is the main character of Adventure Time. He, along with his adoptive brother Jake the Dog are the loyal champions of the Candy Kingdom. Finn vowed to keep the Kingdom and its residence safe at all cost. Finn is a very loyal and kind person, always giving a helping hand to those who need it.

Name: Fishbone D
Summary: Fishbone D was the first Hollow introduced in the series, was eventually killed and cleansed by Ichigo Kurosaki after he initially gained his powers from Rukia Kuchiki.

Name: Flame Queen
Summary: Flame Princess (first name Phoebe and occasionally called FP) is the princess and ruler of the Fire Kingdom, as well as Finn's ex-girlfriend. When Jake asks Flambo if he knows any princesses that are Finn's age so he can fix his broken heart, he introduces Jake to Flame Princess. Flame Princess was locked away in a lantern in the main chamber of the Fire Kingdom when Jake first encounters her. It is later revealed that her father, the Flame King, put her there on Princess Bubblegum's advice when she was an infant, and she did not come out for 14 years. She has a short temper, trust issues, and a heat core that can destroy the world if overblown with emotions.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Flect Turn
Summary: Flect Turn (フレクト・ターン Furekuto Tān) is a villain and the primary antagonist for My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. He is the leader of the global cult Humarise, which subscribes to the Quirk Singularity Doomsday Theory and aims to eliminate Quirks from the world.

Name: Foxy (One Piece)
Summary: Foxy, also known as "The Silver Fox" is the captain of the Foxy Pirates and the main antagonist of the Long Ring Long Land Arc in One Piece. He is notorious for having one of the largest crews in the series, together with one of the largest ships. He has such because of his mastery of the "Davy Back Fight", a sportive event between pirates where crews wage their own crewmates. Although not very combat prone, Foxy is a very scheming and cunning man, making use of different kinds of weapons, disguises, and items, together with his Devil Fruit powers of the Slow-Slow Fruit (Noro Noro no Mi), which allows him to slow everything his beams touch for 30 seconds.

Name: Franky
Key: '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: "Iron Man" Franky, real name Cutty Flam, is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates under captain Monkey D. Luffy. As his epithet implies, he is a cyborg, having rebuilt his own body from iron scraps after he was run over by a sea train. He was formerly a member of a criminal shipbreaking gang called the Franky Family, which operated in the shipbuilders' haven of Water 7. He encountered the Straw Hats when he and the Franky Family brutally beat Usopp and stole a great deal of money from the crew while they were attempting to get their boat fixed on the island. However, his interests subsequently aligned with the Straw Hats' when the secret government organization CP9 kidnapped both him and their crewmate Nico Robin in a bid to construct the ancient superweapon Pluton, which he owned the blueprints to. After escaping the clutches of CP9, Franky decided to join their crew, drawn by their dedication to both their ship and their fellow crewmen.

Name: Fubuki (Blizzard of Hell)
Summary: Fubuki (フブキ?), also known by her hero alias Blizzard of Hell is the B-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. She is an Esper, the younger sister of Tatsumaki, and the leader of the Blizzard Group, a B-Class hero faction. She and her sister are known as the Psychic Sisters. Fubuki is one of the few people who are aware of Saitama's strength and is currently trying to recruit him into her group. She's also a self-declared member of the Saitama Group.

Name: Fuhrer Ugly
Summary: Fuhrer Ugly is a Dragon level Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association. He is an Ugmon, an ugly human that became a monster due to his extreme amount of jealousy and self hatred.

Name: Fukurou
Summary: Fukuro was a member of the CP9. He was first introduced in the Enies Lobby Arc. Like most One Piece characters, Fukuro has a noticeable quirk and his is that he has a big mouth (both figuratively and literally), such as revealing that Jabra’s girlfriend had dumped him.

Name: Fumihiko Takaba
Summary: Fumihiko Takaba (髙たか羽ば 史彦ふみひこ, Takaba Fumihiko?) is a character in the Jujutsu Kaisen series. He was a comedian before awakening his cursed technique during the culling games and becoming one of the strongest competitors and his role was vital in defeating the Special Grade past sorcerer Kenjaku.

Name: Fumikage Tokoyami (Tsukuyomi)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Fumikage Tokoyami (常闇踏陰 Tokoyami Fumikage), also known as Tsukuyomi (ツクヨミ Tsukuyomi), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. An oddly dark and serious individual, his strange mannerisms belie his powerful Quirk and the heart of a true hero, earning him an internship under Hawks, one of Japan's top Pro Heroes.

Name: G4
Summary: G4 is a self-proclaimed "Machine God" built by the same organization that Hammerhead stole his armor from. His goal was to force "The World's Strongest Man" King to fight him in order to test his abilities. Being far too terrified to face him however, King runs away, leaving the S-Class cyborg Genos to fight the Machine God instead.

Name: G5 (One-Punch Man)
Summary: G5, the self-proclaimed "machine god", is the immediate successor of the battle robot G4 and was created by the same mysterious group known simply as "The Organization". For unknown reasons, which he refuses to reveal to Gyoro Gyoro, The Organization sent G5 on their behalf as an ally of the Monster Association, defeating Narinki's Private Squad to prove his loyalty.

Name: Galdino (Mr. 3)
Summary: Galdino, also known by his epithet “Loan Shark Galdino” and his alias Mr. 3, is a former officer agent, alongside his former partner Miss Goldenweek. He is regarded as the smartest of the officers and only got the position of "Mr. 3" because of that. He has eaten the Doru Doru no Mi which allows him to create and control candle wax at will.

Name: Gale Wind
Summary: Gale Wind (疾風のウィンド, Hayate no uindo) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Hellfire Flame. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Ganju Shiba
Summary: Ganju Shiba (志波 岩鷲, Shiba Ganju) is a resident of Rukongai in Soul Society. He is a member of the former noble Shiba Clan, and the younger brother of Kaien and Kūkaku Shiba.

Name: Garogas
Summary: The Garogas (ガロガ星人) are an evil alien race created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Gears (Transformers Movie Novels)
Summary: Gears likes complaining. It makes him happy. But more importantly, he knows that his fellow Autobots find his endless litanies amusing rather than annoying. And in a war that's run a few million years, a little laughter can make a big difference, so he keeps at it.

Name: Gedatsu
Summary: One of God's priests. Gedatsu was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Swamp, which had a fifty percent rate of survival.

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Giant Toad
Summary: The Giant Toad is the guardian of the pond named after itself. It is usually calm and gentle, even protecting the pond.

Name: Gigakigan
Summary: Gigakigan was a gigantic rock monster. After spending over a thousand years collecting energy underneath a mountain of magma whilst bearing witness to his brethren being mined away by humans, he gained consciousness in order to take his revenge against humanity, first seen splitting a cliff-side apart over an unknown city before being reduced to rubble by Tatsumaki.

Name: Gigantomachia
