Summary: Ratchet was a civilian mechanic, and one of the best on all of Cybertron during the war. He became a Space Bridge technician because he could not stand the violence any longer, so he ends up with Optimus and his crew.

Name: Rathalos
Key: '''Base/HC/Azure/HC Azure/Destruction Wyvern Rathalos''' | '''Flame Rathalos''' | '''Silver/HC Silver Rathalos''' | '''Dreadking Rathalos''' | '''Zenith Rathalos''' | '''Zerureusu'''
Summary: The flagship monster of the entire Monster Hunter series and one of only two monsters to have appeared in every game in the series. Rathalos is a type of monster known as a Flying Wyvern, and it uses the fire element as its primary weapon.

Name: Rattrap (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Rattrap is a spy that works for the Maximals. He is a guy who prefers attacking from the back than face on.

Name: Ravager (Minecraft)
Summary: Ravagers are large hostile mobs that spawn in raids.

Name: Raven (Tekken)
Summary: Raven is a character of the Tekken fighting game series, which was introduced in Tekken 5 as one of the new characters. He is an international intelligence agent that was tasked to enter the fifth tournament in order to find out who announced and was behind it.

Name: Raven Branwen
Summary: Raven Branwen is the mysterious mother of Yang Xiao Long and Qrow Branwen's twin sister. She was originally a member of Team STRQ, though unlike most Hunters, she has little issue killing and is described by her brother as a dangerous person. Raven has a high "survival of the fittest" mentality in which she is rather indifferent towards innocents dying if they were too weak to defend themselves. On one occasion she saved the life of her daughter, who she had abandoned shortly after her birth, though not without warning that she won't be looking out for her a second time. Raven is currently concerned about Salem and the power that she possesses.

Name: Renji Abarai
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Post-Bankai Training''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Post-Timeskip''' | '''Post-Royal Guard Training'''
Summary: Renji Abarai (阿散あば井らい 恋れん次じ, Abarai Renji?) is the lieutenant of the 6th Division under Captain Byakuya Kuchiki. He formerly served as the 6th Seat of the 11th Division under Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Reverb (Transformers)
Summary: Reverb is the main Decepticon antagonist of the Transformers: Classified novels

Name: Rhino Wrestler
Summary: Rhino Wrestler (サイレスラー, Sai Resurā) was a Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association who first appeared during the attack in S-City.

Name: Rikiya Yotsubashi (Re-Destro)
Summary: Rikiya Yotsubashi (四ツ橋力也 Yotsubashi Rikiya), also known as Re-Destro (リ・デストロ Ri-Desutoro), is the President and CEO of the Detnerat Company, a lifestyle support company, as well as the Grand Commander of the modern Meta Liberation Army, which he runs in secret. He is also the son of the infamous villain Destro, and is the main antagonist of the Meta Liberation Army Arc. His organization later merged with the League of Villains to create a union known as the Paranormal Liberation Front. He stepped down as Grand Commander to become one of the group's nine lieutenants.

Name: Rikuo
Summary: Rikuo known as Aulbath in Japan, is a playable character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He was the emperor of a kindgom of 30.000 mermen, located in a lake deep beneath the Amazon. When Pyron arrived on Earth, his landing caused an earthquake and a volcanic eruption to occur right where the kingdom was. When Rikuo, who was exploring a far territory, realized what happened, it was already too late, a huge fissure had swallowed all the water of the lake and its inhabitants. Filled with rage, and sensing the evil aura coming off the ground, Rikuo sworn vengeance against the alien.

Name: Rin Kaenbyou
Summary: Rin Kaenbyou (火焔猫 燐), also known as Orin, is one of Satori Komeiji's pets. She carts the dead and dying into the Hell of Blazing Fires, where they are burnt as fuel.

Name: Ritsu Kageyama
Summary: Ritsu Kageyama is the younger brother of Mob and a major supporting character in the anime/manga series Mob Psycho 100. While his brother is socially inept and lacking in motivation and accomplishment, Ritsu is a star student, with perfect grades and a place on the Student Council of Salt Middle School, and is generally amiable to his older brother. However, his drive to be a good brother towards Mob was discovered to be a front to his genuine fear and jealousy of his brother's power only striving to be a good sibling to avoid confronting the form that he observed his brother take when knocked out.

Name: Roboco-san
Summary: Roboco-san, or simply Roboco, is a soft-spoken and kind robot girl, who supposedly came from a faraway wasteland, and the second-ever talent within Hololive Production. Due to being a robot, she's more solidly built than her fellow coworkers, but her robot body requires frequent maintenance in exchange. Her arms are frequently seen detaching from her body and falling off; for that reason, she's often described as clunky. Roboco is easily scared, clumsy, emotional and forgetful, but she's also one of the most mature members of Hololive, making her a reliable person. She's fairly competitive at video games.

Name: Rock Howard (The King of Fighters)
Summary: nan

Name: Roku
Summary: Roku was the Fire Nation-born Avatar immediately succeeding Avatar Kyoshi and preceding Avatar Aang. Roku's memory served as a guiding force for Aang throughout his quest to end the Hundred Year War.

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Royal Ripper
Summary: Royal Ripper (キリサキング, Kirisa Kingu) is a monster affiliated with the Monster Association.

Name: Rukia Kuchiki
Summary: Rukia Kuchiki (朽くち木き ルキア, Kuchiki Rukia?) is the current Captain of the 13th Division. She formerly served as lieutenant of the 13th Division under Captain Jūshirō Ukitake. Rukia is the adoptive younger sister of Byakuya Kuchiki and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Ryomen Sukuna
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Ryu Ishigori
Summary: In my first life, I was a moderate eater. I fought worthy opponents and met a good woman. So I don't particularly have any regrets. But I can't stand this vague thirst Okkotsu. And no one understands why I can't get no satisfaction. These cigarettes have a sweet aftertaste. My life never had dessert.

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sari Sumdac
Summary: Sari is a technorganic and the daughter of Isaac Sumdac. She spent all her time within her father's laboratories, receiving her education from robots. Despite this, she doesn't seem like a shut-in. She's curious, excitable and adventurous.

Name: Sasquatch
Summary: Sasquatch is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He is the leader and hero of the bigfoots, a tribe of about 100 individuals that lives deep in the Rocky Mountains of Canada. His job is to defend them from external threats, including humans, animals and monsters.

Name: Satono Nishida
Summary: Satono Nishida is one of the two humans acting as Okina's subordinates and dancer, who have for job to draw the latent abilities in all things. They used to be regular human children, but due to Okina's magical power, their humanity is questionable.

Name: Satori (One Piece)
Summary: One of God's priests, Satori was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Balls, which had a ten percent rate of survival.

Name: Satori Komeiji
Summary: Satori Komeiji (古明地 さとり) is the mistress of the Palace of the Earth Spirits, and the elder sister of Koishi Komeiji. Her ability to passively read the minds of others has caused her to be loathed and feared by humans and youkai, but she finds love in the animals that cannot normally be understood by others. She has many pets, including Utsuho Reiuji and Rin Kaenbyou.

Name: Satoru Gojo
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Scorcher (Adventure Time)
Summary: Scorcher is a character from Adventure Time.

Name: Scorponok (Michael Bay)
Summary: Scorponok is a Decepticon scout and partner of Blackout. He was dispatched during Blackout's attack on a military base in Qatar and stalked several surviving soldiers until they fought him off. He later appeared in Egypt to help the Fallen harvest Earth's Sun. He attacked Jetfire and mortally wounded him before having his head crushed.

Name: Scourge (2018 Reboot)
Summary: Scourge is the cunning, ruthless, and treacherous leader of the Terrorcons and the most fearsome hunter in the universe.

Name: Seimei Ketsuno
Summary: Seimei Ketsuno (結野 晴明, Ketsuno Seimei) is the current head of the Ketsuno clan. He is a genius and is considered to be the strongest onmyoji in the clan's entire history. He is also the brother of Ketsuno Crystel.

Name: Senior Centipede
Summary: Senior Centipede (ムカデ先輩, Mukade Senpai; Viz: Centisenpai) was a Monster that appeared after Metal Bat defeated Junior Centipede and Venus Mantrap. He was killed by Metal Bat in the manga, and by Garou in the Webcomic.

Name: Sentinel Prime (Michael Bay)
Summary: Sentinel Prime was one of the Primes, he used to be the leader of the Autobots until the Ark was lost in space, landing on the moon in 1961.

Name: Sentinel Prime (Transformers One)
Summary: Sentinel Prime is the initial antagonist of the film Transformers One. Beloved by the citizens of Iacon city, Sentinel proclaims himself as the savior of Cybertron, and the last of the Thirteen Primes, having been the only Prime to survive the war against the Quintessons. He is highly respected by everyone within Iacon, especially by D-16, who seeks to impress Sentinel and to one day earn his approval.

Name: Sergei Dragunov
Summary: Sergei Dragunov is a member of the Spetsnaz (also known as the Russian Special Operatives) who have dubbed him "The White Angel of Death" because of his overwhelming fighting powers and cold, inscrutable personality.

Name: Serpenters
Summary: Serpenters (サーペンターズ Sāpentāzu) are a villain duo comprised of twin brothers Ena (エナ Ena) and Dio (ディオ Dio). They work for Flect Turn in My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. They are incredibly sadistic and take pleasure in making their opponents suffer, a trait that is amplified when they take the Quirk enhancing drug Trigger. They were defeated after a brutal combat encounter with Dynamight.

Name: Shaggy Rogers (Cartoon)
Summary: Norville "Shaggy" Rogers is a member of Mystery Inc., and the owner and best friend of their team's mascot: Scooby Doo, a talking Great Dane.

Name: Shego
Summary: Shego is a villainess who works for Dr. Drakken as his sidekick. Since her main duty to Drakken entails stealing things on his request and protecting him from harm, she frequently engages Team Possible in battle. Though under contract with the scientist, she has occasionally worked with other villains as well, such as Motor Ed and Señor Senior, Junior.

Name: Shinji Nishiya (Kamui Woods)
Summary: Shinji Nishiya (西屋森児 Nishiya Shinji), also known by his hero name, Kamui Woods (シンリンカムイ Shinrin Kamui), is the No. 7 Pro Hero and member of The Lurkers.

Name: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna
Summary: Shinmyoumaru Sukuna (少名 針妙丸 Sukuna Shinmyoumaru) is an inchling living in the Shining Needle Castle. Her ancestor Issun-Boushi exterminated an oni, and obtained the oni's treasure, the "Miracle Mallet".

Name: Shinsuke Takasugi
Summary: Shinsuke Takasugi (高杉 晋助, Takasugi Shinsuke) is the leader of the Kiheitai, an extremist group which he resurrected from the Joui Wars. The Kiheitai is a Joui faction bent on causing world destruction. He's one of the main characters who were originally meant to be a main antagonist of the series due to his first appearance.

Name: Shion Murasaki
Summary: Shion Murasaki is a young-looking girl who's a witch. It is told she randomly comes and goes from the Underworld Academy. She's a self-proclaimed adult and a self-proclaimed talented dark magician, though neither have been confirmed with certainty, so her childish appearance and mannerisms make her attempts to appear adult-like end up looking silly. Shion is generally playful, mischievous, smug and enjoys playing pranks on her comrades, not mindful of the consequences; she's often referred to as a kusogaki or "shitty brat". She tends to act proud or full of herself when casting her magic and she loves receiving attention, but some of her spells often malfunction and cause nefarious side effects to either herself or others. She's often seen bickering with Aqua Minato.

Name: Shockwave (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Eons after the Dynasty of Primes were vanquished, Cybertron fell into dark times. The AllSpark had been buried somewhere within Cybertron and been dismissed as a legend, and the planet itself lacked a star to orbit. As energy became more and more scarce, Cybertronians segregated into tribes. Shockwave chose to rally behind Sentinel Prime, who claimed to be descended from Primus himself. However, he faced opposition from the non-believer Thetacons, and Shockwave joined Megatron, Optimus, and several others in repelling their attacks. Ultimately, Sentinel Prime won the day, as he and Wheeljack were successful in locating the lost AllSpark and harnessing a new sun to orbit. This, however, did not please Shockwave. Now that the war was over, he was dissatisfied, and he no longer knew his purpose. This shocked his old friend, Megatron, and Shockwave explained that it was the journey he enjoyed, not the destination. Plus, well, that new sun was kind of bright.

Name: Shockwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Shockwave was left to watch Cybertron by Megatron long ago, but he would eventually follow the call of the AllSpark to Earth. Deadly efficient with a cold devotion to logic, Shockwave is a killing machine like few others, one of the very few who could rival Megatron, and quite popular amongst the Decepticons. In a way, some respect him enough to willingly work with him, while others idolize him to the point of avenging his death. Nevertheless, Shockwave is ready and willing to destroy whichever Autobots dare stand in his way with his arm-mounted AstroMag Cannon.

Name: Shoto Todoroki (Shoto)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Shoto Todoroki (轟焦凍 Todoroki Shōto), also known as Shoto (ショート Shōto), is one of main protagonists of the My Hero Academia manga and anime series.

Name: Showerhead
Summary: Showerhead was a Demon level threat and a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen attacking Garou alongside his teammates Super Mouse and Unihorn, before the three of them were incinerated by Overgrown Rover's energy blast.

Name: Shuichi Iguchi (Spinner)
Summary: Shuichi Iguchi (伊口秀一 Iguchi Shūichi), also known as Spinner (スピナー Supinā), is a villain affiliated with the League of Villains and was part of its Vanguard Action Squad. He is obsessed with the ideals of the Hero Killer: Stain, and is determined to revive Stain's vision of society through himself. His group later merged with the Meta Liberation Army to form the Paranormal Liberation Front, and became one of its nine lieutenants.

Name: Shura (One Piece)
Summary: One of God's priests, Shura was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Strings which had a three percent rate of survival.

Name: Shūhei Hisagi
Summary: Shūhei Hisagi (檜佐木ひさぎ 修しゅう兵へい, Hisagi Shūhei?) is the co-lieutenant of the 9th Division, formerly under Captain Kaname Tosen and currently under Captain Kensei Muguruma. He shares his position with Mashiro Kuna.

Name: Sideswipe (Michael Bay)
Summary: Sideswipe is true to his function of Warrior. Though proficient with guns, he prefers melee combat to ranged weapons and will employ any maneuver it takes to get close enough to the enemy to use his arm-mounted Cybertanium swords. His agile, wheel-legged form more than allows for this. His tactics are merciless and he's utterly unapologetic about this—war, after all, is messy.

Name: Snek
Summary: Snek, also known by his hero alias, Snakebite Snek is the Rank 37 A-Class Hero, he is in charge of F-City.

Name: Soga no Tojiko
Summary: Soga no Tojiko (蘇我 屠自古) is a vengeful spirit and one of Toyosatomimi no Miko's followers.

Name: Solf J. Kimblee
Summary: Solf J. Kimblee (ゾルフ・J・キンブリー, Zorufu J Kinburī), the Crimson Lotus Alchemist (紅蓮の錬金術師, Guren no Renkinjutsushi), sometimes referred to as the Crimson Alchemist, is a recurring antagonist in the Fullmetal Alchemist series. He is a former State Alchemist and special agent working under the direct orders of Führer King Bradley. Admittedly sadistic and arguably psychopathic, Kimblee was imprisoned in Central City for several years after his official involvement in the Ishval Civil War for having infamously turned his unique brand of combustion-based combat alchemy on people who were not on his government-approved kill list. Due to conspiratorial acts at the top of government, Kimblee is officially exonerated of his crimes so as to serve as the Führer's hidden left hand in the secret battles to come.

Name: Sora (Kingdom Hearts Manga)
Summary: Sora is the main protagonist of the Kingdom Hearts series, as well as a Keyblade master. He is an upbeat teenager who may seem simple-minded at times but is very aware of the importance of his quest. He possesses a strong sense of justice and an unrelenting heart. At times he is impulsive and quick to anger, but he is always sincere about what he says and does.

Name: Sougo Okita
Summary: Sougo Okita (沖田 総悟, Okita Sougo) is the former 1st Division Captain of the Shinsengumi and was a trainee at Kondou Isao's dojo in his youth. He is the younger brother of Okita Mitsuba who raised him after their parents passed away. He was one of the best swordsmen there even before joining the force where he is also recognized as one of the best swordsmen in the Shinsengumi.

Name: Soul Edge
Summary: Soul Edge also known as the Cursed Sword serves as the main weapon of Nightmare and overall the main antagonist of the entire Soulcalibur franchise. Soul Edge serves as the catalyst on basically all the events in the franchise. All Soul Edge cares for is the devouring of souls and pure destruction. It's release of the Evil Seed corrupted countless people across the world, driving them mad or even transforming them into monsters. Soul Edge's counterpart is Soul Calibur. Soul Edge is known to be able to shape shift in order to morph into a form that best fits its wielder.

Name: Soundwave (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Thousands of years ago, on Cybertron, Soundwave stood by Megatron's side on Unification Day; when a new era of Cybertronian government was ushered in that saw the planet ruled by two bodies—Megatron's Defense Force, of which Soundwave became a part, and Optimus's Science Division. Megatron's lust for power soon led him to claim dominion over Optimus, however, and Soundwave was silently present when Megatron summoned Optimus and made this declaration.

Name: Soundwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Soundwave, the Decepticon communications officer and one of Megatron's staunchest supporters, doesn't just master the frequencies that carry information across our planet, he revels in them. Stationed high in the upper atmosphere and capable of processing millions of data streams at once, he is fully capable of taking over communications on a planetary scale. Whether he uses this to direct civilization or destroy it remains to be seen.

Name: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic
Summary: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic (音速のソニック Onsoku no Sonikku) is a villain in the series, first appearing as a bodyguard hired by Mr. Monier. He grew up in a ninja village, honing his skills to near perfection. He views Saitama as his eternal rival, ever since the hero "defeated" him in a rather embarrassing manner.

Name: Spring Mustachio
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''Monster Raid Arc and Onwards'''
Summary: Spring Mustache (バネヒゲ, Banehige) is an A-Class Superhero, rank 28. He was partnered up with Golden Ball to investigate the monster rumor in Z-City.

Name: Staff Officer Black
Summary: Staff Officer Black (ブラック参謀) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and in the anime Dragon Ball, also making short appearances in Dragon Ball GT. He is an assistant of Commander Red and is not given much of a role until the near end of the Commander Red Saga. He is a tall, soft-spoken and quick-witted person. Black carries out Commander Red's orders and informs Commander Red of the current situations with the remaining Red Ribbon Army officers.

Name: Star Saber (Transformers: Prime)
Summary: An ancient and exalted weapon of the Primes, much of the Star Saber's abilities and origins remain a mystery to this day. Some say it was created out of the fusion of three bots and wielded itself, others say it was integrated into the frame of one of the Thirteen from creation, others still say that it was forged by Solus Prime from the core of a star.

Name: Starscream (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Many years before civil war broke out on Cybertron, Starscream was guarding a hatchling school trip when they were attacked by a subterranean monster. He was saved by Megatron and Shockwave, much to his irritation, but Megatron liked Starscream's "feisty" attitude, and saw a place for him in the future of Cybertron he hoped to shape. He later joined Megatron's Defense Force, and was very much at home, killing a malcontent that challenged the new order in spite of surrendering.

Name: Starscream (Michael Bay)
Summary: Starscream is a hero on the wrong side. Over the centuries he's come to believe both Optimus and Megatron have lost sight of what is best for the Cybertronian race, and simply pursue their own agendas. At some point, he came to the decision that, for the good of the species, a new leader must emerge, and he would be that leader. However, over time, he became as corrupt in his own way as Megatron, although he prefers subtlety and deception to Megatron's brute force. Now, what may once have been noble goals are buried under layers of self-interest, transforming Starscream into that which he supposedly despised.

Name: Starscream (Transformers Animated)
Summary: Starscream is the second-in-command of the Decepticon army. He is also a backstabbing and short-tempered soldier. His mission is to eliminate Megatron so he can become the one in charge instead. After being killed by Megatron for his traitorous deeds, he was accidentally imbued with a shard of the Allspark when it was destroyed by Optimus Prime, allowing him to continuously revive after being slain.

Name: Stinger
Summary: Stinger (スティンガー, Sutingā) is the A-Class Rank 10 professional hero for the Hero Association.

Name: Stinger (Michael Bay)
Summary: Stinger was one of the many models made by the factory KSI, modeled to be a "superior" version of Bumblebee. He would be deployed twice, first alongside Galvatron and later in the final battle in Shanghai, where he would be given sentience from Galvatron and fought against his predecessor, where he would meet his end.

Name: Subspace Army
Summary: The Subspace Army is an organization hailing from Subspace led by Tabuu. It is the main antagonistic force of the Subspace Emissary, acting as the source behind most threats faced by the heroes. Its goal is the absorption of the World of Trophy into Subspace, done by the usage of Subspace Bombs. As Tabuu cannot leave Subspace, most of the forces are located in the World of Trophy while Tabuu manipulates them from Subspace. Those include the Isle of the Ancients, the Halberd (Piloted by Mr. Game & Watch) and the Koopa Troop. Most relations within the army are quite fragile, however, as a lot of them are done either through force or trickery. Notably, almost no one knows the existence of Tabuu, as the latter hides behind Master Hand to communicate his orders to his commanders.

Name: Suguru Geto
Summary: An endless cycle of exorcism and consumption. Exorcise. Consume. It's a taste that nobody knows. The taste of a curse. Like ingesting a rag used to wipe up vomit. Exorcise. Consume. For whom? Ever since that day... It's been running through my head. What I saw was nothing out of the ordinary. A hideous evil known to everyone. Knowing that full well... I chose to protect them as a Jujutsu Sorcerer. Don't lose your way. Follow through with your duty as a Jujutsu Sorcerer... Monkeys...

Name: Suiryu (One Punch Man)
Summary: Suiryu (スイリュー, Suiryū) is a Martial Artist and user of the Void Fist. He is said to be a top contender in the Super Fight tournament. Initially, he is shown to be easygoing and laidback, only caring about the prize money for the tournament he was joining. His power and level of skill had also turned him into something akin to Saitama, who is always bored by the lack of challenge he receives from his opponents.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: Susan Strong
Summary: Susan Strong, otherwise known as X-J-7-7 is a major recurring protagonist in Adventure Time. Much like Finn, Susan is a simple minded, but heroic person. Susan is a very mysterious character, with her backstory being the driving focus of multiple episodes.

Name: Sweet Mask
Summary: Handsomely Masked Sweet Mask (イケメン仮面アマイマスク,Ikemen Kamen Amai Masuku) is the A-Class Rank 1 superhero, voluntarily staying in the position to stop those he deems unworthy from getting into S-Class. He is also a singer, model, and actor. Known for being the most popular member of the Hero Association.

Name: Swift Heart Rabbit
Summary: Swift Heart Rabbit is one of the Care Bear Cousins who has been a frequently recurring character since the first feature-length movie. True to her name, she is easily the fastest member of the Family, and she's not one to let people forget that. Her hubris and insistence to get things done as quickly as possible frequently lead to much needed lessons in humility. Despite her flaws, she's quick to get back up, and will always be there to lend her speed and a helping hand where she can.

Name: Taishiro Toyomitsu (Fat Gum)
Summary: Taishiro Toyomitsu (豊満太志郎 Toyomitsu Taishirō), also known as Fat Gum, is a Pro Hero and was part of the group sent to rescue Eri during the Hero Internship Arc. Fat Gum is a very kind and cheerful individual who always seems to be hungry, as he's rarely seen without a snack on his person.

Name: Takako Uro
Summary: Silence! "Live for others"! "You don't need to be anybody special"! The only ones who say that are people who have already achieved something!

Name: Tamaki Amajiki (Suneater)
Summary: Tamaki Amajiki (天喰 環 Amajiki Tamaki), also known as Suneater (サンイーター San'ītā), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Tanktop Master
Summary: Tanktop Master (タンクトップマスター, Tankutoppu Masutā) is the S-Class Rank 16 hero. He is the eldest and most powerful of the Tanktop brothers, as well as the most level-headed and wise. He plays a minor role in the Alien Invasion arc and a greater role in the Hero Hunt arc. Tanktop Master battles Garou to avenge Tanktop Vegetarian, and proves to be superior. However, upon seeing Garou's state, along with advice from Mumen Rider, he decides to spare the human monster. Unfortunately, once Garou had seen through Tanktop Master's attacks, he went back on the offense and defeated the hero. In the hospital, Tanktop Master tells Saitama that Garou's fighting style makes him especially deadly to heroes.

Name: Tenderheart Bear (Original)
Summary: Tenderheart Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared as an illustration on American Greetings greeting cards in August 1982. Exemplifying the very best qualities of the Care Bears, Tenderheart is usually considered the de facto leader of the gang. He frequently organizes their efforts to help spread love and care around the world, and keep their own home of Care-a-Lot in working shape. He is responsible for initiating new members into the Care Bear Family by bestowing their very own belly symbols, and has been directly involved in nearly every major event in their history.

Name: Teru Momijiyama (Shy)
Key: '''Beginning of Series to Yuri Orphanage Arc''' | '''Tokyo Recapture arc'''
Summary: Teru Momijiyama (紅葉山テル, Momijiyama Teru), better known as Shy (シャイ Shai), is the main protagonist of the manga series SHY. Living in a world where every country has a hero to protect it. She is a middle school student and the successor to her older sister Mei Momijiyama, the previous Hero of Japan. After her passing, her Heart Shift Bracelets were given to her at her funeral. After which she chose to use the Bracelets to become Japan's new hero, and to live up to her sister's legacy. Even though she struggles with talking to crowds, or even just doing her job as a hero.

Name: Teruki Hanazawa
Summary: Teruki Hanazawa is a former antagonist and current ally of Mob. He used to be an arrogant and proud esper who believed he was the star protagonist of his life. This mainly stems from his belief that only he had the power of an esper to make his life easier. But his encounter with Mob did not just change his beliefs but also his hairstyle.

Name: Tetsucabra
Summary: Tetsucabra is the first Amphibian fought in Monster Hunter 4. It is a large, frog-like monster.

Name: The Console (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: The Game Child (or simply The Console) is a handheld console in The Amazing World of Gumball, serving as an obvious spoof of the Nintendo Game Boy. It was bought by Richard Watterson from The Awesome Store in the episode The Console. It eventually warped the entire town of Elmore into a video game, trapping Gumball, Darwin, Anais, and everybody else.
ID: The Console (The Amazing World of Gumball)-TheAmazingWorldofGumball-7

Name: The Demi-Hollow
Summary: The Demi-Hollow was previously a Jibakurei before he was transformed into a Hollow after Don Kanoji accidentally destroyed his Chain of Fate, was eventually killed and cleansed by Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: The Devourer
Summary: The Devourer is a monster from Fortnite: Battle Royale, it has been a prominent part of the story during season 9 of the game, having been first spotted in Polar Peak, and has since broke out of the glacier and battled the Mecha Team Leader.

Name: The Driller
Summary: The Driller is a large cybertronian beast which is under the command of Shockwave. It and Shockwave crashed and were frozen on Earth at an unknown period and they were later freed by Megatron. It was later sent with Shockwave to intercept Optimus at Chernobyl and steal an engine part from the Ark. After that, it ventured to Chicago with Shockwave and attempted to kill some soldiers that were hiding in a skyscraper, though it was killed by Optimus in the process.

Name: The End (Minecraft)
Summary: The End is a dark, space-like dimension which the player travels to through the use of an Ender Portal. The dimension is filled with end stone islands surrounded by a pitch-black void, a void similar to that found beneath the Overworld as well as both above and below the Nether.

Name: The Final Guardian
Summary: The Final Guardian is a Guardian Knack faces towards the end of the game. It is a titanic creature made up of stone that protects the Giant Orb. It is capable of becoming one with the Giant Orb, making it one of the biggest characters in the first game.

Name: The Foundation (Fortnite)
Summary: The Foundation is the founder and leader of the Seven. He is an organic entity in a suit that has been keeping him alive in infinite realities and in the Nothing beyond them. He has a lot of knowledge about The Zero Point and The Cube. The Foundation assisted Agent Jones in fixing the Zero Point after it was nearly absorbed by Galactus, and after the initial invasion of the Last Reality, eventually makes his way back to flip the Athena Island to the other side.

Name: The Last Prime (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: The Last Prime was the last surviving member of the Dynasty of Primes, who were the first Transformers created by the Allspark. He used the last remnants of his power and energy to seal away the Fallen and created a tomb to hide the Matrix, the key to the Star Harvester.

Name: The Mecha
Summary: The Mecha is a large robot introduced in Season 9 of Fortnite: Battle Royale. Serving as a protagonist that would eventually contend with, and overcome The Devourer.

Name: The Menos Grande
Summary: The Menos Grande is seemingly a special type of Hollow, being compared similar to that of a Gillian Menos Grande, was eventually killed and erased by Ryūken Ishida

Name: The Player (Minecraft)
Summary: The Player is the protagonist of Minecraft. Known as either Steve or Alex depending on the player's choice, they are a lone miner in an endless blocky world, trying their best to survive.

Name: The Spirit (Care Bears)
Summary: The Spirit is the primary antagonist of the first Care Bears feature film. While Nicholas Cherrywood was cleaning out the old trunk which belonged to the magician, Mr. Fettuccine, he stumbled upon an ancient book of spells. The book spoke to him from within its pages and beckoned him to open it, offering the fame and notoriety he had been seeking all his life. Upon doing so, he met The Spirit. This would initiate their venture to render everyone in the world just as cold and uncaring as The Spirit herself.

Name: The Three Crows
Summary: The Three Crows were Gouketsu's disciples back before any of them had become monsterfied. After the monsterfication process took place they all transformed into three identical-looking monsterized crows, completely devoid of their individual personalities. The three first appeared alongside their master during the monster raid where they attacked the Super Fight tournament to recruit new members for the Monster Association. After incapacitating several martial artists, the three were soundly dispatched and killed by Suiryu, Lightning Max and Snek.

Name: Thermobaric missile (Resident Evil)
Summary: The thermobaric missile is used to blow up Raccoon City in an attempt to stop the infection from spreading.

Name: Tina Rex
Summary: Tina Rex is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is a feared bully at Elmore Junior High and lives at the local junkyard with her father. Despite being a bully, it has been hinted that Tina is sensitive and insecure deep down. In "The Fight", it was revealed Tina bullied Gumball because she thinks of him as a friend; in fact, she only acts like a monster because she looks like one and is treated as such. Tina is the love interest of Hector Jötunheim.

Name: Tommy Oliver (Turbo)
Summary: Dimetria: That was cutting it very close, Rangers.

Name: Tonraq
Summary: Tonraq is a powerful waterbending master and chief of the Southern Water Tribe. Born as heir to the chief of the Water Tribes, he is the older brother of Unalaq. Growing up in the Northern Water Tribe, Tonraq served as the Northern military's general in his youth, though was banished and disinherited following the destruction of a sacred spiritual forest at his hands.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Toph Beifong
Summary: Toph Beifong is an earthbending master, one of the most powerful of her time, and the discoverer of metalbending. Blind since birth, Toph was constantly treated condescendingly because of her disability, particularly by her overprotective parents, Lao and Poppy Beifong. Upon discovering badgermoles, earthbending animals who were also blind, she learned how to use earthbending as an extension of her senses. This gave her the ability to "see" every vibration that passes through the ground. She became Avatar Aang's earthbending teacher.

Name: Toushirou Hijikata
Summary: Toushirou Hijikata (土方 十四郎, Hijikata Tōshirō) is currently the Vice-Commander of the Shinsengumi. He is commonly known as the Demonic Vice-Commander (鬼の副長, Oni no Fukucho), striking fear into his enemies and subordinates (with the exceptions of Isao Kondou and Sougo Okita).

Name: Tsukune Aono
Summary: Tsukune Aono (nicknamed Tsuki by his cousin Kyouko) is a former human and the main protagonist of the Rosario + Vampire series. He is mistakenly enrolled in Yokai Academy, a high school dedicated to teaching monsters to peacefully live alongside humans in disguise, where he meets and falls in love with Moka Akashiya, a vampire who takes a mutual interest in him and the sweet flavor of his blood. Tsukune becomes a member of the school’s Newspaper Club and eventually befriends several monster girls, including Kurumu Kurono, Yukari Sendo, Ruby Tojo, and Mizore Shirayuki—all of whom become obsessed with him—as well as Kokoa Shuzen, Moka’s younger half-sister. He also makes friends with several male monsters such as Ginei Morioka, Hokuto Kaneshiro, Fang-Fang Huang, and Haiji Miyamoto. They support Tsukune’s belief that monsters and humans can coexist and be more than just enemies, their friendship with him being a prime example of that sentiment.

Name: Tsukuyo
Summary: Tsukuyo (月詠), also known as the Death God Courtesan (死神太夫, shinigami tayuu), is a highly skilled ninja, specializing in the usage of kunai, having trained under the infamous assassin and then-Leader of Hyakka, Jiraia. She is the current leader of the Hyakka Yoshiwara's guardians (吉原自警団「百華」の頭), an all-female law enforcement squad formerly deployed by Housen.

Name: Tsuyu Asui (Froppy)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Tsuyu Asui (蛙吹梅雨 Asui Tsuyu), also known as Froppy (フロッピー Furoppī), is a member of Class 1-A at U.A. High School. She's known for her stoic and unflappable attitude, being able to work well under pressure, contrasting heavily against her far more emotional classmates.

Name: Ultra Magnus (Transformers: Prime)
Summary: An exalted leader of the Autobot cause and one of Optimus Prime's closest lieutenants, Ultra Magnus has been an instrumental asset in the fight against the Decepticons, as both a highly competent fighter and tactical genius, and is rightfully feared by them as the next most dangerous bot one could meet, bar only his commander.

Name: Unihorn
Summary: Unihorn was a Demon level threat and a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen attacking Garou alongside his teammates Super Mouse and Showerhead, before being snapped to pieces by Overgrown Rover

Name: Uragaan
Summary: Uragaans are Brute Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter 3.

Name: Uraume
Summary: nan

Name: Urgence Evergreen
Summary: Urgence Evergreen was the previous Ice Elemental, and one of the few beings who lived before the Mushroom Bomb, he was an eccentric elemental who created the Ice Crown in an attempt of stopping the Catalyst Comet.

Name: Urouge
Summary: Urouge, also known as Mad Monk, is a pirate who hails from a sky island and is the captain of the Fallen Monk Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation " (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 108,000,000.

Name: Uryū Ishida
Summary: Uryu Ishida (石いし田だ 雨う竜りゅう, Ishida Uryū?) is a Gemischt Quincy residing in Karakura Town. He is a doctor at Karakura Hospital, and a friend of Ichigo Kurosaki. He is also a former member of the Wandenreich with the designation "A" - "Antithesis", one of Yhwach's "Schutzstaffel" (親衛隊シュッツシュタッフェル, Shuttsushutafferu?), and his future successor.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Utsuro
Summary: Utsuro (虚) was an immortal being born with the ability to absorb a high amount of Altana which granted him his ageless immortality and regenerative capabilities.

Name: Vaccine Man
Summary: Vaccine Man (ワクチンマン, Wakuchin Man) is a Mysterious Being born due to the massive pollution released across the Earth by human beings, on top of the first monster we're introduced to in the series. According to him, he was created as an incarnation of nature's wrath, meant to wipe out humanity and thus effectively vaccinate the earth against future infections.

Name: Vacuuma
Summary: Vacuuma was a member of the Monster Association. He was first seen absorbing several weaker monsters into his trunk to gain their abilities, before being killed by Pri-Pri-Prisoner.

Name: Van Hohenheim
Summary: Van Hohenheim (ヴァン・ホーエンハイム, Ban Hōenhaimu) is the estranged father of Edward and Alphonse Elric. Previously, he had been known only as Slave No. 23. However, the Homunculus, grateful for the blood that brought him into the world and the unwavering friendship, bestowed upon the slave the gifts of a proper name, education, freedom, and ultimately, a body that never decays. Nevertheless, the freed slave, now known as Hohenheim, strongly condemned the gift of immortality that cost countless lives. Since then, Hohenheim has turned bitterly against Homunculus, sworn to end his agonizing immortality, and set free all the souls trapped within their bodies. Likewise, to prevent a similar tragedy from ever happening again.

Name: Victor Chevalier
Summary: Victor Chevalier is a member of the United Nations and the leader and founder of it's armed forces: The Raven Unit.

Name: Victor von Gerdenheim
Summary: Victor von Gerdenheim is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He is the culmination of the homonymus professor's dream. Professor Gerdenheim spent 30 years researching a way to revive dead cells and ultimately completed his creation: A body composed by various pieces sewn together, with various other components added to it, such as an electrostatic organic material, a charged liquid flowing through it and an electrode and a pacemaker connected to the heart. The last step was provide stimulation with a high voltage current, something that could be achieved only by using a natural lightning.

Name: Volgin
Summary: Yevgeny Borisovich Volgin was a Stalinist colonel who attempted to seize control of the Soviet Union by ousting Khrushchev and installing Brezhnev in his place. He was the son of Boris Volgin, a treasurer for the Philosophers. After his death, Volgin acquired their vast fortune, which his father had stolen, granting him access to what were practically limitless funds. With this money, Volgin constructed the Groznyj Grad fort and began building the Shagohod, a nuclear-armed tank designed by Nikolai Stepanovich Sokolov.

Name: Wanze
Summary: Wanze is a member of the CP7 and a cook, specializing in making ramen noodles, introduced as an antagonist in the Enies Lobby arc. He's a man that takes pride in his abilities and appears to be quite confident in them, though he can be a bit dense and short tempered. One of the main attribute to Wanze is that his facial expression seems to never change, even when he claims to be scared, which often lead to the annoyance and irritation of his enemies.

Name: Warden (Minecraft)
Summary: The Warden is an extremely powerful hostile mob that is native to the Deep Dark biome and its ancient cities. It is thought that the Wardens patrol these cities to guard whatever treasures lie inside. Their most distinguishable feature is their blindness - they instead determine where their victims are through their heightened senses of sound and smell.

Name: Waspinator (Beast Wars Cartoon)
Summary: Waspinator is a Predacon and the "red-shirt" of the army; he works as a recon unit, checking out and spying on their enemies, the Maximals.

Name: Watchdog Man
Summary: Watchdog Man (番犬マン Banken-man) holds the 12th rank among the S-Class Heroes of the Hero Association. Despite his silly appearance, he is widely feared and respected worldwide. As the vigilant protector of Q-city, Watchdog Man actively hunts down monsters within his jurisdiction and appears to effortlessly handle any challenges that come his way. His formidable reputation deters almost everyone from challenging him. However, the self-proclaimed "hero hunter" Garou, though fatigued, dared to confront him but was swiftly overpowered and forced to retreat.

Name: William (The Amazing World of Gumball)
Summary: William is a minor recurring character in The Amazing World of Gumball.

Name: Winter Schnee
Summary: Winter Schnee is a character in RWBY and the elder sister of Weiss Schnee. Despite being the eldest child, Winter's right to inherit the Schnee Dust Company was abdicated upon her decision to join the Atlas Military. At first glance, Winter appears to be cold, dignified, and distant, preferring to keep her emotions subdued and speaking in a very high-class, eloquent, almost robotic fashion. However, when interacting with Weiss, she smiles and shows that she cares about her younger sister's life and well-being. Although she strives to keep her emotions in check, she can be rather hot-headed at times. Once she becomes angry, she drops her dignified ladylike demeanor and loses all restraint. Winter consistently wrestles with her emotions, never letting them overpower her, yet still allowing them to guide her on what she believes to be a righteous path.

Name: Wish Bear (Original)
Summary: Wish Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. As one can infer from her name, she is tasked with making sure the wishes of everyone on Earth, and often even those of the Care Bear Family, come true. Sometimes this can be accomplished by her own supernatural wish granting abilities; other times she prefers to work towards seeing the wishes of others and even herself come to light.

Name: Wither
Summary: The Wither is a floating, three-headed powerful boss mob, and is the second boss mob to be added to Minecraft after the Ender Dragon. It can be summoned by Steve via placing three Wither Skulls on top of Soul Sand in a T pattern.

Name: Wreckage (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Cold, distant, quiet among Decepticons, Wreckage is the indiscriminate, hot-blooded, stone-cold destroyer, a bringer of destruction, and a counterpart to the hot-wired Brawl. Deliberate and methodical in his attacks, he enjoys getting up close and personal to his targets and watching his foes squirm in agony as his twin swords cut deep below their armor. Circuits popping and vital processors sizzling to uselessness are the music he longs to make, and none of the Decepticons can argue with his taste for making Autobots suffer.

Name: Wyper
Summary: "Berserker" Wyper is a Shandian, who are a group of natives from the Blue Sea blasted into Skypeia, fighting to reclaim hid homeland for his people who were unjustly ousted from it by the Skypeians. He was the leader of the Shandia warriors fighting to take Upper Yard back from Enel. He is the direct descendant of Kalgara. After the time-skip, he is one of God's Guards.

Name: Wyvern (RWBY)
Summary: The Wyvern is a giant, flying Creature of Grimm capable of summoning other Grimm. It first appeared in "Battle of Beacon".

Name: X Drake
Summary: X Drake (read as "Diez Drake") is a former Marine rear admiral from North Blue who has become a pirate under the epithet of the "Red Flag". He is one of twelve pirates referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly as the "Eleven Supernovas"), and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 222,000,000.

Name: Yama (One Piece)
Summary: The Commander of Enel's Divine Soldiers who moves lightly despite his great size. Yama is fanatically loyal to Enel to the point he will even reprimand The Priests if he feels like they’re being disrespectful in his god’s presence. He also has no interest in the past. During his fight with Robin, he kept mercilessly destroying the ancient ruins, thus earning her wrath and spurring her to defeat him.

Name: Yamame Kurodani
Summary: Yamame Kurodani (黒谷 ヤマメ) is a tsuchigumo - an earth spider, that lives in the entrance to the Underworld.

Name: Yasutora Sado (Chad)
Key: '''Substitute Shinigami Arc''' | '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Arrancar Arc''' | '''Lost Agent Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War Arc'''
Summary: Yasutora Sado (茶渡 泰虎, Sado Yasutora), also known as Chad (チャド, Chado) is a human teenager who lives in Karakura Town. He is a student at Karakura High School, where he is in the same class as Ichigo Kurosaki.

Name: Yawara Chatora (Tiger)
Summary: Yawara Chatora (茶ちゃ虎とら柔やわら Chatora Yawara), also known as Tiger (虎とら Tora), is a Pro Hero and member of the Wild, Wild Pussycats.

Name: Yian Garuga
Summary: Yian Garugas are Bird Wyverns introduced in Monster Hunter Freedom.

Name: Yorozu
Summary: Cut It!! Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut, Cut Me Open! Cut My Love Buried In This Flesh!! And See It With Your Own Eyes!

Name: Yoshika Miyako
Summary: Yoshika Miyako is a Jiang Shi that has been brought back to life by her mistress, Seiga Kaku. She mainly wanders around the cemetery and guards it, with no particular reasons.

Name: Yoshimitsu (Tekken)
Summary: Yoshimitsu is the head of the Manji Clan, a modern group of ninjas who focus their efforts on stealing from the rich to support the poor. He is a good friend of the genius Doctor Bosconovitch.

Name: Youkai Mountain
Summary: The Youkai Mountain is an important landmark in Gensokyo and home to several youkai, as per its name. The mountain covers several smaller locations such as the Giant Toad's Pond, the Moriya Shrine, the Genbu Ravine and the Untrodden Valley.

Name: Yuga Aoyama (Can't Stop Twinkling)
Summary: Yuga Aoyama (青山優雅 Aoyama Yūga), also known as Can't Stop Twinkling (キャント・ストップ・トゥインクリング Kyanto Sutoppu Tuinkuringu), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. He is flamboyant and loves the spotlight, but is prone to cracking under pressure and is somewhat cowardly. Nevertheless, he does pitch in when push comes to shove.

Name: Yuji Itadori
Key: '''Fearsome Womb Arc to Kyoto Goodwill Event (Pre-Chapter 37)''' | '''Kyoto Goodwill Event (Post-Chapter 37) to Shibuya Incident''' | '''Itadori's Extermination Arc to Culling Game''' | '''Shinjuku Showdown Arc'''
Summary: You know... up until recently I thought I should simply live to fulfill my role as I understood it. I thought if I died like that, I could at least consider this a proper death. But know... I feel like that's not entirely right. Walking the dog, raising a family, any sort of role like that is just fine. Even if you don't have anything like that, as long as you can eat, shit and sleep. Even if you're stuck in bed sick, even if you spent all your life with no connections and nothing remains of you... More than memories made in one's image, it's within the little, tiny fragments that remain drifting off, where the value of life lies. It never had anything to do with the ways people die. I just couldn't ever forgive those who acted as if that value didn't exist. Sukuna... I loathe you. Humans aren't tools. We aren't born with any set role. Which is to say... I don't know. I don't know whether humans are fundamentally good or evil. I could very well be doing the wrong thing here. So I thought I should at least let you see the humanity of someone other than yourself. Of someone you see no value in

Name: Yuki Tsukumo
Summary: What kind of woman is your type?

Name: Yuki Yoshida
Summary: Yuki Yoshida is a character in The Amazing World of Gumball. She is Masami's mother, and Nicole Watterson's old friend/nemesis.

Name: Yumichika Ayasegawa
Key: '''Soul Society Arc''' | '''Early Arrancar Arc''' | '''Late Arrancar Arc''' | '''Thousand Year Blood War'''
Summary: Yumichika Ayasegawa (綾あや瀬せ川がわ 弓ゆみ親ちか, Ayasegawa Yumichika?) is the 3rd Seat officer and former 5th Seat officer in the 11th Division of the Gotei 13, under Captain Kenpachi Zaraki.

Name: Yuta Okkotsu
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Zala (Miss Doublefinger)
Summary: Zala, better known by her alias Miss Doublefinger, was the second highest ranking female agent in the secret organization known as Baroque Works. As an officer agent, she was partnered with Mr. 1. Like her partner, she's calm and professional, although feels sorry for Nami's awkwardness with her new weapon. She has eaten the Toge Toge no Mi which gives her the ability to grow spikes able to pierce walls on all her body or turn her body parts in big spikes.

Name: Zinogre
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | High 8-C | High 6-C | 7-B

Name: Zombie (Minecraft)
Summary: The Zombie is a hostile mob and the most common and basic enemy of the sandbox video game, Minecraft. They come out only at night, and attack local villages, killing Villagers and often turning them into Zombie Villagers.

Name: Zombieman
Summary: Zombieman is the S-Class Rank 8 superhero for the Hero Association. He was created by the founder of the House of Evolution, Dr. Genus.

Name: Zone Angel
Summary: Zone Angel (ゾーンエンジェル), the real name Hotaru Sakimori (防人 螢 Sakimori Hotaru), is a Seijin created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter.

Name: Zone Fighter
Key: '''Hikari''' | '''Zone Fighter (During the First Episodes)''' | '''Zone Fighter (End of the Series)'''
Summary: After their home planet, Peaceland was destroyed by the Garoga Baron. The Zone family fled to earth in order to seek shelter. Calling themselves the Sakimori family, the Zone family tried to start a new peaceful life, the oldest son, Hikaru Sakimori even finds a job working as a test driver for cars.

Name: Zone Junior
Summary: Zone Junior (Real Name: Akira Sakimori) is the youngest and third member of the Zone Fighter team, brother of Zone Fighter and Zone Angel, and the weakest member of the Zone Fighter team. Although the weakest in the Zone Fighter team he is still strong enough to defeat foes the size of human adults. Like his family he is a alien from the destroyed planet Peaceland, he now protects the earth so it doesn't suffer the same fate. Being a child he's unskilled in combat, meaning he still has much to learn about it. Zone Junior is also extremely quick, being able to dodge and out run most characters. He like his sister is various mysterious and not much is known about him. If he and his sister are both in superhero form, they can summon a spacecraft called Smokey to aid them. Zone Junior lacks a lot abilities due to his young age, but with time he will be able to gain the abilities of both his sister and brother. Zone Junior is overall a small, unskilled, but strong young hero who seeks to protect the earth.

Name: Zuko
Summary: Even as the prince of the Fire Nation, Zuko has always struggled in life, particularly in matching his prodigy sister Azula and getting his father's acknowledgment. This came to a head when Ozai punished him for a perceived slight by horrifically burning his face and sending him into exile, refusing to let him return until he had captured the Avatar. (This was intended to be an impossible task, since Aang had been missing for a century). Determined to prove his worth to his father, Zuko hunted Aang across the world for the first season while trying to find his own destiny. Eventually, Zuko betrays Iroh and helps Azula take over Ba Sing Se. Granted amnesty for his actions, Zuko is finally allowed to come home. He has his honor restored, the adoration of a nation, the love of his life, and the respect of his father. And he finds himself lacking. After some soul-searching, Zuko finally realizes what Iroh had always tried to teach him. After calling out Ozai for controlling him, making him feel worthless, burning his face, banishing him for three years and generally being an evil, contemptible douchebag, Zuko defects to join the Gaang as Aang's Firebending teacher. Though initially mistrusted, grudges dissolve into friendships and Zuko soon becomes a core member of the group. At the end of the series, Zuko becomes the new Fire Lord and strives to rebuild the world into an era of peace. And hopefully find his mother.

Name: Absalom (One Piece)
Summary: Absalom, also known as “Absalom of the Graveyard”, was the leader of the Zombie Soldiers and Zombie Generals of Thriller Bark and a member of the Mysterious Four before Gekko Moriah's defeat. He was also a well-known pervert, unashamed of the idea of sexual harassment or assault as he desperately seeks a woman to be his bride, specifically, a human one that was too weak to fight off his advances; the zombies under his command nickname him "Erosalom" due to his highly amorous nature, despite him being their leader.

Name: Aqua Minato
Summary: Aqua Minato is a "marine maid-styled virtual maid". She's a kind and sweet girl, who's always there to help her friends or those in need in acts of selflessness. She's fairly childish and airheaded, so while she enjoys pulling pranks, she often gets pranked instead. Likely out of a hobby of hers, she cosplays as a maid and she isn't actually one. She can fly with her twintails, which are also somehow detachable from her head. She's hopelessly infatuated with Okayu Nekomata. She's often seen bickering with Shion Murasaki.

Name: Ayame Nakiri
Summary: Ayame Nakiri is an oni, a type of demon, has two horns growing out of her forehead and is over 1500 years old. She's from the Underworld Academy, of which she's the respected student council president, and is a trained swordswoman who wields two katanas, Rakshasa and Asura. Despite her status, she's fairly chaotic and uncontrollable, tends to act in nonsensical ways, and enjoys pranking people with will-o’-the-wisps. She's also fairly airheaded and easily excitable, which sometimes causes trouble.

Name: Bandit Princess
Summary: Bandit Princess is a minor antagonist in Adventure Time and the primary antagonist in the episode I am a Sword! She is a villainous princess of an unknown kingdom who found the Finn Sword after he lost it. Much of Bandit Princess' personality and origin is currently unknown, however she appears to be a cartoonishly evil character, slaying various inhabitants of Ooo, sacking their villages and stealing their wealth .

Name: Bella Noche
Summary: Bella Noche is a minor antagonist in Adventure Time, appearing in the episode, "Betty". Her true form originally existed in another dimension, before being freed through a ritual performed by a group of wizards in Wizard City. However, she would be defeated by Betty by being kicked in the face.

Name: Bentham (Mr. 2 Bon Clay)
Summary: Bentham, also known by his epithet "Bentham of the Wild" and his alias Mr. 2 Bon Clay, is a former officer agent of Baroque Works and an okama (a Japanese slang term for a transvestite). Strangely enough, he was the only higher up member that lacks a female partner of the same rank. Possibly due to believing he fits the role of both male and female, probably due to his powers and lifestyle as a self-proclaimed okama. He was thus assigned both a number and a holiday for his code name.

Name: Betty Grof
Summary: Betty Grof was once a kind and collected young woman who was a budding Antiquarian, as well as the fiance to Simon Petrikov. Though little of her personality has been shown, she has been depicted as being very strong willed and tough, as well as determined and dedicated to protecting her boyfriend. After Simon first went mad with the crown, she ran to find safety, only to force herself through a portal to the future to be with Simon once again.

Name: Blueno
Summary: Blueno is one of the members of CP9.

Name: Brook
Summary: Brook is the crew's musician. He ate the Revive-Revive Fruit (Yomi Yomi no Mi), which enabled his spirit to reanimate his corpse after he died. Unfortunately, after his death, his spirit got lost for an entire year before finding his body, and it had decayed into a skeleton. He later developed the ability to control his own soul. Deprived of his shadow by the Warlord of the Sea, Gecko Moria, he was adrift within the gloomy Florian Triangle until he met the Straw Hats by chance.

Name: Calliope Mori (Holo no Graffiti)
Summary: Calliope Mori is Death-sensei's, the Grim Reaper's, first apprentice. Due to modern medical care causing a decline in the reaping business, Calliope decided to become a VTuber to harvest souls instead, and pursue a music career. Calliope is a reaper herself, who has existed since the dawn of life.

Name: Chatsberry
Summary: Chatsberry is the Candy Elemental, and one of the beings that have existed before the Mushroom War. He, along with the other Elementals of his time, was frozen by Urgence Evergreen after trying to stop him. It is unknown what happened to Chatsberry after that, but it is likely that he perished when the Catalyst Comet arrived.

Name: Cinnamon Bun
Summary: Cinnamon Bun is a major recurring character in Adventure Time. Originally a dim witted but friendly servant and surrogate son of Princess Bubblegum, Cinnamon Bun was infamous for his childish antics and clumsy behavior, often making huge mistakes or even destroying buildings in his misguided attempts to be cool. After defecting to the Flame Kingdom, Cinnamon Bun matured and grew greatly, but also became much more cynical and confused about his life.

Name: Daz Bonez (Mr. 1)
Summary: Daz Bonez is a former bounty hunter who joined Baroque Works and was the highest ranked male Officer Agent and the strongest under Crocodile himself. His codename was Mr. 1 and his partner was Miss Doublefinger.

Name: Dhalsim
Summary: Dhalsim is a video game character from the Street Fighter series of fighting games. Dhalsim is famous throughout the Street Fighter series for his stretchy, lanky body and fire attacks.

Name: Dimple
Summary: Dimple is an on and off again antagonist and supporting character in the Mob Psycho 100 anime/manga series. He is a spirit whose goal is to become a god through gathering individuals in a cult around himself, a goal which put him at odds with espers such as Keiji Mogami and Shigeo Kageyama on multiple occasions.

Name: Earl of Lemongrab (Original)
Summary: Earl of Lemongrab is a recurring character in Adventure Time. He first appears in the episode Too Young. He is the high-strung, overly-zealous, obnoxious, stubborn ruler of the Earldom of Lemongrab, and the heir to the Candy Kingdom. It is possible that he is no longer heir to the throne because as of Hot Diggity Doom, the Candy Kingdom is now a democracy. He is the creation of Princess Bubblegum and the first of her experiments to go wrong. He was able to usurp the throne of the Candy Kingdom on the technicality of Bubblegum's de-aging. Once Princess Bubblegum was 18 again, she fires him, and he returns to Lemongrab.

Name: Earl of Lemongrab 3
Summary: Earl of Lemongrab 3 is the third Earl of Lemongrab, created by Princess Bubblegum from the parts of the original Lemongrab, Lemongrab 2 and various Lemon People. The current Lemongrab now resides in Castle Lemongrab, where he continues ruling the Earldom and its people. He retains at least some of his earlier incarnations memories, if not all of them.

Name: Finn the Human
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Finn the Human, real name Finn Mertens is the main character of Adventure Time. He, along with his adoptive brother Jake the Dog are the loyal champions of the Candy Kingdom. Finn vowed to keep the Kingdom and its residence safe at all cost. Finn is a very loyal and kind person, always giving a helping hand to those who need it.

Name: Flame Queen
Summary: Flame Princess (first name Phoebe and occasionally called FP) is the princess and ruler of the Fire Kingdom, as well as Finn's ex-girlfriend. When Jake asks Flambo if he knows any princesses that are Finn's age so he can fix his broken heart, he introduces Jake to Flame Princess. Flame Princess was locked away in a lantern in the main chamber of the Fire Kingdom when Jake first encounters her. It is later revealed that her father, the Flame King, put her there on Princess Bubblegum's advice when she was an infant, and she did not come out for 14 years. She has a short temper, trust issues, and a heat core that can destroy the world if overblown with emotions.

Name: Franky
Key: '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: "Iron Man" Franky, real name Cutty Flam, is the shipwright of the Straw Hat Pirates under captain Monkey D. Luffy. As his epithet implies, he is a cyborg, having rebuilt his own body from iron scraps after he was run over by a sea train. He was formerly a member of a criminal shipbreaking gang called the Franky Family, which operated in the shipbuilders' haven of Water 7. He encountered the Straw Hats when he and the Franky Family brutally beat Usopp and stole a great deal of money from the crew while they were attempting to get their boat fixed on the island. However, his interests subsequently aligned with the Straw Hats' when the secret government organization CP9 kidnapped both him and their crewmate Nico Robin in a bid to construct the ancient superweapon Pluton, which he owned the blueprints to. After escaping the clutches of CP9, Franky decided to join their crew, drawn by their dedication to both their ship and their fellow crewmen.

Name: Fukurou
Summary: Fukuro was a member of the CP9. He was first introduced in the Enies Lobby Arc. Like most One Piece characters, Fukuro has a noticeable quirk and his is that he has a big mouth (both figuratively and literally), such as revealing that Jabra’s girlfriend had dumped him.

Name: Galdino (Mr. 3)
Summary: Galdino, also known by his epithet “Loan Shark Galdino” and his alias Mr. 3, is a former officer agent, alongside his former partner Miss Goldenweek. He is regarded as the smartest of the officers and only got the position of "Mr. 3" because of that. He has eaten the Doru Doru no Mi which allows him to create and control candle wax at will.

Name: Goliad
Summary: Goliad was a character who appeared in the episode of the same name in Adventure Time. She was a candy sphinx created by Princess Bubblegum to rule the kingdom if she were to ever die. Despite being so young, Goliad is an immensely powerful telepath who intended to rule the entire Candy Kingdom through her telepathy.

Name: Haato Akai
Summary: Haato Akai is schoolgirl who loves all cute things, particularyl red ribbons and heart shapes, which she wears as accessories. She's sweet and attentionate, but tends to act like a tsundere. In spite of that, chaos seems to follow wherever she goes, as she frequently brushes aside common sense. She rides the line between purity and insanity, and is sometimes shown performing various odd jobs. Haato's chaotic nature is called Haachama, often treated like a different entity from Haato. She frequently says her catchphrase Haachama-chama~!. She's infamous for being a terrible cook.

Name: Humandrill
Summary: A Humandrill is a type of baboon with a high learning ability that inhabits Kuraigana Island, in the "Grand Line".

Name: Hyouzou
Summary: Hyouzou is a poisonous blue-ringed octopus merman. Prior to his imprisonment, he was a mercenary and working as the New Fish-Man Pirates' assassin, and later became one of the officers. Hyouzou was also known as the strongest swordsman on Fish-Man Island.

Name: Ice King (Adventure Time)
Summary: The Ice King, also known as Simon Petrikov was a main recurring antagonist in Adventure Time, though now is considered something similar to a protagonist and was reverted back into his sane, non-magic human self in the finale of the main series. In the background of the show, before The Great Mushroom War, Simon was a respectable archaeologist, appearing to be mild-mannered, intelligent, kind and adventurous. On a trip to Scandinavia, Simon discovered a Crown of mysterious origin. After wearing his crown, his life changed for the worse. His relationship with his fiance was shattered and his sanity was starting to diminish. However, the crown would keep him alive, allowing him to be one of the very few human survivors of The Great Mushroom War.

Name: Jake the Dog
Key: '''Seasons 1-Dungeon Train''' | '''Dungeon Train - Dad's Dungeon''' | '''Dad's Dungeon - Apple Wedding''' | '''Blade of Grass - Reboot''' | '''Two Swords - Elementals Arc''' | '''Season 10''' | '''Deceased'''
Summary: Jake is the deuteragonist of Adventure Time, is a dog/shape-shifter hybrid, he is Finn's constant companion, best friend, and adoptive brother. Jake has shape shifting abilities so he can "stretch" into different objects.

Name: Joshua
Summary: Joshua the Dog is the father of brothers Jake, Finn, and Jermaine. He and his wife, Margaret, adopted Finn as a baby. He speaks in a 1940s Mid-Atlantic accent. Joshua's personality is demonstrated as an old-fashioned manly dog who is willing to push his sons to fight, particularly when they need to.

Name: Kalifa
Summary: Kalifa was first introduced as being Iceberg's attendant at Water 7, when in reality, for the 5 years she had been working with Iceberg, she was a spy working as a CP9 member that was tasked with finding the blueprints regarding Pluton.

Name: Korone Inugami
Summary: Korone Inugami is a doggirl with a happy and cheerful disposition. She enjoys having fun and is willing to partake in various - sometimes dangerous - activities that often go out of control. In spite of that, Korone doesn't seem to care and generally ignores common sense. She works at a bakery in the city. She often appears goofy and unintelligent, but she's skilled at sensing motives and can become intimidating to the point of causing intense fear to others; for that reason, few dare to mess with her. She's often seen with her best friend Okayu Nekomata.

Name: Kumadori
Summary: Kumadori was a former member of the Cipher Pol 9. He was first introduced in the Enies Lobby Arc when fellow agents Rob Lucci, Kaku, Blueno, and Kalifa finally made their return after their 5-year long undercover mission in Water 7.

Name: Little Oars Jr.
Summary: "Little" Oars Jr. (リトルオーズJr., Ritoru Ōzu Jr.?) is a pirate captain who is the descendant of Oars and an ally of the Whitebeard Pirates. He is among the several New World pirates aiding the Whitebeard Pirates in saving Ace.

Name: Luna Himemori
Summary: Luna Himemori is the young princess of the Candy Kingdom, a country in another world. She loves being spoiled and pampered, despite her butler's warnings. As a result of her young age, Luna is innocent, immature, bratty, rarely listens to advice, often asks unreasonable requests and speaks in a sickeningly sweet and childlike manner. She's nevertheless affectionate, loving and cares for her friends. Perhaps due to her lineage, Luna possesses potent magical powers. She loves takoyaki and sweets.

Name: M. Bison
Key: '''Base''' | '''Empowered by the Psycho Drive''' | '''Empowered by the Black Moons''' | '''Street Fighter VI'''
Summary: For unknown reasons, the child who grew up to be M. Bison (Vega in Japan) murdered his parents in cold blood before he was adopted by a tribe of Romani who taught him the art of Soul Power, an ancient art that allows the user to manipulate one's soul. Bison quickly mastered Soul Power and used it to expel all of the good and humanity out of him, turning him into an egotistical psychopath. He then evolved Soul Power into Psycho Power, took on the title M. Bison, and organized a group of mercenaries to help him succeed in global conquest.

Name: Maja The Sky Witch
Summary: Maja The Sky Witch is a recurring villain in Adventure Time. Her goal is to steal items of sentimental value for her own nefarious gain. During the events of Sky Witch, she bought Hambo from Ash to use in a ritual but was stopped by Princess Bubblegum and Marcy. During Something Big, she summoned Darren the Ancient Sleeper to destroy the Candy Kingdom.

Name: Marceline Abadeer
Summary: Marceline Abadeer (full title: Marceline the Vampire Queen) is one of the main characters in Adventure Time and a half-demon/half-human, and vampire who is over 1003 years old. During her first encounter with Finn and Jake, she forces the two out of their tree fort. Despite initially being an adversary to the two, Marceline quickly becomes one of Finn and Jake's closest friends. Her father, Hunson Abadeer, is the demon who rules the Nightosphere.

Name: Marine Houshou
Summary: Marine Houshou is a pirate and the captain of the Houshou Pirates. She loves jewels, money and all kinds of treasure, and enjoys hunting for more riches. While serving as a sort of big sister by many Hololive members, she has a quick temper, and often shamelessly flirts and seduces people like it's second nature. She gets along very well with Rushia Uruha, though they have a complicated romantic relationship, is very protective of Aqua Minato and acts like a mother to her, and has a friendly rivalry with Suisei Hoshimachi.

Name: Nami (One Piece)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypeia Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Whole Cake Arc''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Nami, also known by her epithet "Cat Burglar", is the navigator of the Straw Hats who was initially introduced as a thief who detested pirates and stole from them, tagging along Luffy with dubious loyalty to him. However, it is revealed that her surrogate home, the Conomi Archipelago, was occupied by the Arlong Pirates and she only wished to buy her home back. When Luffy freed the archipelago from Arlong’s grip, she fully joined the Straw Hats afterward.

Name: Necalli
Summary: Necalli (ネカリ Nekari) is a character in the Street Fighter series who first appeared in Street Fighter 5. Necalli is described as the 'Emissary of the Gods', with a rather ominous moniker of 'The Soul Consuming Darkness'. As the "Warrior Prophet" reveals, every few hundred years the stars herald the 'Hour of Battle' ('Hour of Necalli'). During this period of time Necalli awakens to consume the souls of strong warriors.

Name: Nico Robin
Key: '''Alabasta Arc''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Thriller Bark Arc''' - '''Sabaody Archipelago Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Adventurer, archaeologist, ex-Dragon, and Ms. Exposition, Nico Robin is one of the darker and more enigmatic members of the Straw Hats.

Name: Noel Shirogane
Summary: Noel Shirogane is a human knight. She's easy-going and fairly innocent, but has the dangerous habit of attempting to muscle her way through her problems with her immense physical strength; she's the dictionary definition of brawn-for-brains. She can be competitive and enjoys testing her strength against others. Noel possesses a large appetite for the purpose of replenishing her power, though usually simply because she's hungry - usually gyudons. She's often seen with Flare.

Name: Princess Bubblegum
Summary: Princess Bonnibel Bubblegum, also known a P.B. and Peebles is one of the main characters in Adventure Time. She is the kind and compassionate ruler of the Candy Kingdom and is one of Finn's best friends. She originally met Finn when he saved her from the Ice King during the original pilot. Bonnibel is also extremely intelligent and is considered one of the top minds in all of Ooo. She has created many lifeforms such as her Candy People, the Earl of Lemongrab, Goliad and more.

Name: Psycho Helmet
Summary: Psycho Helmet is an entity born from the Divine Tree, a massive stalk of broccoli that originated in the aftermath of Toichiro and Mob's fight. Originally the result of Dimple fusing with the Divine Tree, it later became an entirely separate entity from him, only keeping Dimple's original goal of becoming the 'God of the modern world'.

Name: Roboco-san
Summary: Roboco-san, or simply Roboco, is a soft-spoken and kind robot girl, who supposedly came from a faraway wasteland, and the second-ever talent within Hololive Production. Due to being a robot, she's more solidly built than her fellow coworkers, but her robot body requires frequent maintenance in exchange. Her arms are frequently seen detaching from her body and falling off; for that reason, she's often described as clunky.
