Roboco is easily scared, clumsy, emotional and forgetful, but she's also one of the most mature members of Hololive, making her a reliable person. She's fairly competitive at video games.

Name: Ryu (Street Fighter)
Summary: The lead character of the Street Fighter franchise and a fighting game character, Ryu is a stoic Japanese martial artist who wanders the globe seeking the meaning of being a "true warrior". He can be recognized by his sleeveless white karate gi and a red or white hachimaki/headband depending on the game. He trained alongside his friendly rival Ken under their mutual master Gouken and was the victor of the first Street Fighter tournament. His encounter with his master's nemesis Akuma during the Street Fighter Alpha sub-series awoke the untapped Satsui no Hadou or "murderous intent" within him although this power was eventually overwhelmed in Street Fighter V, when he mastered the Power of Nothingness, a source of higher power arising from a state of consciousness in which the mind is free from thoughts and emotions. In Street Fighter III, he continues to travel the world in search of strong opponents.

Name: Scorcher (Adventure Time)
Summary: Scorcher is a character from Adventure Time.

Name: Shion Murasaki
Summary: Shion Murasaki is a young-looking girl who's a witch. It is told she randomly comes and goes from the Underworld Academy. She's a self-proclaimed adult and a self-proclaimed talented dark magician, though neither have been confirmed with certainty, so her childish appearance and mannerisms make her attempts to appear adult-like end up looking silly. Shion is generally playful, mischievous, smug and enjoys playing pranks on her comrades, not mindful of the consequences; she's often referred to as a kusogaki or "shitty brat". She tends to act proud or full of herself when casting her magic and she loves receiving attention, but some of her spells often malfunction and cause nefarious side effects to either herself or others. She's often seen bickering with Aqua Minato.

Name: Susan Strong
Summary: Susan Strong, otherwise known as X-J-7-7 is a major recurring protagonist in Adventure Time. Much like Finn, Susan is a simple minded, but heroic person. Susan is a very mysterious character, with her backstory being the driving focus of multiple episodes.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Urgence Evergreen
Summary: Urgence Evergreen was the previous Ice Elemental, and one of the few beings who lived before the Mushroom Bomb, he was an eccentric elemental who created the Ice Crown in an attempt of stopping the Catalyst Comet.

Name: Urouge
Summary: Urouge, also known as Mad Monk, is a pirate who hails from a sky island and is the captain of the Fallen Monk Pirates. He is one of twelve pirates who are referred to as the "Worst Generation " (formerly known as the "Eleven Supernovas"). and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 108,000,000.

Name: X Drake
Summary: X Drake (read as "Diez Drake") is a former Marine rear admiral from North Blue who has become a pirate under the epithet of the "Red Flag". He is one of twelve pirates referred to as the "Worst Generation" (formerly as the "Eleven Supernovas"), and prior to the two-year timeskip had a bounty of 222,000,000.

Name: Airachnid (Transformers One)
Summary: Airachnid is Sentinel Prime's assistant and primary enforcer. To call her "no nonsense" would be an understatement; the only time she smiles is when she's causing others suffering or going in for the kill. She is an unrelenting, and humorless, hunter and spy with a vast array of receptors and scanners at her disposal, which allow for her to keep tabs on anything that might jeopardize Sentinel's claim to power.

Name: B-127 (Transformers One)
Summary: B-127 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A worker in the lowest level of Waste Management, sub-level 50, Bee's isolation caused him to become extremely talkative, to the point of talking to himself and his imaginary friends, all to keep himself company. Upon meeting Orion Pax and D-16, who had both been banished to waste management, the trio would accidentally stumble upon a map leading to the lost Matrix of Leadership. Bee would then assist the two in finding the artifact, hoping to become good friends with the two.

Name: Barricade (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Dark of the Moon''' | '''The Last Knight'''
Summary: Barricade is apparently a complicated robot. He's considered "fractious" even by Decepticon standards, yet is willing to give Starscream the benefit of the doubt and follow where he leads, at least for the time being. Though not totally dedicated to the service of the Decepticons' current leader, he is much more cautious and reserved about expressing mutinous dissent than say most. He believes that Starscream is vital in their search for Megatron and the AllSpark. In many ways this makes him Starscream's closest ally in the naturally combative Decepticon ranks. Then again, it's been said that he likes to trick people into trusting him, just so he can see their reactions when they find out just how much of a bad idea it was. As such, he has disguised himself as an Earth police car in an attempt to fool the humans around him.

Name: Bedtime Bear (Original)
Summary: Bedtime Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. As his name would suggest, he can most often be found dozing off at just about any place or time. However, when the situation calls for it, he can be dependable and is always willing to help out those who need it. It is his duty to make sure everyone on Earth and in the Care Bear family gets enough sleep and dreams peacefully.

Name: Beros (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Beros (ベロス Berosu) was a villain working for Flect Turn in My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. She was the main hunter of Deku and Rody Soul, attempting to stop their interference in the plans of Humarize.

Name: Brawl (Michael Bay)
Summary: To say Brawl is a warrior is like calling Cybertron a hunk of metal. Brawl does not just enjoy fighting, he is consumed by it. Tearing Autobots apart is embedded into his very core, and every fiber-optic cable of his being is obsessed with wild, unyielding combat. The only thing he enjoys, or even cares about, is the fury of battle. And he loves a good explosion. Particularly if it's one he created, and if it's an Autobot that is exploding.

Name: Bug God
Summary: Bug God (蟲神, Mushigami) was a Demon-level Mysterious Being from the Monster Association.

Name: Bumblebee (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Revenge of the Fallen''' | '''Dark of the Moon''' | '''Age of Extinction to The Last Knight'''
Summary: Bumblebee is an Autobot Scout and one of Optimus Prime's most trusted lieutenants. Although he is not the strongest or most powerful of the Autobots, Bumblebee more than makes up for this with a bottomless well of luck, determination, and bravery. He would gladly give his life to protect others and stop the Decepticons.

Name: Bushidrill
Summary: Bushidrill is the A-Class rank 4 hero and a Disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. Alongside his partners Iaian and Okamaitachi, Bushidrill is a skilled and powerful swordsman. Each is described as being worthy of S-Class, though they are forced to stay in their current positions due to Sweet Mask, who remains at Rank 1 of A-Class.

Name: Cheer Bear (Original)
Summary: Cheer Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first debuted as a character on American Greetings cards in 1982. True to her name, Cheer specializes in lifting people's spirits whenever they're feeling down. Just about the only time one will find her feeling down is when there's someone who seems like they are nigh-impossible to encourage. However, this only ever leads Cheer to try harder. She constantly surprises those who doubt her capabilities with how multi-talented she truly is.

Name: Chojuro Kon (Chimera)
Summary: Chojuro Kon (今こん鳥ちょう獣じゅう郎ろう Kon Chojuro), also known as Chimera (キメラ Kimera), is a villain working with Nine in the film My Hero Academia: Heroes Rising.

Name: Cozy Heart Penguin
Summary: Cozy Heart Penguin is a Care Bear Cousin who originated in the first feature length Care Bears Movie. She can frequently be found swimming in the arctic waters of the Forest of Feelings, and she considers it her task to spread warmth and joy to all she comes across. Cozy Heart also happens to be the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't a mammal.

Name: Crankcase (Michael Bay)
Summary: Crankcase is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was tasked with capturing Sentinel Prime but was intercepted by Ironhide and Sideswipe and was killed by the former.

Name: Crosshairs
Summary: When the chips are down, Crosshairs is the kind of guy you'd want on your team. Or you would, if it wasn't for the fact that he's self-loving and more than a bit of a jerk. Crosshairs is a paratrooper who's a mouthful of snark with a bad attitude. He's got little respect for Optimus Prime, harboring a desire to just be on his own or otherwise be in charge himself. Despite these vices, Crosshairs is still a crack shot who always hits the ground running and makes mincemeat out of Decepticons with his firearms before they even know what hit them. And if the chips are really down, he'll come through in the end for his fellow Autobots.

Name: Crowbar (Michael Bay)
Summary: Crowbar is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was tasked with capturing Sentinel Prime but was intercepted by Ironhide and Sideswipe and was killed by the former.

Name: Dark Heart
Summary: Dark Heart is the primary antagonist of the second Care Bears feature film. He is a demonic entity who intends to capture each member of the Care Bear Family and spread his influence to everyone on Earth. Unlike most other adversaries of Care-a-Lot, however, Dark Heart's malicious ways come not from his hatred of caring but from his initial inability to understand it. After the near-death of his friend, Christy, helps him realize his capacity to care about others, he abandons his evil ways and his powers in the process.

Name: Demon Cat
Summary: The Demon Cat is a dungeon boss encountered in the S01E18 episode Dungeon in Adventure Time. He is a sadistic creature who takes pride in having approximate knowledge of many things.

Name: Demonic Fan
Summary: Demonic Fan (扇風鬼, Senpūki) was a Mysterious Being of unknown origin that appears to be a sentient robotic fan.

Name: Devil Long Hair
Summary: Devil Long Hair is a Demon-level member of the Monster Association. He is extremely obsessed with his very long head of hair, and treats his opponents mockingly.

Name: Dino (Michael Bay)
Summary: A vigorous warrior, Dino (Or Mirage) is always among the first on the battlefield thanks to his impatience. His peers would call him either bold or reckless, depending on who you ask.

Name: Do-S
Summary: "Monster Princess" Do-S (怪人姫弩S, Kaijin Hime Do S) is a Demon-level mysterious being and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Eijiro Kirishima (Red Riot)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Shie Hassaikai Arc''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Eijiro Kirishima (切島鋭児郎 Kirishima Eijirō), also known as Red Riot (烈怒頼雄斗 Reddo Raiotto), is a student at U.A. High School training to become a Pro Hero. Like Deku, he's kind, friendly, and has real dreams of being an altruistic hero, having been inspired by his idol, Crimson Riot. He has a bit of a fixation with doing "manly" things, rating actions as "manly" or "unmanly" depending on how much he approves of them.

Name: Elita-1 (Transformers One)
Summary: Elita-1 is the Tritagonist of the film Transformers One. A no-nonsense bot, Elita-1 was the head of an Energon mining crew, maintaining a spotless record while harvesting large amounts of energon for the good of Cybertron. Up until a mining incident involving Orion Pax and D-16, which involved her demotion, leading to a disdain particularly towards the former.

Name: Enforcer (Michael Bay)
Summary: The Enforcer is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was sent to kill Dino and Bumblebee after they activated a Decepticon space port, though he was killed soon after.

Name: Evil Natural Water
Summary: Evil Natural Water (エビル天然水てんねんすい, Ebiru Tennensui?) is a mighty being that works for the Monster Association, an elite group of horrifying creatures working to dismantle the Hero Association.

Name: Face Ripper
Summary: Face Ripper (カオハギ, Kaohagi) was a Demon-level monster and a member of the Monster Association.

Name: Fubuki (Blizzard of Hell)
Summary: Fubuki (フブキ?), also known by her hero alias Blizzard of Hell is the B-Class Rank 1 professional hero of the Hero Association. She is an Esper, the younger sister of Tatsumaki, and the leader of the Blizzard Group, a B-Class hero faction. She and her sister are known as the Psychic Sisters. Fubuki is one of the few people who are aware of Saitama's strength and is currently trying to recruit him into her group. She's also a self-declared member of the Saitama Group.

Name: G4
Summary: G4 is a self-proclaimed "Machine God" built by the same organization that Hammerhead stole his armor from. His goal was to force "The World's Strongest Man" King to fight him in order to test his abilities. Being far too terrified to face him however, King runs away, leaving the S-Class cyborg Genos to fight the Machine God instead.

Name: G5 (One-Punch Man)
Summary: G5, the self-proclaimed "machine god", is the immediate successor of the battle robot G4 and was created by the same mysterious group known simply as "The Organization". For unknown reasons, which he refuses to reveal to Gyoro Gyoro, The Organization sent G5 on their behalf as an ally of the Monster Association, defeating Narinki's Private Squad to prove his loyalty.

Name: Gale Wind
Summary: Gale Wind (疾風のウィンド, Hayate no uindo) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Hellfire Flame. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Garogas
Summary: The Garogas (ガロガ星人) are an evil alien race created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter.

Name: Garou
Key: '''Hero Hunter''' | '''Half-Monster''' | '''Post-Darkshine''' | '''Post-Sage Centipede''' | '''Awakened Garou''' | '''Parallel Timeline Awakened Garou'''
Summary: Saitama: Hey, you got a little better again! Garou: You call this a little?!

Name: Genos (Demon Cyborg)
Key: '''Beginning of Series''' | '''House of Evolution to Alien Conquerors Arc''' | '''Post-VGS''' | '''Post-G4''' | '''Post-Superfight''' | '''Post-Elder Centipede'''
Summary: King: Mr. Genos risked his life to save Miss Tatsumaki. It was truly admirable! Saitama: So that's why! You really hung in there, Genos! Nice fight! Genos: Master... when the time came for me to self-destruct, I was no longer able to do it. Can one truly say I've become stronger? Saitama: I don't really get it, but you didn't blow up, right? [touches his core] That means this part here got stronger too, doesn't it?

Name: Gold Garoga
Summary: Gold Garoga is an alien created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter. He is probably the oldest and strongest Garoga ever, and is also their leader.

Name: Good Luck Bear (Original)
Summary: Good Luck Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. Good Luck is a fortuitous bear that never seems to run out of good luck. However, this has just as much to do with his exceptionally bright, positive outlook on life as it does with his ability to create his own four-leaf clovers. Truly believing that there is no such thing as "bad luck", the fortunate fellow tries to help others by improving the power of their own self-confidence and removing all doubt from their heart.

Name: Grumpy Bear (Original)
Summary: Grumpy Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who originally appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in 1982. He is quite recognizable, possibly more so than his friends, due to being the only member of the Care Bear Family who isn't always smiling and cheerful. Despite his default mood, he is just as caring and dedicated to helping others as anyone else in Care-a-lot.

Name: Hatchet (Michael Bay)
Summary: Hatchet is a Decepticon and one of the Dreads. He was tasked with capturing Sentinel Prime but was attacked by Bumblebee, Dino, and Sideswipe, being shot at by all three before being killed for good by Dino.

Name: Hellfire Flame
Summary: Hellfire Flame (業火のフレイム, Gōka no fureimu) was a powerful ninja, who originated from the same village as Speed-o'-Sound Sonic and Flashy Flash. He was from the 37th graduating class, known as "Golden," along with his partner Gale Wind. Originally a human, he eventually decided to join the Monster Association while becoming a monster himself, as he sympathized with the association's goal of ruling over the world. However, his main goal was to kill the S-Class hero, Flashy Flash.

Name: Hero Association
Summary: The Hero Association is an organization founded by the multi-millionaire Agoni after his grandson was saved from a monster by a passerby. Operating independently of the government, the Hero Association recruits various individuals, ordinary and extraordinary alike, to fight for justice against the evil in the world. Those registered within the National Hero Registry database are tasked with protecting civilians from harm against monsters, villains, natural disasters, and other threats and are compensated for their efforts.

Name: Iaian
Summary: Iaian is the A-Class rank 2 hero of the Hero Association and a disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. He wears Western armor and specializes in Iaido. His left arm was blown off by an alien, and he has been a one-armed man ever since. He and the other two students of Atomic Samurai, Okamaitachi and Bushidrill, are all immensely powerful swordsmen. The three of them together can even defeat stronger Demon-level threats. Still, they cannot advance to S-Class because Sweet Mask, an eligibility examiner of S-Class, judges them to be unworthy. Nonetheless, Iaian is aware of the fact and still tries his best to become stronger.

Name: Ironhide (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ironhide is the Autobots' resident weapons specialist and Optimus Prime's old friend. He is old because he is hard. He's probably had enough replacement parts to build a small army, but Ironhide doggedly refuses to roll over and die for anyone. He'll fight to the bitter end and take down more than his fair share of Decepticons in the process.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: Jazz (Michael Bay)
Summary: First Lieutenant Jazz is one happy-go-lucky Autobot. Good-natured and always able to take things in stride, he provides a stark contrast to the more serious demeanor of Ironhide or Optimus Prime himself. He's also a talker, something Ironhide and Prime like to tease him about. He might be the smallest Autobot but he's by no means a coward, willing to take on any foe, big or small.

Name: Jetfire (Michael Bay)
Summary: Jetfire is an ancient cybertronian, one who served as a Decepticon under the Fallen. After realizing that the Decepticon cause wasn't just, Jetfire abandoned them and defected to the Autobots. For years he laid dormant in the Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum until Sam Witwickey awakened him. Journeying to Egypt, he helped him retrieve the Matrix of Leadership and sacrificed himself to give Optimus Prime enough strength to fight the Fallen.

Name: Jogo
Summary: Jogo (漏じょう瑚ご, Jōgo?) is a character in Jujutsu Kaisen. He is a Cursed Spirit and one of the main antagonists of the series. Jogo has immense pride as a Cursed Spirit and a passionate hatred for humans. He believes that Curses are the actual humans as they represent pure truths of life, such as hatred, while normal humans fake many positive emotions and should be exterminated.

Name: Katsuki Bakugo (Dynamight) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''With One For All'''
Summary: Katsuki Bakugo (爆豪勝己 Bakugō Katsuki) is a student in Class 1-A at U.A High School training to become a Pro Hero. He is the complete opposite of Deku, being stubborn, hot-headed, arrogant, and gifted.

Name: Kendo Rappa
Summary: Kendo Rappa (乱波肩動 Rappa Kendō), also known as The Rapper (ザ ラッパー Za Rappā), is a member of Overhaul's Shie Hassaikai. Rappa is a hot-blooded man who thrives on violence and bloodshed. He has a warrior-like mentality and only cares about seeking out a battle that can satisfy him. Originally an MMA fighter who fought in many underground rings for years. He was usually unsatisfied, most of his opponents were defeated in one punch and those that could take his punch would beg for their lives. His routine would end after he met Overhaul who offered him to join his group.

Name: Kugo Sakamata (Gang Orca)
Key: '''Provisional Hero License Exam Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Kugo Sakamata (逆さか俣また空くう悟ご Sakamata Kūgo), also known as Gang Orca (ギャングオルカ Gyangu Oruka), is the current No. 11 Pro Hero (formerly No. 10). He was a member of the Hideout Raid Team and the makeshift villain during the Provisional Hero License Exam.

Name: Leviathan (My Hero Academia)
Summary: Leviathan (レヴィアタン Reviatan) is a hulking villain that works for Flect Turn in My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. He worked towards the downfall of hero society, but was ultimately defeated by Shoto.

Name: Mahoraga
Summary: Eight-Handled Sword Divergent Sila Divine General Mahoraga (八やつ握かの剣つるぎ異い戒かい神しん将しょう魔ま虚こ羅ら, Yatsuka-no-Tsurugi Ikaishinshō Makora?) is the most powerful shikigami of the Ten Shadows Technique. In order to summon this entity, an individual must stretch out both hands and recite the incantation "Furube Yurayura".

Name: Martin Mertens
Summary: Martin Mertens, also formerly known as Mr. M, is Finn's biological father. Billy calls him "Dad the Human", similar to Finn's title "Finn the Human". He was first revealed in the episode "Billy's Bucket List".

Name: Matthew (Adventure Time)
Summary: The meat bodies who journeyed to this mountain have distilled themselves to their original source materials, and now exist in oneness. I keep adding to myself until the second age of terror, when i will emerge in my final form and restore the world

Name: Megatron (Transformers One)
Summary: Megatron is the Deuteragonist and eventual main Antagonist of Transformers One. Once a lowly miner named D-16, the young bot idolized the legendary Megatronus Prime and was a stickler for protocol, believing that following the rules and believing in the system would one day allow him to ascend up the hierarchy. He was also the best friend of the rebellious Orion Pax, often acting as the straight man to Orion's shenanigans, but willing to back Orion up no matter what.

Name: Mirai Sasaki (Sir Nighteye)
Summary: Mirai Sasaki (佐々木未来 Sasaki Mirai), better known as Sir Nighteye (サー・ナイトアイ Sā Naitoai), is a Pro Hero and Lemillion's mentor. He is also a former sidekick of All Might.

Name: Mixmaster (Michael Bay)
Summary: Mixmaster is a Decepticon and member of the Constructicons. He aided in Megatron's resurrection and the Fallen's plan to harvest Earth's Sun in Egypt. Two versions of him were there in the battle, one that formed into Devastator and the other that battled against the Autobots. Both were slain, one by the US military and the other by Jetfire.

Name: Momo Yaoyorozu (Creati)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Momo Yaoyorozu (八百万百 Yaoyorozu Momo) is a member of Class 1-A and a hero-in-training under the name, "The Everything Hero: Creati" (万物ヒーロー クリエイティ Banbutsu Hīrō Kurieiti). She is a very intelligent and dedicated person who acts as a natural leader. She is generally very level-headed and calm even in dangerous situations.

Name: Narinki’s Private Squad
Summary: Narinki's Private Squad is a private rescue squad created by Narinki to free his son, Waganma, from the Monster Association.

Name: No Heart
Summary: No Heart is the primary antagonist of Nelvana's Care Bears cartoon series. He is a wicked sorcerer whose goal is to rid the world of any and all love and caring. Though his creations are dastardly and his plans thorough, he is thwarted time and again by the Care Bears' intervention and the incompetence of his own henchmen. Although he is an expert in his craft, he is constantly irritable and will often snap at the slightest hindrance to himself and his objective.

Name: Okamaitachi
Summary: Okamaitachi is the A-Class rank 3 hero and a Disciple of the S-Class hero Atomic Samurai. Alongside her partners Iaian and Bushidrill, she is an immensely powerful and skilled swordswoman. Each is described as being worthy of S-Class, though they are forced to stay in their current positions due to Sweet Mask, who remains at Rank 1 of A-Class.

Name: Optimus Prime (Transformers One)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the main protagonist of Transformers One. Once a low class Miner, Orion Pax sought out to find the Matrix of Leadership, in order to end the need for him and his fellow miners to stay in the dangerous mines, and to prove that cogless bots like him were so much more, often facing prejudice by Cybertronians born with Transformation cogs.

Name: Ratchet (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ratchet is the Autobots' medic, and probably the bravest of them all. He'll risk his life to pull any wounded comrade from the battlefield. Indeed, he did not join Optimus Prime's team to be a soldier; rather, he's there to save lives, and thinks Prime is the best chance the universe has for peace.

Name: Rhino Wrestler
Summary: Rhino Wrestler (サイレスラー, Sai Resurā) was a Mysterious Being and a member of the Monster Association who first appeared during the attack in S-City.

Name: Royal Ripper
Summary: Royal Ripper (キリサキング, Kirisa Kingu) is a monster affiliated with the Monster Association.

Name: Ryomen Sukuna
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Satoru Gojo
Summary: This article contains plot details about an upcoming or recently released episode/chapter/movie/book/game/etc.

Name: Scorponok (Michael Bay)
Summary: Scorponok is a Decepticon scout and partner of Blackout. He was dispatched during Blackout's attack on a military base in Qatar and stalked several surviving soldiers until they fought him off. He later appeared in Egypt to help the Fallen harvest Earth's Sun. He attacked Jetfire and mortally wounded him before having his head crushed.

Name: Sentinel Prime (Transformers One)
Summary: Sentinel Prime is the initial antagonist of the film Transformers One. Beloved by the citizens of Iacon city, Sentinel proclaims himself as the savior of Cybertron, and the last of the Thirteen Primes, having been the only Prime to survive the war against the Quintessons. He is highly respected by everyone within Iacon, especially by D-16, who seeks to impress Sentinel and to one day earn his approval.

Name: Serpenters
Summary: Serpenters (サーペンターズ Sāpentāzu) are a villain duo comprised of twin brothers Ena (エナ Ena) and Dio (ディオ Dio). They work for Flect Turn in My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. They are incredibly sadistic and take pleasure in making their opponents suffer, a trait that is amplified when they take the Quirk enhancing drug Trigger. They were defeated after a brutal combat encounter with Dynamight.

Name: Shoto Todoroki (Shoto)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Shoto Todoroki (轟焦凍 Todoroki Shōto), also known as Shoto (ショート Shōto), is one of main protagonists of the My Hero Academia manga and anime series.

Name: Sideswipe (Michael Bay)
Summary: Sideswipe is true to his function of Warrior. Though proficient with guns, he prefers melee combat to ranged weapons and will employ any maneuver it takes to get close enough to the enemy to use his arm-mounted Cybertanium swords. His agile, wheel-legged form more than allows for this. His tactics are merciless and he's utterly unapologetic about this—war, after all, is messy.

Name: Soundwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Soundwave, the Decepticon communications officer and one of Megatron's staunchest supporters, doesn't just master the frequencies that carry information across our planet, he revels in them. Stationed high in the upper atmosphere and capable of processing millions of data streams at once, he is fully capable of taking over communications on a planetary scale. Whether he uses this to direct civilization or destroy it remains to be seen.

Name: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic
Summary: Speed-o'-Sound Sonic (音速のソニック Onsoku no Sonikku) is a villain in the series, first appearing as a bodyguard hired by Mr. Monier. He grew up in a ninja village, honing his skills to near perfection. He views Saitama as his eternal rival, ever since the hero "defeated" him in a rather embarrassing manner.

Name: Staff Officer Black
Summary: Staff Officer Black (ブラック参謀) is an antagonist in the Dragon Ball manga, and in the anime Dragon Ball, also making short appearances in Dragon Ball GT. He is an assistant of Commander Red and is not given much of a role until the near end of the Commander Red Saga. He is a tall, soft-spoken and quick-witted person. Black carries out Commander Red's orders and informs Commander Red of the current situations with the remaining Red Ribbon Army officers.

Name: Swift Heart Rabbit
Summary: Swift Heart Rabbit is one of the Care Bear Cousins who has been a frequently recurring character since the first feature-length movie. True to her name, she is easily the fastest member of the Family, and she's not one to let people forget that. Her hubris and insistence to get things done as quickly as possible frequently lead to much needed lessons in humility. Despite her flaws, she's quick to get back up, and will always be there to lend her speed and a helping hand where she can.

Name: Taishiro Toyomitsu (Fat Gum)
Summary: Taishiro Toyomitsu (豊満太志郎 Toyomitsu Taishirō), also known as Fat Gum, is a Pro Hero and was part of the group sent to rescue Eri during the Hero Internship Arc. Fat Gum is a very kind and cheerful individual who always seems to be hungry, as he's rarely seen without a snack on his person.

Name: Tamaki Amajiki (Suneater)
Summary: Tamaki Amajiki (天喰 環 Amajiki Tamaki), also known as Suneater (サンイーター San'ītā), is a recently graduated hero from U.A. High School and a former member of the Big 3.

Name: Tanktop Master
Summary: Tanktop Master (タンクトップマスター, Tankutoppu Masutā) is the S-Class Rank 16 hero. He is the eldest and most powerful of the Tanktop brothers, as well as the most level-headed and wise. He plays a minor role in the Alien Invasion arc and a greater role in the Hero Hunt arc. Tanktop Master battles Garou to avenge Tanktop Vegetarian, and proves to be superior. However, upon seeing Garou's state, along with advice from Mumen Rider, he decides to spare the human monster. Unfortunately, once Garou had seen through Tanktop Master's attacks, he went back on the offense and defeated the hero. In the hospital, Tanktop Master tells Saitama that Garou's fighting style makes him especially deadly to heroes.

Name: Tenderheart Bear (Original)
Summary: Tenderheart Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared as an illustration on American Greetings greeting cards in August 1982. Exemplifying the very best qualities of the Care Bears, Tenderheart is usually considered the de facto leader of the gang. He frequently organizes their efforts to help spread love and care around the world, and keep their own home of Care-a-Lot in working shape. He is responsible for initiating new members into the Care Bear Family by bestowing their very own belly symbols, and has been directly involved in nearly every major event in their history.

Name: The Spirit (Care Bears)
Summary: The Spirit is the primary antagonist of the first Care Bears feature film. While Nicholas Cherrywood was cleaning out the old trunk which belonged to the magician, Mr. Fettuccine, he stumbled upon an ancient book of spells. The book spoke to him from within its pages and beckoned him to open it, offering the fame and notoriety he had been seeking all his life. Upon doing so, he met The Spirit. This would initiate their venture to render everyone in the world just as cold and uncaring as The Spirit herself.

Name: Watchdog Man
Summary: Watchdog Man (番犬マン Banken-man) holds the 12th rank among the S-Class Heroes of the Hero Association. Despite his silly appearance, he is widely feared and respected worldwide. As the vigilant protector of Q-city, Watchdog Man actively hunts down monsters within his jurisdiction and appears to effortlessly handle any challenges that come his way. His formidable reputation deters almost everyone from challenging him. However, the self-proclaimed "hero hunter" Garou, though fatigued, dared to confront him but was swiftly overpowered and forced to retreat.

Name: Wish Bear (Original)
Summary: Wish Bear is one of the ten original Care Bears who first appeared on American Greetings greeting cards in late 1982. As one can infer from her name, she is tasked with making sure the wishes of everyone on Earth, and often even those of the Care Bear Family, come true. Sometimes this can be accomplished by her own supernatural wish granting abilities; other times she prefers to work towards seeing the wishes of others and even herself come to light.

Name: Yuga Aoyama (Can't Stop Twinkling)
Summary: Yuga Aoyama (青山優雅 Aoyama Yūga), also known as Can't Stop Twinkling (キャント・ストップ・トゥインクリング Kyanto Sutoppu Tuinkuringu), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. He is flamboyant and loves the spotlight, but is prone to cracking under pressure and is somewhat cowardly. Nevertheless, he does pitch in when push comes to shove.

Name: Zone Angel
Summary: Zone Angel (ゾーンエンジェル), the real name Hotaru Sakimori (防人 螢 Sakimori Hotaru), is a Seijin created by Toho that first appeared in the 1973 tokusatsu kaiju series, Zone Fighter.

Name: Zone Fighter
Key: '''Hikari''' | '''Zone Fighter (During the First Episodes)''' | '''Zone Fighter (End of the Series)'''
Summary: After their home planet, Peaceland was destroyed by the Garoga Baron. The Zone family fled to earth in order to seek shelter. Calling themselves the Sakimori family, the Zone family tried to start a new peaceful life, the oldest son, Hikaru Sakimori even finds a job working as a test driver for cars.

Name: Zone Junior
Summary: Zone Junior (Real Name: Akira Sakimori) is the youngest and third member of the Zone Fighter team, brother of Zone Fighter and Zone Angel, and the weakest member of the Zone Fighter team. Although the weakest in the Zone Fighter team he is still strong enough to defeat foes the size of human adults. Like his family he is a alien from the destroyed planet Peaceland, he now protects the earth so it doesn't suffer the same fate. Being a child he's unskilled in combat, meaning he still has much to learn about it. Zone Junior is also extremely quick, being able to dodge and out run most characters. He like his sister is various mysterious and not much is known about him. If he and his sister are both in superhero form, they can summon a spacecraft called Smokey to aid them. Zone Junior lacks a lot abilities due to his young age, but with time he will be able to gain the abilities of both his sister and brother. Zone Junior is overall a small, unskilled, but strong young hero who seeks to protect the earth.

Name: Akua Shuzen
Summary: Akua Shuzen is the oldest daughter of the Shuzen vampire sisters and is considered as the strongest among them. She is the last descendant of Alucard and shared the first vampire's desire to eradicate the human race after humans mercilessly killed her best friend, Jasmine. However, after being introduced to her youngest sister, who strongly resembles Jasmine, she gradually neglects her revenge and vows to protect Moka at any cost.

Name: Alucard (Rosario + Vampire)
Summary: nan

Name: Amber (RWBY)
Summary: Amber was the previous Fall Maiden. As a young girl, she received the powers of the Fall Maiden, granting her tremendous power and becoming the next in a line that persisted for thousands of years. However, due to the actions of Cinder Fall, half of her powers were stolen, causing her to fall into a coma. As she was unlikely to ever wake up, and in order to ensure that the rest of the powers would not go to her assailant, Ozpin and his group planned on transferring her portion to someone else. However, she would eventually be killed by Cinder during the Battle of Beacon, causing the rest of the powers to go to her.

Name: Anakaris
Summary: Anakaris is a video game character in Capcom's Darkstalkers fighting game series, first appearing in Darkstalkers: The Night Warriors. Pharaoh Anakaris was the wise ruler of a large kindgom in Egypt, 5000 years ago. Upon his death, his remains have been entombed into a pyramid, in order to preserve them and allow him to ascend to godhood. However, after the pharaoh's death, the kingdom quickly fell to ruin.

Name: B.B. Hood
Summary: B.B. Hood, or Baby Bonnie Hood (known as Bulleta in Japan), is a playable character introduced in Darkstalkers 3. She is an exceptional Darkhunter who goes after the Darkstalkers for profit, and one of the few in the world able to fight with the strongest of them.

Name: Barricade (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Many years in the past, when Cybertron had just come under the rule of the Defense Force and the Science Division, Barricade was a member of the Defense Force under the command of High Protector Megatron. He participated in missions to rid the planet of "malcontents" who protested against the new order, and like many of his peers, he did so ruthlessly.

Name: Bishamon
Summary: Bishamon is a playable character in the Darkstalkers series and covers the role of the accursed samurai.

Name: Blackout (Michael Bay)
Summary: The massive Blackout has been described as the "hound" of Megatron. In better days he was always to be found looming powerful and silent behind his leader's right shoulder. When given a target he hunts it down with fierce determination. Blackout is not happy with the progress Starscream is making towards finding the missing Decepticon leader. He suspects (quite rightly) that Starscream would prefer Megatron to stay lost. Blackout is openly mutinous and will challenge Starscream's leadership at any opportunity, not for his own sake, but to better serve his ultimate goal of finding his lost master. Blackout has a sneaky side and uses his symbiotic companion Scorponok's small size to great advantage.

Name: Bonecrusher (Michael Bay)
Summary: Bonecrusher, known as the Claw of Megatron, is a Transformer that can be described with one word: Hate. While other Decepticons get by on greed, ambition, or just their fondness for dispensing chaos, Bonecrusher is fueled by sheer, unrelenting hate. He hates everyone and everything, be they Autobot, Decepticon, or anything in-between—he even hates himself, revolted by his misshapen, hunchbacked robot mode, which he considers a reflection of all the ugliness and malice inside himself. The full force of this vicious cycle of hatred finds release in explosive frenzied bursts of psychotic brutality, as Bonecrusher takes out the full force of his bitterness and self-loathing on anyone who looks at him sideways. He hates that. He also hates Megatron, but would hate being terminated by the Decepticon leader more, so he sticks around.

Name: Bumblebee (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Bumblebee was born over 10,000 years ago, one of the second generation of Cybertronians spawned by the AllSpark since its rediscovery and the revitalization of Cybertron. He and Cliffjumper were guardians of the AllSpark at the Temple of Simfur. During the war, Bumblebee was placed in command of a small Autobot unit at the AllSpark's hiding place in Tyger Pax, on the assumption that the Decepticon would focus their attention on Simfur; unfortunately, Megatron sensed the AllSpark's true location, and Bumblebee and his men found themselves under attack by the Decepticon leader and his troops. Swindle tried and failed to torture the AllSpark's precise hiding spot out of Bumblebee, forcing Megatron to take up the task, but even 'Bee did not know exactly where it was—moments later, both he and Megatron could only watch as the cube was blasted into space from a launch site nearby. A furious Megatron crushed Bumblebee's voice capacitor beyond repair in a petty act of revenge and took off after the AllSpark; although the young bot survived and was dubbed a hero for his actions, he feared that all the Autobots had done was potentially spread their war to other worlds.

Name: Bumblebee (Michael Bay)
Key: '''2007 to Revenge of the Fallen''' | '''Dark of the Moon''' | '''Age of Extinction to The Last Knight'''
Summary: Bumblebee is an Autobot Scout and one of Optimus Prime's most trusted lieutenants. Although he is not the strongest or most powerful of the Autobots, Bumblebee more than makes up for this with a bottomless well of luck, determination, and bravery. He would gladly give his life to protect others and stop the Decepticons.

Name: Cade Yeager
Summary: All humans make mistakes. Sometimes, what comes from those mistakes comes the best thing that ever happened to them. That's what Cade Yeager believes when he looks at his daughter, to whom he and his girlfriend gave birth at the cost of their high school graduation. While Cade is not the most responsible father in the world, his most redeeming quality is that when it comes to keeping his daughter safe, he does not go back on his word, no matter what; a promise he made to his bride before she passed away. He does have a creative and optimistic mind, lending it to building all kinds of inventions to make a good business out of. Sadly, none of these inventions have brought in much profit for his family. Knowing all of the opportunities he lost, he has sworn not to let history repeat itself, which is probably why he disapproves of Tessa dating boys before she graduates from high school.

Name: Cinder Fall
Summary: Cinder Fall is one of the main antagonists in RWBY. She is a member of Salem's Inner Circle as well as the leader of her own faction, which includes Roman Torchwick, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black. Cinder is imperious and cunning, with a touch of cruelty. Usually, she maintains a calm and collected demeanor and is willing to take over a fight if necessary. She is also ambitious and demanding, doesn't seem to tolerate failure, and dislikes when she is disobeyed, reprimanding Emerald and Mercury when they failed to obey her orders to keep their hands clean. She is shown to be an excellent strategist as well, often planning ahead to keep her goals in reach while keeping her accomplices on a strict "need to know" basis. Following the Battle of Beacon, Cinder is the current Fall Maiden.

Name: Denki Kaminari (Chargebolt)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Final War Arc'''
Summary: Denki Kaminari (上鳴電気 Kaminari Denki), also known as Chargebolt (チャージズマ Chājizuma), is a member of Class 1-A who is training to become a Pro Hero. Chargebolt is a friendly, social, and energetic boy who likes to hang out with people. He is rather casual when interacting with others, including the generally unfriendly Dynamight. He may come off as blunt and reckless at times, but is always well-meaning.

Name: Devastator (Michael Bay)
Summary: Devastator is a Decepticon combiner formed from the Constructicons. He was formed in Egypt to aid the Fallen and Megatron in their quest to harvest Earth's Sun.

Name: Diamond Dogs
Summary: The Diamond Dogs were a PMC (Private Military Contractor) formed by Kazuhira Miller in the early 1980s, and commanded from 1984 onwards by Venom Snake, after recovering from his coma. Under his command, it would become an extremely powerful and highly influential player in the worldwide military-industrial complex, taking on jobs for all clients. The organization would end up at odds with XOF, the covert strike force of the shadow government known as The Patriots, due to the feud between Big Boss/Venom Snake and XOF's leader, Skull Face. Ultimately, Diamond Dogs would emerge victorious, with Venom Snake and Kazuhira Miller dealing the finishing blows to Skull Face and scattering XOF. The PMC would remain in operation for roughly a decade more, before being supplanted and its strength absorbed by Big Boss' military fortress nation, Outer Heaven.

Name: Donovan Baine
Summary: Donovan was a half-vampire, half-human child. He and his mother were outcasts of their village due to Donovan's cursed blood. During his childhood, something caused his cursed blood to awaken and he killed everyone in the village including his mother.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Enel
Summary: Enel is the former "God" of Skypiea and the main antagonist of the Skypiea Arc. Two years ago, after his defeat by the Straw Hat Pirates, he arrived at the moon and became its new ruler.

Name: Felicia (Darkstalkers)
Summary: Felicia is one of the protagonists in the Darkstalkers video game franchise created by Capcom. She is a catwoman (bakaneko in Japanese folklore) who was taken in and raised by a sister named Rose, who gave her the name Felicia from the word Felicity.

Name: FLDSMDFR
Origin: Cloudy with a Chance of Meatballs
Summary: The Flint Lockwood Diatonic Super Mutating Dynamic Food Replicator, or FLDSMDFR for short, is the machine which the two Cloudy With A Chance Of Meatballs movies revolve around.

Name: Flect Turn
Summary: Flect Turn (フレクト・ターン Furekuto Tān) is a villain and the primary antagonist for My Hero Academia: World Heroes' Mission. He is the leader of the global cult Humarise, which subscribes to the Quirk Singularity Doomsday Theory and aims to eliminate Quirks from the world.

Name: Foxy (One Piece)
Summary: Foxy, also known as "The Silver Fox" is the captain of the Foxy Pirates and the main antagonist of the Long Ring Long Land Arc in One Piece. He is notorious for having one of the largest crews in the series, together with one of the largest ships. He has such because of his mastery of the "Davy Back Fight", a sportive event between pirates where crews wage their own crewmates. Although not very combat prone, Foxy is a very scheming and cunning man, making use of different kinds of weapons, disguises, and items, together with his Devil Fruit powers of the Slow-Slow Fruit (Noro Noro no Mi), which allows him to slow everything his beams touch for 30 seconds.

Name: Gears (Transformers Movie Novels)
Summary: Gears likes complaining. It makes him happy. But more importantly, he knows that his fellow Autobots find his endless litanies amusing rather than annoying. And in a war that's run a few million years, a little laughter can make a big difference, so he keeps at it.

Name: Gedatsu
Summary: One of God's priests. Gedatsu was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Swamp, which had a fifty percent rate of survival.

Name: Godzilla (Original)
Summary: Godzilla (ゴジラ, Gojira?) was designed by Teizo Toshimitsu and Akira Watanabe under Eiji Tsuburaya's supervision. Early on, Tanaka contemplated on having the monster be gorilla-like or whale-like in design due to the name "Gojira" (a combination of the Japanese words for gorilla which is gorira, and whale which is kujira) but eventually settled on a dinosaur-like design.

Name: Grimlock (Michael Bay)
Summary: Grimlock is a Dinobot with a rather rough n' tough attitude. One of the most powerful warriors alive, his general approach to a problem is to smash it first, worry about the specifics later. This attitudes extends to his Autobot companions, who are expected to meet Grimlock's standard of strength. That said, the Autobots have a lot less to fear from this behemoth than the Decepticons.

Name: Grindor (Michael Bay)
Summary: You have to get up pretty early in the morning to get one over on Grindor. A master strategist, and close combat specialist, Grindor can predict his opponents' next move before they know it themselves. It's reached the point where it's less planning and more instinct on his part. With every possible move planned out beforehand, Grindor confidently wades into the center of battle, ready for any and all comers.

Name: Hound (Michael Bay)
Summary: Hound is a technical specialist and highly experienced, gutsy Autobot commando. He is a boisterous warrior who throws himself into every mission with no more worries than a duck landing on a pond, and quick to draw any of his many, many guns. And while his tendency to switch from gun to gun in quick succession in a single battle often leaves him bereft of weapons and ammunition, Hound's bravery and resourcefulness is never in doubt. The only thing that just might take a toll on him is the loss of a friend; Hound's boisterous streak hides a soft-Sparked 'bot, who despite arguments and bickering, loves his fellow Autobots and commander even more than he loves a good rumble. It's this love for his comrades that makes him such an effective warrior. He will take on an entire Decepticon army if he has to, and he would sooner go down swinging than abandon his allies on the battlefield.

Name: Hsien-Ko
Summary: Hsien-Ko is a playable character in the Darkstalkers series. She and her sister Mei-Ling were twins born in a family of chinese hermits, whose village was once attacked by a pack of Darkstalkers. Their mother sacrificed herself by using a powerful spell to annihilate the monsters, condemning her soul to be trapped in darkness in return. In order to free her, Hsien-Ko and Mei-Ling unleashed a forbidden ritual which turned them both into supernatural creatures and allowed them to hunt the Darkstalkers as Darkhunters. Hsien-Ko gained incredible strength and special powers, though with the risk of falling victim of her savage new nature. Mei-Ling then developed the ability to transform into a talisman and place herself on her sister's forehead, preventing her from losing control.

Name: Huitzil
Summary: Huitzil is one of many robots that were created by Pyron who came to Earth 65 million years ago. When they were created, they were programmed with orders to destroy all life on the planet.

Name: Ironhide (Michael Bay)
Summary: Ironhide is the Autobots' resident weapons specialist and Optimus Prime's old friend. He is old because he is hard. He's probably had enough replacement parts to build a small army, but Ironhide doggedly refuses to roll over and die for anyone. He'll fight to the bitter end and take down more than his fair share of Decepticons in the process.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Final Act)
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as the One For All Hero: Deku (ワン・フォー・オール ヒーロー デク Wan Fō Ōru Hīrō: Deku), is one of the 20% of people on Earth who were born without a Quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in modern society, causing him endless torment at school. However, thanks to his innate heroism, he was able to earn the Quirk "One For All", bestowed upon him by his idol All Might, and use it to grow into one of the world's greatest heroes.

Name: Izuku Midoriya (Deku) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc'''
Summary: Izuku Midoriya (緑谷出久 Midoriya Izuku), also known as Deku (デク Deku), was one of the 20 percent of people on Earth to be born without a quirk, a natural superpower that is a basic biological function in the modern society, earning him endless amounts of torment and bullying in school.

Name: Jack (Tekken)
Summary: Jack (ジャック Jakku), sometimes capitalized as JACK, is the name of a series of robots that are upgraded in each main installment in the Tekken series of fighting games.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome. He's the only son of Hugh and Lila and brother of Susan and Mary (who had brown hair in the 2004 pilot). Because he has Susan and Mary by his side, he can live any kid's dream, only to find that some dreams aren't worth living. He is usually seen with his partner-in-crime and best friend Dukey, his genetically altered dog. He also gives Johnny Coupons to his sisters for helping him with his daily problems. When redeemed, he does their tests for free. Johnny and his sisters are often the cause of some problems in Porkbelly.

Name: Jon Talbain
Summary: Jon Talbain, known as Gallon in Japan, first appeared in Capcom's Darkstalkers: The Night Warriors. Born from a human mother and a werewolf father, Jon was left orphaned and has been rejected by society when, during a night of full moon, he turned into a werewolf. From that moment, Jon decided to take himself past his own limits, in order to regain his humanity. He trained in martial arts, and fought in the tournament held by Pyron when it came to Earth.

Name: Kahlua Shuzen
Summary: Kahlua Shuzen is the second oldest Shuzen sister and one of the most powerful. She hates killing despite being forced into being an assassin by her mother. She often cries out of guilt for killing. She is suicidal and often holds back on opponents, especially family members.

Name: Kai Chisaki (Overhaul)
Summary: Kai Chisaki (治崎廻 Chisaki Kai), better known as Overhaul (オーバーホール Ōbāhōru), is the leader of the Shie Hassaikai ("Eight Precepts of Death") yakuza group in the world of My Hero Academia.

Name: Katsuki Bakugo (Dynamight) (Final Act)
Summary: Katsuki Bakugo (爆豪勝己 Bakugō Katsuki) is a student in Class 1-A at U.A High School training to become a Pro Hero. He is the complete opposite of Deku, being stubborn, hot-headed, arrogant, and gifted.

Name: Katsuki Bakugo (Dynamight) (Pre-Final Act)
Key: '''U.A. Beginnings Saga''' | '''Joint Training Arc''' | '''Endeavor Agency Arc''' | '''With One For All'''
Summary: Katsuki Bakugo (爆豪勝己 Bakugō Katsuki) is a student in Class 1-A at U.A High School training to become a Pro Hero. He is the complete opposite of Deku, being stubborn, hot-headed, arrogant, and gifted.

Name: Kirin (Monster Hunter)
Summary: The appearance of the Kirin resembles that of a Unicorn, however, the Kirin is much more; It is fast on its feet, agile, and can command powerful lightning bolts effortlessly.

Name: Leanbow
Summary: Leanbow is Udonna's husband, Bowen's father (AKA Nick Russel), and the mentor of Daggeron and Calindor. He was known for his honor and valor which Calindor resented. As a Mystic, he can assume "Ancient Mystic Mode", resembling a red/purple fiery demon wielding a sword and shield. Twenty years prior to the series, Leanbow led the other Mystics in the Great Battle against the Supreme Master of the Underworld, and his Forces of Darkness led by Morticon in order to prevent them entering the human realm. The forces of good magic eventually forced the Forces of Darkness through the Gate of the Underworld, with Leanbow personally taking on Morticon at one point. In order to keep the Forces of Darkness from escaping the Underworld, he held back the Darkness hordes from the Gate while Niella the Gatekeeper sealed both it and Leanbow into the Underworld.

Name: Lockdown (Michael Bay)
Summary: Even the Decepticons are afraid of Lockdown because once he has been hired to track down a subject, nothing stops him from completing his transaction short of total deactivation! Answering only to his enigmatic "Creators", Lockdown holds himself above the Autobot/Decepticon war and sees both sides as squabbling children that he has to reign in personally. He doesn't think much higher of other civilized species across the galaxy (particularly humans), though isn't above working with them if it suits him.

Name: Lord Raptor
Summary: Zabel Zarock, better known as Lord Raptor, is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He was a young rocker who became instantly famous all over Australia after the release of his first album, "Oral Dead". His next songs sold millions of copies and his concerts attracted thousands of people. Turmoils at his lives were common enough, but one day a violent brawl broken out, leading to the law enforcement officials starting monitoring him and advising against hosting other events.

Name: M. Bison
Key: '''Base''' | '''Empowered by the Psycho Drive''' | '''Empowered by the Black Moons''' | '''Street Fighter VI'''
Summary: For unknown reasons, the child who grew up to be M. Bison (Vega in Japan) murdered his parents in cold blood before he was adopted by a tribe of Romani who taught him the art of Soul Power, an ancient art that allows the user to manipulate one's soul. Bison quickly mastered Soul Power and used it to expel all of the good and humanity out of him, turning him into an egotistical psychopath. He then evolved Soul Power into Psycho Power, took on the title M. Bison, and organized a group of mercenaries to help him succeed in global conquest.

Name: Manga Fukidashi (Comicman)
Summary: Manga Fukidashi (吹ふき出だし漫まん我が Fukidashi Manga), also known as Comicman (コミックマン Komikkuman), is one of the secondary protagonists of the anime and manga series My Hero Academia. He is also a student in Class 1-B at U.A. High School, training to become a Pro Hero.

Name: Megatron (Michael Bay)
Summary: Optimus: You have no soul! Galvatron: That is why I have no fear!

Name: Moka Akashiya
Summary: Moka Akashiya (Akashiya Moka, 赤夜 萌香) is a vampiress in Yōkai Academy and the main female protagonist of the series. She serves as the primary love interest to Tsukune Aono, who is the sole human enrolled in an academy of monsters. She has an enchanted rosary that gives her a split personality; her outer persona is gentle, compassionate, and seemingly weaker than average monsters. In contrast, the inner persona is a bold and domineering vampire lady; she is also a remarkably strong fighter, even among vampires.

Name: Monkey D. Luffy (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''Young''' | '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Arc''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Paramount War Saga'''
Summary: Monkey D. Luffy (モンキー・Ｄディー・ルフィ, Monkī Dī Rufi?), known as "Straw Hat Luffy", is the main protagonist of the manga and anime, One Piece. He's the son of Monkey D. Dragon, a revolutionary considered “The World's Most Dangerous Criminal”; the grandson of Monkey D. Garp, a powerful Marine Vice-Admiral who had cornered the late Pirate King himself on several occasions; the sworn brother of late "Fire Fist" Portgas D. Ace and Revolutionary chief of staff Sabo; and the foster son of Curly Dadan. He seeks to find One Piece and become the Pirate King; to accomplish this, he founded the Straw Hat Pirates and set out on the high seas at age 17 in search of the elusive treasure, beginning a series of increasingly odd and dangerous adventures. He has eaten the Gomu Gomu no Mi, which gives him stretching powers that he has become quite a master of and he's quite creative with them as he has developed two unique techniques with them: Gear 2nd, which makes him much faster, and Gear 3rd, which allows him to inflate any body parts for a stronger attack.

Name: Ohm
Summary: One of God's Priests. Ohm is one of the 4 Priests responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. He ran the Ordeal of Iron, which had the lowest percent rate of survival out of all of the Ordeals... 0.

Name: Optimus Prime (Michael Bay)
Summary: Optimus Prime is the heroic leader of the Autobots. A descendant of the Primes, a former knight of Cybertron and once Sentinel Prime's former pupil, he would go on to lead the Autobot resistance against Megatron's forces. Their battle would eventually lead to planet Earth. Now, Optimus seeks to defend his adopted world from any threats from the cosmos.

Name: Ozpin
Summary: Professor Ozpin is the headmaster of Beacon Academy, first seen in Volume 1 inquiring Ruby Rose about where she learned how to fight, her future goals, and her desire to join his school. He is frequently seen with his cane despite having no visible motor impairment.

Name: Peace Walker
Summary: Peace Walker, also known as Basilisk, was a walking nuclear-armed AI weapon developed by Huey Emmerich and Strangelove. In 1973, CIA Station Chief Hot Coldman commissioned the creation of Peace Walker in order to fulfill his vision of the "perfect nuclear deterrent".

Name: Penny Polendina
Summary: Penny Polendina is a character introduced in the episode "The Stray," when she was found lying on the ground after Weiss Schnee crashed into her whilst chasing after Sun Wukong. Penny speaks robotically, behaves erratically, and is overly active in general. All her actions and emotional states were rather extreme and overacted. When Ruby Rose unintentionally made an unconditional offer of friendship, Penny seemed both immensely pleased and somewhat surprised.

Name: Princess Bubblegum
Summary: Princess Bonnibel Bubblegum, also known a P.B. and Peebles is one of the main characters in Adventure Time. She is the kind and compassionate ruler of the Candy Kingdom and is one of Finn's best friends. She originally met Finn when he saved her from the Ice King during the original pilot. Bonnibel is also extremely intelligent and is considered one of the top minds in all of Ooo. She has created many lifeforms such as her Candy People, the Earl of Lemongrab, Goliad and more.

Name: Q-Bee
Summary: Q-Bee is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise, introduced in Darkstalkers 3, also known as Vampire Savior. She is the current queen of a race of bugs called Soul Bees. These creatures live in Makai, the demon world, and are famous for their ability to eat almost everything, with a special preference for the souls of their victims. They lived in the lands of the Dohma Family, but almost faced extintion during the period in which Jedah Dohma was dead, as their home began to crumble without anyone watching over them. When the demon lord came back to life, he started gathering powerful souls in the newly created Majigen to fulfill his own plans. Q-Bee noticed this vast amount of souls and headed there, in order to satisfy her hunger and that of her hive, as the sole interests of the Soul Bees are feeding, reproducing and expanding their colony.

Name: Raven Branwen
Summary: Raven Branwen is the mysterious mother of Yang Xiao Long and Qrow Branwen's twin sister. She was originally a member of Team STRQ, though unlike most Hunters, she has little issue killing and is described by her brother as a dangerous person. Raven has a high "survival of the fittest" mentality in which she is rather indifferent towards innocents dying if they were too weak to defend themselves. On one occasion she saved the life of her daughter, who she had abandoned shortly after her birth, though not without warning that she won't be looking out for her a second time. Raven is currently concerned about Salem and the power that she possesses.

Name: Reverb (Transformers)
Summary: Reverb is the main Decepticon antagonist of the Transformers: Classified novels

Name: Rikuo
Summary: Rikuo known as Aulbath in Japan, is a playable character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He was the emperor of a kindgom of 30.000 mermen, located in a lake deep beneath the Amazon. When Pyron arrived on Earth, his landing caused an earthquake and a volcanic eruption to occur right where the kingdom was. When Rikuo, who was exploring a far territory, realized what happened, it was already too late, a huge fissure had swallowed all the water of the lake and its inhabitants. Filled with rage, and sensing the evil aura coming off the ground, Rikuo sworn vengeance against the alien.

Name: Rock Howard (The King of Fighters)
Summary: nan

Name: Roronoa Zoro (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Roronoa Zoro (ロロノア・ゾロ?), also known by his epithet “Pirate Hunter”, is the premier swordsman of the Straw Hat Pirates and a member of the Monster Trio.

Name: Sanji (Pre-Timeskip)
Key: '''East Blue Saga''' | '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc'''
Summary: Sanji Vinsmoke, more commonly known as "Sanji" is the crew's chain-smoking chef and a member of the Monster Trio. There is not a dish he cannot cook, a pretty girl he will not try to woo, or something he will not argue with Zoro over. As a chef, he believes that he cannot afford to harm his hands, and so uses a fighting style which uses only his feet called the "Black Leg Style" (Kuroashi no Waza).

Name: Sasquatch
Summary: Sasquatch is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He is the leader and hero of the bigfoots, a tribe of about 100 individuals that lives deep in the Rocky Mountains of Canada. His job is to defend them from external threats, including humans, animals and monsters.

Name: Satori (One Piece)
Summary: One of God's priests, Satori was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Balls, which had a ten percent rate of survival.

Name: Sentinel Prime (Michael Bay)
Summary: Sentinel Prime was one of the Primes, he used to be the leader of the Autobots until the Ark was lost in space, landing on the moon in 1961.

Name: Shockwave (Michael Bay)
Summary: Shockwave was left to watch Cybertron by Megatron long ago, but he would eventually follow the call of the AllSpark to Earth. Deadly efficient with a cold devotion to logic, Shockwave is a killing machine like few others, one of the very few who could rival Megatron, and quite popular amongst the Decepticons. In a way, some respect him enough to willingly work with him, while others idolize him to the point of avenging his death. Nevertheless, Shockwave is ready and willing to destroy whichever Autobots dare stand in his way with his arm-mounted AstroMag Cannon.

Name: Shura (One Piece)
Summary: One of God's priests, Shura was responsible for the security of Upper Yard in Skypiea. His territory was the Ordeal of Strings which had a three percent rate of survival.

Name: Soul Edge
Summary: Soul Edge also known as the Cursed Sword serves as the main weapon of Nightmare and overall the main antagonist of the entire Soulcalibur franchise. Soul Edge serves as the catalyst on basically all the events in the franchise. All Soul Edge cares for is the devouring of souls and pure destruction. It's release of the Evil Seed corrupted countless people across the world, driving them mad or even transforming them into monsters. Soul Edge's counterpart is Soul Calibur. Soul Edge is known to be able to shape shift in order to morph into a form that best fits its wielder.

Name: Soundwave (IDW Movie Comics)
Summary: Thousands of years ago, on Cybertron, Soundwave stood by Megatron's side on Unification Day; when a new era of Cybertronian government was ushered in that saw the planet ruled by two bodies—Megatron's Defense Force, of which Soundwave became a part, and Optimus's Science Division. Megatron's lust for power soon led him to claim dominion over Optimus, however, and Soundwave was silently present when Megatron summoned Optimus and made this declaration.

Name: Starscream (Michael Bay)
Summary: Starscream is a hero on the wrong side. Over the centuries he's come to believe both Optimus and Megatron have lost sight of what is best for the Cybertronian race, and simply pursue their own agendas. At some point, he came to the decision that, for the good of the species, a new leader must emerge, and he would be that leader. However, over time, he became as corrupt in his own way as Megatron, although he prefers subtlety and deception to Megatron's brute force. Now, what may once have been noble goals are buried under layers of self-interest, transforming Starscream into that which he supposedly despised.

Name: Stinger (Michael Bay)
Summary: Stinger was one of the many models made by the factory KSI, modeled to be a "superior" version of Bumblebee. He would be deployed twice, first alongside Galvatron and later in the final battle in Shanghai, where he would be given sentience from Galvatron and fought against his predecessor, where he would meet his end.

Name: Sung Jin-Woo (Novel)
Summary: nan

Name: The Driller
Summary: The Driller is a large cybertronian beast which is under the command of Shockwave. It and Shockwave crashed and were frozen on Earth at an unknown period and they were later freed by Megatron. It was later sent with Shockwave to intercept Optimus at Chernobyl and steal an engine part from the Ark. After that, it ventured to Chicago with Shockwave and attempted to kill some soldiers that were hiding in a skyscraper, though it was killed by Optimus in the process.

Name: Tony Tony Chopper
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Enies Lobby Saga''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Tony Tony Chopper serves as the ship's doctor. He's a reindeer who was cast out of his herd for having a blue nose, later compounded by eating the Human-Human Fruit (Hito Hito no Mi) and being feared by the people of Drum Island as a monster. Although he initially mistrusted humans, after having met and joined the Straw Hats, he has become very curious about the world and is eager to please.

Name: Tsukune Aono
Summary: Tsukune Aono (nicknamed Tsuki by his cousin Kyouko) is a former human and the main protagonist of the Rosario + Vampire series. He is mistakenly enrolled in Yokai Academy, a high school dedicated to teaching monsters to peacefully live alongside humans in disguise, where he meets and falls in love with Moka Akashiya, a vampire who takes a mutual interest in him and the sweet flavor of his blood. Tsukune becomes a member of the school’s Newspaper Club and eventually befriends several monster girls, including Kurumu Kurono, Yukari Sendo, Ruby Tojo, and Mizore Shirayuki—all of whom become obsessed with him—as well as Kokoa Shuzen, Moka’s younger half-sister. He also makes friends with several male monsters such as Ginei Morioka, Hokuto Kaneshiro, Fang-Fang Huang, and Haiji Miyamoto. They support Tsukune’s belief that monsters and humans can coexist and be more than just enemies, their friendship with him being a prime example of that sentiment.

Name: Usopp
Key: '''Alabasta Saga''' | '''Skypiea Saga''' | '''Water 7 Arc''' | '''Enies Lobby Arc''' - '''Thriller Bark Arc''' | '''Dressrosa Saga''' | '''Onigashima Raid''' | '''Egghead Island'''
Summary: Usopp serves as the crew's sharpshooter and previously served as the (barely competent) repairman for the ship. He's the son of Yasopp, a sharpshooter serving under Shanks, and comes from the East Blue. Usopp had a reputation on his home island of being a serial liar who claimed that pirates were attacking, which came back to haunt him when real pirates actually attacked. He's a rather boastful seventeen/nineteen-year-old who likes to tell tall tales (several of which actually do come true, after a fashion), though he's more prone to hiding behind the stronger crew members such as Zoro when he actually gets into a fight. However, when push comes to shove, he is very dependable. He specializes in the use of a slingshot, called the Galaxy Slingshot (Ginga Pachinko), which he replaced with the Kabuto and later the Black Kabuto. This slingshot, coupled with his talent in tricking enemies, and his absurd sniping skills, make him a redoubtable sniper able to intervene at a very long range.

Name: Victor von Gerdenheim
Summary: Victor von Gerdenheim is a character in the Darkstalkers franchise. He is the culmination of the homonymus professor's dream. Professor Gerdenheim spent 30 years researching a way to revive dead cells and ultimately completed his creation: A body composed by various pieces sewn together, with various other components added to it, such as an electrostatic organic material, a charged liquid flowing through it and an electrode and a pacemaker connected to the heart. The last step was provide stimulation with a high voltage current, something that could be achieved only by using a natural lightning.

Name: Wanze
Summary: Wanze is a member of the CP7 and a cook, specializing in making ramen noodles, introduced as an antagonist in the Enies Lobby arc. He's a man that takes pride in his abilities and appears to be quite confident in them, though he can be a bit dense and short tempered. One of the main attribute to Wanze is that his facial expression seems to never change, even when he claims to be scared, which often lead to the annoyance and irritation of his enemies.

Name: Winter Schnee
Summary: Winter Schnee is a character in RWBY and the elder sister of Weiss Schnee. Despite being the eldest child, Winter's right to inherit the Schnee Dust Company was abdicated upon her decision to join the Atlas Military. At first glance, Winter appears to be cold, dignified, and distant, preferring to keep her emotions subdued and speaking in a very high-class, eloquent, almost robotic fashion. However, when interacting with Weiss, she smiles and shows that she cares about her younger sister's life and well-being. Although she strives to keep her emotions in check, she can be rather hot-headed at times. Once she becomes angry, she drops her dignified ladylike demeanor and loses all restraint. Winter consistently wrestles with her emotions, never letting them overpower her, yet still allowing them to guide her on what she believes to be a righteous path.

Name: Wyper
Summary: "Berserker" Wyper is a Shandian, who are a group of natives from the Blue Sea blasted into Skypeia, fighting to reclaim hid homeland for his people who were unjustly ousted from it by the Skypeians. He was the leader of the Shandia warriors fighting to take Upper Yard back from Enel. He is the direct descendant of Kalgara. After the time-skip, he is one of God's Guards.

Name: Aang
Summary: Aang was a male Air Nomad born in 12 BG and the Avatar during the Hundred Year War, succeeding Avatar Roku and preceding Avatar Korra. As the Avatar of his time, he was the only person capable of using all four Bending arts: Airbending, Waterbending, Earthbending, and Firebending. He was also one of a select few Avatars and one of the first in many cycles to learn the ancient art of Energybending and the first Avatar known to have actively used the technique.

Name: Abuto
Summary: Abuto (阿伏兎) is a member of the 7th Division of Harusame's Thunder Guns, the most powerful combat unit under Captain Kamui's leadership, within the Harusame group. He is the secondary main antagonist of Yoshiwara in Flames Arc.

Name: Atlas (RWBY)
Summary: Atlas is a kingdom located in Solitas, the far northern continent of Remnant. Formerly known as Mantle, Atlas was founded by settlers who traveled north to the barren, icy continent of Solitas. Where the people were forced to adapt quickly in order to survive the difficult climate, leading them to quickly learn to utilize Dust and other technologies. Following the end of the Great War, Atlas Academy was founded to the north of the original city of Mantle, soon growing to overshadow Mantle and eventually becoming the new capital and namesake of the kingdom.

Name: Atlesian Colossus
Summary: The Atlesian Colossus is an enormous mech created by Atlas with the purpose of defend the city of Argus if giant Grimm were to attack the city from the ocean. While not in use it is stored inside the Argus Military Base.

Name: Ayame Sarutobi
Summary: Ayame Sarutobi (猿飛 あやめ, Sarutobi Ayame), mostly referred to as Sa-chan, is a ninja from the Oniwabanshuu by training, but is currently working as an assassin. She also has a part-time job at the Kunoichi Café. Since her initial appearance, she has developed a seriously obsessive infatuation with Sakata Gintoki, to the point of even stalking him.

Name: Azula
Summary: Azula was the princess of the Fire Nation, daughter of Fire Lord Ozai and Princess Ursa, younger sister of Zuko, niece of Iroh, the older half-sister of Kiyi, the aunt of Izumi, and the grand aunt of Iroh II.

Name: Bad Mr. Frosty
Summary: Bad Mr. Frosty is a sentient snowman brought to life by the impact of a strange meteorite. Since then, he has become a rather aggressive, violent creature who participates in the ClayFighter tournaments.

Name: Bobert
Summary: Bobert is a supporting character in The Amazing World of Gumball. It is a robot that is a student at Elmore Junior High.

Name: Dukey
Summary: Dukey is the pet dog of Johnny Test and the deuteragonist of the series. One of his most notable qualities is that he has the ability to speak. Johnny got him as a birthday gift for his 11th birthday. He's a dog mutated by Susan and Mary. Since then, he became very intelligent. He is also a master at karate, knows how to speak Chinese, play video games and gives great advice.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Hector Jötunheim
Summary: Hector Jötunheim is an enormous, gorilla-like giant with bluish-purple skin covered in shaggy, orange and pink fur, with only his hands, feet, and buttocks being bare. His face, when shown, is often covered by his hair, but his face is finally revealed in "The Butterfly," and resembles an ape's.

Name: Hollow (SHY)
Summary: Mai is a former ninja from a village that was cut off from the rest of society, only protecting it from the shadows. She is the sister of Ai and is a member of Amarariruku.

Name: Iroh
Summary: Iroh is a supporting character in Avatar: The Last Airbender.

Name: Johnny Test (Character)
Summary: Johnathan "Johnny" Test is a troublesome, narcissistic 11-year-old boy also known for his love of anything he considers awesome.
